117 static std::optional<llvm::Triple> getOffloadTargetTriple(const Driver &D,
118  const ArgList &Args) {
119  auto OffloadTargets = Args.getAllArgValues(options::OPT_offload_EQ);
120  // Offload compilation flow does not support multiple targets for now. We
121  // need the HIPActionBuilder (and possibly the CudaActionBuilder{,Base}too)
122  // to support multiple tool chains first.
123  switch (OffloadTargets.size()) {
124  default:
125  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_only_one_offload_target_supported);
126  return std::nullopt;
127  case 0:
128  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_or_unsupported_offload_target) << "";
129  return std::nullopt;
130  case 1:
131  break;
132  }
133  return llvm::Triple(OffloadTargets[0]);
134 }
135 
136 static std::optional<llvm::Triple>
137 getNVIDIAOffloadTargetTriple(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args,
138  const llvm::Triple &HostTriple) {
139  if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_offload_EQ)) {
140  return llvm::Triple(HostTriple.isArch64Bit() ? "nvptx64-nvidia-cuda"
141  : "nvptx-nvidia-cuda");
142  }
143  auto TT = getOffloadTargetTriple(D, Args);
144  if (TT && (TT->getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv32 ||
145  TT->getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv64)) {
146  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm))
147  return TT;
148  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_cuda_offload_only_emit_bc);
149  return std::nullopt;
150  }
151  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_or_unsupported_offload_target) << TT->str();
152  return std::nullopt;
153 }
154 static std::optional<llvm::Triple>
155 getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args) {
156  if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_offload_EQ)) {
157  return llvm::Triple("amdgcn-amd-amdhsa"); // Default HIP triple.
158  }
159  auto TT = getOffloadTargetTriple(D, Args);
160  if (!TT)
161  return std::nullopt;
162  if (TT->getArch() == llvm::Triple::amdgcn &&
163  TT->getVendor() == llvm::Triple::AMD &&
164  TT->getOS() == llvm::Triple::AMDHSA)
165  return TT;
166  if (TT->getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv64)
167  return TT;
168  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_or_unsupported_offload_target) << TT->str();
169  return std::nullopt;
170 }

172 // static
173 std::string Driver::GetResourcesPath(StringRef BinaryPath,
174  StringRef CustomResourceDir) {
175  // Since the resource directory is embedded in the module hash, it's important
176  // that all places that need it call this function, so that they get the
177  // exact same string ("a/../b/" and "b/" get different hashes, for example).
178 
179  // Dir is bin/ or lib/, depending on where BinaryPath is.
180  std::string Dir = std::string(llvm::sys::path::parent_path(BinaryPath));
181 
182  SmallString<128> P(Dir);
183  if (CustomResourceDir != "") {
184  llvm::sys::path::append(P, CustomResourceDir);
185  } else {
186  // On Windows, libclang.dll is in bin/.
187  // On non-Windows, libclang.so/.dylib is in lib/.
188  // With a static-library build of libclang, LibClangPath will contain the
189  // path of the embedding binary, which for LLVM binaries will be in bin/.
190  // ../lib gets us to lib/ in both cases.
191  P = llvm::sys::path::parent_path(Dir);
192  // This search path is also created in the COFF driver of lld, so any
193  // changes here also needs to happen in lld/COFF/Driver.cpp
194  llvm::sys::path::append(P, CLANG_INSTALL_LIBDIR_BASENAME, "clang",
195  CLANG_VERSION_MAJOR_STRING);
196  }
197 
198  return std::string(P);
199 }
200 
201 Driver::Driver(StringRef ClangExecutable, StringRef TargetTriple,
202  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, std::string Title,
203  IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> VFS)
204  : Diags(Diags), VFS(std::move(VFS)), DumpDeviceCode(false), Mode(GCCMode),
205  SaveTemps(SaveTempsNone), BitcodeEmbed(EmbedNone),
206  Offload(OffloadHostDevice), CXX20HeaderType(HeaderMode_None),
207  ModulesModeCXX20(false), LTOMode(LTOK_None), OffloadLTOMode(LTOK_None),
208  ClangExecutable(ClangExecutable), SysRoot(DEFAULT_SYSROOT),
209  DriverTitle(Title), CCCPrintBindings(false), CCPrintOptions(false),
210  CCLogDiagnostics(false), CCGenDiagnostics(false),
211  CCPrintProcessStats(false), CCPrintInternalStats(false),
212  TargetTriple(TargetTriple), Saver(Alloc), PrependArg(nullptr),
213  CheckInputsExist(true), ProbePrecompiled(true),
214  SuppressMissingInputWarning(false) {
215  // Provide a sane fallback if no VFS is specified.
216  if (!this->VFS)
217  this->VFS = llvm::vfs::getRealFileSystem();
218 
219  Name = std::string(llvm::sys::path::filename(ClangExecutable));
220  Dir = std::string(llvm::sys::path::parent_path(ClangExecutable));
221 
222  if ((!SysRoot.empty()) && llvm::sys::path::is_relative(SysRoot)) {
223  // Prepend InstalledDir if SysRoot is relative
224  SmallString<128> P(Dir);
225  llvm::sys::path::append(P, SysRoot);
226  SysRoot = std::string(P);
227  }
228 
229 #if defined(CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_SYSTEM_DIR)
230  SystemConfigDir = CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_SYSTEM_DIR;
231 #endif
232 #if defined(CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_USER_DIR)
233  {
234  SmallString<128> P;
235  llvm::sys::fs::expand_tilde(CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_USER_DIR, P);
236  UserConfigDir = static_cast<std::string>(P);
237  }
238 #endif
239 
240  // Compute the path to the resource directory.
241  ResourceDir = GetResourcesPath(ClangExecutable, CLANG_RESOURCE_DIR);
242 }
243 
244 void Driver::setDriverMode(StringRef Value) {
245  static StringRef OptName =
246  getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_driver_mode).getPrefixedName();
247  if (auto M = llvm::StringSwitch<std::optional<DriverMode>>(Value)
248  .Case("gcc", GCCMode)
249  .Case("g++", GXXMode)
250  .Case("cpp", CPPMode)
251  .Case("cl", CLMode)
252  .Case("flang", FlangMode)
253  .Case("dxc", DXCMode)
254  .Default(std::nullopt))
255  Mode = *M;
256  else
257  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument) << OptName << Value;
258 }
259 
260 InputArgList Driver::ParseArgStrings(ArrayRef<const char *> ArgStrings,
261  bool UseDriverMode, bool &ContainsError) {
262  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Command line argument parsing");
263  ContainsError = false;
264 
265  llvm::opt::Visibility VisibilityMask = getOptionVisibilityMask(UseDriverMode);
266  unsigned MissingArgIndex, MissingArgCount;
267  InputArgList Args = getOpts().ParseArgs(ArgStrings, MissingArgIndex,
268  MissingArgCount, VisibilityMask);
269 
270  // Check for missing argument error.
271  if (MissingArgCount) {
272  Diag(diag::err_drv_missing_argument)
273  << Args.getArgString(MissingArgIndex) << MissingArgCount;
274  ContainsError |=
275  Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(diag::err_drv_missing_argument,
276  SourceLocation()) > DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
277  }
278 
279  // Check for unsupported options.
280  for (const Arg *A : Args) {
281  if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::Unsupported)) {
282  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt) << A->getAsString(Args);
283  ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt,
284  SourceLocation()) >
285  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
286  continue;
287  }
288 
289  // Deprecated options emit a diagnostic about deprecation, but are still
290  // supported until removed. It's possible to have a deprecated option which
291  // aliases with a non-deprecated option, so always compute the argument
292  // actually used before checking for deprecation.
293  const Arg *Used = A;
294  while (Used->getAlias())
295  Used = Used->getAlias();
296  if (Used->getOption().hasFlag(options::Deprecated)) {
297  Diag(diag::warn_drv_deprecated_option_release) << Used->getAsString(Args);
298  ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(
299  diag::warn_drv_deprecated_option_release,
300  SourceLocation()) > DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
301  }
302 
303  // Warn about -mcpu= without an argument.
304  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mcpu_EQ) && A->containsValue("")) {
305  Diag(diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument) << A->getAsString(Args);
306  ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(
307  diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument,
308  SourceLocation()) > DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
309  }
310  }
311 
312  for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_UNKNOWN)) {
313  unsigned DiagID;
314  auto ArgString = A->getAsString(Args);
315  std::string Nearest;
316  if (getOpts().findNearest(ArgString, Nearest, VisibilityMask) > 1) {
317  if (!IsCLMode() &&
318  getOpts().findExact(ArgString, Nearest,
319  llvm::opt::Visibility(options::CC1Option))) {
320  DiagID = diag::err_drv_unknown_argument_with_suggestion;
321  Diags.Report(DiagID) << ArgString << "-Xclang " + Nearest;
322  } else {
323  DiagID = IsCLMode() ? diag::warn_drv_unknown_argument_clang_cl
324  : diag::err_drv_unknown_argument;
325  Diags.Report(DiagID) << ArgString;
326  }
327  } else {
328  DiagID = IsCLMode()
329  ? diag::warn_drv_unknown_argument_clang_cl_with_suggestion
330  : diag::err_drv_unknown_argument_with_suggestion;
331  Diags.Report(DiagID) << ArgString << Nearest;
332  }
333  ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(DiagID, SourceLocation()) >
334  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
335  }
336 
337  for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_o)) {
338  if (ArgStrings[A->getIndex()] == A->getSpelling())
339  continue;
340 
341  // Warn on joined arguments that are similar to a long argument.
342  std::string ArgString = ArgStrings[A->getIndex()];
343  std::string Nearest;
344  if (getOpts().findExact("-" + ArgString, Nearest, VisibilityMask))
345  Diags.Report(diag::warn_drv_potentially_misspelled_joined_argument)
346  << A->getAsString(Args) << Nearest;
347  }
348 
349  return Args;
350 }
351 
352 // Determine which compilation mode we are in. We look for options which
353 // affect the phase, starting with the earliest phases, and record which
354 // option we used to determine the final phase.
355 phases::ID Driver::getFinalPhase(const DerivedArgList &DAL,
356  Arg **FinalPhaseArg) const {
357  Arg *PhaseArg = nullptr;
358  phases::ID FinalPhase;
359 
360  // -{E,EP,P,M,MM} only run the preprocessor.
361  if (CCCIsCPP() || (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_E)) ||
362  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP)) ||
363  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM)) ||
364  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_P)) ||
365  CCGenDiagnostics) {
366  FinalPhase = phases::Preprocess;
367 
368  // --precompile only runs up to precompilation.
369  // Options that cause the output of C++20 compiled module interfaces or
370  // header units have the same effect.
371  } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__precompile)) ||
372  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_extract_api)) ||
373  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodule_header,
374  options::OPT_fmodule_header_EQ))) {
375  FinalPhase = phases::Precompile;
376  // -{fsyntax-only,-analyze,emit-ast} only run up to the compiler.
377  } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only)) ||
378  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_print_supported_cpus)) ||
379  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_module_file_info)) ||
380  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_verify_pch)) ||
381  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc)) ||
382  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_rewrite_legacy_objc)) ||
383  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__migrate)) ||
384  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__analyze)) ||
385  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_emit_ast))) {
386  FinalPhase = phases::Compile;
387 
388  // -S only runs up to the backend.
389  } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_S)) ||
390  (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_only))) {
391  FinalPhase = phases::Backend;
392 
393  // -c compilation only runs up to the assembler.
394  } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_c))) {
395  FinalPhase = phases::Assemble;
396 
397  } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_emit_interface_stubs))) {
398  FinalPhase = phases::IfsMerge;
399 
400  // Otherwise do everything.
401  } else
402  FinalPhase = phases::Link;
403 
404  if (FinalPhaseArg)
405  *FinalPhaseArg = PhaseArg;
406 
407  return FinalPhase;
408 }
409 
410 static Arg *MakeInputArg(DerivedArgList &Args, const OptTable &Opts,
411  StringRef Value, bool Claim = true) {
412  Arg *A = new Arg(Opts.getOption(options::OPT_INPUT), Value,
413  Args.getBaseArgs().MakeIndex(Value), Value.data());
414  Args.AddSynthesizedArg(A);
415  if (Claim)
416  A->claim();
417  return A;
418 }
419 
420 DerivedArgList *Driver::TranslateInputArgs(const InputArgList &Args) const {
421  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = getOpts();
422  DerivedArgList *DAL = new DerivedArgList(Args);
423 
424  bool HasNostdlib = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nostdlib);
425  bool HasNostdlibxx = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nostdlibxx);
426  bool HasNodefaultlib = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nodefaultlibs);
427  bool IgnoreUnused = false;
428  for (Arg *A : Args) {
429  if (IgnoreUnused)
430  A->claim();
431 
432  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_start_no_unused_arguments)) {
433  IgnoreUnused = true;
434  continue;
435  }
436  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_end_no_unused_arguments)) {
437  IgnoreUnused = false;
438  continue;
439  }
440 
441  // Unfortunately, we have to parse some forwarding options (-Xassembler,
442  // -Xlinker, -Xpreprocessor) because we either integrate their functionality
443  // (assembler and preprocessor), or bypass a previous driver ('collect2').
444 
445  // Rewrite linker options, to replace --no-demangle with a custom internal
446  // option.
447  if ((A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Wl_COMMA) ||
448  A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xlinker)) &&
449  A->containsValue("--no-demangle")) {
450  // Add the rewritten no-demangle argument.
451  DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_Z_Xlinker__no_demangle));
452 
453  // Add the remaining values as Xlinker arguments.
454  for (StringRef Val : A->getValues())
455  if (Val != "--no-demangle")
456  DAL->AddSeparateArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_Xlinker), Val);
457 
458  continue;
459  }
460 
461  // Rewrite preprocessor options, to replace -Wp,-MD,FOO which is used by
462  // some build systems. We don't try to be complete here because we don't
463  // care to encourage this usage model.
464  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Wp_COMMA) &&
465  (A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MD") ||
466  A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MMD"))) {
467  // Rewrite to -MD/-MMD along with -MF.
468  if (A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MD"))
469  DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_MD));
470  else
471  DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_MMD));
472  if (A->getNumValues() == 2)
473  DAL->AddSeparateArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_MF), A->getValue(1));
474  continue;
475  }
476 
477  // Rewrite reserved library names.
478  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_l)) {
479  StringRef Value = A->getValue();
480 
481  // Rewrite unless -nostdlib is present.
482  if (!HasNostdlib && !HasNodefaultlib && !HasNostdlibxx &&
483  Value == "stdc++") {
484  DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_Z_reserved_lib_stdcxx));
485  continue;
486  }
487 
488  // Rewrite unconditionally.
489  if (Value == "cc_kext") {
490  DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_Z_reserved_lib_cckext));
491  continue;
492  }
493  }
494 
495  // Pick up inputs via the -- option.
496  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__DASH_DASH)) {
497  A->claim();
498  for (StringRef Val : A->getValues())
499  DAL->append(MakeInputArg(*DAL, Opts, Val, false));
500  continue;
501  }
502 
503  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_lib_Group)) {
504  if (!A->getNumValues()) {
505  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_unused_argument) << A->getSpelling();
506  continue;
507  }
508  }
509 
510  DAL->append(A);
511  }
512 
513  // DXC mode quits before assembly if an output object file isn't specified.
514  if (IsDXCMode() && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_dxc_Fo))
515  DAL->AddFlagArg(nullptr, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_S));
516 
517  // Enforce -static if -miamcu is present.
518  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_miamcu, options::OPT_mno_iamcu, false))
519  DAL->AddFlagArg(nullptr, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_static));
520 
521  // Use of -fintelfpga implies -g and -fsycl
522  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga)) {
523  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false))
524  DAL->AddFlagArg(0, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_fsycl));
525  // if any -gN option is provided, use that.
526  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gN_Group))
527  DAL->append(A);
528  else
529  DAL->AddFlagArg(0, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_g_Flag));
530  }
531 
532 // Add a default value of -mlinker-version=, if one was given and the user
533 // didn't specify one.
534 #if defined(HOST_LINK_VERSION)
535  if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ) &&
536  strlen(HOST_LINK_VERSION) > 0) {
537  DAL->AddJoinedArg(0, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ),
538  HOST_LINK_VERSION);
539  DAL->getLastArg(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ)->claim();
540  }
541 #endif
542 
543  return DAL;
544 }
545 
546 /// Compute target triple from args.
547 ///
548 /// This routine provides the logic to compute a target triple from various
549 /// args passed to the driver and the default triple string.
550 static llvm::Triple computeTargetTriple(const Driver &D,
551  StringRef TargetTriple,
552  const ArgList &Args,
553  StringRef DarwinArchName = "") {
554  // FIXME: Already done in Compilation *Driver::BuildCompilation
555  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target))
556  TargetTriple = A->getValue();
557 
558  llvm::Triple Target(llvm::Triple::normalize(TargetTriple));
559 
560  // GNU/Hurd's triples should have been -hurd-gnu*, but were historically made
561  // -gnu* only, and we can not change this, so we have to detect that case as
562  // being the Hurd OS.
563  if (TargetTriple.contains("-unknown-gnu") || TargetTriple.contains("-pc-gnu"))
564  Target.setOSName("hurd");
565 
566  // Handle Apple-specific options available here.
567  if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
568  // If an explicit Darwin arch name is given, that trumps all.
569  if (!DarwinArchName.empty()) {
570  tools::darwin::setTripleTypeForMachOArchName(Target, DarwinArchName,
571  Args);
572  return Target;
573  }
574 
575  // Handle the Darwin '-arch' flag.
576  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_arch)) {
577  StringRef ArchName = A->getValue();
578  tools::darwin::setTripleTypeForMachOArchName(Target, ArchName, Args);
579  }
580  }
581 
582  // Handle pseudo-target flags '-mlittle-endian'/'-EL' and
583  // '-mbig-endian'/'-EB'.
584  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT_mlittle_endian,
585  options::OPT_mbig_endian)) {
586  llvm::Triple T = A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlittle_endian)
587  ? Target.getLittleEndianArchVariant()
588  : Target.getBigEndianArchVariant();
589  if (T.getArch() != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch) {
590  Target = std::move(T);
591  Args.claimAllArgs(options::OPT_mlittle_endian, options::OPT_mbig_endian);
592  }
593  }
594 
595  // Skip further flag support on OSes which don't support '-m32' or '-m64'.
596  if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::tce)
597  return Target;
598 
599  // On AIX, the env OBJECT_MODE may affect the resulting arch variant.
600  if (Target.isOSAIX()) {
601  if (std::optional<std::string> ObjectModeValue =
602  llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("OBJECT_MODE")) {
603  StringRef ObjectMode = *ObjectModeValue;
604  llvm::Triple::ArchType AT = llvm::Triple::UnknownArch;
605 
606  if (ObjectMode.equals("64")) {
607  AT = Target.get64BitArchVariant().getArch();
608  } else if (ObjectMode.equals("32")) {
609  AT = Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch();
610  } else {
611  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_object_mode) << ObjectMode;
612  }
613 
614  if (AT != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch && AT != Target.getArch())
615  Target.setArch(AT);
616  }
617  }
618 
619  // The `-maix[32|64]` flags are only valid for AIX targets.
620  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT_maix32, options::OPT_maix64);
621  A && !Target.isOSAIX())
622  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target)
623  << A->getAsString(Args) << Target.str();
624 
625  // Handle pseudo-target flags '-m64', '-mx32', '-m32' and '-m16'.
626  Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_m64, options::OPT_mx32,
627  options::OPT_m32, options::OPT_m16,
628  options::OPT_maix32, options::OPT_maix64);
629  if (A) {
630  llvm::Triple::ArchType AT = llvm::Triple::UnknownArch;
631 
632  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m64) ||
633  A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_maix64)) {
634  AT = Target.get64BitArchVariant().getArch();
635  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUX32)
636  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
637  else if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::MuslX32)
638  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::Musl);
639  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mx32) &&
640  Target.get64BitArchVariant().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
641  AT = llvm::Triple::x86_64;
642  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::Musl)
643  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::MuslX32);
644  else
645  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUX32);
646  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m32) ||
647  A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_maix32)) {
648  AT = Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch();
649  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUX32)
650  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
651  else if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::MuslX32)
652  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::Musl);
653  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m16) &&
654  Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86) {
655  AT = llvm::Triple::x86;
656  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::CODE16);
657  }
658 
659  if (AT != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch && AT != Target.getArch()) {
660  Target.setArch(AT);
661  if (Target.isWindowsGNUEnvironment())
662  toolchains::MinGW::fixTripleArch(D, Target, Args);
663  }
664  }
665 
666  // Handle -miamcu flag.
667  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_miamcu, options::OPT_mno_iamcu, false)) {
668  if (Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch() != llvm::Triple::x86)
669  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target) << "-miamcu"
670  << Target.str();
671 
672  if (A && !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m32))
673  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
674  << "-miamcu" << A->getBaseArg().getAsString(Args);
675 
676  Target.setArch(llvm::Triple::x86);
677  Target.setArchName("i586");
678  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment);
679  Target.setEnvironmentName("");
680  Target.setOS(llvm::Triple::ELFIAMCU);
681  Target.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
682  Target.setVendorName("intel");
683  }
684 
685  // If target is MIPS adjust the target triple
686  // accordingly to provided ABI name.
687  if (Target.isMIPS()) {
688  if ((A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mabi_EQ))) {
689  StringRef ABIName = A->getValue();
690  if (ABIName == "32") {
691  Target = Target.get32BitArchVariant();
692  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABI64 ||
693  Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32)
694  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
695  } else if (ABIName == "n32") {
696  Target = Target.get64BitArchVariant();
697  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNU ||
698  Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABI64)
699  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32);
700  } else if (ABIName == "64") {
701  Target = Target.get64BitArchVariant();
702  if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNU ||
703  Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32)
704  Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUABI64);
705  }
706  }
707  }
708 
709  // If target is RISC-V adjust the target triple according to
710  // provided architecture name
711  if (Target.isRISCV()) {
712  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_march_EQ) ||
713  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mcpu_EQ)) {
714  StringRef ArchName = tools::riscv::getRISCVArch(Args, Target);
715  auto ISAInfo = llvm::RISCVISAInfo::parseArchString(
716  ArchName, /*EnableExperimentalExtensions=*/true);
717  if (!llvm::errorToBool(ISAInfo.takeError())) {
718  unsigned XLen = (*ISAInfo)->getXLen();
719  if (XLen == 32)
720  Target.setArch(llvm::Triple::riscv32);
721  else if (XLen == 64)
722  Target.setArch(llvm::Triple::riscv64);
723  }
724  }
725  }
726 
727  return Target;
728 }
729 
730 // Parse the LTO options and record the type of LTO compilation
731 // based on which -f(no-)?lto(=.*)? or -f(no-)?offload-lto(=.*)?
732 // option occurs last.
733 static driver::LTOKind parseLTOMode(Driver &D, const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args,
734  OptSpecifier OptEq, OptSpecifier OptNeg) {
735  if (!Args.hasFlag(OptEq, OptNeg, false))
736  return LTOK_None;
737 
738  const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OptEq);
739  StringRef LTOName = A->getValue();
740 
741  driver::LTOKind LTOMode = llvm::StringSwitch<LTOKind>(LTOName)
742  .Case("full", LTOK_Full)
743  .Case("thin", LTOK_Thin)
744  .Default(LTOK_Unknown);
745 
746  if (LTOMode == LTOK_Unknown) {
747  D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
748  << A->getSpelling() << A->getValue();
749  return LTOK_None;
750  }
751  return LTOMode;
752 }
753 
754 // Parse the LTO options.
755 void Driver::setLTOMode(const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args) {
756  LTOMode =
757  parseLTOMode(*this, Args, options::OPT_flto_EQ, options::OPT_fno_lto);
758 
759  OffloadLTOMode = parseLTOMode(*this, Args, options::OPT_foffload_lto_EQ,
760  options::OPT_fno_offload_lto);
761 
762  // Try to enable `-foffload-lto=full` if `-fopenmp-target-jit` is on.
763  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fopenmp_target_jit,
764  options::OPT_fno_openmp_target_jit, false)) {
765  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_foffload_lto_EQ,
766  options::OPT_fno_offload_lto))
767  if (OffloadLTOMode != LTOK_Full)
768  Diag(diag::err_drv_incompatible_options)
769  << A->getSpelling() << "-fopenmp-target-jit";
770  OffloadLTOMode = LTOK_Full;
771  }
772 }
773 
774 /// Compute the desired OpenMP runtime from the flags provided.
775 Driver::OpenMPRuntimeKind Driver::getOpenMPRuntime(const ArgList &Args) const {
776  StringRef RuntimeName(CLANG_DEFAULT_OPENMP_RUNTIME);
777 
778  const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_EQ);
779  if (A)
780  RuntimeName = A->getValue();
781 
782  auto RT = llvm::StringSwitch<OpenMPRuntimeKind>(RuntimeName)
783  .Case("libomp", OMPRT_OMP)
784  .Case("libgomp", OMPRT_GOMP)
785  .Case("libiomp5", OMPRT_IOMP5)
786  .Default(OMPRT_Unknown);
787 
788  if (RT == OMPRT_Unknown) {
789  if (A)
790  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
791  << A->getSpelling() << A->getValue();
792  else
793  // FIXME: We could use a nicer diagnostic here.
794  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt) << "-fopenmp";
795  }
796 
797  return RT;
798 }
799 
800 static bool isValidSYCLTriple(llvm::Triple T) {
801  // NVPTX is valid for SYCL.
802  if (T.isNVPTX())
803  return true;
804 
805  // AMDGCN is valid for SYCL
806  if (T.isAMDGCN())
807  return true;
808 
809  // Check for invalid SYCL device triple values.
810  // Non-SPIR/SPIRV arch.
811  if (!T.isSPIROrSPIRV())
812  return false;
813  // SPIR/SPIRV arch, but has invalid SubArch for AOT.
814  StringRef A(T.getArchName());
815  if (T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch &&
816  ((T.getArch() == llvm::Triple::spir && !A.equals("spir")) ||
817  (T.getArch() == llvm::Triple::spir64 && !A.equals("spir64"))))
818  return false;
819  return true;
820 }
821 
822 static const char *getDefaultSYCLArch(Compilation &C) {
823  if (C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86)
824  return "spir";
825  return "spir64";
826 }
827 
828 static bool addSYCLDefaultTriple(Compilation &C,
829  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Triple> &SYCLTriples) {
830  /// Returns true if a triple is added to SYCLTriples, false otherwise
831  if (!C.getDriver().isSYCLDefaultTripleImplied())
832  return false;
833  if (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_force_target_EQ))
834  return false;
835  for (const auto &SYCLTriple : SYCLTriples) {
836  if (SYCLTriple.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch &&
837  SYCLTriple.isSPIROrSPIRV())
838  return false;
839  // If we encounter a known non-spir* target, do not add the default triple.
840  if (SYCLTriple.isNVPTX() || SYCLTriple.isAMDGCN())
841  return false;
842  }
843  // Add the default triple as it was not found.
844  llvm::Triple DefaultTriple =
845  C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(getDefaultSYCLArch(C));
846  SYCLTriples.insert(SYCLTriples.begin(), DefaultTriple);
847  return true;
848 }
849 
850 void Driver::CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains(Compilation &C,
851  InputList &Inputs) {
852 
853  //
854  // CUDA/HIP
855  //
856  // We need to generate a CUDA/HIP toolchain if any of the inputs has a CUDA
857  // or HIP type. However, mixed CUDA/HIP compilation is not supported.
858  using namespace tools::SYCL;
859  bool IsCuda =
860  llvm::any_of(Inputs, [](std::pair<types::ID, const llvm::opt::Arg *> &I) {
861  return types::isCuda(I.first);
862  });
863  bool IsHIP =
864  llvm::any_of(Inputs,
865  [](std::pair<types::ID, const llvm::opt::Arg *> &I) {
866  return types::isHIP(I.first);
867  }) ||
868  C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_hip_link) ||
869  C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_hipstdpar);
870  if (IsCuda && IsHIP) {
871  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_mix_cuda_hip);
872  return;
873  }
874  if (IsCuda) {
875  const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
876  const llvm::Triple &HostTriple = HostTC->getTriple();
877  auto OFK = Action::OFK_Cuda;
878  auto CudaTriple =
879  getNVIDIAOffloadTargetTriple(*this, C.getInputArgs(), HostTriple);
880  if (!CudaTriple)
881  return;
882  // Use the CUDA and host triples as the key into the ToolChains map,
883  // because the device toolchain we create depends on both.
884  auto &CudaTC = ToolChains[CudaTriple->str() + "/" + HostTriple.str()];
885  if (!CudaTC) {
886  CudaTC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
887  *this, *CudaTriple, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs(), OFK);
888 
889  // Emit a warning if the detected CUDA version is too new.
890  CudaInstallationDetector &CudaInstallation =
891  static_cast<toolchains::CudaToolChain &>(*CudaTC).CudaInstallation;
892  if (CudaInstallation.isValid())
893  CudaInstallation.WarnIfUnsupportedVersion();
894  }
895  C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(CudaTC.get(), OFK);
896  } else if (IsHIP) {
897  if (auto *OMPTargetArg =
898  C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ)) {
899  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_language_mode)
900  << OMPTargetArg->getSpelling() << "HIP";
901  return;
902  }
903  const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
904  auto OFK = Action::OFK_HIP;
905  auto HIPTriple = getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(*this, C.getInputArgs());
906  if (!HIPTriple)
907  return;
908  auto *HIPTC = &getOffloadingDeviceToolChain(C.getInputArgs(), *HIPTriple,
909  *HostTC, OFK);
910  assert(HIPTC && "Could not create offloading device tool chain.");
911  C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(HIPTC, OFK);
912  }
913 
914  //
915  // OpenMP
916  //
917  // We need to generate an OpenMP toolchain if the user specified targets with
918  // the -fopenmp-targets option or used --offload-arch with OpenMP enabled.
919  bool IsOpenMPOffloading =
920  C.getInputArgs().hasFlag(options::OPT_fopenmp, options::OPT_fopenmp_EQ,
921  options::OPT_fno_openmp, false) &&
922  (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ) ||
923  C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ));
924  if (IsOpenMPOffloading) {
925  // We expect that -fopenmp-targets is always used in conjunction with the
926  // option -fopenmp specifying a valid runtime with offloading support, i.e.
927  // libomp or libiomp.
928  OpenMPRuntimeKind RuntimeKind = getOpenMPRuntime(C.getInputArgs());
929  if (RuntimeKind != OMPRT_OMP && RuntimeKind != OMPRT_IOMP5) {
930  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_expecting_fopenmp_with_fopenmp_targets);
931  return;
932  }
933 
934  llvm::StringMap<llvm::DenseSet<StringRef>> DerivedArchs;
935  llvm::StringMap<StringRef> FoundNormalizedTriples;
936  std::multiset<StringRef> OpenMPTriples;
937 
938  // If the user specified -fopenmp-targets= we create a toolchain for each
939  // valid triple. Otherwise, if only --offload-arch= was specified we instead
940  // attempt to derive the appropriate toolchains from the arguments.
941  if (Arg *OpenMPTargets =
942  C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ)) {
943  if (OpenMPTargets && !OpenMPTargets->getNumValues()) {
944  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument)
945  << OpenMPTargets->getAsString(C.getInputArgs());
946  return;
947  }
948  for (StringRef T : OpenMPTargets->getValues())
949  OpenMPTriples.insert(T);
950  } else if (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ) &&
951  !IsHIP && !IsCuda) {
952  const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
953  auto AMDTriple = getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(*this, C.getInputArgs());
954  auto NVPTXTriple = getNVIDIAOffloadTargetTriple(*this, C.getInputArgs(),
955  HostTC->getTriple());
956 
957  // Attempt to deduce the offloading triple from the set of architectures.
958  // We can only correctly deduce NVPTX / AMDGPU triples currently. We need
959  // to temporarily create these toolchains so that we can access tools for
960  // inferring architectures.
961  llvm::DenseSet<StringRef> Archs;
962  if (NVPTXTriple) {
963  auto TempTC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
964  *this, *NVPTXTriple, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs(), Action::OFK_None);
965  for (StringRef Arch : getOffloadArchs(
966  C, C.getArgs(), Action::OFK_OpenMP, &*TempTC, true))
967  Archs.insert(Arch);
968  }
969  if (AMDTriple) {
970  auto TempTC = std::make_unique<toolchains::AMDGPUOpenMPToolChain>(
971  *this, *AMDTriple, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs());
972  for (StringRef Arch : getOffloadArchs(
973  C, C.getArgs(), Action::OFK_OpenMP, &*TempTC, true))
974  Archs.insert(Arch);
975  }
976  if (!AMDTriple && !NVPTXTriple) {
977  for (StringRef Arch :
978  getOffloadArchs(C, C.getArgs(), Action::OFK_OpenMP, nullptr, true))
979  Archs.insert(Arch);
980  }
981 
982  for (StringRef Arch : Archs) {
983  if (NVPTXTriple && IsNVIDIAGpuArch(StringToCudaArch(
984  getProcessorFromTargetID(*NVPTXTriple, Arch)))) {
985  DerivedArchs[NVPTXTriple->getTriple()].insert(Arch);
986  } else if (AMDTriple &&
987  IsAMDGpuArch(StringToCudaArch(
988  getProcessorFromTargetID(*AMDTriple, Arch)))) {
989  DerivedArchs[AMDTriple->getTriple()].insert(Arch);
990  } else {
991  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_failed_to_deduce_target_from_arch) << Arch;
992  return;
993  }
994  }
995 
996  // If the set is empty then we failed to find a native architecture.
997  if (Archs.empty()) {
998  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_failed_to_deduce_target_from_arch)
999  << "native";
1000  return;
1001  }
1002 
1003  for (const auto &TripleAndArchs : DerivedArchs)
1004  OpenMPTriples.insert(TripleAndArchs.first());
1005  }
1006 
1007  for (StringRef Val : OpenMPTriples) {
1008  llvm::Triple TT(ToolChain::getOpenMPTriple(Val));
1009  std::string NormalizedName = TT.normalize();
1010 
1011  // Make sure we don't have a duplicate triple.
1012  auto Duplicate = FoundNormalizedTriples.find(NormalizedName);
1013  if (Duplicate != FoundNormalizedTriples.end()) {
1014  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_omp_offload_target_duplicate)
1015  << Val << Duplicate->second;
1016  continue;
1017  }
1018 
1019  // Store the current triple so that we can check for duplicates in the
1020  // following iterations.
1021  FoundNormalizedTriples[NormalizedName] = Val;
1022 
1023  // If the specified target is invalid, emit a diagnostic.
1024  if (TT.getArch() == llvm::Triple::UnknownArch)
1025  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_omp_target) << Val;
1026  else {
1027  const ToolChain *TC;
1028  // Device toolchains have to be selected differently. They pair host
1029  // and device in their implementation.
1030  if (TT.isNVPTX() || TT.isAMDGCN()) {
1031  const ToolChain *HostTC =
1032  C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
1033  assert(HostTC && "Host toolchain should be always defined.");
1034  auto &DeviceTC =
1035  ToolChains[TT.str() + "/" + HostTC->getTriple().normalize()];
1036  if (!DeviceTC) {
1037  if (TT.isNVPTX())
1038  DeviceTC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
1039  *this, TT, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs(), Action::OFK_OpenMP);
1040  else if (TT.isAMDGCN())
1041  DeviceTC = std::make_unique<toolchains::AMDGPUOpenMPToolChain>(
1042  *this, TT, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs());
1043  else
1044  assert(DeviceTC && "Device toolchain not defined.");
1045  }
1046 
1047  TC = DeviceTC.get();
1048  } else
1049  TC = &getToolChain(C.getInputArgs(), TT);
1050  C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(TC, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
1051  if (DerivedArchs.contains(TT.getTriple()))
1052  KnownArchs[TC] = DerivedArchs[TT.getTriple()];
1053  }
1054  }
1055  } else if (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ)) {
1056  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_expecting_fopenmp_with_fopenmp_targets);
1057  return;
1058  }
1059 
1060  //
1061  // SYCL
1062  //
1063  // We need to generate a SYCL toolchain if the user specified targets with
1064  // the -fsycl-targets, -fsycl-add-targets or -fsycl-link-targets option.
1065  // If -fsycl is supplied without any of these we will assume SPIR-V.
1066  // Use of -fsycl-device-only overrides -fsycl.
1067  bool HasValidSYCLRuntime =
1068  C.getInputArgs().hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl,
1069  false) ||
1070  C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_only);
1071 
1072  Arg *SYCLfpga = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga);
1073 
1074  // Make -fintelfpga flag imply -fsycl.
1075  if (SYCLfpga && !HasValidSYCLRuntime)
1076  HasValidSYCLRuntime = true;
1077 
1078  // A mechanism for retrieving SYCL-specific options, erroring out
1079  // if SYCL offloading wasn't enabled prior to that
1080  auto getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime = [&](OptSpecifier OptId) -> Arg * {
1081  Arg *SYCLArg = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(OptId);
1082  if (SYCLArg && !HasValidSYCLRuntime) {
1083  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_expecting_fsycl_with_sycl_opt)
1084  // Dropping the '=' symbol, which would otherwise pollute
1085  // the diagnostics for the most of options
1086  << SYCLArg->getSpelling().split('=').first;
1087  return nullptr;
1088  }
1089  return SYCLArg;
1090  };
1091 
1092  Arg *SYCLTargets = getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_targets_EQ);
1093  Arg *SYCLLinkTargets =
1094  getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_link_targets_EQ);
1095  Arg *SYCLAddTargets =
1096  getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_add_targets_EQ);
1097  Arg *SYCLLink = getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ);
1098 
1099  // Check if -fsycl-host-compiler is used in conjunction with -fsycl.
1100  Arg *SYCLHostCompiler =
1101  getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_host_compiler_EQ);
1102  Arg *SYCLHostCompilerOptions =
1103  getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_host_compiler_options_EQ);
1104 
1105  // -fsycl-targets cannot be used with -fsycl-link-targets
1106  if (SYCLTargets && SYCLLinkTargets)
1107  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_option_conflict)
1108  << SYCLTargets->getSpelling() << SYCLLinkTargets->getSpelling();
1109  // -fsycl-link-targets and -fsycl-add-targets cannot be used together
1110  if (SYCLLinkTargets && SYCLAddTargets)
1111  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_option_conflict)
1112  << SYCLLinkTargets->getSpelling() << SYCLAddTargets->getSpelling();
1113  // -fsycl-link-targets is not allowed with -fsycl-link
1114  if (SYCLLinkTargets && SYCLLink)
1115  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_option_conflict)
1116  << SYCLLink->getSpelling() << SYCLLinkTargets->getSpelling();
1117  // -fsycl-targets cannot be used with -fintelfpga
1118  if (SYCLTargets && SYCLfpga)
1119  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_option_conflict)
1120  << SYCLTargets->getSpelling() << SYCLfpga->getSpelling();
1121  // -fsycl-host-compiler-options cannot be used without -fsycl-host-compiler
1122  if (SYCLHostCompilerOptions && !SYCLHostCompiler)
1123  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_opt_requires_opt)
1124  << SYCLHostCompilerOptions->getSpelling().split('=').first
1125  << "-fsycl-host-compiler";
1126 
1127  auto argSYCLIncompatible = [&](OptSpecifier OptId) {
1128  if (!HasValidSYCLRuntime)
1129  return;
1130  if (Arg *IncompatArg = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(OptId))
1131  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_fsycl_unsupported_with_opt)
1132  << IncompatArg->getSpelling();
1133  };
1134  // -static-libstdc++ is not compatible with -fsycl.
1135  argSYCLIncompatible(options::OPT_static_libstdcxx);
1136  // -ffreestanding cannot be used with -fsycl
1137  argSYCLIncompatible(options::OPT_ffreestanding);
1138 
1139  // Diagnose incorrect inputs to SYCL options.
1140  // FIXME: Since the option definition includes the list of possible values,
1141  // the validation must be automatic, not requiring separate disjointed code
1142  // blocks accross the driver code. Long-term, the detection of incorrect
1143  // values must happen at the level of TableGen and Arg class design, with
1144  // Compilation/Driver class constructors handling the driver-specific
1145  // diagnostic output.
1146  auto checkSingleArgValidity = [&](Arg *A,
1147  SmallVector<StringRef, 4> AllowedValues) {
1148  if (!A)
1149  return;
1150  const char *ArgValue = A->getValue();
1151  for (const StringRef AllowedValue : AllowedValues)
1152  if (AllowedValue.equals(ArgValue))
1153  return;
1154  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_argument_to_option)
1155  << ArgValue << A->getOption().getName();
1156  };
1157  Arg *DeviceCodeSplit =
1158  C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_code_split_EQ);
1159  checkSingleArgValidity(SYCLLink, {"early", "image"});
1160  checkSingleArgValidity(DeviceCodeSplit,
1161  {"per_kernel", "per_source", "auto", "off"});
1162 
1163  Arg *RangeRoundingPreference =
1164  C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_range_rounding_EQ);
1165  checkSingleArgValidity(RangeRoundingPreference, {"disable", "force", "on"});
1166 
1167  Arg *SYCLForceTarget =
1168  getArgRequiringSYCLRuntime(options::OPT_fsycl_force_target_EQ);
1169  if (SYCLForceTarget) {
1170  StringRef Val(SYCLForceTarget->getValue());
1171  llvm::Triple TT(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(Val));
1172  if (!isValidSYCLTriple(TT))
1173  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << Val;
1174  }
1175  bool HasSYCLTargetsOption = SYCLTargets || SYCLLinkTargets || SYCLAddTargets;
1176 
1177  llvm::StringMap<StringRef> FoundNormalizedTriples;
1178  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Triple, 4> UniqueSYCLTriplesVec;
1179  if (HasSYCLTargetsOption) {
1180  // At this point, we know we have a valid combination
1181  // of -fsycl*target options passed
1182  Arg *SYCLTargetsValues = SYCLTargets ? SYCLTargets : SYCLLinkTargets;
1183  if (SYCLTargetsValues) {
1184  if (SYCLTargetsValues->getNumValues()) {
1185 
1186  // Multiple targets are currently not supported when using
1187  // -fsycl-force-target as the bundler does not allow for multiple
1188  // outputs of the same target.
1189  if (SYCLForceTarget && SYCLTargetsValues->getNumValues() > 1)
1190  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_multiple_target_with_forced_target)
1191  << SYCLTargetsValues->getAsString(C.getInputArgs())
1192  << SYCLForceTarget->getAsString(C.getInputArgs());
1193 
1194  for (StringRef Val : SYCLTargetsValues->getValues()) {
1195  StringRef UserTargetName(Val);
1196  if (auto Device = gen::isGPUTarget<gen::IntelGPU>(Val)) {
1197  if (Device->empty()) {
1198  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << Val;
1199  continue;
1200  }
1201  UserTargetName = "spir64_gen";
1202  } else if (auto Device = gen::isGPUTarget<gen::NvidiaGPU>(Val)) {
1203  if (Device->empty()) {
1204  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << Val;
1205  continue;
1206  }
1207  UserTargetName = "nvptx64-nvidia-cuda";
1208  } else if (auto Device = gen::isGPUTarget<gen::AmdGPU>(Val)) {
1209  if (Device->empty()) {
1210  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << Val;
1211  continue;
1212  }
1213  UserTargetName = "amdgcn-amd-amdhsa";
1214  } else if (Val == "native_cpu") {
1215  const ToolChain *HostTC =
1216  C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
1217  llvm::Triple HostTriple = HostTC->getTriple();
1218  UniqueSYCLTriplesVec.push_back(HostTriple);
1219  continue;
1220  }
1221 
1222  if (!isValidSYCLTriple(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(UserTargetName))) {
1223  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << Val;
1224  continue;
1225  }
1226 
1227  // Make sure we don't have a duplicate triple.
1228  std::string NormalizedName = MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(Val).normalize();
1229  auto Duplicate = FoundNormalizedTriples.find(NormalizedName);
1230  if (Duplicate != FoundNormalizedTriples.end()) {
1231  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_sycl_offload_target_duplicate)
1232  << Val << Duplicate->second;
1233  continue;
1234  }
1235 
1236  // Store the current triple so that we can check for duplicates in
1237  // the following iterations.
1238  FoundNormalizedTriples[NormalizedName] = Val;
1239  UniqueSYCLTriplesVec.push_back(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(UserTargetName));
1240  }
1241  addSYCLDefaultTriple(C, UniqueSYCLTriplesVec);
1242  } else
1243  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument)
1244  << SYCLTargetsValues->getAsString(C.getInputArgs());
1245  }
1246  // -fsycl-add-targets is a list of paired items (Triple and file) which are
1247  // gathered and used to be linked into the final device binary. This can
1248  // be used with -fsycl-targets to put together the final conglomerate binary
1249  if (SYCLAddTargets) {
1250  if (SYCLAddTargets->getNumValues()) {
1251  // Use of -fsycl-add-targets adds additional files to the SYCL device
1252  // link step. Regular offload processing occurs below
1253  for (StringRef Val : SYCLAddTargets->getValues()) {
1254  // Parse out the Triple and Input (triple:binary) and create a
1255  // ToolChain for each entry.
1256  // The expected format is 'triple:file', any other format will
1257  // not be accepted.
1258  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> I = Val.split(':');
1259  if (!I.first.empty() && !I.second.empty()) {
1260  llvm::Triple TT(I.first);
1261  if (!isValidSYCLTriple(TT)) {
1262  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_sycl_target) << I.first;
1263  continue;
1264  }
1265  std::string NormalizedName = TT.normalize();
1266 
1267  // Make sure we don't have a duplicate triple.
1268  auto Duplicate = FoundNormalizedTriples.find(NormalizedName);
1269  if (Duplicate != FoundNormalizedTriples.end())
1270  // The toolchain for this triple was already created
1271  continue;
1272 
1273  // Store the current triple so that we can check for duplicates in
1274  // the following iterations.
1275  FoundNormalizedTriples[NormalizedName] = Val;
1276  UniqueSYCLTriplesVec.push_back(TT);
1277  } else {
1278  // No colon found, do not use the input
1279  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
1280  << SYCLAddTargets->getSpelling() << Val;
1281  }
1282  }
1283  } else
1284  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument)
1285  << SYCLAddTargets->getAsString(C.getInputArgs());
1286  }
1287  } else {
1288  // If -fsycl is supplied without -fsycl-*targets we will assume SPIR-V
1289  // unless -fintelfpga is supplied, which uses SPIR-V with fpga AOT.
1290  // For -fsycl-device-only, we also setup the implied triple as needed.
1291  if (HasValidSYCLRuntime) {
1292  StringRef SYCLTargetArch = getDefaultSYCLArch(C);
1293  if (SYCLfpga)
1294  // Triple for -fintelfpga is spir64_fpga.
1295  SYCLTargetArch = "spir64_fpga";
1296  UniqueSYCLTriplesVec.push_back(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(SYCLTargetArch));
1297  addSYCLDefaultTriple(C, UniqueSYCLTriplesVec);
1298  }
1299  }
1300  // -fno-sycl-libspirv flag is reserved for very unusual cases where the
1301  // libspirv library is not linked when using CUDA/HIP: so output appropriate
1302  // warnings.
1303  if (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fno_sycl_libspirv)) {
1304  for (auto &TT : UniqueSYCLTriplesVec) {
1305  if (TT.isNVPTX() || TT.isAMDGCN()) {
1306  Diag(diag::warn_flag_no_sycl_libspirv) << TT.getTriple();
1307  } else {
1308  Diag(diag::warn_drv_unsupported_option_for_target)
1309  << "-fno-sycl-libspirv" << TT.getTriple();
1310  }
1311  }
1312  }
1313  // Define macros associated with `any_device_has/all_devices_have` according
1314  // to the aspects defined in the DeviceConfigFile for the SYCL targets.
1315  populateSYCLDeviceTraitsMacrosArgs(C.getInputArgs(), UniqueSYCLTriplesVec);
1316  // We'll need to use the SYCL and host triples as the key into
1317  // getOffloadingDeviceToolChain, because the device toolchains we're
1318  // going to create will depend on both.
1319  const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
1320  for (auto &TT : UniqueSYCLTriplesVec) {
1321  auto SYCLTC = &getOffloadingDeviceToolChain(C.getInputArgs(), TT, *HostTC,
1322  Action::OFK_SYCL);
1323  C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(SYCLTC, Action::OFK_SYCL);
1324  }
1325 
1326  //
1327  // TODO: Add support for other offloading programming models here.
1328  //
1329 }
1330 
1331 static void appendOneArg(InputArgList &Args, const Arg *Opt,
1332  const Arg *BaseArg) {
1333  // The args for config files or /clang: flags belong to different InputArgList
1334  // objects than Args. This copies an Arg from one of those other InputArgLists
1335  // to the ownership of Args.
1336  unsigned Index = Args.MakeIndex(Opt->getSpelling());
1337  Arg *Copy = new llvm::opt::Arg(Opt->getOption(), Args.getArgString(Index),
1338  Index, BaseArg);
1339  Copy->getValues() = Opt->getValues();
1340  if (Opt->isClaimed())
1341  Copy->claim();
1342  Copy->setOwnsValues(Opt->getOwnsValues());
1343  Opt->setOwnsValues(false);
1344  Args.append(Copy);
1345 }
1346 
1347 bool Driver::readConfigFile(StringRef FileName,
1348  llvm::cl::ExpansionContext &ExpCtx) {
1349  // Try opening the given file.
1350  auto Status = getVFS().status(FileName);
1351  if (!Status) {
1352  Diag(diag::err_drv_cannot_open_config_file)
1353  << FileName << Status.getError().message();
1354  return true;
1355  }
1356  if (Status->getType() != llvm::sys::fs::file_type::regular_file) {
1357  Diag(diag::err_drv_cannot_open_config_file)
1358  << FileName << "not a regular file";
1359  return true;
1360  }
1361 
1362  // Try reading the given file.
1363  SmallVector<const char *, 32> NewCfgArgs;
1364  if (llvm::Error Err = ExpCtx.readConfigFile(FileName, NewCfgArgs)) {
1365  Diag(diag::err_drv_cannot_read_config_file)
1366  << FileName << toString(std::move(Err));
1367  return true;
1368  }
1369 
1370  // Read options from config file.
1371  llvm::SmallString<128> CfgFileName(FileName);
1372  llvm::sys::path::native(CfgFileName);
1373  bool ContainErrors;
1374  std::unique_ptr<InputArgList> NewOptions = std::make_unique<InputArgList>(
1375  ParseArgStrings(NewCfgArgs, /*UseDriverMode=*/true, ContainErrors));
1376  if (ContainErrors)
1377  return true;
1378 
1379  // Claim all arguments that come from a configuration file so that the driver
1380  // does not warn on any that is unused.
1381  for (Arg *A : *NewOptions)
1382  A->claim();
1383 
1384  if (!CfgOptions)
1385  CfgOptions = std::move(NewOptions);
1386  else {
1387  // If this is a subsequent config file, append options to the previous one.
1388  for (auto *Opt : *NewOptions) {
1389  const Arg *BaseArg = &Opt->getBaseArg();
1390  if (BaseArg == Opt)
1391  BaseArg = nullptr;
1392  appendOneArg(*CfgOptions, Opt, BaseArg);
1393  }
1394  }
1395  ConfigFiles.push_back(std::string(CfgFileName));
1396  return false;
1397 }
1398 
1399 bool Driver::loadConfigFiles() {
1400  llvm::cl::ExpansionContext ExpCtx(Saver.getAllocator(),
1401  llvm::cl::tokenizeConfigFile);
1402  ExpCtx.setVFS(&getVFS());
1403 
1404  // Process options that change search path for config files.
1405  if (CLOptions) {
1406  if (CLOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_config_system_dir_EQ)) {
1407  SmallString<128> CfgDir;
1408  CfgDir.append(
1409  CLOptions->getLastArgValue(options::OPT_config_system_dir_EQ));
1410  if (CfgDir.empty() || getVFS().makeAbsolute(CfgDir))
1411  SystemConfigDir.clear();
1412  else
1413  SystemConfigDir = static_cast<std::string>(CfgDir);
1414  }
1415  if (CLOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_config_user_dir_EQ)) {
1416  SmallString<128> CfgDir;
1417  llvm::sys::fs::expand_tilde(
1418  CLOptions->getLastArgValue(options::OPT_config_user_dir_EQ), CfgDir);
1419  if (CfgDir.empty() || getVFS().makeAbsolute(CfgDir))
1420  UserConfigDir.clear();
1421  else
1422  UserConfigDir = static_cast<std::string>(CfgDir);
1423  }
1424  }
1425 
1426  // Prepare list of directories where config file is searched for.
1427  StringRef CfgFileSearchDirs[] = {UserConfigDir, SystemConfigDir, Dir};
1428  ExpCtx.setSearchDirs(CfgFileSearchDirs);
1429 
1430  // First try to load configuration from the default files, return on error.
1431  if (loadDefaultConfigFiles(ExpCtx))
1432  return true;
1433 
1434  // Then load configuration files specified explicitly.
1435  SmallString<128> CfgFilePath;
1436  if (CLOptions) {
1437  for (auto CfgFileName : CLOptions->getAllArgValues(options::OPT_config)) {
1438  // If argument contains directory separator, treat it as a path to
1439  // configuration file.
1440  if (llvm::sys::path::has_parent_path(CfgFileName)) {
1441  CfgFilePath.assign(CfgFileName);
1442  if (llvm::sys::path::is_relative(CfgFilePath)) {
1443  if (getVFS().makeAbsolute(CfgFilePath)) {
1444  Diag(diag::err_drv_cannot_open_config_file)
1445  << CfgFilePath << "cannot get absolute path";
1446  return true;
1447  }
1448  }
1449  } else if (!ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath)) {
1450  // Report an error that the config file could not be found.
1451  Diag(diag::err_drv_config_file_not_found) << CfgFileName;
1452  for (const StringRef &SearchDir : CfgFileSearchDirs)
1453  if (!SearchDir.empty())
1454  Diag(diag::note_drv_config_file_searched_in) << SearchDir;
1455  return true;
1456  }
1457 
1458  // Try to read the config file, return on error.
1459  if (readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx))
1460  return true;
1461  }
1462  }
1463 
1464  // No error occurred.
1465  return false;
1466 }
1467 
1468 bool Driver::loadDefaultConfigFiles(llvm::cl::ExpansionContext &ExpCtx) {
1469  // Disable default config if CLANG_NO_DEFAULT_CONFIG is set to a non-empty
1470  // value.
1471  if (const char *NoConfigEnv = ::getenv("CLANG_NO_DEFAULT_CONFIG")) {
1472  if (*NoConfigEnv)
1473  return false;
1474  }
1475  if (CLOptions && CLOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_no_default_config))
1476  return false;
1477 
1478  std::string RealMode = getExecutableForDriverMode(Mode);
1479  std::string Triple;
1480 
1481  // If name prefix is present, no --target= override was passed via CLOptions
1482  // and the name prefix is not a valid triple, force it for backwards
1483  // compatibility.
1484  if (!ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix.empty() &&
1485  computeTargetTriple(*this, "/invalid/", *CLOptions).str() ==
1486  "/invalid/") {
1487  llvm::Triple PrefixTriple{ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix};
1488  if (PrefixTriple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::UnknownArch ||
1489  PrefixTriple.isOSUnknown())
1490  Triple = PrefixTriple.str();
1491  }
1492 
1493  // Otherwise, use the real triple as used by the driver.
1494  if (Triple.empty()) {
1495  llvm::Triple RealTriple =
1496  computeTargetTriple(*this, TargetTriple, *CLOptions);
1497  Triple = RealTriple.str();
1498  assert(!Triple.empty());
1499  }
1500 
1501  // Search for config files in the following order:
1502  // 1. <triple>-<mode>.cfg using real driver mode
1503  // (e.g. i386-pc-linux-gnu-clang++.cfg).
1504  // 2. <triple>-<mode>.cfg using executable suffix
1505  // (e.g. i386-pc-linux-gnu-clang-g++.cfg for *clang-g++).
1506  // 3. <triple>.cfg + <mode>.cfg using real driver mode
1507  // (e.g. i386-pc-linux-gnu.cfg + clang++.cfg).
1508  // 4. <triple>.cfg + <mode>.cfg using executable suffix
1509  // (e.g. i386-pc-linux-gnu.cfg + clang-g++.cfg for *clang-g++).
1510 
1511  // Try loading <triple>-<mode>.cfg, and return if we find a match.
1512  SmallString<128> CfgFilePath;
1513  std::string CfgFileName = Triple + '-' + RealMode + ".cfg";
1514  if (ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath))
1515  return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx);
1516 
1517  bool TryModeSuffix = !ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix.empty() &&
1518  ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix != RealMode;
1519  if (TryModeSuffix) {
1520  CfgFileName = Triple + '-' + ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix + ".cfg";
1521  if (ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath))
1522  return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx);
1523  }
1524 
1525  // Try loading <mode>.cfg, and return if loading failed. If a matching file
1526  // was not found, still proceed on to try <triple>.cfg.
1527  CfgFileName = RealMode + ".cfg";
1528  if (ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath)) {
1529  if (readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx))
1530  return true;
1531  } else if (TryModeSuffix) {
1532  CfgFileName = ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix + ".cfg";
1533  if (ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath) &&
1534  readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx))
1535  return true;
1536  }
1537 
1538  // Try loading <triple>.cfg and return if we find a match.
1539  CfgFileName = Triple + ".cfg";
1540  if (ExpCtx.findConfigFile(CfgFileName, CfgFilePath))
1541  return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath, ExpCtx);
1542 
1543  // If we were unable to find a config file deduced from executable name,
1544  // that is not an error.
1545  return false;
1546 }
1547 
1548 Compilation *Driver::BuildCompilation(ArrayRef<const char *> ArgList) {
1549  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Compilation construction");
1550 
1551  // FIXME: Handle environment options which affect driver behavior, somewhere
1552  // (client?). GCC_EXEC_PREFIX, LPATH, CC_PRINT_OPTIONS.
1553 
1554  // We look for the driver mode option early, because the mode can affect
1555  // how other options are parsed.
1556 
1557  auto DriverMode = getDriverMode(ClangExecutable, ArgList.slice(1));
1558  if (!DriverMode.empty())
1559  setDriverMode(DriverMode);
1560 
1561  // FIXME: What are we going to do with -V and -b?
1562 
1563  // Arguments specified in command line.
1564  bool ContainsError;
1565  CLOptions = std::make_unique<InputArgList>(
1566  ParseArgStrings(ArgList.slice(1), /*UseDriverMode=*/true, ContainsError));
1567 
1568  // Try parsing configuration file.
1569  if (!ContainsError)
1570  ContainsError = loadConfigFiles();
1571  bool HasConfigFile = !ContainsError && (CfgOptions.get() != nullptr);
1572 
1573  // All arguments, from both config file and command line.
1574  InputArgList Args = std::move(HasConfigFile ? std::move(*CfgOptions)
1575  : std::move(*CLOptions));
1576 
1577  if (HasConfigFile)
1578  for (auto *Opt : *CLOptions) {
1579  if (Opt->getOption().matches(options::OPT_config))
1580  continue;
1581  const Arg *BaseArg = &Opt->getBaseArg();
1582  if (BaseArg == Opt)
1583  BaseArg = nullptr;
1584  appendOneArg(Args, Opt, BaseArg);
1585  }
1586 
1587  // In CL mode, look for any pass-through arguments
1588  if (IsCLMode() && !ContainsError) {
1589  SmallVector<const char *, 16> CLModePassThroughArgList;
1590  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT__SLASH_clang)) {
1591  A->claim();
1592  CLModePassThroughArgList.push_back(A->getValue());
1593  }
1594 
1595  if (!CLModePassThroughArgList.empty()) {
1596  // Parse any pass through args using default clang processing rather
1597  // than clang-cl processing.
1598  auto CLModePassThroughOptions = std::make_unique<InputArgList>(
1599  ParseArgStrings(CLModePassThroughArgList, /*UseDriverMode=*/false,
1600  ContainsError));
1601 
1602  if (!ContainsError)
1603  for (auto *Opt : *CLModePassThroughOptions) {
1604  appendOneArg(Args, Opt, nullptr);
1605  }
1606  }
1607  }
1608 
1609  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false) &&
1610  CCCIsCC())
1611  setDriverMode("g++");
1612 
1613  // Check for working directory option before accessing any files
1614  if (Arg *WD = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_working_directory))
1615  if (VFS->setCurrentWorkingDirectory(WD->getValue()))
1616  Diag(diag::err_drv_unable_to_set_working_directory) << WD->getValue();
1617 
1618  // FIXME: This stuff needs to go into the Compilation, not the driver.
1619  bool CCCPrintPhases;
1620 
1621  // -canonical-prefixes, -no-canonical-prefixes are used very early in main.
1622  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_canonical_prefixes);
1623  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_no_canonical_prefixes);
1624 
1625  // f(no-)integated-cc1 is also used very early in main.
1626  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fintegrated_cc1);
1627  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fno_integrated_cc1);
1628 
1629  // Ignore -pipe.
1630  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_pipe);
1631 
1632  // Extract -ccc args.
1633  //
1634  // FIXME: We need to figure out where this behavior should live. Most of it
1635  // should be outside in the client; the parts that aren't should have proper
1636  // options, either by introducing new ones or by overloading gcc ones like -V
1637  // or -b.
1638  CCCPrintPhases = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ccc_print_phases);
1639  CCCPrintBindings = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ccc_print_bindings);
1640  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ccc_gcc_name))
1641  CCCGenericGCCName = A->getValue();
1642 
1643  // Process -fproc-stat-report options.
1644  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fproc_stat_report_EQ)) {
1645  CCPrintProcessStats = true;
1646  CCPrintStatReportFilename = A->getValue();
1647  }
1648  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fproc_stat_report))
1649  CCPrintProcessStats = true;
1650 
1651  // FIXME: TargetTriple is used by the target-prefixed calls to as/ld
1652  // and getToolChain is const.
1653  if (IsCLMode()) {
1654  // clang-cl targets MSVC-style Win32.
1655  llvm::Triple T(TargetTriple);
1656  T.setOS(llvm::Triple::Win32);
1657  T.setVendor(llvm::Triple::PC);
1658  T.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::MSVC);
1659  T.setObjectFormat(llvm::Triple::COFF);
1660  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_arm64EC))
1661  T.setArch(llvm::Triple::aarch64, llvm::Triple::AArch64SubArch_arm64ec);
1662  TargetTriple = T.str();
1663  } else if (IsDXCMode()) {
1664  // Build TargetTriple from target_profile option for clang-dxc.
1665  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target_profile)) {
1666  StringRef TargetProfile = A->getValue();
1667  if (auto Triple =
1668  toolchains::HLSLToolChain::parseTargetProfile(TargetProfile))
1669  TargetTriple = *Triple;
1670  else
1671  Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_directx_shader_module) << TargetProfile;
1672 
1673  A->claim();
1674 
1675  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_spirv)) {
1676  llvm::Triple T(TargetTriple);
1677  T.setArch(llvm::Triple::spirv);
1678  T.setOS(llvm::Triple::Vulkan);
1679 
1680  // Set specific Vulkan version if applicable.
1681  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fspv_target_env_EQ)) {
1682  const llvm::StringSet<> ValidValues = {"vulkan1.2", "vulkan1.3"};
1683  if (ValidValues.contains(A->getValue())) {
1684  T.setOSName(A->getValue());
1685  } else {
1686  Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
1687  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
1688  }
1689  A->claim();
1690  }
1691 
1692  TargetTriple = T.str();
1693  }
1694  } else {
1695  Diag(diag::err_drv_dxc_missing_target_profile);
1696  }
1697  }
1698 
1699  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target))
1700  TargetTriple = A->getValue();
1701  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ccc_install_dir))
1702  Dir = Dir = A->getValue();
1703  for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_B)) {
1704  A->claim();
1705  PrefixDirs.push_back(A->getValue(0));
1706  }
1707  if (std::optional<std::string> CompilerPathValue =
1708  llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("COMPILER_PATH")) {
1709  StringRef CompilerPath = *CompilerPathValue;
1710  while (!CompilerPath.empty()) {
1711  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split =
1712  CompilerPath.split(llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator);
1713  PrefixDirs.push_back(std::string(Split.first));
1714  CompilerPath = Split.second;
1715  }
1716  }
1717  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__sysroot_EQ))
1718  SysRoot = A->getValue();
1719  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__dyld_prefix_EQ))
1720  DyldPrefix = A->getValue();
1721 
1722  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_resource_dir))
1723  ResourceDir = A->getValue();
1724 
1725  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_save_temps_EQ)) {
1726  SaveTemps = llvm::StringSwitch<SaveTempsMode>(A->getValue())
1727  .Case("cwd", SaveTempsCwd)
1728  .Case("obj", SaveTempsObj)
1729  .Default(SaveTempsCwd);
1730  }
1731 
1732  if (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_dump_device_code_EQ))
1733  DumpDeviceCode = true;
1734 
1735  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_offload_host_only,
1736  options::OPT_offload_device_only,
1737  options::OPT_offload_host_device)) {
1738  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_host_only))
1739  Offload = OffloadHost;
1740  else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_device_only))
1741  Offload = OffloadDevice;
1742  else
1743  Offload = OffloadHostDevice;
1744  }
1745 
1746  setLTOMode(Args);
1747 
1748  // Process -fembed-bitcode= flags.
1749  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fembed_bitcode_EQ)) {
1750  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
1751  unsigned Model = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
1752  .Case("off", EmbedNone)
1753  .Case("all", EmbedBitcode)
1754  .Case("bitcode", EmbedBitcode)
1755  .Case("marker", EmbedMarker)
1756  .Default(~0U);
1757  if (Model == ~0U) {
1758  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args)
1759  << Name;
1760  } else
1761  BitcodeEmbed = static_cast<BitcodeEmbedMode>(Model);
1762  }
1763 
1764  // Remove existing compilation database so that each job can append to it.
1765  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_MJ))
1766  llvm::sys::fs::remove(A->getValue());
1767 
1768  // Setting up the jobs for some precompile cases depends on whether we are
1769  // treating them as PCH, implicit modules or C++20 ones.
1770  // TODO: inferring the mode like this seems fragile (it meets the objective
1771  // of not requiring anything new for operation, however).
1772  const Arg *Std = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_std_EQ);
1773  ModulesModeCXX20 =
1774  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fmodules) && Std &&
1775  (Std->containsValue("c++20") || Std->containsValue("c++2a") ||
1776  Std->containsValue("c++23") || Std->containsValue("c++2b") ||
1777  Std->containsValue("c++26") || Std->containsValue("c++2c") ||
1778  Std->containsValue("c++latest"));
1779 
1780  // Process -fmodule-header{=} flags.
1781  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodule_header_EQ,
1782  options::OPT_fmodule_header)) {
1783  // These flags force C++20 handling of headers.
1784  ModulesModeCXX20 = true;
1785  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fmodule_header))
1786  CXX20HeaderType = HeaderMode_Default;
1787  else {
1788  StringRef ArgName = A->getValue();
1789  unsigned Kind = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(ArgName)
1790  .Case("user", HeaderMode_User)
1791  .Case("system", HeaderMode_System)
1792  .Default(~0U);
1793  if (Kind == ~0U) {
1794  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
1795  << A->getAsString(Args) << ArgName;
1796  } else
1797  CXX20HeaderType = static_cast<ModuleHeaderMode>(Kind);
1798  }
1799  }
1800 
1801  std::unique_ptr<llvm::opt::InputArgList> UArgs =
1802  std::make_unique<InputArgList>(std::move(Args));
1803 
1804  // Perform the default argument translations.
1805  DerivedArgList *TranslatedArgs = TranslateInputArgs(*UArgs);
1806 
1807  // Owned by the host.
1808  const ToolChain &TC = getToolChain(
1809  *UArgs, computeTargetTriple(*this, TargetTriple, *UArgs));
1810 
1811  // Check if the environment version is valid except wasm case.
1812  llvm::Triple Triple = TC.getTriple();
1813  if (!Triple.isWasm()) {
1814  StringRef TripleVersionName = Triple.getEnvironmentVersionString();
1815  StringRef TripleObjectFormat =
1816  Triple.getObjectFormatTypeName(Triple.getObjectFormat());
1817  if (Triple.getEnvironmentVersion().empty() && TripleVersionName != "" &&
1818  TripleVersionName != TripleObjectFormat) {
1819  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_triple_version_invalid)
1820  << TripleVersionName << TC.getTripleString();
1821  ContainsError = true;
1822  }
1823  }
1824 
1825  // Report warning when arm64EC option is overridden by specified target
1826  if ((TC.getTriple().getArch() != llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
1827  TC.getTriple().getSubArch() != llvm::Triple::AArch64SubArch_arm64ec) &&
1828  UArgs->hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_arm64EC)) {
1829  getDiags().Report(clang::diag::warn_target_override_arm64ec)
1830  << TC.getTriple().str();
1831  }
1832 
1833  // A common user mistake is specifying a target of aarch64-none-eabi or
1834  // arm-none-elf whereas the correct names are aarch64-none-elf &
1835  // arm-none-eabi. Detect these cases and issue a warning.
1836  if (TC.getTriple().getOS() == llvm::Triple::UnknownOS &&
1837  TC.getTriple().getVendor() == llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor) {
1838  switch (TC.getTriple().getArch()) {
1839  case llvm::Triple::arm:
1840  case llvm::Triple::armeb:
1841  case llvm::Triple::thumb:
1842  case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
1843  if (TC.getTriple().getEnvironmentName() == "elf") {
1844  Diag(diag::warn_target_unrecognized_env)
1845  << TargetTriple
1846  << (TC.getTriple().getArchName().str() + "-none-eabi");
1847  }
1848  break;
1849  case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
1850  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
1851  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_32:
1852  if (TC.getTriple().getEnvironmentName().starts_with("eabi")) {
1853  Diag(diag::warn_target_unrecognized_env)
1854  << TargetTriple
1855  << (TC.getTriple().getArchName().str() + "-none-elf");
1856  }
1857  break;
1858  default:
1859  break;
1860  }
1861  }
1862 
1863  // The compilation takes ownership of Args.
1864  Compilation *C = new Compilation(*this, TC, UArgs.release(), TranslatedArgs,
1865  ContainsError);
1866 
1867  if (!HandleImmediateArgs(*C))
1868  return C;
1869 
1870  // Construct the list of inputs.
1871  InputList Inputs;
1872  BuildInputs(C->getDefaultToolChain(), *TranslatedArgs, Inputs);
1873 
1874  // Determine if there are any offload static libraries.
1875  if (checkForOffloadStaticLib(*C, *TranslatedArgs))
1876  setOffloadStaticLibSeen();
1877 
1878  // Check for any objects/archives that need to be compiled with the default
1879  // triple.
1880  if (checkForSYCLDefaultDevice(*C, *TranslatedArgs))
1881  setSYCLDefaultTriple(true);
1882 
1883  // Populate the tool chains for the offloading devices, if any.
1884  CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains(*C, Inputs);
1885 
1886  // Use new offloading path for OpenMP. This is disabled as the SYCL
1887  // offloading path is not properly setup to use the updated device linking
1888  // scheme.
1889  if ((C->isOffloadingHostKind(Action::OFK_OpenMP) &&
1890  TranslatedArgs->hasFlag(options::OPT_fopenmp_new_driver,
1891  options::OPT_no_offload_new_driver, true)) ||
1892  TranslatedArgs->hasFlag(options::OPT_offload_new_driver,
1893  options::OPT_no_offload_new_driver, false))
1894  setUseNewOffloadingDriver();
1895 
1896  // Determine FPGA emulation status.
1897  if (C->hasOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_SYCL>()) {
1898  auto SYCLTCRange = C->getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_SYCL>();
1899  for (auto TI = SYCLTCRange.first, TE = SYCLTCRange.second; TI != TE; ++TI) {
1900  if (TI->second->getTriple().getSubArch() !=
1901  llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga)
1902  continue;
1903  ArgStringList TargetArgs;
1904  const toolchains::SYCLToolChain *FPGATC =
1905  static_cast<const toolchains::SYCLToolChain *>(TI->second);
1906  FPGATC->TranslateBackendTargetArgs(FPGATC->getTriple(), *TranslatedArgs,
1907  TargetArgs);
1908  // By default, FPGAEmulationMode is true due to the fact that
1909  // an external option setting is required to target hardware.
1910  setOffloadCompileMode(FPGAEmulationMode);
1911  for (StringRef ArgString : TargetArgs) {
1912  if (ArgString.equals("-hardware") || ArgString.equals("-simulation")) {
1913  setOffloadCompileMode(FPGAHWMode);
1914  break;
1915  }
1916  }
1917  break;
1918  }
1919  }
1920 
1921  // Construct the list of abstract actions to perform for this compilation. On
1922  // MachO targets this uses the driver-driver and universal actions.
1923  if (TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
1924  BuildUniversalActions(*C, C->getDefaultToolChain(), Inputs);
1925  else
1926  BuildActions(*C, C->getArgs(), Inputs, C->getActions());
1927 
1928  if (CCCPrintPhases) {
1929  PrintActions(*C);
1930  return C;
1931  }
1932 
1933  BuildJobs(*C);
1934 
1935  return C;
1936 }
1937 
1938 static void printArgList(raw_ostream &OS, const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args) {
1939  llvm::opt::ArgStringList ASL;
1940  for (const auto *A : Args) {
1941  // Use user's original spelling of flags. For example, use
1942  // `/source-charset:utf-8` instead of `-finput-charset=utf-8` if the user
1943  // wrote the former.
1944  while (A->getAlias())
1945  A = A->getAlias();
1946  A->render(Args, ASL);
1947  }
1948 
1949  for (auto I = ASL.begin(), E = ASL.end(); I != E; ++I) {
1950  if (I != ASL.begin())
1951  OS << ' ';
1952  llvm::sys::printArg(OS, *I, true);
1953  }
1954  OS << '\n';
1955 }
1956 
1957 bool Driver::getCrashDiagnosticFile(StringRef ReproCrashFilename,
1958  SmallString<128> &CrashDiagDir) {
1959  using namespace llvm::sys;
1960  assert(llvm::Triple(llvm::sys::getProcessTriple()).isOSDarwin() &&
1961  "Only knows about .crash files on Darwin");
1962 
1963  // The .crash file can be found on at ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/
1964  // (or /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports for root) and has the filename pattern
1965  // clang-<VERSION>_<YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS>_<hostname>.crash.
1966  path::home_directory(CrashDiagDir);
1967  if (CrashDiagDir.starts_with("/var/root"))
1968  CrashDiagDir = "/";
1969  path::append(CrashDiagDir, "Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports");
1970  int PID =
1971 #if LLVM_ON_UNIX
1972  getpid();
1973 #else
1974  0;
1975 #endif
1976  std::error_code EC;
1977  fs::file_status FileStatus;
1978  TimePoint<> LastAccessTime;
1979  SmallString<128> CrashFilePath;
1980  // Lookup the .crash files and get the one generated by a subprocess spawned
1981  // by this driver invocation.
1982  for (fs::directory_iterator File(CrashDiagDir, EC), FileEnd;
1983  File != FileEnd && !EC; File.increment(EC)) {
1984  StringRef FileName = path::filename(File->path());
1985  if (!FileName.starts_with(Name))
1986  continue;
1987  if (fs::status(File->path(), FileStatus))
1988  continue;
1989  llvm::ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer>> CrashFile =
1990  llvm::MemoryBuffer::getFile(File->path());
1991  if (!CrashFile)
1992  continue;
1993  // The first line should start with "Process:", otherwise this isn't a real
1994  // .crash file.
1995  StringRef Data = CrashFile.get()->getBuffer();
1996  if (!Data.starts_with("Process:"))
1997  continue;
1998  // Parse parent process pid line, e.g: "Parent Process: clang-4.0 [79141]"
1999  size_t ParentProcPos = Data.find("Parent Process:");
2000  if (ParentProcPos == StringRef::npos)
2001  continue;
2002  size_t LineEnd = Data.find_first_of("\n", ParentProcPos);
2003  if (LineEnd == StringRef::npos)
2004  continue;
2005  StringRef ParentProcess = Data.slice(ParentProcPos+15, LineEnd).trim();
2006  int OpenBracket = -1, CloseBracket = -1;
2007  for (size_t i = 0, e = ParentProcess.size(); i < e; ++i) {
2008  if (ParentProcess[i] == '[')
2009  OpenBracket = i;
2010  if (ParentProcess[i] == ']')
2011  CloseBracket = i;
2012  }
2013  // Extract the parent process PID from the .crash file and check whether
2014  // it matches this driver invocation pid.
2015  int CrashPID;
2016  if (OpenBracket < 0 || CloseBracket < 0 ||
2017  ParentProcess.slice(OpenBracket + 1, CloseBracket)
2018  .getAsInteger(10, CrashPID) || CrashPID != PID) {
2019  continue;
2020  }
2021 
2022  // Found a .crash file matching the driver pid. To avoid getting an older
2023  // and misleading crash file, continue looking for the most recent.
2024  // FIXME: the driver can dispatch multiple cc1 invocations, leading to
2025  // multiple crashes poiting to the same parent process. Since the driver
2026  // does not collect pid information for the dispatched invocation there's
2027  // currently no way to distinguish among them.
2028  const auto FileAccessTime = FileStatus.getLastModificationTime();
2029  if (FileAccessTime > LastAccessTime) {
2030  CrashFilePath.assign(File->path());
2031  LastAccessTime = FileAccessTime;
2032  }
2033  }
2034 
2035  // If found, copy it over to the location of other reproducer files.
2036  if (!CrashFilePath.empty()) {
2037  EC = fs::copy_file(CrashFilePath, ReproCrashFilename);
2038  if (EC)
2039  return false;
2040  return true;
2041  }
2042 
2043  return false;
2044 }
2045 
2046 static const char BugReporMsg[] =
2047  "\n********************\n\n"
2048  "PLEASE ATTACH THE FOLLOWING FILES TO THE BUG REPORT:\n"
2049  "Preprocessed source(s) and associated run script(s) are located at:";
2050 
2051 // When clang crashes, produce diagnostic information including the fully
2052 // preprocessed source file(s). Request that the developer attach the
2053 // diagnostic information to a bug report.
2054 void Driver::generateCompilationDiagnostics(
2055  Compilation &C, const Command &FailingCommand,
2056  StringRef AdditionalInformation, CompilationDiagnosticReport *Report) {
2057  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fno_crash_diagnostics))
2058  return;
2059 
2060  unsigned Level = 1;
2061  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fcrash_diagnostics_EQ)) {
2062  Level = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(A->getValue())
2063  .Case("off", 0)
2064  .Case("compiler", 1)
2065  .Case("all", 2)
2066  .Default(1);
2067  }
2068  if (!Level)
2069  return;
2070 
2071  // Don't try to generate diagnostics for dsymutil jobs.
2072  if (FailingCommand.getCreator().isDsymutilJob())
2073  return;
2074 
2075  bool IsLLD = false;
2076  TempFileList SavedTemps;
2077  if (FailingCommand.getCreator().isLinkJob()) {
2078  C.getDefaultToolChain().GetLinkerPath(&IsLLD);
2079  if (!IsLLD || Level < 2)
2080  return;
2081 
2082  // If lld crashed, we will re-run the same command with the input it used
2083  // to have. In that case we should not remove temp files in
2084  // initCompilationForDiagnostics yet. They will be added back and removed
2085  // later.
2086  SavedTemps = std::move(C.getTempFiles());
2087  assert(!C.getTempFiles().size());
2088  }
2089 
2090  // Print the version of the compiler.
2091  PrintVersion(C, llvm::errs());
2092 
2093  // Suppress driver output and emit preprocessor output to temp file.
2094  CCGenDiagnostics = true;
2095 
2096  // Save the original job command(s).
2097  Command Cmd = FailingCommand;
2098 
2099  // Keep track of whether we produce any errors while trying to produce
2100  // preprocessed sources.
2101  DiagnosticErrorTrap Trap(Diags);
2102 
2103  // Suppress tool output.
2104  C.initCompilationForDiagnostics();
2105 
2106  // If lld failed, rerun it again with --reproduce.
2107  if (IsLLD) {
2108  const char *TmpName = CreateTempFile(C, "linker-crash", "tar");
2109  Command NewLLDInvocation = Cmd;
2110  llvm::opt::ArgStringList ArgList = NewLLDInvocation.getArguments();
2111  StringRef ReproduceOption =
2112  C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment()
2113  ? "/reproduce:"
2114  : "--reproduce=";
2115  ArgList.push_back(Saver.save(Twine(ReproduceOption) + TmpName).data());
2116  NewLLDInvocation.replaceArguments(std::move(ArgList));
2117 
2118  // Redirect stdout/stderr to /dev/null.
2119  NewLLDInvocation.Execute({std::nullopt, {""}, {""}}, nullptr, nullptr);
2120  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << BugReporMsg;
