2121  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << TmpName;
2122  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2123  << "\n\n********************";
2124  if (Report)
2125  Report->TemporaryFiles.push_back(TmpName);
2126  return;
2127  }
2128 
2129  // Construct the list of inputs.
2130  InputList Inputs;
2131  BuildInputs(C.getDefaultToolChain(), C.getArgs(), Inputs);
2132 
2133  for (InputList::iterator it = Inputs.begin(), ie = Inputs.end(); it != ie;) {
2134  bool IgnoreInput = false;
2135 
2136  // Ignore input from stdin or any inputs that cannot be preprocessed.
2137  // Check type first as not all linker inputs have a value.
2138  if (types::getPreprocessedType(it->first) == types::TY_INVALID) {
2139  IgnoreInput = true;
2140  } else if (!strcmp(it->second->getValue(), "-")) {
2141  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2142  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - "
2143  "ignoring input from stdin.";
2144  IgnoreInput = true;
2145  }
2146 
2147  if (IgnoreInput) {
2148  it = Inputs.erase(it);
2149  ie = Inputs.end();
2150  } else {
2151  ++it;
2152  }
2153  }
2154 
2155  if (Inputs.empty()) {
2156  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2157  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - "
2158  "no preprocessable inputs.";
2159  return;
2160  }
2161 
2162  // Don't attempt to generate preprocessed files if multiple -arch options are
2163  // used, unless they're all duplicates.
2164  llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
2165  for (const Arg *A : C.getArgs()) {
2166  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch)) {
2167  StringRef ArchName = A->getValue();
2168  ArchNames.insert(ArchName);
2169  }
2170  }
2171  if (ArchNames.size() > 1) {
2172  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2173  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - cannot generate "
2174  "preprocessed source with multiple -arch options.";
2175  return;
2176  }
2177 
2178  // Construct the list of abstract actions to perform for this compilation. On
2179  // Darwin OSes this uses the driver-driver and builds universal actions.
2180  const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
2181  if (TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
2182  BuildUniversalActions(C, TC, Inputs);
2183  else
2184  BuildActions(C, C.getArgs(), Inputs, C.getActions());
2185 
2186  BuildJobs(C);
2187 
2188  // If there were errors building the compilation, quit now.
2189  if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred()) {
2190  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2191  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
2192  return;
2193  }
2194 
2195  // Generate preprocessed output.
2196  SmallVector<std::pair<int, const Command *>, 4> FailingCommands;
2197  C.ExecuteJobs(C.getJobs(), FailingCommands);
2198 
2199  // If any of the preprocessing commands failed, clean up and exit.
2200  if (!FailingCommands.empty()) {
2201  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2202  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
2203  return;
2204  }
2205 
2206  const TempFileList &TempFiles = C.getTempFiles();
2207  if (TempFiles.empty()) {
2208  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2209  << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
2210  return;
2211  }
2212 
2213  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << BugReporMsg;
2214 
2215  SmallString<128> VFS;
2216  SmallString<128> ReproCrashFilename;
2217  for (auto &TempFile : TempFiles) {
2218  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << TempFile.first;
2219  if (Report)
2220  Report->TemporaryFiles.push_back(TempFile.first);
2221  if (ReproCrashFilename.empty()) {
2222  ReproCrashFilename = TempFile.first;
2223  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(ReproCrashFilename, ".crash");
2224  }
2225  if (StringRef(TempFile.first).ends_with(".cache")) {
2226  // In some cases (modules) we'll dump extra data to help with reproducing
2227  // the crash into a directory next to the output.
2228  VFS = llvm::sys::path::filename(TempFile.first);
2229  llvm::sys::path::append(VFS, "vfs", "vfs.yaml");
2230  }
2231  }
2232 
2233  for (auto &TempFile : SavedTemps)
2234  C.addTempFile(TempFile.first);
2235 
2236  // Assume associated files are based off of the first temporary file.
2237  CrashReportInfo CrashInfo(TempFiles[0].first, VFS);
2238 
2239  llvm::SmallString<128> Script(CrashInfo.Filename);
2240  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Script, "sh");
2241  std::error_code EC;
2242  llvm::raw_fd_ostream ScriptOS(Script, EC, llvm::sys::fs::CD_CreateNew,
2243  llvm::sys::fs::FA_Write,
2244  llvm::sys::fs::OF_Text);
2245  if (EC) {
2246  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2247  << "Error generating run script: " << Script << " " << EC.message();
2248  } else {
2249  ScriptOS << "# Crash reproducer for " << getClangFullVersion() << "\n"
2250  << "# Driver args: ";
2251  printArgList(ScriptOS, C.getInputArgs());
2252  ScriptOS << "# Original command: ";
2253  Cmd.Print(ScriptOS, "\n", /*Quote=*/true);
2254  Cmd.Print(ScriptOS, "\n", /*Quote=*/true, &CrashInfo);
2255  if (!AdditionalInformation.empty())
2256  ScriptOS << "\n# Additional information: " << AdditionalInformation
2257  << "\n";
2258  if (Report)
2259  Report->TemporaryFiles.push_back(std::string(Script));
2260  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << Script;
2261  }
2262 
2263  // On darwin, provide information about the .crash diagnostic report.
2264  if (llvm::Triple(llvm::sys::getProcessTriple()).isOSDarwin()) {
2265  SmallString<128> CrashDiagDir;
2266  if (getCrashDiagnosticFile(ReproCrashFilename, CrashDiagDir)) {
2267  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2268  << ReproCrashFilename.str();
2269  } else { // Suggest a directory for the user to look for .crash files.
2270  llvm::sys::path::append(CrashDiagDir, Name);
2271  CrashDiagDir += "_<YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS>_<hostname>.crash";
2272  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2273  << "Crash backtrace is located in";
2274  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2275  << CrashDiagDir.str();
2276  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2277  << "(choose the .crash file that corresponds to your crash)";
2278  }
2279  }
2280 
2281  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
2282  << "\n\n********************";
2283 }
2284 
2285 void Driver::setUpResponseFiles(Compilation &C, Command &Cmd) {
2286  // Since commandLineFitsWithinSystemLimits() may underestimate system's
2287  // capacity if the tool does not support response files, there is a chance/
2288  // that things will just work without a response file, so we silently just
2289  // skip it.
2290  if (Cmd.getResponseFileSupport().ResponseKind ==
2291  ResponseFileSupport::RF_None ||
2292  llvm::sys::commandLineFitsWithinSystemLimits(Cmd.getExecutable(),
2293  Cmd.getArguments()))
2294  return;
2295 
2296  std::string TmpName = GetTemporaryPath("response", "txt");
2297  Cmd.setResponseFile(C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName)));
2298 }
2299 
2300 int Driver::ExecuteCompilation(
2301  Compilation &C,
2302  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<int, const Command *>> &FailingCommands) {
2303  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fdriver_only)) {
2304  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v))
2305  C.getJobs().Print(llvm::errs(), "\n", true);
2306 
2307  C.ExecuteJobs(C.getJobs(), FailingCommands, /*LogOnly=*/true);
2308 
2309  // If there were errors building the compilation, quit now.
2310  if (!FailingCommands.empty() || Diags.hasErrorOccurred())
2311  return 1;
2312 
2313  return 0;
2314  }
2315 
2316  // Just print if -### was present.
2317  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
2318  C.getJobs().Print(llvm::errs(), "\n", true);
2319  return Diags.hasErrorOccurred() ? 1 : 0;
2320  }
2321 
2322  // If there were errors building the compilation, quit now.
2323  if (Diags.hasErrorOccurred())
2324  return 1;
2325 
2326  // Set up response file names for each command, if necessary.
2327  for (auto &Job : C.getJobs())
2328  setUpResponseFiles(C, Job);
2329 
2330  C.ExecuteJobs(C.getJobs(), FailingCommands);
2331 
2332  // If the command succeeded, we are done.
2333  if (FailingCommands.empty())
2334  return 0;
2335 
2336  // Otherwise, remove result files and print extra information about abnormal
2337  // failures.
2338  int Res = 0;
2339  for (const auto &CmdPair : FailingCommands) {
2340  int CommandRes = CmdPair.first;
2341  const Command *FailingCommand = CmdPair.second;
2342 
2343  // Remove result files if we're not saving temps.
2344  if (!isSaveTempsEnabled()) {
2345  const JobAction *JA = cast<JobAction>(&FailingCommand->getSource());
2346  C.CleanupFileMap(C.getResultFiles(), JA, true);
2347 
2348  // Failure result files are valid unless we crashed.
2349  if (CommandRes < 0)
2350  C.CleanupFileMap(C.getFailureResultFiles(), JA, true);
2351  }
2352 
2353  // llvm/lib/Support/*/Signals.inc will exit with a special return code
2354  // for SIGPIPE. Do not print diagnostics for this case.
2355  if (CommandRes == EX_IOERR) {
2356  Res = CommandRes;
2357  continue;
2358  }
2359 
2360  // Print extra information about abnormal failures, if possible.
2361  //
2362  // This is ad-hoc, but we don't want to be excessively noisy. If the result
2363  // status was 1, assume the command failed normally. In particular, if it
2364  // was the compiler then assume it gave a reasonable error code. Failures
2365  // in other tools are less common, and they generally have worse
2366  // diagnostics, so always print the diagnostic there.
2367  const Tool &FailingTool = FailingCommand->getCreator();
2368 
2369  if (!FailingTool.hasGoodDiagnostics() || CommandRes != 1) {
2370  // FIXME: See FIXME above regarding result code interpretation.
2371  if (CommandRes < 0)
2372  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_command_signalled)
2373  << FailingTool.getShortName();
2374  else
2375  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_command_failed)
2376  << FailingTool.getShortName() << CommandRes;
2377  }
2378 
2379  auto CustomDiag = FailingCommand->getDiagForErrorCode(CommandRes);
2380  if (!CustomDiag.empty())
2381  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << CustomDiag;
2382  }
2383  return Res;
2384 }
2385 
2386 void Driver::PrintHelp(bool ShowHidden) const {
2387  llvm::opt::Visibility VisibilityMask = getOptionVisibilityMask();
2388 
2389  std::string Usage = llvm::formatv("{0} [options] file...", Name).str();
2390  getOpts().printHelp(llvm::outs(), Usage.c_str(), DriverTitle.c_str(),
2391  ShowHidden, /*ShowAllAliases=*/false,
2392  VisibilityMask);
2393 }

2395 llvm::Triple Driver::MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(StringRef TargetArch) const {
2396  SmallVector<StringRef, 5> SYCLAlias = {
2397  "spir", "spir64", "spir64_fpga", "spir64_x86_64",
2398  "spir64_gen", "spirv32", "spirv64"};
2399  if (std::find(SYCLAlias.begin(), SYCLAlias.end(), TargetArch) !=
2400  SYCLAlias.end()) {
2401  llvm::Triple TT;
2402  TT.setArchName(TargetArch);
2403  TT.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
2404  TT.setOS(llvm::Triple::UnknownOS);
2405  return TT;
2406  }
2407  return llvm::Triple(TargetArch);
2408 }

2410 // Print the help from any of the given tools which are used for AOT
2411 // compilation for SYCL
2412 void Driver::PrintSYCLToolHelp(const Compilation &C) const {
2413  SmallVector<std::tuple<llvm::Triple, StringRef, StringRef, StringRef>, 4>
2414  HelpArgs;
2415  // Populate the vector with the tools and help options
2416  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_help_EQ)) {
2417  StringRef AV(A->getValue());
2418  llvm::Triple T;
2419  if (AV == "gen" || AV == "all")
2420  HelpArgs.push_back(std::make_tuple(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("spir64_gen"),
2421  "ocloc", "--help", ""));
2422  if (AV == "fpga" || AV == "all")
2423  HelpArgs.push_back(std::make_tuple(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("spir64_fpga"),
2424  "aoc", "-help", "-sycl"));
2425  if (AV == "x86_64" || AV == "all")
2426  HelpArgs.push_back(std::make_tuple(MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("spir64_x86_64"),
2427  "opencl-aot", "--help", ""));
2428  if (HelpArgs.empty()) {
2429  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
2430  << A->getSpelling() << AV;
2431  return;
2432  }
2433  }
2434 
2435  // Go through the args and emit the help information for each.
2436  for (auto &HA : HelpArgs) {
2437  llvm::outs() << "Emitting help information for " << std::get<1>(HA) << '\n'
2438  << "Use triple of '" << std::get<0>(HA).normalize() <<
2439  "' to enable ahead of time compilation\n";
2440  // Flush out the buffer before calling the external tool.
2441  llvm::outs().flush();
2442  std::vector<StringRef> ToolArgs = {std::get<1>(HA), std::get<2>(HA),
2443  std::get<3>(HA)};
2444  SmallString<128> ExecPath(
2445  C.getDefaultToolChain().GetProgramPath(std::get<1>(HA).data()));
2446  // do not run the tools with -###.
2447  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
2448  llvm::errs() << "\"" << ExecPath << "\" \"" << ToolArgs[1] << "\"";
2449  if (!ToolArgs[2].empty())
2450  llvm::errs() << " \"" << ToolArgs[2] << "\"";
2451  llvm::errs() << "\n";
2452  continue;
2453  }
2454  auto ToolBinary = llvm::sys::findProgramByName(ExecPath);
2455  if (ToolBinary.getError()) {
2456  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_command_failure) << ExecPath;
2457  continue;
2458  }
2459  // Run the Tool.
2460  llvm::sys::ExecuteAndWait(ToolBinary.get(), ToolArgs);
2461  }
2462 }

2464 void Driver::PrintVersion(const Compilation &C, raw_ostream &OS) const {
2465  if (IsFlangMode()) {
2466  OS << getClangToolFullVersion("flang-new") << '\n';
2467  } else {
2468  // FIXME: The following handlers should use a callback mechanism, we don't
2469  // know what the client would like to do.
2470  OS << getClangFullVersion() << '\n';
2471  }
2472  const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
2473  OS << "Target: " << TC.getTripleString() << '\n';
2474 
2475  // Print the threading model.
2476  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_mthread_model)) {
2477  // Don't print if the ToolChain would have barfed on it already
2478  if (TC.isThreadModelSupported(A->getValue()))
2479  OS << "Thread model: " << A->getValue();
2480  } else
2481  OS << "Thread model: " << TC.getThreadModel();
2482  OS << '\n';
2483 
2484  // Print out the install directory.
2485  OS << "InstalledDir: " << Dir << '\n';
2486 
2487  // Print the build config if it's non-default.
2488  // Intended to help LLVM developers understand the configs of compilers
2489  // they're investigating.
2490  if (!llvm::cl::getCompilerBuildConfig().empty())
2491  llvm::cl::printBuildConfig(OS);
2492 
2493  // If configuration files were used, print their paths.
2494  for (auto ConfigFile : ConfigFiles)
2495  OS << "Configuration file: " << ConfigFile << '\n';
2496 }

2498 /// PrintDiagnosticCategories - Implement the --print-diagnostic-categories
2499 /// option.
2500 static void PrintDiagnosticCategories(raw_ostream &OS) {
2501  // Skip the empty category.
2502  for (unsigned i = 1, max = DiagnosticIDs::getNumberOfCategories(); i != max;
2503  ++i)
2504  OS << i << ',' << DiagnosticIDs::getCategoryNameFromID(i) << '\n';
2505 }
2506 
2507 void Driver::HandleAutocompletions(StringRef PassedFlags) const {
2508  if (PassedFlags == "")
2509  return;
2510  // Print out all options that start with a given argument. This is used for
2511  // shell autocompletion.
2512  std::vector<std::string> SuggestedCompletions;
2513  std::vector<std::string> Flags;
2514 
2515  llvm::opt::Visibility VisibilityMask(options::ClangOption);
2516 
2517  // Make sure that Flang-only options don't pollute the Clang output
2518  // TODO: Make sure that Clang-only options don't pollute Flang output
2519  if (IsFlangMode())
2520  VisibilityMask = llvm::opt::Visibility(options::FlangOption);
2521 
2522  // Distinguish "--autocomplete=-someflag" and "--autocomplete=-someflag,"
2523  // because the latter indicates that the user put space before pushing tab
2524  // which should end up in a file completion.
2525  const bool HasSpace = PassedFlags.ends_with(",");
2526 
2527  // Parse PassedFlags by "," as all the command-line flags are passed to this
2528  // function separated by ","
2529  StringRef TargetFlags = PassedFlags;
2530  while (TargetFlags != "") {
2531  StringRef CurFlag;
2532  std::tie(CurFlag, TargetFlags) = TargetFlags.split(",");
2533  Flags.push_back(std::string(CurFlag));
2534  }
2535 
2536  // We want to show cc1-only options only when clang is invoked with -cc1 or
2537  // -Xclang.
2538  if (llvm::is_contained(Flags, "-Xclang") || llvm::is_contained(Flags, "-cc1"))
2539  VisibilityMask = llvm::opt::Visibility(options::CC1Option);
2540 
2541  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = getOpts();
2542  StringRef Cur;
2543  Cur = Flags.at(Flags.size() - 1);
2544  StringRef Prev;
2545  if (Flags.size() >= 2) {
2546  Prev = Flags.at(Flags.size() - 2);
2547  SuggestedCompletions = Opts.suggestValueCompletions(Prev, Cur);
2548  }
2549 
2550  if (SuggestedCompletions.empty())
2551  SuggestedCompletions = Opts.suggestValueCompletions(Cur, "");
2552 
2553  // If Flags were empty, it means the user typed `clang [tab]` where we should
2554  // list all possible flags. If there was no value completion and the user
2555  // pressed tab after a space, we should fall back to a file completion.
2556  // We're printing a newline to be consistent with what we print at the end of
2557  // this function.
2558  if (SuggestedCompletions.empty() && HasSpace && !Flags.empty()) {
2559  llvm::outs() << '\n';
2560  return;
2561  }
2562 
2563  // When flag ends with '=' and there was no value completion, return empty
2564  // string and fall back to the file autocompletion.
2565  if (SuggestedCompletions.empty() && !Cur.ends_with("=")) {
2566  // If the flag is in the form of "--autocomplete=-foo",
2567  // we were requested to print out all option names that start with "-foo".
2568  // For example, "--autocomplete=-fsyn" is expanded to "-fsyntax-only".
2569  SuggestedCompletions = Opts.findByPrefix(
2570  Cur, VisibilityMask,
2571  /*DisableFlags=*/options::Unsupported | options::Ignored);
2572 
2573  // We have to query the -W flags manually as they're not in the OptTable.
2574  // TODO: Find a good way to add them to OptTable instead and them remove
2575  // this code.
2576  for (StringRef S : DiagnosticIDs::getDiagnosticFlags())
2577  if (S.starts_with(Cur))
2578  SuggestedCompletions.push_back(std::string(S));
2579  }
2580 
2581  // Sort the autocomplete candidates so that shells print them out in a
2582  // deterministic order. We could sort in any way, but we chose
2583  // case-insensitive sorting for consistency with the -help option
2584  // which prints out options in the case-insensitive alphabetical order.
2585  llvm::sort(SuggestedCompletions, [](StringRef A, StringRef B) {
2586  if (int X = A.compare_insensitive(B))
2587  return X < 0;
2588  return A.compare(B) > 0;
2589  });
2590 
2591  llvm::outs() << llvm::join(SuggestedCompletions, "\n") << '\n';
2592 }
2593 
2594 bool Driver::HandleImmediateArgs(const Compilation &C) {
2595  // The order these options are handled in gcc is all over the place, but we
2596  // don't expect inconsistencies w.r.t. that to matter in practice.
2597 
2598  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dumpmachine)) {
2599  llvm::outs() << C.getDefaultToolChain().getTripleString() << '\n';
2600  return false;
2601  }
2602 
2603  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dumpversion)) {
2604  // Since -dumpversion is only implemented for pedantic GCC compatibility, we
2605  // return an answer which matches our definition of __VERSION__.
2606  llvm::outs() << CLANG_VERSION_STRING << "\n";
2607  return false;
2608  }
2609 
2610  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__print_diagnostic_categories)) {
2611  PrintDiagnosticCategories(llvm::outs());
2612  return false;
2613  }
2614 
2615  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_help) ||
2616  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__help_hidden)) {
2617  PrintHelp(C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__help_hidden));
2618  return false;
2619  }
2620 
2621  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_help_EQ)) {
2622  PrintSYCLToolHelp(C);
2623  return false;
2624  }
2625 
2626  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__version)) {
2627  // Follow gcc behavior and use stdout for --version and stderr for -v.
2628  PrintVersion(C, llvm::outs());
2629  return false;
2630  }
2631 
2632  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v) ||
2633  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH) ||
2634  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_supported_cpus) ||
2635  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_supported_extensions)) {
2636  PrintVersion(C, llvm::errs());
2637  SuppressMissingInputWarning = true;
2638  }
2639 
2640  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v)) {
2641  if (!SystemConfigDir.empty())
2642  llvm::errs() << "System configuration file directory: "
2643  << SystemConfigDir << "\n";
2644  if (!UserConfigDir.empty())
2645  llvm::errs() << "User configuration file directory: "
2646  << UserConfigDir << "\n";
2647  }
2648 
2649  const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
2650 
2651  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v))
2652  TC.printVerboseInfo(llvm::errs());
2653 
2654  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_resource_dir)) {
2655  llvm::outs() << ResourceDir << '\n';
2656  return false;
2657  }
2658 
2659  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_search_dirs)) {
2660  llvm::outs() << "programs: =";
2661  bool separator = false;
2662  // Print -B and COMPILER_PATH.
2663  for (const std::string &Path : PrefixDirs) {
2664  if (separator)
2665  llvm::outs() << llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator;
2666  llvm::outs() << Path;
2667  separator = true;
2668  }
2669  for (const std::string &Path : TC.getProgramPaths()) {
2670  if (separator)
2671  llvm::outs() << llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator;
2672  llvm::outs() << Path;
2673  separator = true;
2674  }
2675  llvm::outs() << "\n";
2676  llvm::outs() << "libraries: =" << ResourceDir;
2677 
2678  StringRef sysroot = C.getSysRoot();
2679 
2680  for (const std::string &Path : TC.getFilePaths()) {
2681  // Always print a separator. ResourceDir was the first item shown.
2682  llvm::outs() << llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator;
2683  // Interpretation of leading '=' is needed only for NetBSD.
2684  if (Path[0] == '=')
2685  llvm::outs() << sysroot << Path.substr(1);
2686  else
2687  llvm::outs() << Path;
2688  }
2689  llvm::outs() << "\n";
2690  return false;
2691  }
2692 
2693  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_std_module_manifest_path)) {
2694  llvm::outs() << GetStdModuleManifestPath(C, C.getDefaultToolChain())
2695  << '\n';
2696  return false;
2697  }
2698 
2699  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_runtime_dir)) {
2700  if (std::optional<std::string> RuntimePath = TC.getRuntimePath())
2701  llvm::outs() << *RuntimePath << '\n';
2702  else
2703  llvm::outs() << TC.getCompilerRTPath() << '\n';
2704  return false;
2705  }
2706 
2707  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_diagnostic_options)) {
2708  std::vector<std::string> Flags = DiagnosticIDs::getDiagnosticFlags();
2709  for (std::size_t I = 0; I != Flags.size(); I += 2)
2710  llvm::outs() << " " << Flags[I] << "\n " << Flags[I + 1] << "\n\n";
2711  return false;
2712  }
2713 
2714  // FIXME: The following handlers should use a callback mechanism, we don't
2715  // know what the client would like to do.
2716  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_print_file_name_EQ)) {
2717  llvm::outs() << GetFilePath(A->getValue(), TC) << "\n";
2718  return false;
2719  }
2720 
2721  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_print_prog_name_EQ)) {
2722  StringRef ProgName = A->getValue();
2723 
2724  // Null program name cannot have a path.
2725  if (! ProgName.empty())
2726  llvm::outs() << GetProgramPath(ProgName, TC);
2727 
2728  llvm::outs() << "\n";
2729  return false;
2730  }
2731 
2732  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_autocomplete)) {
2733  StringRef PassedFlags = A->getValue();
2734  HandleAutocompletions(PassedFlags);
2735  return false;
2736  }
2737 
2738  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_libgcc_file_name)) {
2739  ToolChain::RuntimeLibType RLT = TC.GetRuntimeLibType(C.getArgs());
2740  const llvm::Triple Triple(TC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(C.getArgs()));
2741  RegisterEffectiveTriple TripleRAII(TC, Triple);
2742  switch (RLT) {
2743  case ToolChain::RLT_CompilerRT:
2744  llvm::outs() << TC.getCompilerRT(C.getArgs(), "builtins") << "\n";
2745  break;
2746  case ToolChain::RLT_Libgcc:
2747  llvm::outs() << GetFilePath("libgcc.a", TC) << "\n";
2748  break;
2749  }
2750  return false;
2751  }
2752 
2753  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_multi_lib)) {
2754  for (const Multilib &Multilib : TC.getMultilibs())
2755  llvm::outs() << Multilib << "\n";
2756  return false;
2757  }
2758 
2759  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_multi_flags)) {
2760  Multilib::flags_list ArgFlags = TC.getMultilibFlags(C.getArgs());
2761  llvm::StringSet<> ExpandedFlags = TC.getMultilibs().expandFlags(ArgFlags);
2762  std::set<llvm::StringRef> SortedFlags;
2763  for (const auto &FlagEntry : ExpandedFlags)
2764  SortedFlags.insert(FlagEntry.getKey());
2765  for (auto Flag : SortedFlags)
2766  llvm::outs() << Flag << '\n';
2767  return false;
2768  }
2769 
2770  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_multi_directory)) {
2771  for (const Multilib &Multilib : TC.getSelectedMultilibs()) {
2772  if (Multilib.gccSuffix().empty())
2773  llvm::outs() << ".\n";
2774  else {
2775  StringRef Suffix(Multilib.gccSuffix());
2776  assert(Suffix.front() == '/');
2777  llvm::outs() << Suffix.substr(1) << "\n";
2778  }
2779  }
2780  return false;
2781  }
2782 
2783  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_target_triple)) {
2784  llvm::outs() << TC.getTripleString() << "\n";
2785  return false;
2786  }
2787 
2788  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_effective_triple)) {
2789  const llvm::Triple Triple(TC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(C.getArgs()));
2790  llvm::outs() << Triple.getTriple() << "\n";
2791  return false;
2792  }
2793 
2794  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_targets)) {
2795  llvm::TargetRegistry::printRegisteredTargetsForVersion(llvm::outs());
2796  return false;
2797  }
2798 
2799  return true;
2800 }
2801 
2802 enum {
2803  TopLevelAction = 0,
2804  HeadSibAction = 1,
2805  OtherSibAction = 2,
2806 };
2807 
2808 // Display an action graph human-readably. Action A is the "sink" node
2809 // and latest-occuring action. Traversal is in pre-order, visiting the
2810 // inputs to each action before printing the action itself.
2811 static unsigned PrintActions1(const Compilation &C, Action *A,
2812  std::map<Action *, unsigned> &Ids,
2813  Twine Indent = {}, int Kind = TopLevelAction) {
2814  if (Ids.count(A)) // A was already visited.
2815  return Ids[A];
2816 
2817  std::string str;
2818  llvm::raw_string_ostream os(str);
2819 
2820  auto getSibIndent = [](int K) -> Twine {
2821  return (K == HeadSibAction) ? " " : (K == OtherSibAction) ? "| " : "";
2822  };
2823 
2824  Twine SibIndent = Indent + getSibIndent(Kind);
2825  int SibKind = HeadSibAction;
2826  os << Action::getClassName(A->getKind()) << ", ";
2827  if (InputAction *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(A)) {
2828  os << "\"" << IA->getInputArg().getValue() << "\"";
2829  } else if (BindArchAction *BIA = dyn_cast<BindArchAction>(A)) {
2830  os << '"' << BIA->getArchName() << '"' << ", {"
2831  << PrintActions1(C, *BIA->input_begin(), Ids, SibIndent, SibKind) << "}";
2832  } else if (OffloadAction *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(A)) {
2833  bool IsFirst = true;
2834  OA->doOnEachDependence(
2835  [&](Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, const char *BoundArch) {
2836  assert(TC && "Unknown host toolchain");
2837  // E.g. for two CUDA device dependences whose bound arch is sm_20 and
2838  // sm_35 this will generate:
2839  // "cuda-device" (nvptx64-nvidia-cuda:sm_20) {#ID}, "cuda-device"
2840  // (nvptx64-nvidia-cuda:sm_35) {#ID}
2841  if (!IsFirst)
2842  os << ", ";
2843  os << '"';
2844  os << A->getOffloadingKindPrefix();
2845  os << " (";
2846  os << TC->getTriple().normalize();
2847  if (BoundArch)
2848  os << ":" << BoundArch;
2849  os << ")";
2850  os << '"';
2851  os << " {" << PrintActions1(C, A, Ids, SibIndent, SibKind) << "}";
2852  IsFirst = false;
2853  SibKind = OtherSibAction;
2854  });
2855  } else {
2856  const ActionList *AL = &A->getInputs();
2857 
2858  if (AL->size()) {
2859  const char *Prefix = "{";
2860  for (Action *PreRequisite : *AL) {
2861  os << Prefix << PrintActions1(C, PreRequisite, Ids, SibIndent, SibKind);
2862  Prefix = ", ";
2863  SibKind = OtherSibAction;
2864  }
2865  os << "}";
2866  } else
2867  os << "{}";
2868  }
2869 
2870  // Append offload info for all options other than the offloading action
2871  // itself (e.g. (cuda-device, sm_20) or (cuda-host)).
2872  std::string offload_str;
2873  llvm::raw_string_ostream offload_os(offload_str);
2874  if (!isa<OffloadAction>(A)) {
2875  auto S = A->getOffloadingKindPrefix();
2876  if (!S.empty()) {
2877  offload_os << ", (" << S;
2878  if (A->getOffloadingArch())
2879  offload_os << ", " << A->getOffloadingArch();
2880  offload_os << ")";
2881  }
2882  }
2883 
2884  auto getSelfIndent = [](int K) -> Twine {
2885  return (K == HeadSibAction) ? "+- " : (K == OtherSibAction) ? "|- " : "";
2886  };
2887 
2888  unsigned Id = Ids.size();
2889  Ids[A] = Id;
2890  llvm::errs() << Indent + getSelfIndent(Kind) << Id << ": " << os.str() << ", "
2891  << types::getTypeName(A->getType()) << offload_os.str() << "\n";
2892 
2893  return Id;
2894 }
2895 
2896 // Print the action graphs in a compilation C.
2897 // For example "clang -c file1.c file2.c" is composed of two subgraphs.
2898 void Driver::PrintActions(const Compilation &C) const {
2899  std::map<Action *, unsigned> Ids;
2900  for (Action *A : C.getActions())
2901  PrintActions1(C, A, Ids);
2902 }
2903 
2904 /// Check whether the given input tree contains any compilation or
2905 /// assembly actions.
2906 static bool ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(const Action *A) {
2907  if (isa<CompileJobAction>(A) || isa<BackendJobAction>(A) ||
2908  isa<AssembleJobAction>(A))
2909  return true;
2910 
2911  return llvm::any_of(A->inputs(), ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction);
2912 }
2913 
2914 void Driver::BuildUniversalActions(Compilation &C, const ToolChain &TC,
2915  const InputList &BAInputs) const {
2916  DerivedArgList &Args = C.getArgs();
2917  ActionList &Actions = C.getActions();
2918  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building universal build actions");
2919  // Collect the list of architectures. Duplicates are allowed, but should only
2920  // be handled once (in the order seen).
2921  llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
2922  SmallVector<const char *, 4> Archs;
2923  for (Arg *A : Args) {
2924  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch)) {
2925  // Validate the option here; we don't save the type here because its
2926  // particular spelling may participate in other driver choices.
2927  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch =
2928  tools::darwin::getArchTypeForMachOArchName(A->getValue());
2929  if (Arch == llvm::Triple::UnknownArch) {
2930  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_arch_name) << A->getAsString(Args);
2931  continue;
2932  }
2933 
2934  A->claim();
2935  if (ArchNames.insert(A->getValue()).second)
2936  Archs.push_back(A->getValue());
2937  }
2938  }
2939 
2940  // When there is no explicit arch for this platform, make sure we still bind
2941  // the architecture (to the default) so that -Xarch_ is handled correctly.
2942  if (!Archs.size())
2943  Archs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TC.getDefaultUniversalArchName()));
2944 
2945  ActionList SingleActions;
2946  BuildActions(C, Args, BAInputs, SingleActions);
2947 
2948  // Add in arch bindings for every top level action, as well as lipo and
2949  // dsymutil steps if needed.
2950  for (Action* Act : SingleActions) {
2951  // Make sure we can lipo this kind of output. If not (and it is an actual
2952  // output) then we disallow, since we can't create an output file with the
2953  // right name without overwriting it. We could remove this oddity by just
2954  // changing the output names to include the arch, which would also fix
2955  // -save-temps. Compatibility wins for now.
2956 
2957  if (Archs.size() > 1 && !types::canLipoType(Act->getType()))
2958  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_output_with_multiple_archs)
2959  << types::getTypeName(Act->getType());
2960 
2961  ActionList Inputs;
2962  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Archs.size(); i != e; ++i)
2963  Inputs.push_back(C.MakeAction<BindArchAction>(Act, Archs[i]));
2964 
2965  // Lipo if necessary, we do it this way because we need to set the arch flag
2966  // so that -Xarch_ gets overwritten.
2967  if (Inputs.size() == 1 || Act->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
2968  Actions.append(Inputs.begin(), Inputs.end());
2969  else
2970  Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<LipoJobAction>(Inputs, Act->getType()));
2971 
2972  // Handle debug info queries.
2973  Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_g_Group);
2974  bool enablesDebugInfo = A && !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_g0) &&
2975  !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gstabs);
2976  if ((enablesDebugInfo || willEmitRemarks(Args)) &&
2977  ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(Actions.back())) {
2978 
2979  // Add a 'dsymutil' step if necessary, when debug info is enabled and we
2980  // have a compile input. We need to run 'dsymutil' ourselves in such cases
2981  // because the debug info will refer to a temporary object file which
2982  // will be removed at the end of the compilation process.
2983  if (Act->getType() == types::TY_Image) {
2984  ActionList Inputs;
2985  Inputs.push_back(Actions.back());
2986  Actions.pop_back();
2987  Actions.push_back(
2988  C.MakeAction<DsymutilJobAction>(Inputs, types::TY_dSYM));
2989  }
2990 
2991  // Verify the debug info output.
2992  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_verify_debug_info)) {
2993  Action* LastAction = Actions.back();
2994  Actions.pop_back();
2995  Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<VerifyDebugInfoJobAction>(
2996  LastAction, types::TY_Nothing));
2997  }
2998  }
2999  }
3000 }
3001 
3002 bool Driver::DiagnoseInputExistence(const DerivedArgList &Args, StringRef Value,
3003  types::ID Ty, bool TypoCorrect) const {
3004  if (!getCheckInputsExist())
3005  return true;
3006 
3007  // stdin always exists.
3008  if (Value == "-")
3009  return true;
3010 
3011  // If it's a header to be found in the system or user search path, then defer
3012  // complaints about its absence until those searches can be done. When we
3013  // are definitely processing headers for C++20 header units, extend this to
3014  // allow the user to put "-fmodule-header -xc++-header vector" for example.
3015  if (Ty == types::TY_CXXSHeader || Ty == types::TY_CXXUHeader ||
3016  (ModulesModeCXX20 && Ty == types::TY_CXXHeader))
3017  return true;
3018 
3019  if (getVFS().exists(Value))
3020  return true;
3021 
3022  if (TypoCorrect) {
3023  // Check if the filename is a typo for an option flag. OptTable thinks
3024  // that all args that are not known options and that start with / are
3025  // filenames, but e.g. `/diagnostic:caret` is more likely a typo for
3026  // the option `/diagnostics:caret` than a reference to a file in the root
3027  // directory.
3028  std::string Nearest;
3029  if (getOpts().findNearest(Value, Nearest, getOptionVisibilityMask()) <= 1) {
3030  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_such_file_with_suggestion)
3031  << Value << Nearest;
3032  return false;
3033  }
3034  }
3035 
3036  // In CL mode, don't error on apparently non-existent linker inputs, because
3037  // they can be influenced by linker flags the clang driver might not
3038  // understand.
3039  // Examples:
3040  // - `clang-cl main.cc ole32.lib` in a non-MSVC shell will make the driver
3041  // module look for an MSVC installation in the registry. (We could ask
3042  // the MSVCToolChain object if it can find `ole32.lib`, but the logic to
3043  // look in the registry might move into lld-link in the future so that
3044  // lld-link invocations in non-MSVC shells just work too.)
3045  // - `clang-cl ... /link ...` can pass arbitrary flags to the linker,
3046  // including /libpath:, which is used to find .lib and .obj files.
3047  // So do not diagnose this on the driver level. Rely on the linker diagnosing
3048  // it. (If we don't end up invoking the linker, this means we'll emit a
3049  // "'linker' input unused [-Wunused-command-line-argument]" warning instead
3050  // of an error.)
3051  //
3052  // Only do this skip after the typo correction step above. `/Brepo` is treated
3053  // as TY_Object, but it's clearly a typo for `/Brepro`. It seems fine to emit
3054  // an error if we have a flag that's within an edit distance of 1 from a
3055  // flag. (Users can use `-Wl,` or `/linker` to launder the flag past the
3056  // driver in the unlikely case they run into this.)
3057  //
3058  // Don't do this for inputs that start with a '/', else we'd pass options
3059  // like /libpath: through to the linker silently.
3060  //
3061  // Emitting an error for linker inputs can also cause incorrect diagnostics
3062  // with the gcc driver. The command
3063  // clang -fuse-ld=lld -Wl,--chroot,some/dir /file.o
3064  // will make lld look for some/dir/file.o, while we will diagnose here that
3065  // `/file.o` does not exist. However, configure scripts check if
3066  // `clang /GR-` compiles without error to see if the compiler is cl.exe,
3067  // so we can't downgrade diagnostics for `/GR-` from an error to a warning
3068  // in cc mode. (We can in cl mode because cl.exe itself only warns on
3069  // unknown flags.)
3070  if (IsCLMode() && Ty == types::TY_Object && !Value.starts_with("/"))
3071  return true;
3072 
3073  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_such_file) << Value;
3074  return false;
3075 }
3076 
3077 // Get the C++20 Header Unit type corresponding to the input type.
3078 static types::ID CXXHeaderUnitType(ModuleHeaderMode HM) {
3079  switch (HM) {
3080  case HeaderMode_User:
3081  return types::TY_CXXUHeader;
3082  case HeaderMode_System:
3083  return types::TY_CXXSHeader;
3084  case HeaderMode_Default:
3085  break;
3086  case HeaderMode_None:
3087  llvm_unreachable("should not be called in this case");
3088  }
3089  return types::TY_CXXHUHeader;
3090 }
3091 
3092 // Construct a the list of inputs and their types.
3093 void Driver::BuildInputs(const ToolChain &TC, DerivedArgList &Args,
3094  InputList &Inputs) const {
3095  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = getOpts();
3096  // Track the current user specified (-x) input. We also explicitly track the
3097  // argument used to set the type; we only want to claim the type when we
3098  // actually use it, so we warn about unused -x arguments.
3099  types::ID InputType = types::TY_Nothing;
3100  Arg *InputTypeArg = nullptr;
3101  bool IsSYCL =
3102  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false) ||
3103  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_only);
3104 
3105  // The last /TC or /TP option sets the input type to C or C++ globally.
3106  if (Arg *TCTP = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT__SLASH_TC,
3107  options::OPT__SLASH_TP)) {
3108  InputTypeArg = TCTP;
3109  InputType = TCTP->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_TC) && !IsSYCL
3110  ? types::TY_C
3111  : types::TY_CXX;
3112 
3113  Arg *Previous = nullptr;
3114  bool ShowNote = false;
3115  for (Arg *A :
3116  Args.filtered(options::OPT__SLASH_TC, options::OPT__SLASH_TP)) {
3117  if (Previous) {
3118  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_overriding_option)
3119  << Previous->getSpelling() << A->getSpelling();
3120  ShowNote = true;
3121  }
3122  Previous = A;
3123  }
3124  if (ShowNote)
3125  Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_t_option_is_global);
3126  }
3127 
3128  // CUDA/HIP and their preprocessor expansions can be accepted by CL mode.
3129  // Warn -x after last input file has no effect
3130  auto LastXArg = Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_x);
3131  const llvm::StringSet<> ValidXArgs = {"cuda", "hip", "cui", "hipi"};
3132  if (!IsCLMode() || ValidXArgs.contains(LastXArg)) {
3133  Arg *LastXArg = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT_x);
3134  Arg *LastInputArg = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT_INPUT);
3135  if (LastXArg && LastInputArg &&
3136  LastInputArg->getIndex() < LastXArg->getIndex())
3137  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_unused_x) << LastXArg->getValue();
3138  } else {
3139  // In CL mode suggest /TC or /TP since -x doesn't make sense if passed via
3140  // /clang:.
3141  if (auto *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_x))
3142  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_with_suggestion)
3143  << A->getAsString(Args) << "/TC' or '/TP";
3144  }
3145 
3146  for (Arg *A : Args) {
3147  if (A->getOption().getKind() == Option::InputClass) {
3148  const char *Value = A->getValue();
3149  types::ID Ty = types::TY_INVALID;
3150 
3151  // Infer the input type if necessary.
3152  if (InputType == types::TY_Nothing) {
3153  // If there was an explicit arg for this, claim it.
3154  if (InputTypeArg)
3155  InputTypeArg->claim();
3156 
3157  types::ID CType = types::TY_C;
3158  // For SYCL, all source file inputs are considered C++.
3159  if (IsSYCL)
3160  CType = types::TY_CXX;
3161 
3162  // stdin must be handled specially.
3163  if (memcmp(Value, "-", 2) == 0) {
3164  if (IsFlangMode()) {
3165  Ty = types::TY_Fortran;
3166  } else if (IsDXCMode()) {
3167  Ty = types::TY_HLSL;
3168  } else {
3169  // If running with -E, treat as a C input (this changes the
3170  // builtin macros, for example). This may be overridden by -ObjC
3171  // below.
3172  //
3173  // Otherwise emit an error but still use a valid type to avoid
3174  // spurious errors (e.g., no inputs).
3175  assert(!CCGenDiagnostics && "stdin produces no crash reproducer");
3176  if (!Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_E) && !CCCIsCPP())
3177  Diag(IsCLMode() ? clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_stdin_type_clang_cl
3178  : clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_stdin_type);
3179  Ty = types::TY_C;
3180  }
3181  } else {
3182  // Otherwise lookup by extension.
3183  // Fallback is C if invoked as C preprocessor, C++ if invoked with
3184  // clang-cl /E, or Object otherwise.
3185  // We use a host hook here because Darwin at least has its own
3186  // idea of what .s is.
3187  if (const char *Ext = strrchr(Value, '.'))
3188  Ty = TC.LookupTypeForExtension(Ext + 1);
3189 
3190  // For SYCL, convert C-type sources to C++-type sources.
3191  if (IsSYCL) {
3192  types::ID OldTy = Ty;
3193  switch (Ty) {
3194  case types::TY_C:
3195  Ty = types::TY_CXX;
3196  break;
3197  case types::TY_CHeader:
3198  Ty = types::TY_CXXHeader;
3199  break;
3200  case types::TY_PP_C:
3201  Ty = types::TY_PP_CXX;
3202  break;
3203  case types::TY_PP_CHeader:
3204  Ty = types::TY_PP_CXXHeader;
3205  break;
3206  default:
3207  break;
3208  }
3209  if (OldTy != Ty) {
3210  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_fsycl_with_c_type)
3211  << getTypeName(OldTy) << getTypeName(Ty);
3212  }
3213  }
3214 
3215  if (Ty == types::TY_INVALID) {
3216  if (IsCLMode() && (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_E) || CCGenDiagnostics))
3217  Ty = types::TY_CXX;
3218  else if (CCCIsCPP() || CCGenDiagnostics)
3219  Ty = CType;
3220  else
3221  Ty = types::TY_Object;
3222  }
3223 
3224  // If the driver is invoked as C++ compiler (like clang++ or c++) it
3225  // should autodetect some input files as C++ for g++ compatibility.
3226  if (CCCIsCXX()) {
3227  types::ID OldTy = Ty;
3228  Ty = types::lookupCXXTypeForCType(Ty);
3229 
3230  // Do not complain about foo.h, when we are known to be processing
3231  // it as a C++20 header unit.
3232  if (Ty != OldTy && !(OldTy == types::TY_CHeader && hasHeaderMode()))
3233  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_treating_input_as_cxx)
3234  << getTypeName(OldTy) << getTypeName(Ty);
3235  }
3236 
3237  // If running with -fthinlto-index=, extensions that normally identify
3238  // native object files actually identify LLVM bitcode files.
3239  if (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_fthinlto_index_EQ) &&
3240  Ty == types::TY_Object)
3241  Ty = types::TY_LLVM_BC;
3242  }
3243 
3244  // -ObjC and -ObjC++ override the default language, but only for "source
3245  // files". We just treat everything that isn't a linker input as a
3246  // source file.
3247  //
3248  // FIXME: Clean this up if we move the phase sequence into the type.
3249  if (Ty != types::TY_Object) {
3250  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ObjC))
3251  Ty = types::TY_ObjC;
3252  else if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ObjCXX))
3253  Ty = types::TY_ObjCXX;
3254  }
3255 
3256  // Disambiguate headers that are meant to be header units from those
3257  // intended to be PCH. Avoid missing '.h' cases that are counted as
3258  // C headers by default - we know we are in C++ mode and we do not
3259  // want to issue a complaint about compiling things in the wrong mode.
3260  if ((Ty == types::TY_CXXHeader || Ty == types::TY_CHeader) &&
3261  hasHeaderMode())
3262  Ty = CXXHeaderUnitType(CXX20HeaderType);
3263  } else {
3264  assert(InputTypeArg && "InputType set w/o InputTypeArg");
3265  if (!InputTypeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_x)) {
3266  // If emulating cl.exe, make sure that /TC and /TP don't affect input
3267  // object files.
3268  const char *Ext = strrchr(Value, '.');
3269  if (Ext && TC.LookupTypeForExtension(Ext + 1) == types::TY_Object)
3270  Ty = types::TY_Object;
3271  }
3272  if (Ty == types::TY_INVALID) {
3273  Ty = InputType;
3274  InputTypeArg->claim();
3275  }
3276  }
3277 
3278  if ((Ty == types::TY_C || Ty == types::TY_CXX) &&
3279  Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_hipstdpar))
3280  Ty = types::TY_HIP;
3281 
3282  if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, Ty, /*TypoCorrect=*/true))
3283  Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(Ty, A));
3284 
3285  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Tc)) {
3286  StringRef Value = A->getValue();
3287  if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, types::TY_C,
3288  /*TypoCorrect=*/false)) {
3289  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, A->getValue());
3290  Inputs.push_back(
3291  std::make_pair(IsSYCL ? types::TY_CXX : types::TY_C, InputArg));
3292  }
3293  A->claim();
3294  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Tp)) {
3295  StringRef Value = A->getValue();
3296  if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, types::TY_CXX,
3297  /*TypoCorrect=*/false)) {
3298  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, A->getValue());
3299  Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_CXX, InputArg));
3300  }
3301  A->claim();
3302  } else if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput)) {
3303  // Just treat as object type, we could make a special type for this if
3304  // necessary.
3305  Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_Object, A));
3306 
3307  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_x)) {
3308  InputTypeArg = A;
3309  InputType = types::lookupTypeForTypeSpecifier(A->getValue());
3310  A->claim();
3311 
3312  // Follow gcc behavior and treat as linker input for invalid -x
3313  // options. Its not clear why we shouldn't just revert to unknown; but
3314  // this isn't very important, we might as well be bug compatible.
3315  if (!InputType) {
3316  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_language) << A->getValue();
3317  InputType = types::TY_Object;
3318  }
3319  // Emit an error if c-compilation is forced in -fsycl mode
3320  if (IsSYCL && (InputType == types::TY_C || InputType == types::TY_PP_C ||
3321  InputType == types::TY_CHeader))
3322  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_fsycl_with_c_type) << A->getAsString(Args);
3323 
3324  // If the user has put -fmodule-header{,=} then we treat C++ headers as
3325  // header unit inputs. So we 'promote' -xc++-header appropriately.
3326  if (InputType == types::TY_CXXHeader && hasHeaderMode())
3327  InputType = CXXHeaderUnitType(CXX20HeaderType);
3328  } else if (A->getOption().getID() == options::OPT_U) {
3329  assert(A->getNumValues() == 1 && "The /U option has one value.");
3330  StringRef Val = A->getValue(0);
3331  if (Val.find_first_of("/\\") != StringRef::npos) {
3332  // Warn about e.g. "/Users/me/myfile.c".
3333  Diag(diag::warn_slash_u_filename) << Val;
3334  Diag(diag::note_use_dashdash);
3335  }
3336  }
3337  // TODO: remove when -foffload-static-lib support is dropped.
3338  else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_lib_Group)) {
3339  // Add the foffload-static-lib library to the command line to allow
3340  // processing when no source or object is supplied as well as proper
3341  // host link.
3342  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, A->getValue());
3343  Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_Object, InputArg));
3344  A->claim();
3345  // Use of -foffload-static-lib and -foffload-whole-static-lib are
3346  // deprecated with the updated functionality to scan the static libs.
3347  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_deprecated_option)
3348  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3349  }
3350  }
3351  if (CCCIsCPP() && Inputs.empty()) {
3352  // If called as standalone preprocessor, stdin is processed
3353  // if no other input is present.
3354  Arg *A = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, "-");
3355  Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_C, A));
3356  }
3357 }
3358 
3359 static bool runBundler(const SmallVectorImpl<StringRef> &InputArgs,
3360  Compilation &C) {
3361  // Find bundler.
3362  StringRef ExecPath(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(C.getDriver().Dir));
3363  llvm::ErrorOr<std::string> BundlerBinary =
3364  llvm::sys::findProgramByName("clang-offload-bundler", ExecPath);
3365  SmallVector<StringRef, 6> BundlerArgs;
3366  BundlerArgs.push_back(BundlerBinary.getError() ? "clang-offload-bundler"
3367  : BundlerBinary.get().c_str());
3368  BundlerArgs.append(InputArgs);
3369  // Since this is run in real time and not in the toolchain, output the
3370  // command line if requested.
3371  bool OutputOnly = C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH);
3372  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v) || OutputOnly) {
3373  for (StringRef A : BundlerArgs)
3374  if (OutputOnly)
3375  llvm::errs() << "\"" << A << "\" ";
3376  else
3377  llvm::errs() << A << " ";
3378  llvm::errs() << '\n';
3379  }
3380  if (BundlerBinary.getError())
3381  return false;
3382 
3383  return !llvm::sys::ExecuteAndWait(BundlerBinary.get(), BundlerArgs);
3384 }
3385 
3386 static bool hasFPGABinary(Compilation &C, std::string Object, types::ID Type) {
3387  assert(types::isFPGA(Type) && "unexpected Type for FPGA binary check");
3388  // Do not do the check if the file doesn't exist
3389  if (!llvm::sys::fs::exists(Object))
3390  return false;
3391 
3392  // Only static archives are valid FPGA Binaries for unbundling.
3393  if (!isStaticArchiveFile(Object))
3394  return false;
3395 
3396  // Temporary names for the output.
3397  llvm::Triple TT;
3398  TT.setArchName(types::getTypeName(Type));
3399  TT.setVendorName("intel");
3400  TT.setOS(llvm::Triple::UnknownOS);
3401 
3402  // Checking uses -check-section option with the input file, no output
3403  // file and the target triple being looked for.
3404  const char *Targets =
3405  C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Twine("-targets=sycl-") + TT.str());
3406  const char *Inputs = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Twine("-input=") + Object);
3407  // Always use -type=ao for aocx/aocr bundle checking. The 'bundles' are
3408  // actually archives.
3409  SmallVector<StringRef, 6> BundlerArgs = {"-type=ao", Targets, Inputs,
3410  "-check-section"};
3411  return runBundler(BundlerArgs, C);
3412 }
3413 
3414 static SmallVector<std::string, 4> getOffloadSections(Compilation &C,
3415  const StringRef &File) {
3416  // Do not do the check if the file doesn't exist
3417  if (!llvm::sys::fs::exists(File))
3418  return {};
3419 
3420  bool IsArchive = isStaticArchiveFile(File);
3421  if (!(IsArchive || isObjectFile(File.str())))
3422  return {};
3423 
3424  // Use the bundler to grab the list of sections from the given archive
3425  // or object.
3426  StringRef ExecPath(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(C.getDriver().Dir));
3427  llvm::ErrorOr<std::string> BundlerBinary =
3428  llvm::sys::findProgramByName("clang-offload-bundler", ExecPath);
3429  const char *Input = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Twine("-input=") + File.str());
3430  // Always use -type=ao for bundle checking. The 'bundles' are
3431  // actually archives.
3432  SmallVector<StringRef, 6> BundlerArgs = {
3433  BundlerBinary.get(), IsArchive ? "-type=ao" : "-type=o", Input, "-list"};
3434  // Since this is run in real time and not in the toolchain, output the
3435  // command line if requested.
3436  bool OutputOnly = C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH);
3437  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v) || OutputOnly) {
3438  for (StringRef A : BundlerArgs)
3439  if (OutputOnly)
3440  llvm::errs() << "\"" << A << "\" ";
3441  else
3442  llvm::errs() << A << " ";
3443  llvm::errs() << '\n';
3444  }
3445  if (BundlerBinary.getError())
3446  return {};
3447  llvm::SmallString<64> OutputFile(
3448  C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath("bundle-list", "txt"));
3449  llvm::FileRemover OutputRemover(OutputFile.c_str());
3450  std::optional<llvm::StringRef> Redirects[] = {
3451  {""},
3452  OutputFile.str(),
3453  OutputFile.str(),
3454  };
3455 
3456  std::string ErrorMessage;
3457  if (llvm::sys::ExecuteAndWait(BundlerBinary.get(), BundlerArgs, {}, Redirects,
3458  /*SecondsToWait*/ 0, /*MemoryLimit*/ 0,
3459  &ErrorMessage)) {
3460  // Could not get the information, return false
3461  return {};
3462  }
3463 
3464  llvm::ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer>> OutputBuf =
3465  llvm::MemoryBuffer::getFile(OutputFile.c_str());
3466  if (!OutputBuf) {
3467  // Could not capture output, return false
3468  return {};
3469  }
3470 
3471  SmallVector<std::string, 4> Sections;
3472  for (llvm::line_iterator LineIt(**OutputBuf); !LineIt.is_at_end(); ++LineIt)
3473  Sections.push_back(LineIt->str());
3474  if (Sections.empty())
3475  return {};
3476 
3477  return Sections;
3478 }
3479 
3480 static bool hasSYCLDefaultSection(Compilation &C, const StringRef &File) {
3481  // Do not do the check if the file doesn't exist
3482  if (!llvm::sys::fs::exists(File))
3483  return false;
3484 
3485  bool IsArchive = isStaticArchiveFile(File);
3486  if (!(IsArchive || isObjectFile(File.str())))
3487  return false;
3488 
3489  llvm::Triple TT(C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(getDefaultSYCLArch(C)));
3490  // Checking uses -check-section option with the input file, no output
3491  // file and the target triple being looked for.
3492  const char *Targets =
3493  C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Twine("-targets=sycl-") + TT.str());
3494  const char *Inputs = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Twine("-input=") + File.str());
3495  SmallVector<StringRef, 6> BundlerArgs = {IsArchive ? "-type=ao" : "-type=o",
3496  Targets, Inputs, "-check-section"};
3497  return runBundler(BundlerArgs, C);
3498 }

3500 static bool hasOffloadSections(Compilation &C, const StringRef &File,
3501  DerivedArgList &Args) {
3502  SmallVector<std::string, 4> Sections(getOffloadSections(C, File));
3503  return !Sections.empty();
3504 }
3505 
3506 // Simple helper function for Linker options, where the option is valid if
3507 // it has '-' or '--' as the designator.
3508 static bool optionMatches(const std::string &Option,
3509  const std::string &OptCheck) {
3510  return (Option == OptCheck || ("-" + Option) == OptCheck);
3511 }
3512 
3513 // Process linker inputs for use with offload static libraries. We are only
3514 // handling options and explicitly named static archives as these need to be
3515 // partially linked.
3516 static SmallVector<const char *, 16>
3517 getLinkerArgs(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args, bool IncludeObj = false) {
3518  SmallVector<const char *, 16> LibArgs;
3519  SmallVector<std::string, 8> LibPaths;
3520  bool IsMSVC = C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment();
3521  // Add search directories from LIBRARY_PATH/LIB env variable
3522  std::optional<std::string> LibPath =
3523  llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv(IsMSVC ? "LIB" : "LIBRARY_PATH");
3524  if (LibPath) {
3525  SmallVector<StringRef, 8> SplitPaths;
3526  const char EnvPathSeparatorStr[] = {llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator, '\0'};
3527  llvm::SplitString(*LibPath, SplitPaths, EnvPathSeparatorStr);
3528  for (StringRef Path : SplitPaths)
3529  LibPaths.emplace_back(Path.trim());
3530  }
3531  // Add directories from user-specified -L options
3532  for (std::string LibDirs : Args.getAllArgValues(options::OPT_L))
3533  LibPaths.emplace_back(LibDirs);
3534 
3535  // Do processing for any -l<arg> options passed and see if any static
3536  // libraries representing the name exists. If so, convert the name and
3537  // use that inline with the rest of the libraries.
3538  // TODO: The static archive processing for SYCL is done in a different
3539  // manner than the OpenMP processing. We should try and refactor this
3540  // to use the OpenMP flow (adding -l<name> to the llvm-link step)
3541  auto resolveStaticLib = [&](StringRef LibName, bool IsStatic) -> bool {
3542  if (!LibName.starts_with("-l"))
3543  return false;
3544  for (auto &LPath : LibPaths) {
3545  if (!IsStatic) {
3546  // Current linking state is dynamic. We will first check for the
3547  // shared object and not pull in the static library if it is found.
3548  SmallString<128> SoLibName(LPath);
3549  llvm::sys::path::append(SoLibName,
3550  Twine("lib" + LibName.substr(2) + ".so").str());
3551  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(SoLibName))
3552  return false;
3553  }
3554  SmallString<128> FullName(LPath);
3555  llvm::sys::path::append(FullName,
3556  Twine("lib" + LibName.substr(2) + ".a").str());
3557  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(FullName)) {
3558  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(FullName));
3559  return true;
3560  }
3561  }
3562  return false;
3563  };
3564  for (const auto *A : Args) {
3565  std::string FileName = A->getAsString(Args);
3566  static bool IsLinkStateStatic(Args.hasArg(options::OPT_static));
3567  auto addLibArg = [&](StringRef LibName) -> bool {
3568  if (isStaticArchiveFile(LibName) ||
3569  (IncludeObj && isObjectFile(LibName.str()))) {
3570  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(LibName));
3571  return true;
3572  }
3573  return false;
3574  };
3575  if (A->getOption().getKind() == Option::InputClass) {
3576  if (addLibArg(FileName))
3577  continue;
3578  }
3579  // Evaluate any libraries passed along after /link. These are typically
3580  // ignored by the driver and sent directly to the linker. When performing
3581  // offload, we should evaluate them at the driver level.
3582  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_link)) {
3583  for (StringRef Value : A->getValues()) {
3584  // Add any libpath values.
3585  if (Value.starts_with_insensitive("-libpath:") ||
3586  Value.starts_with_insensitive("/libpath:"))
3587  LibPaths.emplace_back(Value.substr(std::string("-libpath:").size()));
3588  if (addLibArg(Value))
3589  continue;
3590  for (auto LPath : LibPaths) {
3591  SmallString<128> FullLib(LPath);
3592  llvm::sys::path::append(FullLib, Value);
3593  if (addLibArg(FullLib))
3594  continue;
3595  }
3596  }
3597  }
3598  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Wl_COMMA) ||
3599  A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xlinker)) {
3600  // Parse through additional linker arguments that are meant to go
3601  // directly to the linker.
3602  // Keep the previous arg even if it is a new argument, for example:
3603  // -Xlinker -rpath -Xlinker <dir>.
3604  // Without this history, we do not know that <dir> was assocated with
3605  // -rpath and is processed incorrectly.
3606  static std::string PrevArg;
3607  for (StringRef Value : A->getValues()) {
3608  auto addKnownValues = [&](const StringRef &V) {
3609  // Only add named static libs objects and --whole-archive options.
3610  if (optionMatches("-whole-archive", V.str()) ||
3611  optionMatches("-no-whole-archive", V.str()) ||
3612  isStaticArchiveFile(V) || (IncludeObj && isObjectFile(V.str()))) {
3613  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(V));
3614  return;
3615  }
3616  // Probably not the best way to handle this, but there are options
3617  // that take arguments which we should not add to the known values.
3618  // Handle -z and -rpath for now - can be expanded if/when usage shows
3619  // the need.
3620  if (PrevArg != "-z" && PrevArg != "-rpath" && V[0] != '-' &&
3621  isObjectFile(V.str())) {
3622  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(V));
3623  return;
3624  }
3625  if (optionMatches("-Bstatic", V.str()) ||
3626  optionMatches("-dn", V.str()) ||
3627  optionMatches("-non_shared", V.str()) ||
3628  optionMatches("-static", V.str())) {
3629  IsLinkStateStatic = true;
3630  return;
3631  }
3632  if (optionMatches("-Bdynamic", V.str()) ||
3633  optionMatches("-dy", V.str()) ||
3634  optionMatches("-call_shared", V.str())) {
3635  IsLinkStateStatic = false;
3636  return;
3637  }
3638  resolveStaticLib(V, IsLinkStateStatic);
3639  };
3640  if (Value[0] == '@') {
3641  // Found a response file, we want to expand contents to try and
3642  // discover more libraries and options.
3643  SmallVector<const char *, 20> ExpandArgs;
3644  ExpandArgs.push_back(Value.data());
3645 
3646  llvm::BumpPtrAllocator A;
3647  llvm::StringSaver S(A);
3648  llvm::cl::ExpandResponseFiles(
3649  S,
3650  IsMSVC ? llvm::cl::TokenizeWindowsCommandLine
3651  : llvm::cl::TokenizeGNUCommandLine,
3652  ExpandArgs);
3653  for (StringRef EA : ExpandArgs)
3654  addKnownValues(EA);
3655  } else
3656  addKnownValues(Value);
3657  PrevArg = Value;
3658  }
3659  continue;
3660  }
3661  // Use of -foffload-static-lib and -foffload-whole-static-lib is
3662  // considered deprecated. Usage should move to passing in the static
3663  // library name on the command line, encapsulating with
3664  // -Wl,--whole-archive <lib> -Wl,--no-whole-archive as needed.
3665  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_foffload_static_lib_EQ)) {
3666  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(A->getValue()));
3667  continue;
3668  }
3669  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_foffload_whole_static_lib_EQ)) {
3670  // For -foffload-whole-static-lib, we add the --whole-archive wrap
3671  // around the library which will be used during the partial link step.
3672  LibArgs.push_back("--whole-archive");
3673  LibArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(A->getValue()));
3674  LibArgs.push_back("--no-whole-archive");
3675  continue;
3676  }
3677  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_l))
3678  resolveStaticLib(A->getAsString(Args), IsLinkStateStatic);
3679  }
3680  return LibArgs;
3681 }
3682 
3683 static bool IsSYCLDeviceLibObj(std::string ObjFilePath, bool isMSVCEnv) {
3684  StringRef ObjFileName = llvm::sys::path::filename(ObjFilePath);
3685  StringRef ObjSuffix = isMSVCEnv ? ".obj" : ".o";
3686  bool Ret =
3687  (ObjFileName.starts_with("libsycl-") && ObjFileName.ends_with(ObjSuffix))
3688  ? true
3689  : false;
3690  return Ret;
3691 }
3692 
3693 // Goes through all of the arguments, including inputs expected for the
3694 // linker directly, to determine if we need to potentially add the SYCL
3695 // default triple.
3696 bool Driver::checkForSYCLDefaultDevice(Compilation &C,
3697  DerivedArgList &Args) const {
3698  // Check only if enabled with -fsycl
3699  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false))
3700  return false;
3701 
3702  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_sycl_link_spirv))
3703  return false;
3704 
3705  // Do not do the check if the default device is passed in -fsycl-targets
3706  // or if -fsycl-targets isn't passed (that implies default device)
3707  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_targets_EQ)) {
3708  for (const char *Val : A->getValues()) {
3709  llvm::Triple TT(C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(Val));
3710  if ((TT.isSPIROrSPIRV()) && TT.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch)
3711  // Default triple found
3712  return false;
3713  }
3714  } else if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga))
3715  return false;
3716 
3717  SmallVector<const char *, 16> AllArgs(getLinkerArgs(C, Args, true));
3718  for (StringRef Arg : AllArgs) {
3719  if (hasSYCLDefaultSection(C, Arg))
3720  return true;
3721  }
3722  return false;
3723 }
3724 
3725 // Goes through all of the arguments, including inputs expected for the
3726 // linker directly, to determine if we need to perform additional work for
3727 // static offload libraries.
3728 bool Driver::checkForOffloadStaticLib(Compilation &C,
3729  DerivedArgList &Args) const {
3730  // Check only if enabled with -fsycl or -fopenmp-targets
3731  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false) &&
3732  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ))
3733  return false;
3734 
3735  // Right off the bat, assume the presence of -foffload-static-lib means
3736  // the need to perform linking steps for fat static archive offloading.
3737  // TODO: remove when -foffload-static-lib support is dropped.
3738  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_offload_lib_Group))
3739  return true;
3740  SmallVector<const char *, 16> OffloadLibArgs(getLinkerArgs(C, Args));
3741  for (StringRef OLArg : OffloadLibArgs)
3742  if (isStaticArchiveFile(OLArg) && hasOffloadSections(C, OLArg, Args)) {
3743  // FPGA binaries with AOCX or AOCR sections are not considered fat
3744  // static archives.
3745  return !(hasFPGABinary(C, OLArg.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCR) ||
3746  hasFPGABinary(C, OLArg.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU) ||
3747  hasFPGABinary(C, OLArg.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCX));
3748  }
3749  return false;
3750 }
3751 
3752 /// Check whether the given input tree contains any clang-offload-dependency
3753 /// actions.
3754 static bool ContainsOffloadDepsAction(const Action *A) {
3755  if (isa<OffloadDepsJobAction>(A))
3756  return true;
3757  return llvm::any_of(A->inputs(), ContainsOffloadDepsAction);
3758 }

3760 namespace {
3761 /// Provides a convenient interface for different programming models to generate
3762 /// the required device actions.
3763 class OffloadingActionBuilder final {
3764  /// Flag used to trace errors in the builder.
3765  bool IsValid = false;
3766 
3767  /// The compilation that is using this builder.
3768  Compilation &C;
3769 
3770  /// Map between an input argument and the offload kinds used to process it.
3771  std::map<const Arg *, unsigned> InputArgToOffloadKindMap;
3772 
3773  /// Map between a host action and its originating input argument.
3774  std::map<Action *, const Arg *> HostActionToInputArgMap;
3775 
3776  /// Builder interface. It doesn't build anything or keep any state.
3777  class DeviceActionBuilder {
3778  public:
3779  typedef const llvm::SmallVectorImpl<phases::ID> PhasesTy;
3780 
3781  enum ActionBuilderReturnCode {
3782  // The builder acted successfully on the current action.
3783  ABRT_Success,
3784  // The builder didn't have to act on the current action.
3785  ABRT_Inactive,
3786  // The builder was successful and requested the host action to not be
3787  // generated.
3788  ABRT_Ignore_Host,
3789  };
3790 
3791  protected:
3792  /// Compilation associated with this builder.
3793  Compilation &C;
3794 
3795  /// Tool chains associated with this builder. The same programming
3796  /// model may have associated one or more tool chains.
3797  SmallVector<const ToolChain *, 2> ToolChains;
3798 
3799  /// The derived arguments associated with this builder.
3800  DerivedArgList &Args;
3801 
3802  /// The inputs associated with this builder.
3803  const Driver::InputList &Inputs;
3804 
3805  /// The associated offload kind.
3806  Action::OffloadKind AssociatedOffloadKind = Action::OFK_None;
3807 
3808  /// The OffloadingActionBuilder reference.
3809  OffloadingActionBuilder &OffloadingActionBuilderRef;
3810 
3811  public:
3812  DeviceActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
3813  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
3814  Action::OffloadKind AssociatedOffloadKind,
3815  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
3816  : C(C), Args(Args), Inputs(Inputs),
3817  AssociatedOffloadKind(AssociatedOffloadKind),
3818  OffloadingActionBuilderRef(OAB) {}
3819  virtual ~DeviceActionBuilder() {}
3820 
3821  /// Fill up the array \a DA with all the device dependences that should be
3822  /// added to the provided host action \a HostAction. By default it is
3823  /// inactive.
3824  virtual ActionBuilderReturnCode
3825  getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
3826  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
3827  PhasesTy &Phases) {
3828  return ABRT_Inactive;
3829  }
3830 
3831  /// Update the state to include the provided host action \a HostAction as a
3832  /// dependency of the current device action. By default it is inactive.
3833  virtual ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDependences(Action *HostAction) {
3834  return ABRT_Inactive;
3835  }
3836 
3837  /// Append top level actions generated by the builder.
3838  virtual void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) {}
3839 
3840  /// Append top level actions specific for certain link situations.
3841  virtual void appendTopLevelLinkAction(ActionList &AL) {}
3842 
3843  /// Append linker device actions generated by the builder.
3844  virtual void appendLinkDeviceActions(ActionList &AL) {}
3845 
3846  /// Append linker host action generated by the builder.
3847  virtual Action* appendLinkHostActions(ActionList &AL) { return nullptr; }
3848 
3849  /// Append linker actions generated by the builder.
3850  virtual void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) {}
3851 
3852  /// Append linker actions generated by the builder.
3853  virtual void addDeviceLinkDependencies(OffloadDepsJobAction *DA) {}
3854 
3855  /// Initialize the builder. Return true if any initialization errors are
3856  /// found.
3857  virtual bool initialize() { return false; }
3858 
3859  /// Return true if the builder can use bundling/unbundling.
3860  virtual bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const { return false; }
3861 
3862  /// Return true if this builder is valid. We have a valid builder if we have
3863  /// associated device tool chains.
3864  bool isValid() { return !ToolChains.empty(); }
3865 
3866  /// Return the associated offload kind.
3867  Action::OffloadKind getAssociatedOffloadKind() {
3868  return AssociatedOffloadKind;
3869  }
3870 
3871  /// Push an action from a different DeviceActionBuilder (i.e., foreign
3872  /// action) in the current one
3873  virtual void pushForeignAction(Action *A) {}
3874  };
