3876  /// Base class for CUDA/HIP action builder. It injects device code in
3877  /// the host backend action.
3878  class CudaActionBuilderBase : public DeviceActionBuilder {
3879  protected:
3880  /// Flags to signal if the user requested host-only or device-only
3881  /// compilation.
3882  bool CompileHostOnly = false;
3883  bool CompileDeviceOnly = false;
3884  bool EmitLLVM = false;
3885  bool EmitAsm = false;
3886 
3887  /// ID to identify each device compilation. For CUDA it is simply the
3888  /// GPU arch string. For HIP it is either the GPU arch string or GPU
3889  /// arch string plus feature strings delimited by a plus sign, e.g.
3890  /// gfx906+xnack.
3891  struct TargetID {
3892  /// Target ID string which is persistent throughout the compilation.
3893  const char *ID;
3894  TargetID(CudaArch Arch) { ID = CudaArchToString(Arch); }
3895  TargetID(const char *ID) : ID(ID) {}
3896  operator const char *() { return ID; }
3897  operator StringRef() { return StringRef(ID); }
3898  };
3899  /// List of GPU architectures to use in this compilation.
3900  SmallVector<TargetID, 4> GpuArchList;
3901 
3902  /// The CUDA actions for the current input.
3903  ActionList CudaDeviceActions;
3904 
3905  /// The CUDA fat binary if it was generated for the current input.
3906  Action *CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
3907 
3908  /// Flag that is set to true if this builder acted on the current input.
3909  bool IsActive = false;
3910 
3911  /// Flag for -fgpu-rdc.
3912  bool Relocatable = false;
3913 
3914  /// Default GPU architecture if there's no one specified.
3915  CudaArch DefaultCudaArch = CudaArch::UNKNOWN;
3916 
3917  /// Method to generate compilation unit ID specified by option
3918  /// '-fuse-cuid='.
3919  enum UseCUIDKind { CUID_Hash, CUID_Random, CUID_None, CUID_Invalid };
3920  UseCUIDKind UseCUID = CUID_Hash;
3921 
3922  /// Compilation unit ID specified by option '-cuid='.
3923  StringRef FixedCUID;
3924 
3925  public:
3926  CudaActionBuilderBase(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
3927  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
3928  Action::OffloadKind OFKind,
3929  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
3930  : DeviceActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, OFKind, OAB) {
3931 
3932  CompileDeviceOnly = C.getDriver().offloadDeviceOnly();
3933  Relocatable = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc,
3934  options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, /*Default=*/false);
3935  }
3936 
3937  ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDependences(Action *HostAction) override {
3938  // While generating code for CUDA, we only depend on the host input action
3939  // to trigger the creation of all the CUDA device actions.
3940 
3941  // If we are dealing with an input action, replicate it for each GPU
3942  // architecture. If we are in host-only mode we return 'success' so that
3943  // the host uses the CUDA offload kind.
3944  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(HostAction)) {
3945  assert(!GpuArchList.empty() &&
3946  "We should have at least one GPU architecture.");
3947 
3948  // If the host input is not CUDA or HIP, we don't need to bother about
3949  // this input.
3950  if (!(IA->getType() == types::TY_CUDA ||
3951  IA->getType() == types::TY_HIP ||
3952  IA->getType() == types::TY_PP_HIP)) {
3953  // The builder will ignore this input.
3954  IsActive = false;
3955  return ABRT_Inactive;
3956  }
3957 
3958  // Set the flag to true, so that the builder acts on the current input.
3959  IsActive = true;
3960 
3961  if (CompileHostOnly)
3962  return ABRT_Success;
3963 
3964  // Replicate inputs for each GPU architecture.
3965  auto Ty = IA->getType() == types::TY_HIP ? types::TY_HIP_DEVICE
3966  : types::TY_CUDA_DEVICE;
3967  std::string CUID = FixedCUID.str();
3968  if (CUID.empty()) {
3969  if (UseCUID == CUID_Random)
3970  CUID = llvm::utohexstr(llvm::sys::Process::GetRandomNumber(),
3971  /*LowerCase=*/true);
3972  else if (UseCUID == CUID_Hash) {
3973  llvm::MD5 Hasher;
3974  llvm::MD5::MD5Result Hash;
3975  SmallString<256> RealPath;
3976  llvm::sys::fs::real_path(IA->getInputArg().getValue(), RealPath,
3977  /*expand_tilde=*/true);
3978  Hasher.update(RealPath);
3979  for (auto *A : Args) {
3980  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_INPUT))
3981  continue;
3982  Hasher.update(A->getAsString(Args));
3983  }
3984  Hasher.final(Hash);
3985  CUID = llvm::utohexstr(Hash.low(), /*LowerCase=*/true);
3986  }
3987  }
3988  IA->setId(CUID);
3989 
3990  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
3991  CudaDeviceActions.push_back(
3992  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(IA->getInputArg(), Ty, IA->getId()));
3993  }
3994 
3995  return ABRT_Success;
3996  }
3997 
3998  // If this is an unbundling action use it as is for each CUDA toolchain.
3999  if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction)) {
4000 
4001  // If -fgpu-rdc is disabled, should not unbundle since there is no
4002  // device code to link.
4003  if (UA->getType() == types::TY_Object && !Relocatable)
4004  return ABRT_Inactive;
4005 
4006  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4007  auto *IA = cast<InputAction>(UA->getInputs().back());
4008  std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
4009  // Check if the type of the file is the same as the action. Do not
4010  // unbundle it if it is not. Do not unbundle .so files, for example,
4011  // which are not object files. Files with extension ".lib" is classified
4012  // as TY_Object but they are actually archives, therefore should not be
4013  // unbundled here as objects. They will be handled at other places.
4014  const StringRef LibFileExt = ".lib";
4015  if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
4016  (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName) ||
4017  types::lookupTypeForExtension(
4018  llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName).drop_front()) !=
4019  types::TY_Object ||
4020  llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName) == LibFileExt))
4021  return ABRT_Inactive;
4022 
4023  for (auto Arch : GpuArchList) {
4024  CudaDeviceActions.push_back(UA);
4025  UA->registerDependentActionInfo(ToolChains[0], Arch,
4026  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4027  }
4028  IsActive = true;
4029  return ABRT_Success;
4030  }
4031 
4032  return IsActive ? ABRT_Success : ABRT_Inactive;
4033  }
4034 
4035  void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) override {
4036  // Utility to append actions to the top level list.
4037  auto AddTopLevel = [&](Action *A, TargetID TargetID) {
4038  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
4039  Dep.add(*A, *ToolChains.front(), TargetID, AssociatedOffloadKind);
4040  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
4041  };
4042 
4043  // If we have a fat binary, add it to the list.
4044  if (CudaFatBinary) {
4045  AddTopLevel(CudaFatBinary, CudaArch::UNUSED);
4046  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4047  CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
4048  return;
4049  }
4050 
4051  if (CudaDeviceActions.empty())
4052  return;
4053 
4054  // If we have CUDA actions at this point, that's because we have a have
4055  // partial compilation, so we should have an action for each GPU
4056  // architecture.
4057  assert(CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size() &&
4058  "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
4059  assert(ToolChains.size() == 1 &&
4060  "Expecting to have a single CUDA toolchain.");
4061  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I)
4062  AddTopLevel(CudaDeviceActions[I], GpuArchList[I]);
4063 
4064  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4065  }
4066 
4067  /// Get canonicalized offload arch option. \returns empty StringRef if the
4068  /// option is invalid.
4069  virtual StringRef getCanonicalOffloadArch(StringRef Arch) = 0;
4070 
4071  virtual std::optional<std::pair<llvm::StringRef, llvm::StringRef>>
4072  getConflictOffloadArchCombination(const std::set<StringRef> &GpuArchs) = 0;
4073 
4074  bool initialize() override {
4075  assert(AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda ||
4076  AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP);
4077 
4078  // We don't need to support CUDA.
4079  if (AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda &&
4080  !C.hasOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>())
4081  return false;
4082 
4083  // We don't need to support HIP.
4084  if (AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP &&
4085  !C.hasOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>())
4086  return false;
4087 
4088  const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
4089  assert(HostTC && "No toolchain for host compilation.");
4090  if (HostTC->getTriple().isNVPTX() ||
4091  HostTC->getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::amdgcn) {
4092  // We do not support targeting NVPTX/AMDGCN for host compilation. Throw
4093  // an error and abort pipeline construction early so we don't trip
4094  // asserts that assume device-side compilation.
4095  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_cuda_host_arch)
4096  << HostTC->getTriple().getArchName();
4097  return true;
4098  }
4099 
4100  ToolChains.push_back(
4101  AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda
4102  ? C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>()
4103  : C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>());
4104 
4105  CompileHostOnly = C.getDriver().offloadHostOnly();
4106  EmitLLVM = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm);
4107  EmitAsm = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_S);
4108  FixedCUID = Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_cuid_EQ);
4109  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fuse_cuid_EQ)) {
4110  StringRef UseCUIDStr = A->getValue();
4111  UseCUID = llvm::StringSwitch<UseCUIDKind>(UseCUIDStr)
4112  .Case("hash", CUID_Hash)
4113  .Case("random", CUID_Random)
4114  .Case("none", CUID_None)
4115  .Default(CUID_Invalid);
4116  if (UseCUID == CUID_Invalid) {
4117  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4118  << A->getAsString(Args) << UseCUIDStr;
4119  C.setContainsError();
4120  return true;
4121  }
4122  }
4123 
4124  // --offload and --offload-arch options are mutually exclusive.
4125  if (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_offload_EQ) &&
4126  Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ,
4127  options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ)) {
4128  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_opt_not_valid_with_opt) << "--offload-arch"
4129  << "--offload";
4130  }
4131 
4132  // Collect all offload arch parameters, removing duplicates.
4133  std::set<StringRef> GpuArchs;
4134  bool Error = false;
4135  for (Arg *A : Args) {
4136  if (!(A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ) ||
4137  A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ)))
4138  continue;
4139  A->claim();
4140 
4141  for (StringRef ArchStr : llvm::split(A->getValue(), ",")) {
4142  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ) &&
4143  ArchStr == "all") {
4144  GpuArchs.clear();
4145  } else if (ArchStr == "native") {
4146  const ToolChain &TC = *ToolChains.front();
4147  auto GPUsOrErr = ToolChains.front()->getSystemGPUArchs(Args);
4148  if (!GPUsOrErr) {
4149  TC.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_undetermined_gpu_arch)
4150  << llvm::Triple::getArchTypeName(TC.getArch())
4151  << llvm::toString(GPUsOrErr.takeError()) << "--offload-arch";
4152  continue;
4153  }
4154 
4155  for (auto GPU : *GPUsOrErr) {
4156  GpuArchs.insert(Args.MakeArgString(GPU));
4157  }
4158  } else {
4159  ArchStr = getCanonicalOffloadArch(ArchStr);
4160  if (ArchStr.empty()) {
4161  Error = true;
4162  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ))
4163  GpuArchs.insert(ArchStr);
4164  else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ))
4165  GpuArchs.erase(ArchStr);
4166  else
4167  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected option.");
4168  }
4169  }
4170  }
4171 
4172  auto &&ConflictingArchs = getConflictOffloadArchCombination(GpuArchs);
4173  if (ConflictingArchs) {
4174  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_bad_offload_arch_combo)
4175  << ConflictingArchs->first << ConflictingArchs->second;
4176  C.setContainsError();
4177  return true;
4178  }
4179 
4180  // Collect list of GPUs remaining in the set.
4181  for (auto Arch : GpuArchs)
4182  GpuArchList.push_back(Arch.data());
4183 
4184  // Default to sm_20 which is the lowest common denominator for
4185  // supported GPUs. sm_20 code should work correctly, if
4186  // suboptimally, on all newer GPUs.
4187  if (GpuArchList.empty()) {
4188  if (ToolChains.front()->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV())
4189  GpuArchList.push_back(CudaArch::Generic);
4190  else
4191  GpuArchList.push_back(DefaultCudaArch);
4192  }
4193 
4194  return Error;
4195  }
4196  };
4197 
4198  /// \brief CUDA action builder. It injects device code in the host backend
4199  /// action.
4200  class CudaActionBuilder final : public CudaActionBuilderBase {
4201  public:
4202  CudaActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
4203  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
4204  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
4205  : CudaActionBuilderBase(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_Cuda, OAB) {
4206  DefaultCudaArch = CudaArch::CudaDefault;
4207  }
4208 
4209  StringRef getCanonicalOffloadArch(StringRef ArchStr) override {
4210  CudaArch Arch = StringToCudaArch(ArchStr);
4211  if (Arch == CudaArch::UNKNOWN || !IsNVIDIAGpuArch(Arch)) {
4212  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_cuda_bad_gpu_arch) << ArchStr;
4213  return StringRef();
4214  }
4215  return CudaArchToString(Arch);
4216  }
4217 
4218  std::optional<std::pair<llvm::StringRef, llvm::StringRef>>
4219  getConflictOffloadArchCombination(
4220  const std::set<StringRef> &GpuArchs) override {
4221  return std::nullopt;
4222  }
4223 
4224  bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override {
4225  return Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false);
4226  }
4227 
4228  ActionBuilderReturnCode
4229  getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
4230  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
4231  PhasesTy &Phases) override {
4232  if (!IsActive)
4233  return ABRT_Inactive;
4234 
4235  // If we don't have more CUDA actions, we don't have any dependences to
4236  // create for the host.
4237  if (CudaDeviceActions.empty())
4238  return ABRT_Success;
4239 
4240  assert(CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size() &&
4241  "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
4242  assert(!CompileHostOnly &&
4243  "Not expecting CUDA actions in host-only compilation.");
4244 
4245  // If we are generating code for the device or we are in a backend phase,
4246  // we attempt to generate the fat binary. We compile each arch to ptx and
4247  // assemble to cubin, then feed the cubin *and* the ptx into a device
4248  // "link" action, which uses fatbinary to combine these cubins into one
4249  // fatbin. The fatbin is then an input to the host action if not in
4250  // device-only mode.
4251  if (CompileDeviceOnly || CurPhase == phases::Backend) {
4252  ActionList DeviceActions;
4253  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4254  // Produce the device action from the current phase up to the assemble
4255  // phase.
4256  for (auto Ph : Phases) {
4257  // Skip the phases that were already dealt with.
4258  if (Ph < CurPhase)
4259  continue;
4260  // We have to be consistent with the host final phase.
4261  if (Ph > FinalPhase)
4262  break;
4263 
4264  CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4265  C, Args, Ph, CudaDeviceActions[I], Action::OFK_Cuda);
4266 
4267  if (Ph == phases::Assemble)
4268  break;
4269  }
4270 
4271  // If we didn't reach the assemble phase, we can't generate the fat
4272  // binary. We don't need to generate the fat binary if we are not in
4273  // device-only mode.
4274  if (!isa<AssembleJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions[I]) ||
4275  CompileDeviceOnly)
4276  continue;
4277 
4278  Action *AssembleAction = CudaDeviceActions[I];
4279  assert(AssembleAction->getType() == types::TY_Object);
4280  assert(AssembleAction->getInputs().size() == 1);
4281 
4282  Action *BackendAction = AssembleAction->getInputs()[0];
4283  assert(BackendAction->getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm);
4284 
4285  for (auto &A : {AssembleAction, BackendAction}) {
4286  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
4287  DDep.add(*A, *ToolChains.front(), GpuArchList[I], Action::OFK_Cuda);
4288  DeviceActions.push_back(
4289  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDep, A->getType()));
4290  }
4291  }
4292 
4293  // We generate the fat binary if we have device input actions.
4294  if (!DeviceActions.empty()) {
4295  CudaFatBinary =
4296  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(DeviceActions, types::TY_CUDA_FATBIN);
4297 
4298  if (!CompileDeviceOnly) {
4299  DA.add(*CudaFatBinary, *ToolChains.front(), /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
4300  Action::OFK_Cuda);
4301  // Clear the fat binary, it is already a dependence to an host
4302  // action.
4303  CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
4304  }
4305 
4306  // Remove the CUDA actions as they are already connected to an host
4307  // action or fat binary.
4308  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4309  }
4310 
4311  // We avoid creating host action in device-only mode.
4312  return CompileDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
4313  } else if (CurPhase > phases::Backend) {
4314  // If we are past the backend phase and still have a device action, we
4315  // don't have to do anything as this action is already a device
4316  // top-level action.
4317  return ABRT_Success;
4318  }
4319 
4320  assert(CurPhase < phases::Backend && "Generating single CUDA "
4321  "instructions should only occur "
4322  "before the backend phase!");
4323 
4324  // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
4325  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4326 
4327  CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4328  C, Args, CurPhase, CudaDeviceActions[I]);
4329 
4330  if (CurPhase == phases::Compile) {
4331  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
4332  DDep.add(*CudaDeviceActions[I], *ToolChains.front(), GpuArchList[I],
4333  Action::OFK_Cuda);
4334 
4335  OffloadingActionBuilderRef.pushForeignAction(
4336  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
4337  DDep, DDep.getActions().front()->getType()));
4338  }
4339  }
4340 
4341  return ABRT_Success;
4342  }
4343  };
4344  /// \brief HIP action builder. It injects device code in the host backend
4345  /// action.
4346  class HIPActionBuilder final : public CudaActionBuilderBase {
4347  /// The linker inputs obtained for each device arch.
4348  SmallVector<ActionList, 8> DeviceLinkerInputs;
4349  // The default bundling behavior depends on the type of output, therefore
4350  // BundleOutput needs to be tri-value: None, true, or false.
4351  // Bundle code objects except --no-gpu-output is specified for device
4352  // only compilation. Bundle other type of output files only if
4353  // --gpu-bundle-output is specified for device only compilation.
4354  std::optional<bool> BundleOutput;
4355  std::optional<bool> EmitReloc;
4356 
4357  public:
4358  HIPActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
4359  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
4360  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
4361  : CudaActionBuilderBase(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_HIP, OAB) {
4362 
4363  DefaultCudaArch = CudaArch::HIPDefault;
4364 
4365  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fhip_emit_relocatable,
4366  options::OPT_fno_hip_emit_relocatable)) {
4367  EmitReloc = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fhip_emit_relocatable,
4368  options::OPT_fno_hip_emit_relocatable, false);
4369 
4370  if (*EmitReloc) {
4371  if (Relocatable) {
4372  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_opt_not_valid_with_opt)
4373  << "-fhip-emit-relocatable"
4374  << "-fgpu-rdc";
4375  }
4376 
4377  if (!CompileDeviceOnly) {
4378  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_opt_not_valid_without_opt)
4379  << "-fhip-emit-relocatable"
4380  << "--cuda-device-only";
4381  }
4382  }
4383  }
4384 
4385  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_gpu_bundle_output,
4386  options::OPT_no_gpu_bundle_output))
4387  BundleOutput = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gpu_bundle_output,
4388  options::OPT_no_gpu_bundle_output, true) &&
4389  (!EmitReloc || !*EmitReloc);
4390  }
4391 
4392  bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override { return true; }
4393 
4394  StringRef getCanonicalOffloadArch(StringRef IdStr) override {
4395  llvm::StringMap<bool> Features;
4396  // getHIPOffloadTargetTriple() is known to return valid value as it has
4397  // been called successfully in the CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains().
4398  auto ArchStr = parseTargetID(
4399  *getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(C.getDriver(), C.getInputArgs()), IdStr,
4400  &Features);
4401  if (!ArchStr) {
4402  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_bad_target_id) << IdStr;
4403  C.setContainsError();
4404  return StringRef();
4405  }
4406  auto CanId = getCanonicalTargetID(*ArchStr, Features);
4407  return Args.MakeArgStringRef(CanId);
4408  };
4409 
4410  std::optional<std::pair<llvm::StringRef, llvm::StringRef>>
4411  getConflictOffloadArchCombination(
4412  const std::set<StringRef> &GpuArchs) override {
4413  return getConflictTargetIDCombination(GpuArchs);
4414  }
4415 
4416  ActionBuilderReturnCode
4417  getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
4418  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
4419  PhasesTy &Phases) override {
4420  if (!IsActive)
4421  return ABRT_Inactive;
4422 
4423  // amdgcn does not support linking of object files, therefore we skip
4424  // backend and assemble phases to output LLVM IR. Except for generating
4425  // non-relocatable device code, where we generate fat binary for device
4426  // code and pass to host in Backend phase.
4427  if (CudaDeviceActions.empty())
4428  return ABRT_Success;
4429 
4430  assert(((CurPhase == phases::Link && Relocatable) ||
4431  CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size()) &&
4432  "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
4433  assert(!CompileHostOnly &&
4434  "Not expecting HIP actions in host-only compilation.");
4435 
4436  bool ShouldLink = !EmitReloc || !*EmitReloc;
4437 
4438  if (!Relocatable && CurPhase == phases::Backend && !EmitLLVM &&
4439  !EmitAsm && ShouldLink) {
4440  // If we are in backend phase, we attempt to generate the fat binary.
4441  // We compile each arch to IR and use a link action to generate code
4442  // object containing ISA. Then we use a special "link" action to create
4443  // a fat binary containing all the code objects for different GPU's.
4444  // The fat binary is then an input to the host action.
4445  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4446  if (C.getDriver().isUsingLTO(/*IsOffload=*/true)) {
4447  // When LTO is enabled, skip the backend and assemble phases and
4448  // use lld to link the bitcode.
4449  ActionList AL;
4450  AL.push_back(CudaDeviceActions[I]);
4451  // Create a link action to link device IR with device library
4452  // and generate ISA.
4453  CudaDeviceActions[I] =
4454  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(AL, types::TY_Image);
4455  } else {
4456  // When LTO is not enabled, we follow the conventional
4457  // compiler phases, including backend and assemble phases.
4458  ActionList AL;
4459  Action *BackendAction = nullptr;
4460  if (ToolChains.front()->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV()) {
4461  // Emit LLVM bitcode for SPIR-V targets. SPIR-V device tool chain
4462  // (HIPSPVToolChain) runs post-link LLVM IR passes.
4463  types::ID Output = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S)
4464  ? types::TY_LLVM_IR
4465  : types::TY_LLVM_BC;
4466  BackendAction =
4467  C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions[I], Output);
4468  } else
4469  BackendAction = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4470  C, Args, phases::Backend, CudaDeviceActions[I],
4471  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4472  auto AssembleAction = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4473  C, Args, phases::Assemble, BackendAction,
4474  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4475  AL.push_back(AssembleAction);
4476  // Create a link action to link device IR with device library
4477  // and generate ISA.
4478  CudaDeviceActions[I] =
4479  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(AL, types::TY_Image);
4480  }
4481 
4482  // OffloadingActionBuilder propagates device arch until an offload
4483  // action. Since the next action for creating fatbin does
4484  // not have device arch, whereas the above link action and its input
4485  // have device arch, an offload action is needed to stop the null
4486  // device arch of the next action being propagated to the above link
4487  // action.
4488  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
4489  DDep.add(*CudaDeviceActions[I], *ToolChains.front(), GpuArchList[I],
4490  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4491  CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
4492  DDep, CudaDeviceActions[I]->getType());
4493  }
4494 
4495  if (!CompileDeviceOnly || !BundleOutput || *BundleOutput) {
4496  // Create HIP fat binary with a special "link" action.
4497  CudaFatBinary = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions,
4498  types::TY_HIP_FATBIN);
4499 
4500  if (!CompileDeviceOnly) {
4501  DA.add(*CudaFatBinary, *ToolChains.front(), /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
4502  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4503  // Clear the fat binary, it is already a dependence to an host
4504  // action.
4505  CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
4506  }
4507 
4508  // Remove the CUDA actions as they are already connected to an host
4509  // action or fat binary.
4510  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4511  }
4512 
4513  return CompileDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
4514  } else if (CurPhase == phases::Link) {
4515  if (!ShouldLink)
4516  return ABRT_Success;
4517  // Save CudaDeviceActions to DeviceLinkerInputs for each GPU subarch.
4518  // This happens to each device action originated from each input file.
4519  // Later on, device actions in DeviceLinkerInputs are used to create
4520  // device link actions in appendLinkDependences and the created device
4521  // link actions are passed to the offload action as device dependence.
4522  DeviceLinkerInputs.resize(CudaDeviceActions.size());
4523  auto LI = DeviceLinkerInputs.begin();
4524  for (auto *A : CudaDeviceActions) {
4525  LI->push_back(A);
4526  ++LI;
4527  }
4528 
4529  // We will pass the device action as a host dependence, so we don't
4530  // need to do anything else with them.
4531  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4532  return CompileDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
4533  }
4534 
4535  // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
4536  for (Action *&A : CudaDeviceActions)
4537  A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A,
4538  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4539 
4540  if (CompileDeviceOnly && CurPhase == FinalPhase && BundleOutput &&
4541  *BundleOutput) {
4542  for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
4543  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
4544  DDep.add(*CudaDeviceActions[I], *ToolChains.front(), GpuArchList[I],
4545  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4546  CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
4547  DDep, CudaDeviceActions[I]->getType());
4548  }
4549  CudaFatBinary =
4550  C.MakeAction<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions);
4551  CudaDeviceActions.clear();
4552  }
4553 
4554  return (CompileDeviceOnly &&
4555  (CurPhase == FinalPhase ||
4556  (!ShouldLink && CurPhase == phases::Assemble)))
4557  ? ABRT_Ignore_Host
4558  : ABRT_Success;
4559  }
4560 
4561  void appendLinkDeviceActions(ActionList &AL) override {
4562  if (DeviceLinkerInputs.size() == 0)
4563  return;
4564 
4565  assert(DeviceLinkerInputs.size() == GpuArchList.size() &&
4566  "Linker inputs and GPU arch list sizes do not match.");
4567 
4568  ActionList Actions;
4569  unsigned I = 0;
4570  // Append a new link action for each device.
4571  // Each entry in DeviceLinkerInputs corresponds to a GPU arch.
4572  for (auto &LI : DeviceLinkerInputs) {
4573 
4574  types::ID Output = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm)
4575  ? types::TY_LLVM_BC
4576  : types::TY_Image;
4577 
4578  auto *DeviceLinkAction = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LI, Output);
4579  // Linking all inputs for the current GPU arch.
4580  // LI contains all the inputs for the linker.
4581  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DeviceLinkDeps;
4582  DeviceLinkDeps.add(*DeviceLinkAction, *ToolChains[0],
4583  GpuArchList[I], AssociatedOffloadKind);
4584  Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
4585  DeviceLinkDeps, DeviceLinkAction->getType()));
4586  ++I;
4587  }
4588  DeviceLinkerInputs.clear();
4589 
4590  // If emitting LLVM, do not generate final host/device compilation action
4591  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm)) {
4592  AL.append(Actions);
4593  return;
4594  }
4595 
4596  // Create a host object from all the device images by embedding them
4597  // in a fat binary for mixed host-device compilation. For device-only
4598  // compilation, creates a fat binary.
4599  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
4600  if (!CompileDeviceOnly || !BundleOutput || *BundleOutput) {
4601  auto *TopDeviceLinkAction = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(
4602  Actions,
4603  CompileDeviceOnly ? types::TY_HIP_FATBIN : types::TY_Object);
4604  DDeps.add(*TopDeviceLinkAction, *ToolChains[0], nullptr,
4605  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4606  // Offload the host object to the host linker.
4607  AL.push_back(
4608  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDeps, TopDeviceLinkAction->getType()));
4609  } else {
4610  AL.append(Actions);
4611  }
4612  }
4613 
4614  Action* appendLinkHostActions(ActionList &AL) override { return AL.back(); }
4615 
4616  void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) override {}
4617  };
4618 
4619  /// OpenMP action builder. The host bitcode is passed to the device frontend
4620  /// and all the device linked images are passed to the host link phase.
4621  class OpenMPActionBuilder final : public DeviceActionBuilder {
4622  /// The OpenMP actions for the current input.
4623  ActionList OpenMPDeviceActions;
4624 
4625  /// The linker inputs obtained for each toolchain.
4626  SmallVector<ActionList, 8> DeviceLinkerInputs;
4627 
4628  public:
4629  OpenMPActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
4630  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
4631  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
4632  : DeviceActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_OpenMP, OAB) {}
4633 
4634  ActionBuilderReturnCode
4635  getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
4636  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
4637  PhasesTy &Phases) override {
4638  if (OpenMPDeviceActions.empty())
4639  return ABRT_Inactive;
4640 
4641  // We should always have an action for each input.
4642  assert(OpenMPDeviceActions.size() == ToolChains.size() &&
4643  "Number of OpenMP actions and toolchains do not match.");
4644 
4645  // The host only depends on device action in the linking phase, when all
4646  // the device images have to be embedded in the host image.
4647  if (CurPhase == phases::Link) {
4648  assert(ToolChains.size() == DeviceLinkerInputs.size() &&
4649  "Toolchains and linker inputs sizes do not match.");
4650  auto LI = DeviceLinkerInputs.begin();
4651  for (auto *A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
4652  LI->push_back(A);
4653  ++LI;
4654  }
4655 
4656  // We passed the device action as a host dependence, so we don't need to
4657  // do anything else with them.
4658  OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
4659  return ABRT_Success;
4660  }
4661 
4662  // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
4663  for (Action *&A : OpenMPDeviceActions)
4664  A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A);
4665 
4666  return ABRT_Success;
4667  }
4668 
4669  ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDependences(Action *HostAction) override {
4670 
4671  // If this is an input action replicate it for each OpenMP toolchain.
4672  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(HostAction)) {
4673  OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
4674  for (unsigned I = 0; I < ToolChains.size(); ++I)
4675  OpenMPDeviceActions.push_back(
4676  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(IA->getInputArg(), IA->getType()));
4677  return ABRT_Success;
4678  }
4679 
4680  // If this is an unbundling action use it as is for each OpenMP toolchain.
4681  if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction)) {
4682  OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
4683  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(UA->getInputs().back())) {
4684  std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
4685  // Check if the type of the file is the same as the action. Do not
4686  // unbundle it if it is not. Do not unbundle .so files, for example,
4687  // which are not object files.
4688  if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
4689  (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName) ||
4690  types::lookupTypeForExtension(
4691  llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName).drop_front()) !=
4692  types::TY_Object))
4693  return ABRT_Inactive;
4694  }
4695  for (unsigned I = 0; I < ToolChains.size(); ++I) {
4696  OpenMPDeviceActions.push_back(UA);
4697  UA->registerDependentActionInfo(
4698  ToolChains[I], /*BoundArch=*/StringRef(), Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4699  }
4700  return ABRT_Success;
4701  }
4702 
4703  // When generating code for OpenMP we use the host compile phase result as
4704  // a dependence to the device compile phase so that it can learn what
4705  // declarations should be emitted. However, this is not the only use for
4706  // the host action, so we prevent it from being collapsed.
4707  if (isa<CompileJobAction>(HostAction)) {
4708  HostAction->setCannotBeCollapsedWithNextDependentAction();
4709  assert(ToolChains.size() == OpenMPDeviceActions.size() &&
4710  "Toolchains and device action sizes do not match.");
4711  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
4712  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
4713  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4714  auto TC = ToolChains.begin();
4715  for (Action *&A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
4716  assert(isa<CompileJobAction>(A));
4717  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
4718  DDep.add(*A, **TC, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4719  A = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDep);
4720  ++TC;
4721  }
4722  }
4723  return ABRT_Success;
4724  }
4725 
4726  void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) override {
4727  if (OpenMPDeviceActions.empty())
4728  return;
4729 
4730  // We should always have an action for each input.
4731  assert(OpenMPDeviceActions.size() == ToolChains.size() &&
4732  "Number of OpenMP actions and toolchains do not match.");
4733 
4734  // Append all device actions followed by the proper offload action.
4735  auto TI = ToolChains.begin();
4736  for (auto *A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
4737  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
4738  Dep.add(*A, **TI, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4739  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
4740  ++TI;
4741  }
4742  // We no longer need the action stored in this builder.
4743  OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
4744  }
4745 
4746  void appendLinkDeviceActions(ActionList &AL) override {
4747  assert(ToolChains.size() == DeviceLinkerInputs.size() &&
4748  "Toolchains and linker inputs sizes do not match.");
4749 
4750  // Append a new link action for each device.
4751  auto TC = ToolChains.begin();
4752  for (auto &LI : DeviceLinkerInputs) {
4753  auto *DeviceLinkAction =
4754  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LI, types::TY_Image);
4755  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DeviceLinkDeps;
4756  DeviceLinkDeps.add(*DeviceLinkAction, **TC, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
4757  Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4758  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DeviceLinkDeps,
4759  DeviceLinkAction->getType()));
4760  ++TC;
4761  }
4762  DeviceLinkerInputs.clear();
4763  }
4764 
4765  Action* appendLinkHostActions(ActionList &AL) override {
4766  // Create wrapper bitcode from the result of device link actions and compile
4767  // it to an object which will be added to the host link command.
4768  auto *BC = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(AL, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
4769  auto *ASM = C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(BC, types::TY_PP_Asm);
4770  return C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(ASM, types::TY_Object);
4771  }
4772 
4773  void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) override {}
4774 
4775  void addDeviceLinkDependencies(OffloadDepsJobAction *DA) override {
4776  for (unsigned I = 0; I < ToolChains.size(); ++I) {
4777  // Register dependent toolchain.
4778  DA->registerDependentActionInfo(
4779  ToolChains[I], /*BoundArch=*/StringRef(), Action::OFK_OpenMP);
4780 
4781  if (!ToolChains[I]->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV()) {
4782  // Create object from the deps bitcode.
4783  auto *BA = C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(DA, types::TY_PP_Asm);
4784  auto *AA = C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(BA, types::TY_Object);
4785 
4786  // Add deps object to linker inputs.
4787  DeviceLinkerInputs[I].push_back(AA);
4788  } else
4789  DeviceLinkerInputs[I].push_back(DA);
4790  }
4791  }
4792 
4793  bool initialize() override {
4794  // Get the OpenMP toolchains. If we don't get any, the action builder will
4795  // know there is nothing to do related to OpenMP offloading.
4796  auto OpenMPTCRange = C.getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_OpenMP>();
4797  for (auto TI = OpenMPTCRange.first, TE = OpenMPTCRange.second; TI != TE;
4798  ++TI)
4799  ToolChains.push_back(TI->second);
4800 
4801  DeviceLinkerInputs.resize(ToolChains.size());
4802  return false;
4803  }
4804 
4805  bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override {
4806  // OpenMP should use bundled files whenever possible.
4807  return true;
4808  }
4809  };

4811  /// SYCL action builder. The host bitcode is passed to the device frontend
4812  /// and all the device linked images are passed to the host link phase.
4813  /// SPIR related are wrapped before added to the fat binary
4814  class SYCLActionBuilder final : public DeviceActionBuilder {
4815  /// Flag to signal if the user requested device-only compilation.
4816  bool CompileDeviceOnly = false;
4817 
4818  /// Flag to signal if the user requested the device object to be wrapped.
4819  bool WrapDeviceOnlyBinary = false;
4820 
4821  /// Flag to signal if the user requested device code split.
4822  bool DeviceCodeSplit = false;
4823 
4824  /// List of offload device toolchain, bound arch needed to track for
4825  /// different binary constructions.
4826  /// POD to hold information about a SYCL device action.
4827  /// Each Action is bound to a <TC, arch> pair,
4828  /// we keep them together under a struct for clarity.
4829  struct DeviceTargetInfo {
4830  DeviceTargetInfo(const ToolChain *TC, const char *BA)
4831  : TC(TC), BoundArch(BA) {}
4832 
4833  const ToolChain *TC;
4834  const char *BoundArch;
4835  };
4836  SmallVector<DeviceTargetInfo, 4> SYCLTargetInfoList;
4837 
4838  /// The SYCL actions for the current input.
4839  /// One action per triple/boundarch.
4840  ActionList SYCLDeviceActions;
4841 
4842  /// The linker inputs obtained for each input/toolchain/arch.
4843  SmallVector<ActionList, 4> DeviceLinkerInputs;
4844 
4845  /// The SYCL link binary if it was generated for the current input.
4846  Action *SYCLLinkBinary = nullptr;
4847 
4848  /// Running list of SYCL actions specific for device linking.
4849  ActionList SYCLLinkBinaryList;
4850 
4851  /// List of SYCL Final Device binaries that should be unbundled as a final
4852  /// device binary and not further processed.
4853  SmallVector<std::pair<Action *, SmallVector<std::string, 4>>, 4>
4854  SYCLFinalDeviceList;
4855 
4856  /// SYCL ahead of time compilation inputs
4857  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Triple, const char *>, 8> SYCLAOTInputs;
4858 
4859  /// List of offload device triples as provided on the CLI.
4860  /// Does not track AOT binary inputs triples.
4861  SmallVector<llvm::Triple, 4> SYCLTripleList;
4862 
4863  /// Type of output file for FPGA device compilation.
4864  types::ID FPGAOutType = types::TY_FPGA_AOCX;
4865 
4866  /// List of objects to extract FPGA dependency info from
4867  ActionList FPGAObjectInputs;
4868 
4869  /// List of static archives to extract FPGA dependency info from
4870  ActionList FPGAArchiveInputs;
4871 
4872  /// List of AOCR based archives that contain BC members to use for
4873  /// providing symbols and properties.
4874  ActionList FPGAAOCArchives;
4875 
4876  // SYCLInstallation is needed in order to link SYCLDeviceLibs
4877  SYCLInstallationDetector SYCLInstallation;
4878 
4879  /// List of GPU architectures to use in this compilation with NVPTX/AMDGCN
4880  /// targets.
4881  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Triple, const char *>, 8> GpuArchList;
4882 
4883  /// Build the last steps for CUDA after all BC files have been linked.
4884  JobAction *finalizeNVPTXDependences(Action *Input, const llvm::Triple &TT) {
4885  auto *BA = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4886  C, Args, phases::Backend, Input, AssociatedOffloadKind);
4887  if (TT.getOS() != llvm::Triple::NVCL) {
4888  auto *AA = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4889  C, Args, phases::Assemble, BA, AssociatedOffloadKind);
4890  ActionList DeviceActions = {BA, AA};
4891  return C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(DeviceActions,
4892  types::TY_CUDA_FATBIN);
4893  }
4894  return cast<JobAction>(BA);
4895  }
4896 
4897  JobAction *finalizeAMDGCNDependences(Action *Input,
4898  const llvm::Triple &TT) {
4899  auto *BA = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
4900  C, Args, phases::Backend, Input, AssociatedOffloadKind);
4901 
4902  auto *AA = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, phases::Assemble,
4903  BA, AssociatedOffloadKind);
4904 
4905  ActionList AL = {AA};
4906  Action *LinkAction = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(AL, types::TY_Image);
4907  ActionList HIPActions = {LinkAction};
4908  JobAction *HIPFatBinary =
4909  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(HIPActions, types::TY_HIP_FATBIN);
4910  return HIPFatBinary;
4911  }
4912 
4913  Action *ExternalCudaAction = nullptr;
4914 
4915  public:
4916  SYCLActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
4917  const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
4918  OffloadingActionBuilder &OAB)
4919  : DeviceActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_SYCL, OAB),
4920  SYCLInstallation(C.getDriver()) {}
4921 
4922  void withBoundArchForToolChain(const ToolChain *TC,
4923  llvm::function_ref<void(const char *)> Op) {
4924  for (auto &A : GpuArchList) {
4925  if (TC->getTriple() == A.first) {
4926  Op(A.second ? Args.MakeArgString(A.second) : nullptr);
4927  return;
4928  }
4929  }
4930 
4931  // no bound arch for this toolchain
4932  Op(nullptr);
4933  }
4934 
4935  void pushForeignAction(Action *A) override {
4936  // Accept a foreign action from the CudaActionBuilder for compiling CUDA
4937  // sources
4938  if (A->getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_Cuda)
4939  ExternalCudaAction = A;
4940  }
4941 
4942  ActionBuilderReturnCode
4943  getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
4944  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
4945  PhasesTy &Phases) override {
4946  bool SYCLDeviceOnly = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_only);
4947  if (CurPhase == phases::Preprocess) {
4948  // Do not perform the host compilation when doing preprocessing only
4949  // with -fsycl-device-only.
4950  bool IsPreprocessOnly =
4951  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_E) ||
4952  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP, options::OPT__SLASH_P) ||
4953  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM);
4954  if (IsPreprocessOnly) {
4955  for (auto TargetActionInfo :
4956  llvm::zip(SYCLDeviceActions, SYCLTargetInfoList)) {
4957  Action *&A = std::get<0>(TargetActionInfo);
4958  auto &TargetInfo = std::get<1>(TargetActionInfo);
4959  A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A,
4960  AssociatedOffloadKind);
4961  if (SYCLDeviceOnly)
4962  continue;
4963  // Add an additional compile action to generate the integration
4964  // header.
4965  Action *CompileAction =
4966  C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(A, types::TY_Nothing);
4967  DA.add(*CompileAction, *TargetInfo.TC, TargetInfo.BoundArch,
4968  Action::OFK_SYCL);
4969  }
4970  return SYCLDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
4971  }
4972  }
4973 
4974  // Device compilation generates LLVM BC.
4975  if (CurPhase == phases::Compile && !SYCLTargetInfoList.empty()) {
4976  // TODO: handle stubfile handling when mix and matching programming
4977  // model.
4978  if (SYCLDeviceActions.empty())
4979  return ABRT_Success;
4980 
4981  Action *DeviceCompilerInput = nullptr;
4982  const DeviceTargetInfo &DevTarget = SYCLTargetInfoList.back();
4983  for (auto TargetActionInfo :
4984  llvm::zip(SYCLDeviceActions, SYCLTargetInfoList)) {
4985  Action *&A = std::get<0>(TargetActionInfo);
4986  auto &TargetInfo = std::get<1>(TargetActionInfo);
4987  types::ID OutputType = types::TY_LLVM_BC;
4988  if ((SYCLDeviceOnly || Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm)) &&
4989  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S))
4990  OutputType = types::TY_LLVM_IR;
4991  // Use of -fsycl-device-obj=spirv converts the original LLVM-IR
4992  // file to SPIR-V for later consumption.
4993  if ((SYCLDeviceOnly || FinalPhase != phases::Link) &&
4994  Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fsycl_device_obj_EQ)
4995  .equals_insensitive("spirv")) {
4996  auto *CompileAction =
4997  C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(A, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
4998  A = C.MakeAction<SPIRVTranslatorJobAction>(CompileAction,
4999  types::TY_SPIRV);
5000  if (SYCLDeviceOnly)
5001  continue;
5002  } else {
5003  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only))
5004  OutputType = types::TY_Nothing;
5005  A = C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(A, OutputType);
5006  }
5007  // Add any of the device linking steps when -fno-sycl-rdc is
5008  // specified. Device linking is only available for AOT at this
5009  // time.
5010  llvm::Triple TargetTriple = TargetInfo.TC->getTriple();
5011  if (tools::SYCL::shouldDoPerObjectFileLinking(C) &&
5012  TargetTriple.isSPIRAOT() && FinalPhase != phases::Link) {
5013  ActionList CAList;
5014  CAList.push_back(A);
5015  ActionList DeviceLinkActions;
5016  appendSYCLDeviceLink(CAList, TargetInfo.TC, DeviceLinkActions,
5017  TargetInfo.BoundArch, /*SkipWrapper=*/false);
5018  // The list of actions generated from appendSYCLDeviceLink is kept
5019  // in DeviceLinkActions. Instead of adding the dependency on the
5020  // compiled device file, add the dependency against the compiled
5021  // device binary to be added to the resulting fat object.
5022  A = DeviceLinkActions.back();
5023  }
5024  DeviceCompilerInput = A;
5025  }
5026  DA.add(*DeviceCompilerInput, *DevTarget.TC, DevTarget.BoundArch,
5027  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5028  return SYCLDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
5029  }
5030 
5031  // Backend/Assemble actions are obsolete for the SYCL device side
5032  if (CurPhase == phases::Backend || CurPhase == phases::Assemble)
5033  return ABRT_Inactive;
5034 
5035  // The host only depends on device action in the linking phase, when all
5036  // the device images have to be embedded in the host image.
5037  if (CurPhase == phases::Link) {
5038  if (!SYCLDeviceActions.empty()) {
5039  assert(SYCLDeviceActions.size() == DeviceLinkerInputs.size() &&
5040  "Device action and device linker inputs sizes do not match.");
5041 
5042  for (auto TargetAction :
5043  llvm::zip(DeviceLinkerInputs, SYCLDeviceActions)) {
5044  ActionList &LinkerList = std::get<0>(TargetAction);
5045  Action *A = std::get<1>(TargetAction);
5046 
5047  LinkerList.push_back(A);
5048  }
5049  }
5050 
5051  if (ExternalCudaAction) {
5052  assert(DeviceLinkerInputs.size() == 1 &&
5053  "Number of SYCL actions and toolchains/boundarch pairs do not "
5054  "match.");
5055  DeviceLinkerInputs[0].push_back(ExternalCudaAction);
5056  ExternalCudaAction = nullptr;
5057  }
5058 
5059  // With -fsycl-link-targets, we will take the unbundled binaries
5060  // for each device and link them together to a single binary that will
5061  // be used in a split compilation step.
5062  if (CompileDeviceOnly && !SYCLDeviceActions.empty()) {
5063  for (auto SDA : SYCLDeviceActions)
5064  SYCLLinkBinaryList.push_back(SDA);
5065  // Remove the SYCL actions as they are already connected to an host
5066  // action or fat binary.
5067  SYCLDeviceActions.clear();
5068 
5069  if (WrapDeviceOnlyBinary)
5070  return ABRT_Ignore_Host;
5071  auto *Link =
5072  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(SYCLLinkBinaryList, types::TY_Image);
5073  SYCLLinkBinary =
5074  C.MakeAction<SPIRVTranslatorJobAction>(Link, types::TY_Image);
5075  // We avoid creating host action in device-only mode.
5076  return ABRT_Ignore_Host;
5077  }
5078 
5079  // We passed the device action as a host dependence, so we don't need to
5080  // do anything else with them.
5081  SYCLDeviceActions.clear();
5082  return ABRT_Success;
5083  }
5084 
5085  // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
5086  auto TC = ToolChains.begin();
5087  for (Action *&A : SYCLDeviceActions) {
5088  if ((*TC)->getTriple().isNVPTX() && CurPhase >= phases::Backend) {
5089  // For CUDA, stop to emit LLVM IR so it can be linked later on.
5090  ++TC;
5091  continue;
5092  }
5093 
5094  A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A,
5095  AssociatedOffloadKind);
5096  ++TC;
5097  }
5098 
5099  return ABRT_Success;
5100  }
5101 
5102  ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDependences(Action *HostAction) override {
5103 
5104  // If this is an input action replicate it for each SYCL toolchain.
5105  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(HostAction)) {
5106  SYCLDeviceActions.clear();
5107 
5108  // Options that are considered LinkerInput are not valid input actions
5109  // to the device tool chain.
5110  if (IA->getInputArg().getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput))
5111  return ABRT_Inactive;
5112 
5113  std::string InputName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
5114  // Objects will be consumed as part of the partial link step when
5115  // dealing with offload static libraries
5116  if (C.getDriver().getOffloadStaticLibSeen() &&
5117  IA->getType() == types::TY_Object && isObjectFile(InputName))
5118  return ABRT_Inactive;
5119 
5120  // Libraries are not processed in the SYCL toolchain
5121  if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object && !isObjectFile(InputName))
5122  return ABRT_Inactive;
5123 
5124  for (auto &TargetInfo : SYCLTargetInfoList) {
5125  (void)TargetInfo;
5126  SYCLDeviceActions.push_back(
5127  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(IA->getInputArg(), IA->getType()));
5128  }
5129  return ABRT_Success;
5130  }
5131 
5132  // If this is an unbundling action use it as is for each SYCL toolchain.
5133  if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction)) {
5134  SYCLDeviceActions.clear();
5135  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(UA->getInputs().back())) {
5136  // Options that are considered LinkerInput are not valid input actions
5137  // to the device tool chain.
5138  if (IA->getInputArg().getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput))
5139  return ABRT_Inactive;
5140 
5141  std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
5142  // Check if the type of the file is the same as the action. Do not
5143  // unbundle it if it is not. Do not unbundle .so files, for example,
5144  // which are not object files.
5145  if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object) {
5146  if (!isObjectFile(FileName))
5147  return ABRT_Inactive;
5148  // For SYCL device libraries, don't need to add them to
5149  // FPGAObjectInputs as there is no FPGA dep files inside.
5150  const auto *TC = ToolChains.front();
5151  if (TC->getTriple().getSubArch() ==
5152  llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga &&
5153  !IsSYCLDeviceLibObj(FileName, C.getDefaultToolChain()
5154  .getTriple()
5155  .isWindowsMSVCEnvironment()))
5156  FPGAObjectInputs.push_back(IA);
5157  }
5158  }
5159  // Create 1 device action per triple/bound arch
5160  for (auto &TargetInfo : SYCLTargetInfoList) {
5161  SYCLDeviceActions.push_back(UA);
5162  UA->registerDependentActionInfo(TargetInfo.TC, TargetInfo.BoundArch,
5163  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5164  }
5165  return ABRT_Success;
5166  }
5167  return ABRT_Success;
5168  }
5169 
5170  void appendLinkDeviceActions(ActionList &AL) override {
5171  if (DeviceLinkerInputs.size() == 0)
5172  return;
5173 
5174  for (const auto &LinkInputEnum : enumerate(DeviceLinkerInputs)) {
5175  auto &LI = LinkInputEnum.value();
5176  int Index = LinkInputEnum.index();
5177  const ToolChain *TC = SYCLTargetInfoList[Index].TC;
5178  const char *BoundArch = SYCLTargetInfoList[Index].BoundArch;
5179 
5180  auto TripleIt = llvm::find_if(SYCLTripleList, [&](auto &SYCLTriple) {
5181  return SYCLTriple == TC->getTriple();
5182  });
5183  if (TripleIt == SYCLTripleList.end()) {
5184  // If the toolchain's triple is absent in this "main" triple
5185  // collection, this means it was created specifically for one of
5186  // the SYCL AOT inputs. Those will be handled separately.
5187  continue;
5188  }
5189  if (LI.empty())
5190  // Current list is empty, nothing to process.
5191  continue;
5192  // Do not add the wrapper when performing -fsycl-link.
5193  // TODO: Update when wrappers are not added to be more general,
5194  // improving the number of wrapper calls occuring. For now, only
5195  // restrict the wrappers from being inlined with each device link
5196  // when performing -fsycl-link behaviors.
5197  appendSYCLDeviceLink(LI, TC, AL, BoundArch,
5198  /*SkipWrapper=*/WrapDeviceOnlyBinary,
5199  /*AddOffloadAction=*/true);
5200  }
5201  DeviceLinkerInputs.clear();
5202  }
5203 
5204  Action *appendLinkHostActions(ActionList &AL) override {
5205  // Only add wrapping actions when performing -fsycl-link
5206  if (!WrapDeviceOnlyBinary)
5207  return nullptr;
5208 
5209  // Create wrapper bitcode from the result of device link actions and
5210  // compile it to an object which will be added to the host link command.
5211  auto *BC = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(AL, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5212  auto *ASM = C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(BC, types::TY_PP_Asm);
5213  return C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(ASM, types::TY_Object);
5214  }
5215 
5216  // Actions that can only be appended after all Inputs have been processed
5217  // occur here. Not all offload actions are against single files.
5218  void appendTopLevelLinkAction(ActionList &AL) override {
5219  if (!SYCLLinkBinary)
5220  return;
5221 
5222  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
5223  withBoundArchForToolChain(ToolChains.front(), [&](const char *BoundArch) {
5224  Dep.add(*SYCLLinkBinary, *ToolChains.front(), BoundArch,
5225  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5226  });
5227  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, SYCLLinkBinary->getType()));
5228  SYCLLinkBinary = nullptr;
5229  }
5230 
5231  void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) override {
5232  // We should always have an action for each input.
5233  if (!SYCLDeviceActions.empty()) {
5234  assert(SYCLDeviceActions.size() == SYCLTargetInfoList.size() &&
5235  "Number of SYCL actions and toolchains/boundarch pairs do not "
5236  "match.");
5237 
5238  // Append all device actions followed by the proper offload action.
5239  for (auto TargetActionInfo :
5240  llvm::zip(SYCLDeviceActions, SYCLTargetInfoList)) {
5241  Action *A = std::get<0>(TargetActionInfo);
5242  DeviceTargetInfo &TargetInfo = std::get<1>(TargetActionInfo);
5243 
5244  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
5245  Dep.add(*A, *TargetInfo.TC, TargetInfo.BoundArch, Action::OFK_SYCL);
5246  if (ExternalCudaAction) {
5247  assert(
5248  SYCLTargetInfoList.size() == 1 &&
5249  "Number of SYCL actions and toolchains/boundarch pairs do not "
5250  "match.");
5251 
5252  // Link with external CUDA action.
5253  ActionList LinkObjects;
5254  LinkObjects.push_back(
5255  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
5256  LinkObjects.push_back(ExternalCudaAction);
5257  Action *DeviceLinkAction =
5258  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkObjects, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5259 
5260  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
5261  DDep.add(*DeviceLinkAction, *TargetInfo.TC, TargetInfo.BoundArch,
5262  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5263  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDep, A->getType()));
5264 
5265  ExternalCudaAction = nullptr;
5266  } else {
5267  AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
5268  }
5269  }
5270  // We no longer need the action stored in this builder.
5271  SYCLDeviceActions.clear();
5272  }
5273  }
5274 
5275  // Performs device specific linking steps for the SYCL based toolchain.
5276  // This function is used for both the early AOT flow and the typical
5277  // offload device link flow.
5278  // When creating the standard offload device link flow during the link
5279  // phase, the ListIndex input provides an index against the
5280  // SYCLTargetInfoList. This is used to determine associated toolchain
5281  // information for the values being worked against to add the device link
5282  // steps. The generated device link steps are added via dependency
5283  // additions. For early AOT, ListIndex is the base device file that the
5284  // created device linking actions are performed against. The
5285  // DeviceLinkActions is used to hold the actions generated to be added to
5286  // the toolchain.
5287  // TODO: This function takes a list of items to work against. Update this
5288  // to work one action at a time, enabling the ability to pull out the
5289  // wrapping step to be performed solely on the host side of the toolchain.
5290  // Any FPGA specific behaviors should also be specifically scrutinized
5291  // to better compartmentalize that aspect of the compilation.
5292  void appendSYCLDeviceLink(const ActionList &ListIndex, const ToolChain *TC,
5293  ActionList &DeviceLinkActions,
5294  const char *BoundArch, bool SkipWrapper,
5295  bool AddOffloadAction = false) {
5296  auto addDeps = [&](Action *A, const ToolChain *TC,
5297  const char *BoundArch) {
5298  if (AddOffloadAction) {
5299  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Deps;
5300  Deps.add(*A, *TC, BoundArch, Action::OFK_SYCL);
5301  DeviceLinkActions.push_back(
5302  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Deps, A->getType()));
5303  } else
5304  DeviceLinkActions.push_back(A);
5305  };
5306 
5307  // List of device specific libraries to be fed into llvm-link.
5308  ActionList SYCLDeviceLibs;
5309 
5310  // List of device specific library 'objects' (FPGA AOCO libraries) that
5311  // are fed directly to the FPGA offline compiler.
5312  ActionList FPGADeviceLibObjects;
5313 
5314  // List of device objects that go through the device link step.
5315  ActionList LinkObjects;
5316 
5317  // List of FPGA AOC specific device objects/archives.
5318  ActionList FPGAAOCDevices;
5319  auto TargetTriple = TC->getTriple();
5320  auto IsNVPTX = TargetTriple.isNVPTX();
5321  auto IsAMDGCN = TargetTriple.isAMDGCN();
5322  auto IsSPIR = TargetTriple.isSPIROrSPIRV();
5323  bool IsSpirvAOT = TargetTriple.isSPIRAOT();
5324  const bool IsSYCLNativeCPU =
5325  TC->getAuxTriple() &&
5326  driver::isSYCLNativeCPU(TargetTriple, *TC->getAuxTriple());
5327  for (const auto &Input : ListIndex) {
5328  if (TargetTriple.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga &&
5329  types::isFPGA(Input->getType())) {
5330  assert(BoundArch == nullptr &&
5331  "fpga triple bounded arch not nullptr");
5332  // FPGA aoco does not go through the link, everything else does.
5333  if (Input->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCO) {
5334  FPGADeviceLibObjects.push_back(Input);
5335  continue;
5336  }
5337  // FPGA aocr/aocx does not go through the link and is passed
5338  // directly to the backend compilation step (aocr) or wrapper (aocx)
5339  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga)) {
5340  if (Input->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR ||
5341  Input->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU ||
5342  Input->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX)
5343  // Save the AOCR device items. These will be processed along
5344  // with the FPGAAOCArchives.
5345  FPGAAOCDevices.push_back(Input);
5346  else
5347  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected FPGA input type.");
5348  }
5349  continue;
5350  } else if (!types::isFPGA(Input->getType())) {
5351  // No need for any conversion if we are coming in from the
5352  // clang-offload-deps or regular compilation path.
5353  if (IsNVPTX || IsAMDGCN || ContainsOffloadDepsAction(Input) ||
5354  ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(Input)) {
5355  LinkObjects.push_back(Input);
5356  continue;
5357  }
5358  // Any objects or lists of objects that come in from the unbundling
5359  // step can either be LLVM-IR or SPIR-V based. Send these through
5360  // the spirv-to-ir-wrapper to convert to LLVM-IR to be properly
5361  // processed during the device link.
5362  Action *ConvertSPIRVAction = C.MakeAction<SpirvToIrWrapperJobAction>(
5363  Input, Input->getType() == types::TY_Tempfilelist
5364  ? types::TY_Tempfilelist
5365  : types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5366  LinkObjects.push_back(ConvertSPIRVAction);
5367  }
5368  }
5369  // Process AOCR/AOCR_EMU
5370  if (FPGAAOCDevices.size()) {
5371  assert(FPGAAOCDevices.size() == FPGAAOCArchives.size() &&
5372  "Unexpected number of AOC binaries");
5373  // Generate AOCX/AOCR
5374  // Input is the unbundled device binary. Perform an additional
5375  // unbundle against the input file associated to grab the wrapped
5376  // device binary.
5377  for (auto AOCRItem : llvm::zip(FPGAAOCArchives, FPGAAOCDevices)) {
5378  Action *Archive = std::get<0>(AOCRItem);
5379  Action *Device = std::get<1>(AOCRItem);
5380 
5381  auto *UnbundleAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(
5382  Archive, types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5383  UnbundleAction->registerDependentActionInfo(TC, /*BoundArch=*/"",
5384  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5385  auto *RenameUnbundle = C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5386  UnbundleAction, types::TY_Tempfilelist, types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5387  RenameUnbundle->addRenameColumnTform(
5388  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO,
5389  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_SYM_AND_PROPS);
5390 
5391  // Wrap the unbundled device binary along with the additional
5392  // .bc file that contains the Symbols and Properties
5393  if (Device->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX) {
5394  auto *RenameAction = C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5395  Device, types::TY_Tempfilelist, types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5396  RenameAction->addRenameColumnTform(
5397  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO,
5398  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE);
5399  ActionList WrapperItems({RenameAction, RenameUnbundle});
5400  auto *DeviceWrappingAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5401  WrapperItems, types::TY_Object);
5402  addDeps(DeviceWrappingAction, TC, BoundArch);
5403  } else {
5404  auto *FPGAAOTAction =
5405  C.MakeAction<BackendCompileJobAction>(Device, FPGAOutType);
5406  auto *RenameAction = C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5407  FPGAAOTAction, types::TY_Tempfilelist, types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5408  RenameAction->addRenameColumnTform(
5409  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO,
5410  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE);
5411  ActionList WrapperItems({RenameAction, RenameUnbundle});
5412  auto *DeviceWrappingAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5413  WrapperItems, types::TY_Object);
5414 
5415  Action *DeviceAction = DeviceWrappingAction;
5416  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ)) {
5417  if (auto *OWA = dyn_cast<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(DeviceAction))
5418  OWA->setCompileStep(false);
5419  ActionList BundlingActions;
5420  BundlingActions.push_back(DeviceWrappingAction);
5421 
5422  // Wrap and compile the wrapped device device binary. This will
5423  // be used later when consumed as the input .bc file to retain
5424  // the symbols and properties associated.
5425  DeviceAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5426  BundlingActions, types::TY_Object);
5427  if (auto *OWA = dyn_cast<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(DeviceAction))
5428  OWA->setOffloadKind(Action::OFK_Host);
5429  Action *CompiledDeviceAction =
5430  C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(WrapperItems,
5431  types::TY_Object);
5432  addDeps(CompiledDeviceAction, TC, BoundArch);
5433  }
5434  addDeps(DeviceAction, TC, BoundArch);
5435  }
5436  }
5437  }
5438  for (const auto &A : SYCLFinalDeviceList) {
5439  // Given the list of archives that have final device binaries, take
5440  // those archives and unbundle all of the devices seen. These will
5441  // be added to the final host link with no additional processing.
5442  // Gather the targets to unbundle.
5443  auto Input(A.first);
5444  for (StringRef TargetString : A.second) {
5445  // Unbundle
5446  types::ID InputType = Input->getType();
5447  if (InputType == types::TY_Archive)
5448  InputType = types::TY_Tempfilelist;
5449  auto *UA = C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(Input, InputType);
5450  UA->registerDependentActionInfo(TC, /*BoundArch=*/"",
5451  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5452  UA->setTargetString(TargetString.str());
5453 
5454  // Add lists to the final link.
5455  addDeps(UA, TC, "");
5456  }
5457  }
5458  if (!LinkObjects.empty()) {
5459  // The linkage actions subgraph leading to the offload wrapper.
5460  // [cond] Means incoming/outgoing dependence is created only when cond
5461  // is true. A function of:
5462  // n - target is NVPTX/AMDGCN
5463  // a - SPIRV AOT compilation is requested
5464  // s - device code split requested
5465  // r - relocatable device code is requested
5466  // f - link object output type is TY_Tempfilelist (fat archive)
5467  // e - Embedded IR for fusion (-fsycl-embed-ir) was requested
5468  // and target is NVPTX.
5469  // * - "all other cases"
5470  // - no condition means output/input is "always" present
5471  // First symbol indicates output/input type
5472  // . - single file output (TY_SPIRV, TY_LLVM_BC,...)
5473  // - - TY_Tempfilelist
5474  // + - TY_Tempfiletable
5475  //
5476  // .-----------------.
5477  // |Link(LinkObjects)|
5478  // .-----------------.
5479  // ----[-!rf] [*]
5480  // [-!rf] |
5481  // .-------------. |
5482  // | llvm-foreach| |
5483  // .-------------. |
5484  // [.] |
5485  // | |
5486  // | |
5487  // .---------------------------------------.
5488  // | PostLink |[+e]----------------
5489  // .---------------------------------------. |
5490  // [+*] [+] |
5491  // | | |
5492  // | | |
5493  // |--------- | |
5494  // | | | |
5495  // | | | |
5496  // | [+!rf] | |
5497  // | .-------------. | |
5498  // | | llvm-foreach| | |
5499  // | .-------------. | |
5500  // | | | |
5501  // [+*] [+!rf] | |
5502  // .-----------------. | |
5503  // | FileTableTform | | |
5504  // | (extract "Code")| | |
5505  // .-----------------. | |
5506  // [-] |----------- |
5507  // --------------------| | |
5508  // | | | |
5509  // | |----------------- | |
5510  // | | | | |
5511  // | | [-!rf] | |
5512  // | | .--------------. | |
5513  // | | |FileTableTform| | |
5514  // | | | (merge) | | |
5515  // | | .--------------. | |
5516  // | | [-] |------- |
5517  // | | | | | |
5518  // | | | ------| | |
5519  // | | --------| | | |
5520  // [.] [-*] [-!rf] [+!rf] | |
5521  // .---------------. .-------------------. .--------------. | |
5522  // | finalizeNVPTX | | SPIRVTranslator | |FileTableTform| | |
5523  // | finalizeAMDGCN | | | | (merge) | | |
5524  // .---------------. .-------------------. . -------------. | |
5525  // [.] [-as] [-!a] | | |
5526  // | | | | | |
5527  // | [-s] | | | |
5528  // | .----------------. | | | |
5529  // | | BackendCompile | | | | |
5530  // | .----------------. | ------| | |
5531  // | [-s] | | | |
5532  // | | | | | |
5533  // | [-a] [-!a] [-!rf] | |
5534  // | .--------------------. | |
5535  // -----------[-n]| FileTableTform |[+*]--------------| |
5536  // | (replace "Code") | |
5537  // .--------------------. |
5538  // | -------------------------
5539  // [+*] | [+e]
5540  // .--------------------------------------.
5541  // | OffloadWrapper |
5542  // .--------------------------------------.
5543  //
5544  ActionList FullLinkObjects;
5545  bool IsRDC = !tools::SYCL::shouldDoPerObjectFileLinking(C);
5546  if (IsRDC) {
5547  Action *DeviceLinkAction =
5548  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkObjects, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5549  FullLinkObjects.push_back(DeviceLinkAction);
5550  } else
5551  FullLinkObjects = LinkObjects;
5552 
5553  // FIXME: Link all wrapper and fallback device libraries as default,
5554  // When spv online link is supported by all backends, the fallback
5555  // device libraries are only needed when current toolchain is using
5556  // AOT compilation.
5557  bool SYCLDeviceLibLinked = false;
5558  if (IsSPIR || IsNVPTX) {
5559  bool UseJitLink =
5560  IsSPIR &&
5561  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl_device_lib_jit_link,
5562  options::OPT_fno_sycl_device_lib_jit_link, false);
5563  bool UseAOTLink = IsSPIR && (IsSpirvAOT || !UseJitLink);
5564  SYCLDeviceLibLinked = addSYCLDeviceLibs(
5565  TC, SYCLDeviceLibs, UseAOTLink,
5566  C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment());
5567  }
5568  if (IsSYCLNativeCPU) {
5569  SYCLDeviceLibLinked |= addSYCLNativeCPULibs(TC, SYCLDeviceLibs);
5570  }
5571  JobAction *LinkSYCLLibs =
5572  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(SYCLDeviceLibs, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5573  for (Action *FullLinkObject : FullLinkObjects) {
5574  if (FullLinkObject->getKind() ==
5575  clang::driver::Action::OffloadDepsJobClass)
5576  continue;
5577  Action *FullDeviceLinkAction = nullptr;
5578  ActionList WrapperInputs;
5579 
5580  if (SYCLDeviceLibLinked) {
5581  if (IsRDC) {
5582  // First object has to be non-DeviceLib for only-needed to be
5583  // passed.
5584  SYCLDeviceLibs.insert(SYCLDeviceLibs.begin(), FullLinkObject);
5585  FullDeviceLinkAction = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(
5586  SYCLDeviceLibs, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5587  } else {
5588  FullDeviceLinkAction = FullLinkObject;
5589 
5590  ActionList DeviceCodeAndSYCLLibs{FullDeviceLinkAction,
5591  LinkSYCLLibs};
5592  JobAction *LinkDeviceCode = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(
5593  DeviceCodeAndSYCLLibs, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5594 
5595  if (FullDeviceLinkAction->getType() == types::TY_Tempfilelist) {
5596  // If our compiler input outputs a temp file list (eg. fat
5597  // static archive), we need to link the device code against
5598  // each entry in the static archive.
5599  auto *ParallelLinkDeviceCode =
5600  C.MakeAction<ForEachWrappingAction>(
5601  cast<JobAction>(FullDeviceLinkAction), LinkDeviceCode);
5602  // The SYCL device library action tree should not be
5603  // for-eached, it only needs to happen once total. The
5604  // for-each action should start linking device code with the
5605  // device libraries.
5606  std::function<void(const Action *)> traverseActionTree =
5607  [&](const Action *Act) {
5608  ParallelLinkDeviceCode->addSerialAction(Act);
5609  for (const auto &Input : Act->getInputs()) {
5610  traverseActionTree(Input);
5611  }
5612  };
5613  traverseActionTree(LinkSYCLLibs);
5614  ActionList TformInputs{FullDeviceLinkAction,
5615  ParallelLinkDeviceCode};
5616  auto *ReplaceFilesAction =
5617  C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5618  TformInputs, types::TY_Tempfilelist,
5619  types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5620  ReplaceFilesAction->addReplaceColumnTform(
5621  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO,
5622  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO);
5623  ReplaceFilesAction->addExtractColumnTform(
5624  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO, false /*drop titles*/);
5625  FullDeviceLinkAction = ReplaceFilesAction;
5626  } else {
5627  // If our compiler input is singular, just do a single link.
5628  FullDeviceLinkAction = LinkDeviceCode;
5629  }
5630  }
5631  } else
5632  FullDeviceLinkAction = FullLinkObject;
5633 
5634  // reflects whether current target is ahead-of-time and can't
5635  // support runtime setting of specialization constants
5636  bool IsAOT = IsNVPTX || IsAMDGCN || IsSpirvAOT || IsSYCLNativeCPU;
5637 
5638  // post link is not optional - even if not splitting, always need to
5639  // process specialization constants
5640  types::ID PostLinkOutType = IsSPIR || IsSYCLNativeCPU
5641  ? types::TY_Tempfiletable
5642  : types::TY_LLVM_BC;
5643  auto createPostLinkAction = [&]() {
5644  // For SPIR-V targets, force TY_Tempfiletable.
5645  auto TypedPostLinkAction = C.MakeAction<SYCLPostLinkJobAction>(
5646  FullDeviceLinkAction, PostLinkOutType, types::TY_Tempfiletable);
5647  TypedPostLinkAction->setRTSetsSpecConstants(!IsAOT);
5648  return TypedPostLinkAction;
5649  };
5650  Action *PostLinkAction = createPostLinkAction();
5651  if (IsSYCLNativeCPU) {
5652  // for SYCL Native CPU, we just take the linked device
5653  // modules, lower them to an object file , and link it to the host
5654  // object file.
5655  auto *BackendAct = C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(
5656  FullDeviceLinkAction, types::TY_PP_Asm);
5657  auto *AsmAct =
5658  C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(BackendAct, types::TY_Object);
5659  addDeps(AsmAct, TC, BoundArch);
5660  auto *DeviceWrappingAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5661  PostLinkAction, types::TY_Object);
5662  addDeps(DeviceWrappingAction, TC, BoundArch);
5663  continue;
5664  }
5665  if ((IsNVPTX || IsAMDGCN) &&
5666  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_embed_ir)) {
5667  // When compiling for Nvidia/AMD devices and the user requested the
5668  // IR to be embedded in the application (via option), run the output
5669  // of sycl-post-link (filetable referencing LLVM Bitcode + symbols)
5670  // through the offload wrapper and link the resulting object to the
5671  // application.
5672  auto *WrapBitcodeAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5673  PostLinkAction, types::TY_Object, true);
5674  addDeps(WrapBitcodeAction, TC, BoundArch);
5675  }
5676  bool NoRDCFatStaticArchive =
5677  !IsRDC &&
5678  FullDeviceLinkAction->getType() == types::TY_Tempfilelist;
5679  if (NoRDCFatStaticArchive)
5680  PostLinkAction = C.MakeAction<ForEachWrappingAction>(
5681  cast<JobAction>(FullDeviceLinkAction),
5682  cast<JobAction>(PostLinkAction));
5683 
5684  auto createExtractIRFilesAction = [&]() {
5685  auto *TypedExtractIRFilesAction =
5686  C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5687  PostLinkAction,
5688  IsSPIR ? types::TY_Tempfilelist : PostLinkAction->getType(),
5689  types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5690  // single column w/o title fits TY_Tempfilelist format
5691  TypedExtractIRFilesAction->addExtractColumnTform(
5692  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE, false /*drop titles*/);
5693  return TypedExtractIRFilesAction;
5694  };
5695 
5696  Action *ExtractIRFilesAction = createExtractIRFilesAction();
5697 
5698  if (IsNVPTX || IsAMDGCN) {
5699  JobAction *FinAction =
5700  IsNVPTX ? finalizeNVPTXDependences(ExtractIRFilesAction,
5701  TC->getTriple())
5702  : finalizeAMDGCNDependences(ExtractIRFilesAction,
5703  TC->getTriple());
5704  auto *ForEachWrapping = C.MakeAction<ForEachWrappingAction>(
5705  cast<JobAction>(ExtractIRFilesAction), FinAction);
5706 
5707  ActionList TformInputs{PostLinkAction, ForEachWrapping};
5708  auto *ReplaceFilesAction = C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5709  TformInputs, types::TY_Tempfiletable, types::TY_Tempfiletable);
5710  ReplaceFilesAction->addReplaceColumnTform(
5711  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE,
5712  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE);
5713 
5714  WrapperInputs.push_back(ReplaceFilesAction);
5715  } else {
5716  if (NoRDCFatStaticArchive) {
5717  ExtractIRFilesAction = C.MakeAction<ForEachWrappingAction>(
5718  cast<JobAction>(FullDeviceLinkAction),
5719  cast<JobAction>(ExtractIRFilesAction));
5720 
5721  auto *MergeAllTablesIntoOne =
5722  C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(ExtractIRFilesAction,
5723  types::TY_Tempfilelist,
5724  types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5725  MergeAllTablesIntoOne->addMergeTform(
5726  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO);
5727  ExtractIRFilesAction = MergeAllTablesIntoOne;
5728  }
5729  // For SPIRV-based targets - translate to SPIRV then optionally
5730  // compile ahead-of-time to native architecture
5731  Action *BuildCodeAction = C.MakeAction<SPIRVTranslatorJobAction>(
5732  ExtractIRFilesAction, types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5733 
5734  // After the Link, wrap the files before the final host link
5735  if (IsAOT) {
5736  types::ID OutType = types::TY_Tempfilelist;
5737  if (!DeviceCodeSplit) {
5738  OutType = (TargetTriple.getSubArch() ==
5739  llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga)
5740  ? FPGAOutType
5741  : types::TY_Image;
5742  }
5743  // Do the additional Ahead of Time compilation when the specific
5744  // triple calls for it (provided a valid subarch).
5745  ActionList BEInputs;
5746  BEInputs.push_back(BuildCodeAction);
5747  auto unbundleAdd = [&](Action *A, types::ID T) {
5748  ActionList AL;
5749  AL.push_back(A);
5750  Action *UnbundleAction =
5751  C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(AL, T);
5752  BEInputs.push_back(UnbundleAction);
5753  };
5754  // Send any known objects/archives through the unbundler to grab
5755  // the dependency file associated. This is only done for
5756  // -fintelfpga.
5757  for (Action *A : FPGAObjectInputs)
5758  unbundleAdd(A, types::TY_FPGA_Dependencies);
5759  for (Action *A : FPGAArchiveInputs)
5760  unbundleAdd(A, types::TY_FPGA_Dependencies_List);
5761  for (const auto &A : FPGADeviceLibObjects)
5762  BEInputs.push_back(A);
5763  BuildCodeAction =
5764  C.MakeAction<BackendCompileJobAction>(BEInputs, OutType);
5765  }
5766  if (NoRDCFatStaticArchive) {
5767  auto *MergeAllTablesIntoOne =
5768  C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(PostLinkAction,
5769  types::TY_Tempfilelist,
5770  types::TY_Tempfilelist);
5771  MergeAllTablesIntoOne->addMergeTform(
5772  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_ZERO);
5773  PostLinkAction = MergeAllTablesIntoOne;
5774  }
5775  ActionList TformInputs{PostLinkAction, BuildCodeAction};
5776  auto *ReplaceFilesAction = C.MakeAction<FileTableTformJobAction>(
5777  TformInputs, types::TY_Tempfiletable, types::TY_Tempfiletable);
5778  ReplaceFilesAction->addReplaceColumnTform(
5779  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE,
5780  FileTableTformJobAction::COL_CODE);
5781  WrapperInputs.push_back(ReplaceFilesAction);
5782  }
5783  if (SkipWrapper) {
5784  // Wrapper step not requested.
5785  withBoundArchForToolChain(TC, [&](const char *BoundArch) {
5786  addDeps(WrapperInputs.front(), TC, BoundArch);
5787  });
5788  continue;
5789  }
5790 
5791  // After the Link, wrap the files before the final host link
5792  // Add the unbundled wrapped AOC device binary to the wrapper
5793  // call.
5794  auto *DeviceWrappingAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5795  WrapperInputs, types::TY_Object);
5796 
5797  if (IsSpirvAOT) {
5798  // For FPGA with -fsycl-link, we need to bundle the output.
5799  if (TargetTriple.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga) {
5800  Action *DeviceAction = DeviceWrappingAction;
5801  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ)) {
5802  // We do not want to compile the wrapped binary before the link.
5803  if (auto *OWA = dyn_cast<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(DeviceAction))
5804  OWA->setCompileStep(false);
5805  ActionList BundlingActions;
5806  BundlingActions.push_back(DeviceWrappingAction);
5807 
5808  // Wrap and compile the wrapped device device binary. This will
5809  // be used later when consumed as the input .bc file to retain
5810  // the symbols and properties associated.
5811  DeviceAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(
5812  BundlingActions, types::TY_Object);
5813  if (auto *OWA = dyn_cast<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(DeviceAction))
5814  OWA->setOffloadKind(Action::OFK_Host);
5815  Action *CompiledDeviceAction =
5816  C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(WrapperInputs,
5817  types::TY_Object);
5818  addDeps(CompiledDeviceAction, TC, nullptr);
5819  }
5820  addDeps(DeviceAction, TC, nullptr);
5821  } else {
5822  bool AddBA =
5823  (TargetTriple.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_gen &&
5824  BoundArch != nullptr);
5825  addDeps(DeviceWrappingAction, TC, AddBA ? BoundArch : nullptr);
5826  }
5827  } else {
5828  withBoundArchForToolChain(TC, [&](const char *BoundArch) {
5829  addDeps(DeviceWrappingAction, TC, BoundArch);
5830  });
5831  }
5832  }
5833  }
5834  }
5835 
5836  bool addSYCLNativeCPULibs(const ToolChain *TC,
5837  ActionList &DeviceLinkObjects) {
5838  std::string LibSpirvFile;
5839  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_libspirv_path_EQ)) {
5840  auto ProvidedPath =
5841  Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fsycl_libspirv_path_EQ).str();
5842  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(ProvidedPath))
5843  LibSpirvFile = ProvidedPath;
5844  } else {
5845  SmallVector<StringRef, 8> LibraryPaths;
5846 
5847  // Expected path w/out install.
5848  SmallString<256> WithoutInstallPath(C.getDriver().ResourceDir);
5849  llvm::sys::path::append(WithoutInstallPath, Twine("../../clc"));
5850  LibraryPaths.emplace_back(WithoutInstallPath.c_str());
5851
