5852  // Expected path w/ install.
5853  SmallString<256> WithInstallPath(C.getDriver().ResourceDir);
5854  llvm::sys::path::append(WithInstallPath, Twine("../../../share/clc"));
5855  LibraryPaths.emplace_back(WithInstallPath.c_str());
5856 
5857  // Select libclc variant based on target triple
5858  std::string LibSpirvTargetName = "libspirv-";
5859  LibSpirvTargetName.append(TC->getTripleString() + ".bc");
5860 
5861  for (StringRef LibraryPath : LibraryPaths) {
5862  SmallString<128> LibSpirvTargetFile(LibraryPath);
5863  llvm::sys::path::append(LibSpirvTargetFile, LibSpirvTargetName);
5864  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(LibSpirvTargetFile) ||
5865  Args.hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
5866  LibSpirvFile = std::string(LibSpirvTargetFile.str());
5867  break;
5868  }
5869  }
5870  }
5871 
5872  if (!LibSpirvFile.empty()) {
5873  Arg *LibClcInputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, C.getDriver().getOpts(),
5874  Args.MakeArgString(LibSpirvFile));
5875  auto *SYCLLibClcInputAction =
5876  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*LibClcInputArg, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5877  DeviceLinkObjects.push_back(SYCLLibClcInputAction);
5878  return true;
5879  }
5880  return false;
5881  }
5882 
5883  bool addSYCLDeviceLibs(const ToolChain *TC, ActionList &DeviceLinkObjects,
5884  bool isSpirvAOT, bool isMSVCEnv) {
5885  int NumOfDeviceLibLinked = 0;
5886  SmallVector<SmallString<128>, 4> LibLocCandidates;
5887  SYCLInstallation.getSYCLDeviceLibPath(LibLocCandidates);
5888 
5889  SmallVector<std::string, 8> DeviceLibraries;
5890  DeviceLibraries =
5891  tools::SYCL::getDeviceLibraries(C, TC->getTriple(), isSpirvAOT);
5892 
5893  for (const auto &DeviceLib : DeviceLibraries) {
5894  bool LibLocSelected = false;
5895  for (const auto &LLCandidate : LibLocCandidates) {
5896  if (LibLocSelected)
5897  break;
5898  SmallString<128> LibName(LLCandidate);
5899  llvm::sys::path::append(LibName, DeviceLib);
5900  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(LibName)) {
5901  ++NumOfDeviceLibLinked;
5902  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, C.getDriver().getOpts(),
5903  Args.MakeArgString(LibName));
5904  if (TC->getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
5905  auto *SYCLDeviceLibsInputAction =
5906  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, types::TY_Object);
5907  auto *SYCLDeviceLibsUnbundleAction =
5908  C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(
5909  SYCLDeviceLibsInputAction);
5910 
5911  // We are using BoundArch="" here since the NVPTX bundles in
5912  // the devicelib .o files do not contain any arch information
5913  SYCLDeviceLibsUnbundleAction->registerDependentActionInfo(
5914  TC, /*BoundArch=*/"", Action::OFK_SYCL);
5915  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
5916  Dep.add(*SYCLDeviceLibsUnbundleAction, *TC, /*BoundArch=*/"",
5917  Action::OFK_SYCL);
5918  auto *SYCLDeviceLibsDependenciesAction =
5919  C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
5920  Dep, SYCLDeviceLibsUnbundleAction->getType());
5921  DeviceLinkObjects.push_back(SYCLDeviceLibsDependenciesAction);
5922  } else {
5923  // We are using the LLVM-IR device libraries directly, no need
5924  // to unbundle any objects.
5925  auto *SYCLDeviceLibsInputAction =
5926  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5927  DeviceLinkObjects.push_back(SYCLDeviceLibsInputAction);
5928  }
5929  if (!LibLocSelected)
5930  LibLocSelected = !LibLocSelected;
5931  }
5932  }
5933  }
5934 
5935  // For NVPTX backend we need to also link libclc and CUDA libdevice
5936  // at the same stage that we link all of the unbundled SYCL libdevice
5937  // objects together.
5938  if (TC->getTriple().isNVPTX() && NumOfDeviceLibLinked) {
5939  std::string LibSpirvFile;
5940  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_libspirv_path_EQ)) {
5941  auto ProvidedPath =
5942  Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fsycl_libspirv_path_EQ).str();
5943  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(ProvidedPath))
5944  LibSpirvFile = ProvidedPath;
5945  } else {
5946  SmallVector<StringRef, 8> LibraryPaths;
5947 
5948  // Expected path w/out install.
5949  SmallString<256> WithoutInstallPath(C.getDriver().ResourceDir);
5950  llvm::sys::path::append(WithoutInstallPath, Twine("../../clc"));
5951  LibraryPaths.emplace_back(WithoutInstallPath.c_str());
5952 
5953  // Expected path w/ install.
5954  SmallString<256> WithInstallPath(C.getDriver().ResourceDir);
5955  llvm::sys::path::append(WithInstallPath, Twine("../../../share/clc"));
5956  LibraryPaths.emplace_back(WithInstallPath.c_str());
5957 
5958  // Select remangled libclc variant
5959  std::string LibSpirvTargetName =
5960  (TC->getAuxTriple()->isOSWindows())
5961  ? "remangled-l32-signed_char.libspirv-nvptx64-nvidia-cuda."
5962  "bc"
5963  : "remangled-l64-signed_char.libspirv-nvptx64-nvidia-cuda."
5964  "bc";
5965 
5966  for (StringRef LibraryPath : LibraryPaths) {
5967  SmallString<128> LibSpirvTargetFile(LibraryPath);
5968  llvm::sys::path::append(LibSpirvTargetFile, LibSpirvTargetName);
5969  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(LibSpirvTargetFile) ||
5970  Args.hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
5971  LibSpirvFile = std::string(LibSpirvTargetFile.str());
5972  break;
5973  }
5974  }
5975  }
5976 
5977  if (!LibSpirvFile.empty()) {
5978  Arg *LibClcInputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, C.getDriver().getOpts(),
5979  Args.MakeArgString(LibSpirvFile));
5980  auto *SYCLLibClcInputAction =
5981  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*LibClcInputArg, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5982  DeviceLinkObjects.push_back(SYCLLibClcInputAction);
5983  }
5984 
5985  const toolchains::CudaToolChain *CudaTC =
5986  static_cast<const toolchains::CudaToolChain *>(TC);
5987  for (const auto &LinkInputEnum : enumerate(DeviceLinkerInputs)) {
5988  const char *BoundArch =
5989  SYCLTargetInfoList[LinkInputEnum.index()].BoundArch;
5990  std::string LibDeviceFile =
5991  CudaTC->CudaInstallation.getLibDeviceFile(BoundArch);
5992  if (!LibDeviceFile.empty()) {
5993  Arg *CudaDeviceLibInputArg =
5994  MakeInputArg(Args, C.getDriver().getOpts(),
5995  Args.MakeArgString(LibDeviceFile));
5996  auto *SYCLDeviceLibInputAction = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(
5997  *CudaDeviceLibInputArg, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
5998  DeviceLinkObjects.push_back(SYCLDeviceLibInputAction);
5999  }
6000  }
6001  }
6002  return NumOfDeviceLibLinked != 0;
6003  }
6004 
6005  void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) override {
6006  for (auto &SAI : SYCLAOTInputs) {
6007  // Extract binary file name
6008  std::string FN(SAI.second);
6009  const char *FNStr = Args.MakeArgString(FN);
6010  Arg *myArg = Args.MakeSeparateArg(
6011  nullptr, C.getDriver().getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_INPUT),
6012  FNStr);
6013  auto *SYCLAdd =
6014  C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*myArg, types::TY_SYCL_FATBIN);
6015  auto *DeviceWrappingAction =
6016  C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(SYCLAdd, types::TY_Object);
6017 
6018  // Extract the target triple for this binary
6019  llvm::Triple TT(SAI.first);
6020  // Extract the toolchain for this target triple
6021  auto SYCLDeviceTC = llvm::find_if(
6022  ToolChains, [&](auto &TC) { return TC->getTriple() == TT; });
6023  assert(SYCLDeviceTC != ToolChains.end() &&
6024  "No toolchain found for this AOT input");
6025 
6026  DA.add(*DeviceWrappingAction, **SYCLDeviceTC,
6027  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_SYCL);
6028  }
6029  }
6030 
6031  void addDeviceLinkDependencies(OffloadDepsJobAction *DA) override {
6032  unsigned I = 0;
6033  for (auto &TargetInfo : SYCLTargetInfoList) {
6034  DA->registerDependentActionInfo(TargetInfo.TC, TargetInfo.BoundArch,
6035  Action::OFK_SYCL);
6036  DeviceLinkerInputs[I++].push_back(DA);
6037  }
6038  }
6039 
6040  /// Initialize the GPU architecture list from arguments - this populates
6041  /// `GpuArchList` from `--offload-arch` flags. Only relevant if compiling to
6042  /// CUDA or AMDGCN. Return true if any initialization errors are found.
6043  /// FIXME: "offload-arch" and the BoundArch mechanism should also be
6044  // used in the SYCLToolChain for SPIR-V AOT to track the offload
6045  // architecture instead of the Triple sub-arch it currently uses.
6046  bool initializeGpuArchMap() {
6047  const OptTable &Opts = C.getDriver().getOpts();
6048  for (auto *A : Args) {
6049  unsigned Index;
6050  llvm::Triple *TargetBE = nullptr;
6051 
6052  auto GetTripleIt = [&, this](llvm::StringRef Triple) {
6053  llvm::Triple TargetTriple{Triple};
6054  auto TripleIt = llvm::find_if(SYCLTripleList, [&](auto &SYCLTriple) {
6055  return SYCLTriple == TargetTriple;
6056  });
6057  return TripleIt != SYCLTripleList.end() ? &*TripleIt : nullptr;
6058  };
6059 
6060  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xsycl_backend_EQ)) {
6061  TargetBE = GetTripleIt(A->getValue(0));
6062  // Passing device args: -Xsycl-target-backend=<triple> -opt=val.
6063  if (TargetBE)
6064  Index = Args.getBaseArgs().MakeIndex(A->getValue(1));
6065  else
6066  continue;
6067  } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xsycl_backend)) {
6068  if (SYCLTripleList.size() > 1) {
6069  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_Xsycl_target_missing_triple)
6070  << A->getSpelling();
6071  continue;
6072  }
6073  // Passing device args: -Xsycl-target-backend -opt=val.
6074  TargetBE = &SYCLTripleList.front();
6075  Index = Args.getBaseArgs().MakeIndex(A->getValue(0));
6076  } else
6077  continue;
6078 
6079  auto ParsedArg = Opts.ParseOneArg(Args, Index);
6080 
6081  // TODO: Support --no-cuda-gpu-arch, --{,no-}cuda-gpu-arch=all.
6082  if (ParsedArg &&
6083  ParsedArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ)) {
6084  const char *ArchStr = ParsedArg->getValue(0);
6085  if (TargetBE->isNVPTX()) {
6086  // CUDA arch also applies to AMDGCN ...
6087  CudaArch Arch = StringToCudaArch(ArchStr);
6088  if (Arch == CudaArch::UNKNOWN || !IsNVIDIAGpuArch(Arch)) {
6089  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_cuda_bad_gpu_arch)
6090  << ArchStr;
6091  continue;
6092  }
6093  ArchStr = CudaArchToString(Arch);
6094  } else if (TargetBE->isAMDGCN()) {
6095  llvm::StringMap<bool> Features;
6096  auto Arch = parseTargetID(
6097  *getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(C.getDriver(), C.getInputArgs()),
6098  ArchStr, &Features);
6099  if (!Arch) {
6100  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_bad_target_id) << ArchStr;
6101  continue;
6102  }
6103  auto CanId = getCanonicalTargetID(Arch.value(), Features);
6104  ArchStr = Args.MakeArgStringRef(CanId);
6105  }
6106  ParsedArg->claim();
6107  GpuArchList.emplace_back(*TargetBE, ArchStr);
6108  A->claim();
6109  }
6110  }
6111 
6112  // Handle defaults architectures
6113  for (auto &Triple : SYCLTripleList) {
6114  // For NVIDIA use SM_50 as a default
6115  if (Triple.isNVPTX() && llvm::none_of(GpuArchList, [&](auto &P) {
6116  return P.first.isNVPTX();
6117  })) {
6118  const char *DefaultArch = CudaArchToString(CudaArch::SM_50);
6119  GpuArchList.emplace_back(Triple, DefaultArch);
6120  }
6121 
6122  // For AMD require the architecture to be set by the user
6123  if (Triple.isAMDGCN() && llvm::none_of(GpuArchList, [&](auto &P) {
6124  return P.first.isAMDGCN();
6125  })) {
6126  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_sycl_missing_amdgpu_arch)
6127  << (SYCLTripleList.size() > 1) << Triple.str();
6128  return true;
6129  }
6130  }
6131 
6132  return false;
6133  }
6134 
6135  // Goes through all of the arguments, including inputs expected for the
6136  // linker directly, to determine if the targets contained in the objects and
6137  // archives match target expectations being performed.
6138  void
6139  checkForOffloadMismatch(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
6140  SmallVector<DeviceTargetInfo, 4> &Targets) const {
6141  if (Targets.empty())
6142  return;
6143 
6144  SmallVector<const char *, 16> OffloadLibArgs(
6145  getLinkerArgs(C, Args, true));
6146  // Gather all of the sections seen in the offload objects/archives
6147  SmallVector<std::string, 4> UniqueSections;
6148  for (StringRef OLArg : OffloadLibArgs) {
6149  SmallVector<std::string, 4> Sections(getOffloadSections(C, OLArg));
6150  for (auto &Section : Sections) {
6151  // We only care about sections that start with 'sycl-'. Also remove
6152  // the prefix before adding it.
6153  std::string Prefix("sycl-");
6154  if (Section.compare(0, Prefix.length(), Prefix) != 0)
6155  continue;
6156 
6157  std::string Arch = Section.substr(Prefix.length());
6158 
6159  // There are a few different variants for FPGA, if we see one, just
6160  // use the default FPGA triple to reduce possible match confusion.
6161  if (Arch.compare(0, 4, "fpga") == 0)
6162  Arch = C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("spir64_fpga").str();
6163 
6164  if (std::find(UniqueSections.begin(), UniqueSections.end(), Arch) ==
6165  UniqueSections.end())
6166  UniqueSections.push_back(Arch);
6167  }
6168  }
6169 
6170  if (!UniqueSections.size())
6171  return;
6172 
6173  for (auto &SyclTarget : Targets) {
6174  std::string SectionTriple = SyclTarget.TC->getTriple().str();
6175  if (SyclTarget.BoundArch) {
6176  SectionTriple += "-";
6177  SectionTriple += SyclTarget.BoundArch;
6178  }
6179  // If any matching section is found, we are good.
6180  if (std::find(UniqueSections.begin(), UniqueSections.end(),
6181  SectionTriple) != UniqueSections.end())
6182  continue;
6183  // If any section found is an 'image' based object that was created
6184  // with the intention of not requiring the matching SYCL target, do
6185  // not emit the diagnostic.
6186  if (SyclTarget.TC->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV()) {
6187  bool SectionFound = false;
6188  for (auto Section : UniqueSections) {
6189  if (SectionFound)
6190  break;
6191  SmallVector<std::string, 3> ArchList = {"spir64_gen", "spir64_fpga",
6192  "spir64_x86_64"};
6193  for (auto ArchStr : ArchList) {
6194  std::string Arch(ArchStr + "_image");
6195  if (Section.find(Arch) != std::string::npos) {
6196  SectionFound = true;
6197  break;
6198  }
6199  }
6200  }
6201  if (SectionFound)
6202  continue;
6203  }
6204  // Didn't find any matches, return the full list for the diagnostic.
6205  SmallString<128> ArchListStr;
6206  int Cnt = 0;
6207  for (std::string Section : UniqueSections) {
6208  if (Cnt)
6209  ArchListStr += ", ";
6210  ArchListStr += Section;
6211  Cnt++;
6212  }
6213  if (tools::SYCL::shouldDoPerObjectFileLinking(C)) {
6214  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_no_rdc_sycl_target_missing)
6215  << SectionTriple << ArchListStr;
6216  C.setContainsError();
6217  } else {
6218  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::warn_drv_sycl_target_missing)
6219  << SectionTriple << ArchListStr;
6220  }
6221  }
6222  }
6223 
6224  // Function checks that user passed -fsycl-add-default-spec-consts-image
6225  // flag with at least one AOT target. If no AOT target has been passed then
6226  // a warning is issued.
6227  void checkForMisusedAddDefaultSpecConstsImageFlag(
6228  Compilation &C, const DerivedArgList &Args,
6229  const SmallVector<DeviceTargetInfo, 4> &Targets) const {
6230  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl_add_default_spec_consts_image,
6231  options::OPT_fno_sycl_add_default_spec_consts_image,
6232  false))
6233  return;
6234 
6235  bool foundAOT = std::any_of(
6236  Targets.begin(), Targets.end(), [](const DeviceTargetInfo &DTI) {
6237  llvm::Triple T = DTI.TC->getTriple();
6238  bool isSpirvAOT =
6239  T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga ||
6240  T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_gen ||
6241  T.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_x86_64;
6242 
6243  return T.isNVPTX() || T.isAMDGCN() || isSpirvAOT;
6244  });
6245 
6246  if (!foundAOT)
6247  C.getDriver().Diag(
6248  diag::warn_drv_fsycl_add_default_spec_consts_image_flag_in_non_AOT);
6249  }
6250 
6251  // Go through the offload sections of the provided binary. Gather all
6252  // all of the sections which match the expected format of the triple
6253  // generated when creating fat objects that contain full device binaries.
6254  // Expected format is sycl-<aot_arch>_image-unknown-unknown.
6255  // <aot_arch> values: spir64_gen, spir64_x86_64, spir64_fpga
6256  SmallVector<std::string, 4> deviceBinarySections(Compilation &C,
6257  const StringRef &Input) {
6258  SmallVector<std::string, 4> Sections(getOffloadSections(C, Input));
6259  SmallVector<std::string, 4> FinalDeviceSections;
6260  for (auto S : Sections) {
6261  SmallVector<std::string, 3> ArchList = {"spir64_gen", "spir64_fpga",
6262  "spir64_x86_64"};
6263  for (auto A : ArchList) {
6264  std::string Arch("sycl-" + A + "_image");
6265  if (S.find(Arch) != std::string::npos)
6266  FinalDeviceSections.push_back(S);
6267  }
6268  }
6269  return FinalDeviceSections;
6270  }
6271 
6272  bool initialize() override {
6273  using namespace tools::SYCL;
6274  // Get the SYCL toolchains. If we don't get any, the action builder will
6275  // know there is nothing to do related to SYCL offloading.
6276  auto SYCLTCRange = C.getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_SYCL>();
6277  for (auto TI = SYCLTCRange.first, TE = SYCLTCRange.second; TI != TE;
6278  ++TI)
6279  ToolChains.push_back(TI->second);
6280 
6281  // Nothing to offload if no SYCL Toolchain
6282  if (ToolChains.empty())
6283  return false;
6284 
6285  Arg *SYCLLinkTargets =
6286  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_targets_EQ);
6287  auto *DeviceCodeSplitArg =
6288  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_code_split_EQ);
6289  // -fsycl-device-code-split is an alias to
6290  // -fsycl-device-code-split=auto
6291  DeviceCodeSplit = DeviceCodeSplitArg &&
6292  DeviceCodeSplitArg->getValue() != StringRef("off");
6293  // Gather information about the SYCL Ahead of Time targets. The targets
6294  // are determined on the SubArch values passed along in the triple.
6295  Arg *SYCLTargets =
6296  C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_targets_EQ);
6297  Arg *SYCLAddTargets = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_add_targets_EQ);
6298  Arg *SYCLfpga = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga);
6299  bool HasValidSYCLRuntime = C.getInputArgs().hasFlag(
6300  options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false);
6301  bool SYCLfpgaTriple = false;
6302  bool ShouldAddDefaultTriple = true;
6303  bool GpuInitHasErrors = false;
6304  bool HasSYCLTargetsOption =
6305  SYCLAddTargets || SYCLTargets || SYCLLinkTargets;
6306 
6307  // Make -fintelfpga flag imply -fsycl.
6308  if (SYCLfpga && !HasValidSYCLRuntime)
6309  HasValidSYCLRuntime = true;
6310 
6311  if (HasSYCLTargetsOption) {
6312  if (SYCLTargets || SYCLLinkTargets) {
6313  Arg *SYCLTargetsValues = SYCLTargets ? SYCLTargets : SYCLLinkTargets;
6314  // Fill SYCLTripleList
6315  llvm::StringMap<StringRef> FoundNormalizedTriples;
6316  for (StringRef Val : SYCLTargetsValues->getValues()) {
6317  StringRef UserTargetName(Val);
6318  if (auto ValidDevice = gen::isGPUTarget<gen::IntelGPU>(Val)) {
6319  if (ValidDevice->empty())
6320  // Unrecognized, we have already diagnosed this earlier; skip.
6321  continue;
6322  // Add the proper -device value to the list.
6323  GpuArchList.emplace_back(C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(
6324  "spir64_gen"), ValidDevice->data());
6325  UserTargetName = "spir64_gen";
6326  } else if (auto ValidDevice =
6327  gen::isGPUTarget<gen::NvidiaGPU>(Val)) {
6328  if (ValidDevice->empty())
6329  // Unrecognized, we have already diagnosed this earlier; skip.
6330  continue;
6331  // Add the proper -device value to the list.
6332  GpuArchList.emplace_back(
6333  C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("nvptx64-nvidia-cuda"),
6334  ValidDevice->data());
6335  UserTargetName = "nvptx64-nvidia-cuda";
6336  } else if (auto ValidDevice = gen::isGPUTarget<gen::AmdGPU>(Val)) {
6337  if (ValidDevice->empty())
6338  // Unrecognized, we have already diagnosed this earlier; skip.
6339  continue;
6340  // Add the proper -device value to the list.
6341  GpuArchList.emplace_back(
6342  C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple("amdgcn-amd-amdhsa"),
6343  ValidDevice->data());
6344  UserTargetName = "amdgcn-amd-amdhsa";
6345  } else if (Val == "native_cpu") {
6346  const ToolChain *HostTC =
6347  C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
6348  llvm::Triple TT = HostTC->getTriple();
6349  SYCLTripleList.push_back(TT);
6350  continue;
6351  }
6352 
6353  llvm::Triple TT(C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(Val));
6354  std::string NormalizedName = TT.normalize();
6355 
6356  // Make sure we don't have a duplicate triple.
6357  auto Duplicate = FoundNormalizedTriples.find(NormalizedName);
6358  if (Duplicate != FoundNormalizedTriples.end())
6359  continue;
6360 
6361  // Store the current triple so that we can check for duplicates in
6362  // the following iterations.
6363  FoundNormalizedTriples[NormalizedName] = Val;
6364 
6365  SYCLTripleList.push_back(
6366  C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(UserTargetName));
6367  if (TT.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga)
6368  SYCLfpgaTriple = true;
6369  // For user specified spir64_gen, add an empty device value as a
6370  // placeholder.
6371  if (TT.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_gen)
6372  GpuArchList.emplace_back(TT, nullptr);
6373  }
6374 
6375  // Fill GpuArchList, end if there are issues in initializingGpuArchMap
6376  GpuInitHasErrors = initializeGpuArchMap();
6377  if (GpuInitHasErrors)
6378  return true;
6379 
6380  int I = 0;
6381  // Fill SYCLTargetInfoList
6382  for (auto &TT : SYCLTripleList) {
6383  auto TCIt = llvm::find_if(
6384  ToolChains, [&](auto &TC) { return TT == TC->getTriple(); });
6385  assert(TCIt != ToolChains.end() &&
6386  "Toolchain was not created for this platform");
6387  if (!TT.isNVPTX() && !TT.isAMDGCN()) {
6388  // When users specify the target as 'intel_gpu_*', the proper
6389  // triple is 'spir64_gen'. The given string from intel_gpu_*
6390  // is the target device.
6391  if (TT.isSPIR() &&
6392  TT.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_gen) {
6393  StringRef Device(GpuArchList[I].second);
6394  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(
6395  *TCIt, Device.empty() ? nullptr : Device.data());
6396  ++I;
6397  continue;
6398  }
6399  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(*TCIt, nullptr);
6400  } else {
6401  const char *OffloadArch = nullptr;
6402  for (auto &A : GpuArchList) {
6403  if (TT == A.first) {
6404  OffloadArch = A.second;
6405  break;
6406  }
6407  }
6408  assert(OffloadArch && "Failed to find matching arch.");
6409  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(*TCIt, OffloadArch);
6410  ++I;
6411  }
6412  }
6413  }
6414  if (SYCLAddTargets) {
6415  for (StringRef Val : SYCLAddTargets->getValues()) {
6416  // Parse out the Triple and Input (triple:binary). At this point,
6417  // the format has already been validated at the Driver level.
6418  // Populate the pairs. Each of these will be wrapped and fed
6419  // into the final binary.
6420  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> I = Val.split(':');
6421  llvm::Triple TT(I.first);
6422 
6423  auto TCIt = llvm::find_if(
6424  ToolChains, [&](auto &TC) { return TT == TC->getTriple(); });
6425  assert(TCIt != ToolChains.end() &&
6426  "Toolchain was not created for this platform");
6427 
6428  const char *TF = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(I.second);
6429  // populate the AOT binary inputs vector.
6430  SYCLAOTInputs.push_back(std::make_pair(TT, TF));
6431  ShouldAddDefaultTriple = false;
6432  // Add an empty entry to the Device list
6433  if (TT.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_gen)
6434  GpuArchList.emplace_back(TT, nullptr);
6435  }
6436  }
6437  } else if (HasValidSYCLRuntime) {
6438  // -fsycl is provided without -fsycl-*targets.
6439  bool SYCLfpga = C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga);
6440  // -fsycl -fintelfpga implies spir64_fpga
6441  const char *SYCLTargetArch =
6442  SYCLfpga ? "spir64_fpga" : getDefaultSYCLArch(C);
6443  llvm::Triple TT = C.getDriver().MakeSYCLDeviceTriple(SYCLTargetArch);
6444  auto TCIt = llvm::find_if(
6445  ToolChains, [&](auto &TC) { return TT == TC->getTriple(); });
6446  assert(TCIt != ToolChains.end() &&
6447  "Toolchain was not created for this platform");
6448  SYCLTripleList.push_back(TT);
6449  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(*TCIt, nullptr);
6450  if (SYCLfpga)
6451  SYCLfpgaTriple = true;
6452  }
6453 
6454  WrapDeviceOnlyBinary =
6455  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ) && !SYCLfpgaTriple;
6456  // Device only compilation for -fsycl-link (no FPGA) and
6457  // -fsycl-link-targets
6458  CompileDeviceOnly = (SYCLLinkTargets || WrapDeviceOnlyBinary);
6459 
6460  // Set the FPGA output type based on command line (-fsycl-link).
6461  if (auto *A = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ)) {
6462  FPGAOutType = (A->getValue() == StringRef("early"))
6463  ? types::TY_FPGA_AOCR
6464  : types::TY_FPGA_AOCX;
6465  if (C.getDriver().IsFPGAEmulationMode())
6466  FPGAOutType = (A->getValue() == StringRef("early"))
6467  ? types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU
6468  : types::TY_FPGA_AOCX;
6469  }
6470 
6471  auto makeInputAction = [&](const StringRef Name,
6472  types::ID Type) -> Action * {
6473  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = C.getDriver().getOpts();
6474  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, Args.MakeArgString(Name));
6475  Action *Current = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, Type);
6476  return Current;
6477  };
6478  // Populate FPGA archives that could contain dep files to be
6479  // incorporated into the aoc compilation. Consider AOCR type archives
6480  // as well for tracking symbols and properties information.
6481  if (SYCLfpgaTriple && Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga)) {
6482  SmallVector<const char *, 16> LinkArgs(getLinkerArgs(C, Args));
6483  for (StringRef LA : LinkArgs) {
6484  if (isStaticArchiveFile(LA) && hasOffloadSections(C, LA, Args)) {
6485  FPGAArchiveInputs.push_back(makeInputAction(LA, types::TY_Archive));
6486  for (types::ID Type : {types::TY_FPGA_AOCR, types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU,
6487  types::TY_FPGA_AOCX}) {
6488  if (hasFPGABinary(C, LA.str(), Type)) {
6489  FPGAAOCArchives.push_back(makeInputAction(LA, Type));
6490  break;
6491  }
6492  }
6493  }
6494  }
6495  }
6496  // Discover any objects and archives that contain final device binaries.
6497  if (HasValidSYCLRuntime) {
6498  SmallVector<const char *, 16> LinkArgs(getLinkerArgs(C, Args, true));
6499  for (StringRef LA : LinkArgs) {
6500  SmallVector<std::string, 4> DeviceTargets(
6501  deviceBinarySections(C, LA));
6502  if (!DeviceTargets.empty()) {
6503  bool IsArchive = isStaticArchiveFile(LA);
6504  types::ID FileType =
6505  IsArchive ? types::TY_Archive : types::TY_Object;
6506  SYCLFinalDeviceList.push_back(
6507  std::make_pair(makeInputAction(LA, FileType), DeviceTargets));
6508  }
6509  }
6510  }
6511 
6512  if (ShouldAddDefaultTriple && addSYCLDefaultTriple(C, SYCLTripleList)) {
6513  // If a SYCLDefaultTriple is added to SYCLTripleList,
6514  // add new target to SYCLTargetInfoList
6515  llvm::Triple TT = SYCLTripleList.front();
6516  auto TCIt = llvm::find_if(
6517  ToolChains, [&](auto &TC) { return TT == TC->getTriple(); });
6518  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(*TCIt, nullptr);
6519  }
6520  if (SYCLTargetInfoList.empty()) {
6521  // If there are no SYCL Targets add the front toolchain, this is for
6522  // `-fsycl-device-only` is provided with no `fsycl` or when all dummy
6523  // targets are given
6524  const auto *TC = ToolChains.front();
6525  SYCLTargetInfoList.emplace_back(TC, nullptr);
6526  }
6527 
6528  checkForOffloadMismatch(C, Args, SYCLTargetInfoList);
6529  checkForMisusedAddDefaultSpecConstsImageFlag(C, Args, SYCLTargetInfoList);
6530 
6531  DeviceLinkerInputs.resize(SYCLTargetInfoList.size());
6532  return false;
6533  }
6534 
6535  bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override {
6536  // SYCL should use bundled files whenever possible.
6537  return true;
6538  }
6539  };
6540 
6541  ///
6542  /// TODO: Add the implementation for other specialized builders here.
6543  ///
6544 
6545  /// Specialized builders being used by this offloading action builder.
6546  SmallVector<DeviceActionBuilder *, 4> SpecializedBuilders;
6547 
6548  /// Flag set to true if all valid builders allow file bundling/unbundling.
6549  bool CanUseBundler;
6550 
6551 public:
6552  OffloadingActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
6553  const Driver::InputList &Inputs)
6554  : C(C) {
6555  // Create a specialized builder for each device toolchain.
6556 
6557  IsValid = true;
6558 
6559  // Create a specialized builder for CUDA.
6560  SpecializedBuilders.push_back(
6561  new CudaActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, *this));
6562 
6563  // Create a specialized builder for HIP.
6564  SpecializedBuilders.push_back(new HIPActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, *this));
6565 
6566  // Create a specialized builder for OpenMP.
6567  SpecializedBuilders.push_back(
6568  new OpenMPActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, *this));
6569 
6570  // Create a specialized builder for SYCL.
6571  SpecializedBuilders.push_back(
6572  new SYCLActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, *this));
6573 
6574  //
6575  // TODO: Build other specialized builders here.
6576  //
6577 
6578  // Initialize all the builders, keeping track of errors. If all valid
6579  // builders agree that we can use bundling, set the flag to true.
6580  unsigned ValidBuilders = 0u;
6581  unsigned ValidBuildersSupportingBundling = 0u;
6582  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6583  IsValid = IsValid && !SB->initialize();
6584 
6585  // Update the counters if the builder is valid.
6586  if (SB->isValid()) {
6587  ++ValidBuilders;
6588  if (SB->canUseBundlerUnbundler())
6589  ++ValidBuildersSupportingBundling;
6590  }
6591  }
6592  CanUseBundler =
6593  ValidBuilders && ValidBuilders == ValidBuildersSupportingBundling;
6594  }
6595 
6596  ~OffloadingActionBuilder() {
6597  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders)
6598  delete SB;
6599  }
6600 
6601  /// Push an action coming from a specialized DeviceActionBuilder (i.e.,
6602  /// foreign action) to the other ones
6603  void pushForeignAction(Action *A) {
6604  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6605  if (SB->isValid())
6606  SB->pushForeignAction(A);
6607  }
6608  }
6609 
6610  /// Record a host action and its originating input argument.
6611  void recordHostAction(Action *HostAction, const Arg *InputArg) {
6612  assert(HostAction && "Invalid host action");
6613  assert(InputArg && "Invalid input argument");
6614  auto Loc = HostActionToInputArgMap.find(HostAction);
6615  if (Loc == HostActionToInputArgMap.end())
6616  HostActionToInputArgMap[HostAction] = InputArg;
6617  assert(HostActionToInputArgMap[HostAction] == InputArg &&
6618  "host action mapped to multiple input arguments");
6619  }
6620 
6621  /// Generate an action that adds device dependences (if any) to a host action.
6622  /// If no device dependence actions exist, just return the host action \a
6623  /// HostAction. If an error is found or if no builder requires the host action
6624  /// to be generated, return nullptr.
6625  Action *
6626  addDeviceDependencesToHostAction(Action *HostAction, const Arg *InputArg,
6627  phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
6628  DeviceActionBuilder::PhasesTy &Phases) {
6629  if (!IsValid)
6630  return nullptr;
6631 
6632  if (SpecializedBuilders.empty())
6633  return HostAction;
6634 
6635  assert(HostAction && "Invalid host action!");
6636  recordHostAction(HostAction, InputArg);
6637 
6638  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
6639  // Check if all the programming models agree we should not emit the host
6640  // action. Also, keep track of the offloading kinds employed.
6641  auto &OffloadKind = InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg];
6642  unsigned InactiveBuilders = 0u;
6643  unsigned IgnoringBuilders = 0u;
6644  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6645  if (!SB->isValid()) {
6646  ++InactiveBuilders;
6647  continue;
6648  }
6649  auto RetCode =
6650  SB->getDeviceDependences(DDeps, CurPhase, FinalPhase, Phases);
6651 
6652  // If the builder explicitly says the host action should be ignored,
6653  // we need to increment the variable that tracks the builders that request
6654  // the host object to be ignored.
6655  if (RetCode == DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Ignore_Host)
6656  ++IgnoringBuilders;
6657 
6658  // Unless the builder was inactive for this action, we have to record the
6659  // offload kind because the host will have to use it.
6660  if (RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Inactive)
6661  OffloadKind |= SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind();
6662  }
6663 
6664  // If all builders agree that the host object should be ignored, just return
6665  // nullptr.
6666  if (IgnoringBuilders &&
6667  SpecializedBuilders.size() == (InactiveBuilders + IgnoringBuilders))
6668  return nullptr;
6669 
6670  if (DDeps.getActions().empty())
6671  return HostAction;
6672 
6673  // Add host-cuda-sycl offload kind for the SYCL compilation of .cu files
6674  if (OffloadKind == (Action::OFK_Cuda | Action::OFK_SYCL)) {
6675  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
6676  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
6677  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_SYCL | Action::OFK_Cuda);
6678  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDeps);
6679  }
6680 
6681  // We have dependences we need to bundle together. We use an offload action
6682  // for that.
6683  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
6684  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
6685  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, DDeps);
6686  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDeps);
6687  }
6688 
6689  // Update Input action to reflect FPGA device archive specifics based
6690  // on archive contents.
6691  bool updateInputForFPGA(Action *&A, const Arg *InputArg,
6692  DerivedArgList &Args) {
6693  std::string InputName = InputArg->getAsString(Args);
6694  const Driver &D = C.getDriver();
6695  // Only check for FPGA device information when using fpga SubArch.
6696  if (A->getType() == types::TY_Object && isObjectFile(InputName))
6697  return true;
6698 
6699  auto ArchiveTypeMismatch = [&D, &InputName](bool EmitDiag) {
6700  if (EmitDiag)
6701  D.Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_mismatch_fpga_archive) << InputName;
6702  };
6703  // Type FPGA aoco is a special case for static archives
6704  if (A->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCO) {
6705  if (!hasFPGABinary(C, InputName, types::TY_FPGA_AOCO))
6706  return false;
6707  A = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, types::TY_FPGA_AOCO);
6708  return true;
6709  }
6710 
6711  // Type FPGA aocx is considered the same way for Hardware and Emulation.
6712  if (hasFPGABinary(C, InputName, types::TY_FPGA_AOCX)) {
6713  A = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, types::TY_FPGA_AOCX);
6714  return true;
6715  }
6716 
6717  SmallVector<std::pair<types::ID, bool>, 4> FPGAAOCTypes = {
6718  {types::TY_FPGA_AOCR, false},
6719  {types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU, true}};
6720  for (const auto &ArchiveType : FPGAAOCTypes) {
6721  bool BinaryFound = hasFPGABinary(C, InputName, ArchiveType.first);
6722  if (BinaryFound && ArchiveType.second == D.IsFPGAEmulationMode()) {
6723  // Binary matches check and emulation type, we keep this one.
6724  A = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, ArchiveType.first);
6725  return true;
6726  }
6727  ArchiveTypeMismatch(BinaryFound &&
6728  ArchiveType.second == D.IsFPGAHWMode());
6729  }
6730  return true;
6731  }
6732 
6733  /// Generate an action that adds a host dependence to a device action. The
6734  /// results will be kept in this action builder. Return true if an error was
6735  /// found.
6736  bool addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Action *&HostAction,
6737  const Arg *InputArg,
6738  DerivedArgList &Args) {
6739  if (!IsValid)
6740  return true;
6741 
6742  // An FPGA AOCX input does not have a host dependence to the unbundler
6743  if (HostAction->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX)
6744  return false;
6745  recordHostAction(HostAction, InputArg);
6746 
6747  // If we are supporting bundling/unbundling and the current action is an
6748  // input action of non-source file, we replace the host action by the
6749  // unbundling action. The bundler tool has the logic to detect if an input
6750  // is a bundle or not and if the input is not a bundle it assumes it is a
6751  // host file. Therefore it is safe to create an unbundling action even if
6752  // the input is not a bundle.
6753  bool HasFPGATarget = false;
6754  if (CanUseBundler && isa<InputAction>(HostAction) &&
6755  InputArg->getOption().getKind() == llvm::opt::Option::InputClass &&
6756  !InputArg->getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput) &&
6757  (!types::isSrcFile(HostAction->getType()) ||
6758  HostAction->getType() == types::TY_PP_HIP)) {
6759  ActionList HostActionList;
6760  Action *A(HostAction);
6761  bool HasSPIRTarget = false;
6762  // Only check for FPGA device information when using fpga SubArch.
6763  auto SYCLTCRange = C.getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_SYCL>();
6764  for (auto TI = SYCLTCRange.first, TE = SYCLTCRange.second; TI != TE;
6765  ++TI) {
6766  HasFPGATarget |= TI->second->getTriple().getSubArch() ==
6767  llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga;
6768  HasSPIRTarget |= TI->second->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV();
6769  }
6770  bool isArchive = !(HostAction->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
6771  isObjectFile(InputArg->getAsString(Args)));
6772  if (!HasFPGATarget && isArchive &&
6773  HostAction->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCO)
6774  // Archive with Non-FPGA target with AOCO type should not be unbundled.
6775  return false;
6776  if (HasFPGATarget && !updateInputForFPGA(A, InputArg, Args))
6777  return false;
6778  // FIXME - unbundling action with -fsycl-link is unbundling for both host
6779  // and device, where only the device is needed.
6780  auto UnbundlingHostAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(
6781  A, (HasSPIRTarget && HostAction->getType() == types::TY_Archive)
6782  ? types::TY_Tempfilelist
6783  : A->getType());
6784  UnbundlingHostAction->registerDependentActionInfo(
6785  C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
6786  /*BoundArch=*/StringRef(), Action::OFK_Host);
6787  HostAction = UnbundlingHostAction;
6788  recordHostAction(HostAction, InputArg);
6789  }
6790 
6791  assert(HostAction && "Invalid host action!");
6792 
6793  // Register the offload kinds that are used.
6794  auto &OffloadKind = InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg];
6795  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6796  if (!SB->isValid())
6797  continue;
6798 
6799  auto RetCode = SB->addDeviceDependences(HostAction);
6800 
6801  // Host dependences for device actions are not compatible with that same
6802  // action being ignored.
6803  assert(RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Ignore_Host &&
6804  "Host dependence not expected to be ignored.!");
6805 
6806  // Unless the builder was inactive for this action, we have to record the
6807  // offload kind because the host will have to use it.
6808  if (RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Inactive)
6809  OffloadKind |= SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind();
6810  }
6811 
6812  // Do not use unbundler if the Host does not depend on device action.
6813  // Now that we have unbundled the object, when doing -fsycl-link we
6814  // want to continue the host link with the input object.
6815  // For unbundling of an FPGA AOCX binary, we want to link with the original
6816  // FPGA device archive.
6817  if ((OffloadKind == Action::OFK_None && CanUseBundler) ||
6818  (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ) && !HasFPGATarget) ||
6819  (HasFPGATarget && ((Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ) &&
6820  HostAction->getType() == types::TY_Object) ||
6821  HostAction->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX)))
6822  if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction))
6823  HostAction = UA->getInputs().back();
6824 
6825  return false;
6826  }
6827 
6828  /// Add the offloading top level actions that are specific for unique
6829  /// linking situations where objects are used at only the device link
6830  /// with no intermedate steps.
6831  bool appendTopLevelLinkAction(ActionList &AL) {
6832  // Get the device actions to be appended.
6833  ActionList OffloadAL;
6834  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6835  if (!SB->isValid())
6836  continue;
6837  SB->appendTopLevelLinkAction(OffloadAL);
6838  }
6839  // Append the device actions.
6840  AL.append(OffloadAL.begin(), OffloadAL.end());
6841  return false;
6842  }
6843 
6844  /// Add the offloading top level actions to the provided action list. This
6845  /// function can replace the host action by a bundling action if the
6846  /// programming models allow it.
6847  bool appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL, Action *HostAction,
6848  const Arg *InputArg) {
6849  if (HostAction)
6850  recordHostAction(HostAction, InputArg);
6851 
6852  // Get the device actions to be appended.
6853  ActionList OffloadAL;
6854  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6855  if (!SB->isValid())
6856  continue;
6857  SB->appendTopLevelActions(OffloadAL);
6858  }
6859 
6860  // If we can use the bundler, replace the host action by the bundling one in
6861  // the resulting list. Otherwise, just append the device actions. For
6862  // device only compilation, HostAction is a null pointer, therefore only do
6863  // this when HostAction is not a null pointer.
6864  if (CanUseBundler && HostAction &&
6865  HostAction->getType() != types::TY_Nothing && !OffloadAL.empty()) {
6866  // Add the host action to the list in order to create the bundling action.
6867  OffloadAL.push_back(HostAction);
6868 
6869  // We expect that the host action was just appended to the action list
6870  // before this method was called.
6871  assert(HostAction == AL.back() && "Host action not in the list??");
6872  HostAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(OffloadAL);
6873  recordHostAction(HostAction, InputArg);
6874  AL.back() = HostAction;
6875  } else
6876  AL.append(OffloadAL.begin(), OffloadAL.end());
6877 
6878  // Propagate to the current host action (if any) the offload information
6879  // associated with the current input.
6880  if (HostAction)
6881  HostAction->propagateHostOffloadInfo(InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg],
6882  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
6883  return false;
6884  }
6885 
6886  /// Create link job from the given host inputs and feed the result to offload
6887  /// deps job which fetches device dependencies from the linked host image.
6888  /// Offload deps output is then forwarded to active device action builders so
6889  /// they can add it to the device linker inputs.
6890  void addDeviceLinkDependenciesFromHost(ActionList &LinkerInputs) {
6891  // Link image for reading dependencies from it.
6892  auto *LA = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkerInputs,
6893  types::TY_Host_Dependencies_Image);
6894 
6895  // Calculate all the offload kinds used in the current compilation.
6896  unsigned ActiveOffloadKinds = 0u;
6897  for (auto &I : InputArgToOffloadKindMap)
6898  ActiveOffloadKinds |= I.second;
6899 
6900  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
6901  *LA, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
6902  /*BoundArch*/ nullptr, ActiveOffloadKinds);
6903 
6904  auto *DA = C.MakeAction<OffloadDepsJobAction>(HDep, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
6905 
6906  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6907  if (!SB->isValid())
6908  continue;
6909  SB->addDeviceLinkDependencies(DA);
6910  }
6911  }
6912 
6913  void appendDeviceLinkActions(ActionList &AL) {
6914  for (DeviceActionBuilder *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6915  if (!SB->isValid())
6916  continue;
6917  SB->appendLinkDeviceActions(AL);
6918  }
6919  }
6920 
6921  void makeHostLinkDeviceOnlyAction(ActionList &Inputs) {
6922  // Build a list of device linking actions.
6923  ActionList DeviceAL;
6924  appendDeviceLinkActions(DeviceAL);
6925  if (DeviceAL.empty())
6926  return;
6927 
6928  // Let builders add host linking actions.
6929  Action *HA = nullptr;
6930  for (DeviceActionBuilder *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6931  if (!SB->isValid())
6932  continue;
6933  HA = SB->appendLinkHostActions(DeviceAL);
6934  if (!HA)
6935  continue;
6936  // This created host action has no originating input argument, therefore
6937  // needs to set its offloading kind directly.
6938  HA->propagateHostOffloadInfo(SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind(),
6939  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
6940  Inputs.push_back(HA);
6941  }
6942  }
6943 
6944  void makeHostLinkAction(ActionList &LinkerInputs) {
6945 
6946  bool IsCUinSYCL = false;
6947  for (auto &I : InputArgToOffloadKindMap) {
6948  if (I.second == (Action::OFK_Cuda | Action::OFK_SYCL)) {
6949  IsCUinSYCL = true;
6950  }
6951  }
6952 
6953  // Add offload action for the SYCL compilation of .cu files
6954  if (IsCUinSYCL) {
6955  for (size_t i = 0; i < LinkerInputs.size(); ++i) {
6956  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
6957  *LinkerInputs[i], *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
6958  nullptr,
6959  InputArgToOffloadKindMap[HostActionToInputArgMap[LinkerInputs[i]]]);
6960  LinkerInputs[i] = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep);
6961  }
6962  }
6963 
6964  // Build a list of device linking actions.
6965  ActionList DeviceAL;
6966  appendDeviceLinkActions(DeviceAL);
6967  if (DeviceAL.empty())
6968  return;
6969 
6970  // Let builders add host linking actions.
6971  Action* HA = nullptr;
6972  for (DeviceActionBuilder *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
6973  if (!SB->isValid())
6974  continue;
6975  HA = SB->appendLinkHostActions(DeviceAL);
6976  // This created host action has no originating input argument, therefore
6977  // needs to set its offloading kind directly.
6978  if (HA) {
6979  HA->propagateHostOffloadInfo(SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind(),
6980  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
6981  LinkerInputs.push_back(HA);
6982  } else {
6983  // Nothing appended to create a singular input, so add each device
6984  // individually to the inputs.
6985  for (auto &DeviceAction : DeviceAL) {
6986  DeviceAction->propagateHostOffloadInfo(SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind(),
6987  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
6988  LinkerInputs.push_back(DeviceAction);
6989  }
6990  }
6991  }
6992  }
6993 
6994  /// Processes the host linker action. This currently consists of replacing it
6995  /// with an offload action if there are device link objects and propagate to
6996  /// the host action all the offload kinds used in the current compilation. The
6997  /// resulting action is returned.
6998  Action *processHostLinkAction(Action *HostAction) {
6999  // Add all the dependences from the device linking actions.
7000  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
7001  for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
7002  if (!SB->isValid())
7003  continue;
7004 
7005  SB->appendLinkDependences(DDeps);
7006  }
7007 
7008  // Calculate all the offload kinds used in the current compilation.
7009  unsigned ActiveOffloadKinds = 0u;
7010  for (auto &I : InputArgToOffloadKindMap)
7011  ActiveOffloadKinds |= I.second;
7012 
7013  // If we don't have device dependencies, we don't have to create an offload
7014  // action.
7015  if (DDeps.getActions().empty()) {
7016  // Set all the active offloading kinds to the link action. Given that it
7017  // is a link action it is assumed to depend on all actions generated so
7018  // far.
7019  HostAction->setHostOffloadInfo(ActiveOffloadKinds,
7020  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
7021  // Propagate active offloading kinds for each input to the link action.
7022  // Each input may have different active offloading kind.
7023  for (auto *A : HostAction->inputs()) {
7024  auto ArgLoc = HostActionToInputArgMap.find(A);
7025  if (ArgLoc == HostActionToInputArgMap.end())
7026  continue;
7027  auto OFKLoc = InputArgToOffloadKindMap.find(ArgLoc->second);
7028  if (OFKLoc == InputArgToOffloadKindMap.end())
7029  continue;
7030  A->propagateHostOffloadInfo(OFKLoc->second, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
7031  }
7032  return HostAction;
7033  }
7034 
7035  // Create the offload action with all dependences. When an offload action
7036  // is created the kinds are propagated to the host action, so we don't have
7037  // to do that explicitly here.
7038  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
7039  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
7040  /*BoundArch*/ nullptr, ActiveOffloadKinds);
7041  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDeps);
7042  }
7043 
7044  void unbundleStaticArchives(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args) {
7045  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false))
7046  return;
7047 
7048  // Go through all of the args, and create a Linker specific argument list.
7049  // When dealing with fat static archives each archive is individually
7050  // unbundled.
7051  SmallVector<const char *, 16> LinkArgs(getLinkerArgs(C, Args));
7052  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = C.getDriver().getOpts();
7053  auto unbundleStaticLib = [&](types::ID T, const StringRef &A) {
7054  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, Opts, Args.MakeArgString(A));
7055  Action *Current = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, T);
7056  addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Current, InputArg, Args);
7057  auto PL = types::getCompilationPhases(T);
7058  addDeviceDependencesToHostAction(Current, InputArg, phases::Link,
7059  PL.back(), PL);
7060  };
7061  for (StringRef LA : LinkArgs) {
7062  // At this point, we will process the archives for FPGA AOCO and
7063  // individual archive unbundling for Windows.
7064  if (!isStaticArchiveFile(LA))
7065  continue;
7066  // FPGA AOCX/AOCR files are archives, but we do not want to unbundle them
7067  // here as they have already been unbundled and processed for linking.
7068  // TODO: The multiple binary checks for FPGA types getting a little out
7069  // of hand. Improve this by doing a single scan of the args and holding
7070  // that in a data structure for reference.
7071  if (hasFPGABinary(C, LA.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCX) ||
7072  hasFPGABinary(C, LA.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCR) ||
7073  hasFPGABinary(C, LA.str(), types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU))
7074  continue;
7075  // For offload-static-libs we add an unbundling action for each static
7076  // archive which produces list files with extracted objects. Device lists
7077  // are then added to the appropriate device link actions and host list is
7078  // ignored since we are adding offload-static-libs as normal libraries to
7079  // the host link command.
7080  if (hasOffloadSections(C, LA, Args)) {
7081  // Pass along the static libraries to check if we need to add them for
7082  // unbundling for FPGA AOT static lib usage. Uses FPGA aoco type to
7083  // differentiate if aoco unbundling is needed. Unbundling of aoco is
7084  // not needed for emulation, as these are treated as regular archives.
7085  if (C.getDriver().IsFPGAHWMode())
7086  unbundleStaticLib(types::TY_FPGA_AOCO, LA);
7087  unbundleStaticLib(types::TY_Archive, LA);
7088  }
7089  }
7090  }
7091 };
7092 } // anonymous namespace.
7093 
7094 void Driver::handleArguments(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
7095  const InputList &Inputs,
7096  ActionList &Actions) const {
7097 
7098  // Ignore /Yc/Yu if both /Yc and /Yu passed but with different filenames.
7099  Arg *YcArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
7100  Arg *YuArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
7101  if (YcArg && YuArg && strcmp(YcArg->getValue(), YuArg->getValue()) != 0) {
7102  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_ycyu_different_arg_clang_cl);
7103  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
7104  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
7105  YcArg = YuArg = nullptr;
7106  }
7107  if (YcArg && Inputs.size() > 1) {
7108  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_yc_multiple_inputs_clang_cl);
7109  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
7110  YcArg = nullptr;
7111  }
7112 
7113  Arg *FinalPhaseArg;
7114  phases::ID FinalPhase = getFinalPhase(Args, &FinalPhaseArg);
7115 
7116  if (FinalPhase == phases::Link) {
7117  if (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_hipstdpar)) {
7118  Args.AddFlagArg(nullptr, getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_hip_link));
7119  Args.AddFlagArg(nullptr,
7120  getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_frtlib_add_rpath));
7121  }
7122  // Emitting LLVM while linking disabled except in HIPAMD Toolchain
7123  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm) && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_hip_link))
7124  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_emit_llvm_link);
7125  if (IsCLMode() && LTOMode != LTOK_None &&
7126  !Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fuse_ld_EQ)
7127  .equals_insensitive("lld"))
7128  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_lto_without_lld);
7129 
7130  // If -dumpdir is not specified, give a default prefix derived from the link
7131  // output filename. For example, `clang -g -gsplit-dwarf a.c -o x` passes
7132  // `-dumpdir x-` to cc1. If -o is unspecified, use
7133  // stem(getDefaultImageName()) (usually stem("a.out") = "a").
7134  if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_dumpdir)) {
7135  Arg *FinalOutput = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_o, options::OPT__SLASH_o);
7136  Arg *Arg = Args.MakeSeparateArg(
7137  nullptr, getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_dumpdir),
7138  Args.MakeArgString(
7139  (FinalOutput ? FinalOutput->getValue()
7140  : llvm::sys::path::stem(getDefaultImageName())) +
7141  "-"));
7142  Arg->claim();
7143  Args.append(Arg);
7144  }
7145  }
7146 
7147  if (FinalPhase == phases::Preprocess || Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Y_)) {
7148  // If only preprocessing or /Y- is used, all pch handling is disabled.
7149  // Rather than check for it everywhere, just remove clang-cl pch-related
7150  // flags here.
7151  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fp);
7152  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
7153  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
7154  YcArg = YuArg = nullptr;
7155  }
7156 
7157  unsigned LastPLSize = 0;
7158  for (auto &I : Inputs) {
7159  types::ID InputType = I.first;
7160  const Arg *InputArg = I.second;
7161 
7162  auto PL = types::getCompilationPhases(InputType);
7163  LastPLSize = PL.size();
7164 
7165  // If the first step comes after the final phase we are doing as part of
7166  // this compilation, warn the user about it.
7167  phases::ID InitialPhase = PL[0];
7168  if (InitialPhase > FinalPhase) {
7169  if (InputArg->isClaimed())
7170  continue;
7171 
7172  // Claim here to avoid the more general unused warning.
7173  InputArg->claim();
7174 
7175  // Suppress all unused style warnings with -Qunused-arguments
7176  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_Qunused_arguments))
7177  continue;
7178 
7179  // Special case when final phase determined by binary name, rather than
7180  // by a command-line argument with a corresponding Arg.
7181  if (CCCIsCPP())
7182  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_input_file_unused_by_cpp)
7183  << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << getPhaseName(InitialPhase);
7184  // Special case '-E' warning on a previously preprocessed file to make
7185  // more sense.
7186  else if (InitialPhase == phases::Compile &&
7187  (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP,
7188  options::OPT__SLASH_P) ||
7189  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_E) ||
7190  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM)) &&
7191  getPreprocessedType(InputType) == types::TY_INVALID)
7192  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_preprocessed_input_file_unused)
7193  << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << !!FinalPhaseArg
7194  << (FinalPhaseArg ? FinalPhaseArg->getOption().getName() : "");
7195  else
7196  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_input_file_unused)
7197  << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << getPhaseName(InitialPhase)
7198  << !!FinalPhaseArg
7199  << (FinalPhaseArg ? FinalPhaseArg->getOption().getName() : "");
7200  continue;
7201  }
7202 
7203  if (YcArg) {
7204  // Add a separate precompile phase for the compile phase.
7205  if (FinalPhase >= phases::Compile) {
7206  const types::ID HeaderType = lookupHeaderTypeForSourceType(InputType);
7207  // Build the pipeline for the pch file.
7208  Action *ClangClPch = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, HeaderType);
7209  for (phases::ID Phase : types::getCompilationPhases(HeaderType))
7210  ClangClPch = ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, Phase, ClangClPch);
7211  assert(ClangClPch);
7212  Actions.push_back(ClangClPch);
7213  // The driver currently exits after the first failed command. This
7214  // relies on that behavior, to make sure if the pch generation fails,
7215  // the main compilation won't run.
7216  // FIXME: If the main compilation fails, the PCH generation should
7217  // probably not be considered successful either.
7218  }
7219  }
7220  }
7221 
7222  // If we are linking, claim any options which are obviously only used for
7223  // compilation.
7224  // FIXME: Understand why the last Phase List length is used here.
7225  if (FinalPhase == phases::Link && LastPLSize == 1) {
7226  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_CompileOnly_Group);
7227  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cl_compile_Group);
7228  }
7229 }
7230 
7231 void Driver::BuildActions(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
7232  const InputList &Inputs, ActionList &Actions) const {
7233  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation actions");
7234 
7235  if (!SuppressMissingInputWarning && Inputs.empty()) {
7236  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_input_files);
7237  return;
7238  }
7239 
7240  // Diagnose misuse of /Fo.
7241  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo)) {
7242  StringRef V = A->getValue();
7243  if (Inputs.size() > 1 && !V.empty() &&
7244  !llvm::sys::path::is_separator(V.back())) {
7245  // Check whether /Fo tries to name an output file for multiple inputs.
7246  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_out_file_argument_with_multiple_sources)
7247  << A->getSpelling() << V;
7248  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo);
7249  }
7250  }
7251 
7252  // Diagnose misuse of /Fa.
7253  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa)) {
7254  StringRef V = A->getValue();
7255  if (Inputs.size() > 1 && !V.empty() &&
7256  !llvm::sys::path::is_separator(V.back())) {
7257  // Check whether /Fa tries to name an asm file for multiple inputs.
7258  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_out_file_argument_with_multiple_sources)
7259  << A->getSpelling() << V;
7260  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa);
7261  }
7262  }
7263 
7264  // Diagnose misuse of /o.
7265  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
7266  if (A->getValue()[0] == '\0') {
7267  // It has to have a value.
7268  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_missing_argument) << A->getSpelling() << 1;
7269  Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o);
7270  }
7271  }
7272 
7273  handleArguments(C, Args, Inputs, Actions);
7274 
7275  // If '-fintelfpga' is passed, add '-fsycl' to the list of arguments
7276  const llvm::opt::OptTable &Opts = getOpts();
7277  Arg *SYCLFpgaArg = C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga);
7278  if (SYCLFpgaArg &&
7279  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false))
7280  Args.AddFlagArg(0, Opts.getOption(options::OPT_fsycl));
7281 
7282  // When compiling for -fsycl, generate the integration header files and the
7283  // Unique ID that will be used during the compilation.
7284  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false)) {
7285  const bool IsSaveTemps = isSaveTempsEnabled();
7286  SmallString<128> OutFileDir;
7287  if (IsSaveTemps) {
7288  if (SaveTemps == SaveTempsObj) {
7289  auto *OptO = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
7290  OutFileDir = (OptO ? OptO->getValues()[0] : "");
7291  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(OutFileDir);
7292  if (!OutFileDir.empty())
7293  OutFileDir.append(llvm::sys::path::get_separator());
7294  }
7295  }
7296  for (auto &I : Inputs) {
7297  std::string SrcFileName(I.second->getAsString(Args));
7298  if ((I.first == types::TY_PP_C || I.first == types::TY_PP_CXX ||
7299  types::isSrcFile(I.first))) {
7300  // Unique ID is generated for source files and preprocessed files.
7301  SmallString<128> ResultID;
7302  llvm::sys::fs::createUniquePath("uid%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%", ResultID, false);
7303  addSYCLUniqueID(Args.MakeArgString(ResultID.str()), SrcFileName);
7304  }
7305  if (!types::isSrcFile(I.first))
7306  continue;
7307 
7308  std::string TmpFileNameHeader;
7309  std::string TmpFileNameFooter;
7310  auto StemmedSrcFileName = llvm::sys::path::stem(SrcFileName).str();
7311  if (IsSaveTemps) {
7312  TmpFileNameHeader.append(C.getDriver().GetUniquePath(
7313  OutFileDir.c_str() + StemmedSrcFileName + "-header", "h"));
7314  TmpFileNameFooter.append(C.getDriver().GetUniquePath(
7315  OutFileDir.c_str() + StemmedSrcFileName + "-footer", "h"));
7316  } else {
7317  TmpFileNameHeader.assign(C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath(
7318  StemmedSrcFileName + "-header", "h"));
7319  TmpFileNameFooter =
7320  C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath(StemmedSrcFileName + "-footer", "h");
7321  }
7322  StringRef TmpFileHeader =
7323  C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpFileNameHeader));
7324  StringRef TmpFileFooter =
7325  C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpFileNameFooter));
7326  // Use of -fsycl-footer-path puts the integration footer into that
7327  // specified location.
7328  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_footer_path_EQ)) {
7329  SmallString<128> OutName(A->getValue());
7330  llvm::sys::path::append(OutName,
7331  llvm::sys::path::filename(TmpFileNameFooter));
7332  TmpFileFooter = C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(OutName));
7333  }
7334  addIntegrationFiles(TmpFileHeader, TmpFileFooter, SrcFileName);
7335  }
7336  }
7337 
7338  bool UseNewOffloadingDriver =
7339  C.isOffloadingHostKind(Action::OFK_OpenMP) ||
7340  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_offload_new_driver,
7341  options::OPT_no_offload_new_driver, false);
7342 
7343  // Builder to be used to build offloading actions.
7344  std::unique_ptr<OffloadingActionBuilder> OffloadBuilder =
7345  !UseNewOffloadingDriver
7346  ? std::make_unique<OffloadingActionBuilder>(C, Args, Inputs)
7347  : nullptr;
7348 
7349  // Construct the actions to perform.
7350  ExtractAPIJobAction *ExtractAPIAction = nullptr;
7351  ActionList LinkerInputs;
7352  ActionList MergerInputs;
7353  ActionList HostActions;
7354  llvm::SmallVector<const Arg *, 6> LinkerInputArgs;
7355  llvm::SmallVector<phases::ID, phases::MaxNumberOfPhases> PL;
7356 
7357  for (auto &I : Inputs) {
7358  types::ID InputType = I.first;
7359  const Arg *InputArg = I.second;
7360 
7361  PL = types::getCompilationPhases(*this, Args, InputType);
7362  if (PL.empty())
7363  continue;
7364 
7365  auto FullPL = types::getCompilationPhases(InputType);
7366 
7367  // Build the pipeline for this file.
7368  Action *Current = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, InputType);
7369 
7370  // Use the current host action in any of the offloading actions, if
7371  // required.
7372  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7373  if (OffloadBuilder->addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Current, InputArg, Args))
7374  break;
7375 
7376  for (phases::ID Phase : PL) {
7377 
7378  // Add any offload action the host action depends on.
7379  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7380  Current = OffloadBuilder->addDeviceDependencesToHostAction(
7381  Current, InputArg, Phase, PL.back(), FullPL);
7382  if (!Current)
7383  break;
7384 
7385  // Queue linker inputs.
7386  if (Phase == phases::Link) {
7387  assert(Phase == PL.back() && "linking must be final compilation step.");
7388 
7389  // We don't need to generate additional link commands if emitting AMD
7390  // bitcode or compiling only for the offload device
7391  if (!(C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_hip_link) &&
7392  (C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm))) &&
7393  !offloadDeviceOnly())
7394  LinkerInputs.push_back(Current);
7395  Current = nullptr;
7396  break;
7397  }
7398 
7399  // TODO: Consider removing this because the merged may not end up being
7400  // the final Phase in the pipeline. Perhaps the merged could just merge
7401  // and then pass an artifact of some sort to the Link Phase.
7402  // Queue merger inputs.
7403  if (Phase == phases::IfsMerge) {
7404  assert(Phase == PL.back() && "merging must be final compilation step.");
7405  MergerInputs.push_back(Current);
7406  Current = nullptr;
7407  break;
7408  }
7409 
7410  if (Phase == phases::Precompile && ExtractAPIAction) {
7411  ExtractAPIAction->addHeaderInput(Current);
7412  Current = nullptr;
7413  break;
7414  }
7415 
7416  // FIXME: Should we include any prior module file outputs as inputs of
7417  // later actions in the same command line?
7418 
7419  // Otherwise construct the appropriate action.
7420  Action *NewCurrent = ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, Phase, Current);
7421 
7422  // We didn't create a new action, so we will just move to the next phase.
7423  if (NewCurrent == Current)
7424  continue;
7425 
7426  if (auto *EAA = dyn_cast<ExtractAPIJobAction>(NewCurrent))
7427  ExtractAPIAction = EAA;
7428 
7429  Current = NewCurrent;
7430 
7431  // Try to build the offloading actions and add the result as a dependency
7432  // to the host.
7433  if (UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7434  Current = BuildOffloadingActions(C, Args, I, Current);
7435  // Use the current host action in any of the offloading actions, if
7436  // required.
7437  else if (OffloadBuilder->addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Current,
7438  InputArg,
7439  Args))
7440  break;
7441 
7442  if (Current->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
7443  break;
7444  }
7445 
7446  // If we ended with something, add to the output list.
7447  if (Current)
7448  Actions.push_back(Current);
7449 
7450  // Add any top level actions generated for offloading.
7451  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7452  OffloadBuilder->appendTopLevelActions(Actions, Current, InputArg);
7453  else if (Current)
7454  Current->propagateHostOffloadInfo(C.getActiveOffloadKinds(),
7455  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
7456  }
7457 
7458  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver) {
7459  OffloadBuilder->appendTopLevelLinkAction(Actions);
7460 
7461  // With static fat archives we need to create additional steps for
7462  // generating dependence objects for device link actions.
7463  if (!LinkerInputs.empty() && C.getDriver().getOffloadStaticLibSeen())
7464  OffloadBuilder->addDeviceLinkDependenciesFromHost(LinkerInputs);
7465 
7466  OffloadBuilder->unbundleStaticArchives(C, Args);
7467  }
7468 
7469  // For an FPGA archive, we add the unbundling step above to take care of
7470  // the device side, but also unbundle here to extract the host side
7471  bool EarlyLink = false;
7472  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ))
7473  EarlyLink = A->getValue() == StringRef("early");
7474  for (auto &LI : LinkerInputs) {
7475  Action *UnbundlerInput = nullptr;
7476  auto wrapObject = [&] {
7477  if (EarlyLink && Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga)) {
7478  // Only wrap the object with -fsycl-link=early
7479  auto *BC = C.MakeAction<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(LI, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
7480  auto *ASM = C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(BC, types::TY_PP_Asm);
7481  auto *OBJ = C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(ASM, types::TY_Object);
7482  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
7483  *OBJ, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
7484  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_SYCL);
7485  LI = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep);
7486  }
7487  };
7488  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(LI)) {
7489  if (IA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR ||
7490  IA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX ||
7491  IA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU) {
7492  // Add to unbundler.
7493  UnbundlerInput = LI;
7494  } else {
7495  std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
7496  if ((IA->getType() == types::TY_Object && !isObjectFile(FileName)) ||
7497  IA->getInputArg().getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput))
7498  continue;
7499  wrapObject();
7500  }
7501  } else
7502  wrapObject();
7503  if (UnbundlerInput && !PL.empty()) {
7504  if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(UnbundlerInput)) {
7505  std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
7506  Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, getOpts(), FileName);
7507  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7508  OffloadBuilder->addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(UnbundlerInput,
7509  InputArg, Args);
7510  }
7511  }
7512  }
7513 
7514  // Add a link action if necessary.
7515  // When offloading with -fsycl-link-targets, no link action is processed
7516  // as we stop at the spirv-translation step.
7517  Arg *FinalPhaseArg;
7518  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver &&
7519  getFinalPhase(Args, &FinalPhaseArg) == phases::Link &&
7520  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_targets_EQ)) {
7521  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ) &&
7522  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fintelfpga)) {
7523  ActionList LAList;
7524  OffloadBuilder->makeHostLinkDeviceOnlyAction(LAList);
7525  if (!LAList.empty()) {
7526  Action *LA = LAList.front();
7527  LA = OffloadBuilder->processHostLinkAction(LA);
7528  Actions.push_back(LA);
7529  }
7530  } else if (LinkerInputs.empty())
7531  OffloadBuilder->appendDeviceLinkActions(Actions);
7532  }
7533 
7534  if (!LinkerInputs.empty()) {
7535  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7536  OffloadBuilder->makeHostLinkAction(LinkerInputs);
7537  types::ID LinkType(types::TY_Image);
7538  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ))
7539  LinkType = types::TY_Archive;
7540  Action *LA;
7541  // Check if this Linker Job should emit a static library.
7542  if (ShouldEmitStaticLibrary(Args)) {
7543  LA = C.MakeAction<StaticLibJobAction>(LinkerInputs, LinkType);
7544  } else if (UseNewOffloadingDriver ||
7545  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_offload_link)) {
7546  LA = C.MakeAction<LinkerWrapperJobAction>(LinkerInputs, types::TY_Image);
7547  LA->propagateHostOffloadInfo(C.getActiveOffloadKinds(),
7548  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
7549  } else {
7550  LA = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkerInputs, LinkType);
7551  }
7552  if (!UseNewOffloadingDriver)
7553  LA = OffloadBuilder->processHostLinkAction(LA);
7554  Actions.push_back(LA);
7555  }
7556 
7557  // Add an interface stubs merge action if necessary.
7558  if (!MergerInputs.empty())
7559  Actions.push_back(
7560  C.MakeAction<IfsMergeJobAction>(MergerInputs, types::TY_Image));
7561 
7562  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_interface_stubs)) {
7563  auto PhaseList = types::getCompilationPhases(
7564  types::TY_IFS_CPP,
7565  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_c) ? phases::Compile : phases::IfsMerge);
7566 
7567  ActionList MergerInputs;
7568 
7569  for (auto &I : Inputs) {
7570  types::ID InputType = I.first;
7571  const Arg *InputArg = I.second;
7572 
7573  // Currently clang and the llvm assembler do not support generating symbol
7574  // stubs from assembly, so we skip the input on asm files. For ifs files
7575  // we rely on the normal pipeline setup in the pipeline setup code above.
7576  if (InputType == types::TY_IFS || InputType == types::TY_PP_Asm ||
7577  InputType == types::TY_Asm)
7578  continue;
7579 
7580  Action *Current = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, InputType);
7581 
7582  for (auto Phase : PhaseList) {
7583  switch (Phase) {
7584  default:
7585  llvm_unreachable(
7586  "IFS Pipeline can only consist of Compile followed by IfsMerge.");
7587  case phases::Compile: {
7588  // Only IfsMerge (llvm-ifs) can handle .o files by looking for ifs
7589  // files where the .o file is located. The compile action can not
7590  // handle this.
7591  if (InputType == types::TY_Object)
7592  break;
7593 
7594  Current = C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Current, types::TY_IFS_CPP);
7595  break;
7596  }
7597  case phases::IfsMerge: {
7598  assert(Phase == PhaseList.back() &&
7599  "merging must be final compilation step.");
7600  MergerInputs.push_back(Current);
7601  Current = nullptr;
7602  break;
7603  }
7604  }
7605  }
7606 
7607  // If we ended with something, add to the output list.
7608  if (Current)
7609  Actions.push_back(Current);
7610  }
7611 
7612  // Add an interface stubs merge action if necessary.
7613  if (!MergerInputs.empty())
7614  Actions.push_back(
7615  C.MakeAction<IfsMergeJobAction>(MergerInputs, types::TY_Image));
7616  }
7617 
7618  for (auto Opt : {options::OPT_print_supported_cpus,
7619  options::OPT_print_supported_extensions}) {
7620  // If --print-supported-cpus, -mcpu=? or -mtune=? is specified, build a
7621  // custom Compile phase that prints out supported cpu models and quits.
7622  //
7623  // If --print-supported-extensions is specified, call the helper function
7624  // RISCVMarchHelp in RISCVISAInfo.cpp that prints out supported extensions
7625  // and quits.
7626  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(Opt)) {
7627  if (Opt == options::OPT_print_supported_extensions &&
7628  !C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isRISCV() &&
7629  !C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isAArch64() &&
7630  !C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isARM()) {
7631  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_opt_not_valid_on_target)
7632  << "--print-supported-extensions";
7633  return;
7634  }
7635 
7636  // Use the -mcpu=? flag as the dummy input to cc1.
7637  Actions.clear();
7638  Action *InputAc = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*A, types::TY_C);
7639  Actions.push_back(
7640  C.MakeAction<PrecompileJobAction>(InputAc, types::TY_Nothing));
7641  for (auto &I : Inputs)
7642  I.second->claim();
7643  }
7644  }
7645 
7646  // Call validator for dxil when -Vd not in Args.
7647  if (C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isDXIL()) {
7648  // Only add action when needValidation.
7649  const auto &TC =
7650  static_cast<const toolchains::HLSLToolChain &>(C.getDefaultToolChain());
7651  if (TC.requiresValidation(Args)) {
7652  Action *LastAction = Actions.back();
7653  Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<BinaryAnalyzeJobAction>(
7654  LastAction, types::TY_DX_CONTAINER));
7655  }
7656  }
7657 
7658  // Claim ignored clang-cl options.
7659  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cl_ignored_Group);
7660 }
7661 
7662 /// Returns the canonical name for the offloading architecture when using a HIP
7663 /// or CUDA architecture.
7664 static StringRef getCanonicalArchString(Compilation &C,
7665  const llvm::opt::DerivedArgList &Args,
7666  StringRef ArchStr,
7667  const llvm::Triple &Triple,
7668  bool SuppressError = false) {
7669  // Lookup the CUDA / HIP architecture string. Only report an error if we were
7670  // expecting the triple to be only NVPTX / AMDGPU.
7671  CudaArch Arch = StringToCudaArch(getProcessorFromTargetID(Triple, ArchStr));
7672  if (!SuppressError && Triple.isNVPTX() &&
7673  (Arch == CudaArch::UNKNOWN || !IsNVIDIAGpuArch(Arch))) {
7674  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_offload_bad_gpu_arch)
7675  << "CUDA" << ArchStr;
7676  return StringRef();
7677  } else if (!SuppressError && Triple.isAMDGPU() &&
7678  (Arch == CudaArch::UNKNOWN || !IsAMDGpuArch(Arch))) {
7679  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_offload_bad_gpu_arch)
7680  << "HIP" << ArchStr;
7681  return StringRef();
7682  }
7683 
7684  if (IsNVIDIAGpuArch(Arch))
7685  return Args.MakeArgStringRef(CudaArchToString(Arch));
7686 
7687  if (IsAMDGpuArch(Arch)) {
7688  llvm::StringMap<bool> Features;
7689  auto HIPTriple = getHIPOffloadTargetTriple(C.getDriver(), C.getInputArgs());
7690  if (!HIPTriple)
7691  return StringRef();
7692  auto Arch = parseTargetID(*HIPTriple, ArchStr, &Features);
7693  if (!Arch) {
7694  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_bad_target_id) << ArchStr;
7695  C.setContainsError();
7696  return StringRef();
7697  }
7698  return Args.MakeArgStringRef(getCanonicalTargetID(*Arch, Features));
7699  }
7700 
7701  // If the input isn't CUDA or HIP just return the architecture.
7702  return ArchStr;
7703 }
7704 
7705 /// Checks if the set offloading architectures does not conflict. Returns the
7706 /// incompatible pair if a conflict occurs.
7707 static std::optional<std::pair<llvm::StringRef, llvm::StringRef>>
7708 getConflictOffloadArchCombination(const llvm::DenseSet<StringRef> &Archs,
7709  llvm::Triple Triple) {
7710  if (!Triple.isAMDGPU())
7711  return std::nullopt;
7712 
7713  std::set<StringRef> ArchSet;
7714  llvm::copy(Archs, std::inserter(ArchSet, ArchSet.begin()));
7715  return getConflictTargetIDCombination(ArchSet);
7716 }
7717 
7718 llvm::DenseSet<StringRef>
7719 Driver::getOffloadArchs(Compilation &C, const llvm::opt::DerivedArgList &Args,
7720  Action::OffloadKind Kind, const ToolChain *TC,
7721  bool SuppressError) const {
7722  if (!TC)
7723  TC = &C.getDefaultToolChain();
7724 
7725  // --offload and --offload-arch options are mutually exclusive.
7726  if (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_offload_EQ) &&
7727  Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ,
7728  options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ)) {
7729  C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_opt_not_valid_with_opt)
7730  << "--offload"
7731  << (Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ)
7732  ? "--offload-arch"
7733  : "--no-offload-arch");
7734  }
7735 
7736  if (KnownArchs.contains(TC))
7737  return KnownArchs.lookup(TC);
7738 
7739  llvm::DenseSet<StringRef> Archs;
7740  for (auto *Arg : Args) {
7741  // Extract any '--[no-]offload-arch' arguments intended for this toolchain.
7742  std::unique_ptr<llvm::opt::Arg> ExtractedArg = nullptr;
7743  if (Arg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xopenmp_target_EQ) &&
7744  ToolChain::getOpenMPTriple(Arg->getValue(0)) == TC->getTriple()) {
7745  Arg->claim();
7746  unsigned Index = Args.getBaseArgs().MakeIndex(Arg->getValue(1));
7747  ExtractedArg = getOpts().ParseOneArg(Args, Index);
7748  Arg = ExtractedArg.get();
7749  }
7750 
7751  // Add or remove the seen architectures in order of appearance. If an
7752  // invalid architecture is given we simply exit.
7753  if (Arg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ)) {
7754  for (StringRef Arch : llvm::split(Arg->getValue(), ",")) {
7755  if (Arch == "native" || Arch.empty()) {
7756  auto GPUsOrErr = TC->getSystemGPUArchs(Args);
7757  if (!GPUsOrErr) {
7758  if (SuppressError)
7759  llvm::consumeError(GPUsOrErr.takeError());
7760  else
7761  TC->getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_undetermined_gpu_arch)
7762  << llvm::Triple::getArchTypeName(TC->getArch())
7763  << llvm::toString(GPUsOrErr.takeError()) << "--offload-arch";
7764  continue;
7765  }
7766 
7767  for (auto ArchStr : *GPUsOrErr) {
7768  Archs.insert(
7769  getCanonicalArchString(C, Args, Args.MakeArgString(ArchStr),
7770  TC->getTriple(), SuppressError));
7771  }
7772  } else {
7773  StringRef ArchStr = getCanonicalArchString(
7774  C, Args, Arch, TC->getTriple(), SuppressError);
7775  if (ArchStr.empty())
7776  return Archs;
7777  Archs.insert(ArchStr);
7778  }
7779  }
7780  } else if (Arg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ)) {
7781  for (StringRef Arch : llvm::split(Arg->getValue(), ",")) {
7782  if (Arch == "all") {
7783  Archs.clear();
7784  } else {
7785  StringRef ArchStr = getCanonicalArchString(
7786  C, Args, Arch, TC->getTriple(), SuppressError);
7787  if (ArchStr.empty())
7788  return Archs;
7789  Archs.erase(ArchStr);
7790  }
7791  }
7792  }
7793  }
7794 
7795  if (auto ConflictingArchs =
7796  getConflictOffloadArchCombination(Archs, TC->getTriple())) {
7797  C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_bad_offload_arch_combo)
7798  << ConflictingArchs->first << ConflictingArchs->second;
7799  C.setContainsError();
7800  }
7801 
7802  // Skip filling defaults if we're just querying what is availible.
7803  if (SuppressError)
7804  return Archs;
7805 
7806  if (Archs.empty()) {
7807  if (Kind == Action::OFK_Cuda)
7808  Archs.insert(CudaArchToString(CudaArch::CudaDefault));
7809  else if (Kind == Action::OFK_HIP)
7810  Archs.insert(CudaArchToString(CudaArch::HIPDefault));
7811  else if (Kind == Action::OFK_OpenMP)
7812  Archs.insert(StringRef());
7813  else if (Kind == Action::OFK_SYCL)
7814  Archs.insert(StringRef());
7815  } else {
7816  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_offload_arch_EQ);
7817  Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_no_offload_arch_EQ);
7818  }
7819 
7820  return Archs;
7821 }
7822 
7823 Action *Driver::BuildOffloadingActions(Compilation &C,
7824  llvm::opt::DerivedArgList &Args,
7825  const InputTy &Input,
7826  Action *HostAction) const {
7827  // Don't build offloading actions if explicitly disabled or we do not have a
7828  // valid source input and compile action to embed it in. If preprocessing only
7829  // ignore embedding.
7830  if (offloadHostOnly() || !types::isSrcFile(Input.first) ||
7831  !(isa<CompileJobAction>(HostAction) ||
7832  getFinalPhase(Args) == phases::Preprocess))
7833  return HostAction;
7834 
7835  ActionList OffloadActions;
7836  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
7837 
7838  const Action::OffloadKind OffloadKinds[] = {
7839  Action::OFK_OpenMP, Action::OFK_Cuda, Action::OFK_HIP, Action::OFK_SYCL};
7840 
7841  for (Action::OffloadKind Kind : OffloadKinds) {
7842  SmallVector<const ToolChain *, 2> ToolChains;
7843  ActionList DeviceActions;
7844 
7845  auto TCRange = C.getOffloadToolChains(Kind);
