7846  for (auto TI = TCRange.first, TE = TCRange.second; TI != TE; ++TI)
7847  ToolChains.push_back(TI->second);
7848 
7849  if (ToolChains.empty())
7850  continue;
7851 
7852  types::ID InputType = Input.first;
7853  const Arg *InputArg = Input.second;
7854 
7855  // The toolchain can be active for unsupported file types.
7856  if ((Kind == Action::OFK_Cuda && !types::isCuda(InputType)) ||
7857  (Kind == Action::OFK_HIP && !types::isHIP(InputType)))
7858  continue;
7859 
7860  // Get the product of all bound architectures and toolchains.
7861  SmallVector<std::pair<const ToolChain *, StringRef>> TCAndArchs;
7862  for (const ToolChain *TC : ToolChains)
7863  for (StringRef Arch : getOffloadArchs(C, Args, Kind, TC))
7864  TCAndArchs.push_back(std::make_pair(TC, Arch));
7865 
7866  for (unsigned I = 0, E = TCAndArchs.size(); I != E; ++I)
7867  DeviceActions.push_back(C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, InputType));
7868 
7869  if (DeviceActions.empty())
7870  return HostAction;
7871 
7872  auto PL = types::getCompilationPhases(*this, Args, InputType);
7873 
7874  for (phases::ID Phase : PL) {
7875  if (Phase == phases::Link) {
7876  assert(Phase == PL.back() && "linking must be final compilation step.");
7877  break;
7878  }
7879 
7880  auto TCAndArch = TCAndArchs.begin();
7881  for (Action *&A : DeviceActions) {
7882  if (A->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
7883  continue;
7884 
7885  // Propagate the ToolChain so we can use it in ConstructPhaseAction.
7886  A->propagateDeviceOffloadInfo(Kind, TCAndArch->second.data(),
7887  TCAndArch->first);
7888  A = ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, Phase, A, Kind);
7889 
7890  if (isa<CompileJobAction>(A) && isa<CompileJobAction>(HostAction) &&
7891  Kind == Action::OFK_OpenMP &&
7892  HostAction->getType() != types::TY_Nothing) {
7893  // OpenMP offloading has a dependency on the host compile action to
7894  // identify which declarations need to be emitted. This shouldn't be
7895  // collapsed with any other actions so we can use it in the device.
7896  HostAction->setCannotBeCollapsedWithNextDependentAction();
7897  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
7898  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
7899  TCAndArch->second.data(), Kind);
7900  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
7901  DDep.add(*A, *TCAndArch->first, TCAndArch->second.data(), Kind);
7902  A = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDep);
7903  }
7904 
7905  ++TCAndArch;
7906  }
7907  }
7908 
7909  // Compiling HIP in non-RDC mode requires linking each action individually.
7910  for (Action *&A : DeviceActions) {
7911  if ((A->getType() != types::TY_Object &&
7912  A->getType() != types::TY_LTO_BC) ||
7913  Kind != Action::OFK_HIP ||
7914  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, false))
7915  continue;
7916  ActionList LinkerInput = {A};
7917  A = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkerInput, types::TY_Image);
7918  }
7919 
7920  auto TCAndArch = TCAndArchs.begin();
7921  for (Action *A : DeviceActions) {
7922  DDeps.add(*A, *TCAndArch->first, TCAndArch->second.data(), Kind);
7923  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
7924  DDep.add(*A, *TCAndArch->first, TCAndArch->second.data(), Kind);
7925 
7926  // Compiling CUDA in non-RDC mode uses the PTX output if available.
7927  for (Action *Input : A->getInputs())
7928  if (Kind == Action::OFK_Cuda && A->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
7929  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc,
7930  false))
7931  DDep.add(*Input, *TCAndArch->first, TCAndArch->second.data(), Kind);
7932  OffloadActions.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDep, A->getType()));
7933 
7934  ++TCAndArch;
7935  }
7936  }
7937 
7938  // HIP code in non-RDC mode will bundle the output if it invoked the linker.
7939  bool ShouldBundleHIP =
7940  C.isOffloadingHostKind(Action::OFK_HIP) &&
7941  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gpu_bundle_output,
7942  options::OPT_no_gpu_bundle_output, true) &&
7943  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, false) &&
7944  !llvm::any_of(OffloadActions,
7945  [](Action *A) { return A->getType() != types::TY_Image; });
7946 
7947  // All kinds exit now in device-only mode except for non-RDC mode HIP.
7948  if (offloadDeviceOnly() && !ShouldBundleHIP)
7949  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDeps, types::TY_Nothing);
7950 
7951  if (OffloadActions.empty())
7952  return HostAction;
7953 
7954  OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
7955  if (C.isOffloadingHostKind(Action::OFK_Cuda) &&
7956  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, false)) {
7957  // If we are not in RDC-mode we just emit the final CUDA fatbinary for
7958  // each translation unit without requiring any linking.
7959  Action *FatbinAction =
7960  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(OffloadActions, types::TY_CUDA_FATBIN);
7961  DDep.add(*FatbinAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>(),
7962  nullptr, Action::OFK_Cuda);
7963  } else if (C.isOffloadingHostKind(Action::OFK_HIP) &&
7964  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc,
7965  false)) {
7966  // If we are not in RDC-mode we just emit the final HIP fatbinary for each
7967  // translation unit, linking each input individually.
7968  Action *FatbinAction =
7969  C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(OffloadActions, types::TY_HIP_FATBIN);
7970  DDep.add(*FatbinAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>(),
7971  nullptr, Action::OFK_HIP);
7972  } else {
7973  // Package all the offloading actions into a single output that can be
7974  // embedded in the host and linked.
7975  Action *PackagerAction =
7976  C.MakeAction<OffloadPackagerJobAction>(OffloadActions, types::TY_Image);
7977  DDep.add(*PackagerAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
7978  nullptr, C.getActiveOffloadKinds());
7979  }
7980 
7981  // HIP wants '--offload-device-only' to create a fatbinary by default.
7982  if (offloadDeviceOnly())
7983  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDep, types::TY_Nothing);
7984 
7985  // If we are unable to embed a single device output into the host, we need to
7986  // add each device output as a host dependency to ensure they are still built.
7987  bool SingleDeviceOutput = !llvm::any_of(OffloadActions, [](Action *A) {
7988  return A->getType() == types::TY_Nothing;
7989  }) && isa<CompileJobAction>(HostAction);
7990  OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
7991  *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
7992  /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, SingleDeviceOutput ? DDep : DDeps);
7993  return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, SingleDeviceOutput ? DDep : DDeps);
7994 }
7995 
7996 Action *Driver::ConstructPhaseAction(
7997  Compilation &C, const ArgList &Args, phases::ID Phase, Action *Input,
7998  Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
7999  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Constructing phase actions");
8000 
8001  // Some types skip the assembler phase (e.g., llvm-bc), but we can't
8002  // encode this in the steps because the intermediate type depends on
8003  // arguments. Just special case here.
8004  if (Phase == phases::Assemble && Input->getType() != types::TY_PP_Asm)
8005  return Input;
8006 
8007  // Build the appropriate action.
8008  switch (Phase) {
8009  case phases::Link:
8010  llvm_unreachable("link action invalid here.");
8011  case phases::IfsMerge:
8012  llvm_unreachable("ifsmerge action invalid here.");
8013  case phases::Preprocess: {
8014  types::ID OutputTy;
8015  // -M and -MM specify the dependency file name by altering the output type,
8016  // -if -MD and -MMD are not specified.
8017  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM) &&
8018  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_MD, options::OPT_MMD)) {
8019  OutputTy = types::TY_Dependencies;
8020  } else {
8021  OutputTy = Input->getType();
8022  // For these cases, the preprocessor is only translating forms, the Output
8023  // still needs preprocessing.
8024  if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_includes,
8025  options::OPT_fno_rewrite_includes, false) &&
8026  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_imports,
8027  options::OPT_fno_rewrite_imports, false) &&
8028  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdirectives_only,
8029  options::OPT_fno_directives_only, false) &&
8030  !CCGenDiagnostics)
8031  OutputTy = types::getPreprocessedType(OutputTy);
8032  assert(OutputTy != types::TY_INVALID &&
8033  "Cannot preprocess this input type!");
8034  }
8035  types::ID HostPPType = types::getPreprocessedType(Input->getType());
8036  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl) && HostPPType != types::TY_INVALID &&
8037  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_sycl_use_footer) &&
8038  TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_None &&
8039  Input->getType() != types::TY_CUDA_DEVICE) {
8040  // Performing a host compilation with -fsycl. Append the integration
8041  // footer to the source file.
8042  auto *AppendFooter =
8043  C.MakeAction<AppendFooterJobAction>(Input, Input->getType());
8044  // FIXME: There are 2 issues with dependency generation in regards to
8045  // the integration footer that need to be addressed.
8046  // 1) Input file referenced on the RHS of a dependency is based on the
8047  // input src, which is a temporary. We want this to be the true
8048  // user input src file.
8049  // 2) When generating dependencies against a preprocessed file, header
8050  // file information (using -MD or-MMD) is not provided.
8051  return C.MakeAction<PreprocessJobAction>(AppendFooter, OutputTy);
8052  }
8053  return C.MakeAction<PreprocessJobAction>(Input, OutputTy);
8054  }
8055  case phases::Precompile: {
8056  // API extraction should not generate an actual precompilation action.
8057  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_extract_api))
8058  return C.MakeAction<ExtractAPIJobAction>(Input, types::TY_API_INFO);
8059 
8060  // With 'fexperimental-modules-reduced-bmi', we don't want to run the
8061  // precompile phase unless the user specified '--precompile'. In the case
8062  // the '--precompile' flag is enabled, we will try to emit the reduced BMI
8063  // as a by product in GenerateModuleInterfaceAction.
8064  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_modules_reduced_bmi) &&
8065  !Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__precompile))
8066  return Input;
8067 
8068  types::ID OutputTy = getPrecompiledType(Input->getType());
8069  assert(OutputTy != types::TY_INVALID &&
8070  "Cannot precompile this input type!");
8071 
8072  // If we're given a module name, precompile header file inputs as a
8073  // module, not as a precompiled header.
8074  const char *ModName = nullptr;
8075  if (OutputTy == types::TY_PCH) {
8076  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodule_name_EQ))
8077  ModName = A->getValue();
8078  if (ModName)
8079  OutputTy = types::TY_ModuleFile;
8080  }
8081 
8082  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only)) {
8083  // Syntax checks should not emit a PCH file
8084  OutputTy = types::TY_Nothing;
8085  }
8086 
8087  return C.MakeAction<PrecompileJobAction>(Input, OutputTy);
8088  }
8089  case phases::Compile: {
8090  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only))
8091  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Nothing);
8092  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc))
8093  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_RewrittenObjC);
8094  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_legacy_objc))
8095  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input,
8096  types::TY_RewrittenLegacyObjC);
8097  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__analyze))
8098  return C.MakeAction<AnalyzeJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Plist);
8099  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__migrate))
8100  return C.MakeAction<MigrateJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Remap);
8101  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_ast))
8102  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_AST);
8103  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_module_file_info))
8104  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_ModuleFile);
8105  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_verify_pch))
8106  return C.MakeAction<VerifyPCHJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Nothing);
8107  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_extract_api))
8108  return C.MakeAction<ExtractAPIJobAction>(Input, types::TY_API_INFO);
8109  return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
8110  }
8111  case phases::Backend: {
8112  if (isUsingLTO() && TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_None) {
8113  types::ID Output;
8114  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ffat_lto_objects) &&
8115  !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm))
8116  Output = types::TY_PP_Asm;
8117  else if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S))
8118  Output = types::TY_LTO_IR;
8119  else
8120  Output = types::TY_LTO_BC;
8121  return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, Output);
8122  }
8123  if (isUsingLTO(/* IsOffload */ true) &&
8124  TargetDeviceOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None) {
8125  types::ID Output =
8126  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S) ? types::TY_LTO_IR : types::TY_LTO_BC;
8127  return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, Output);
8128  }
8129  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm) ||
8130  (((Input->getOffloadingToolChain() &&
8131  Input->getOffloadingToolChain()->getTriple().isAMDGPU()) ||
8132  TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP) &&
8133  (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc,
8134  false) ||
8135  TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_OpenMP))) {
8136  types::ID Output =
8137  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S) &&
8138  (TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_None ||
8139  offloadDeviceOnly() ||
8140  (TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP &&
8141  !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_offload_new_driver,
8142  options::OPT_no_offload_new_driver, false)))
8143  ? types::TY_LLVM_IR
8144  : types::TY_LLVM_BC;
8145  return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, Output);
8146  }
8147  return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, types::TY_PP_Asm);
8148  }
8149  case phases::Assemble:
8150  return C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(std::move(Input), types::TY_Object);
8151  }
8152 
8153  llvm_unreachable("invalid phase in ConstructPhaseAction");
8154 }
8155 
8156 void Driver::BuildJobs(Compilation &C) const {
8157  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation jobs");
8158 
8159  Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
8160 
8161  // It is an error to provide a -o option if we are making multiple output
8162  // files. There are exceptions:
8163  //
8164  // IfsMergeJob: when generating interface stubs enabled we want to be able to
8165  // generate the stub file at the same time that we generate the real
8166  // library/a.out. So when a .o, .so, etc are the output, with clang interface
8167  // stubs there will also be a .ifs and .ifso at the same location.
8168  //
8169  // CompileJob of type TY_IFS_CPP: when generating interface stubs is enabled
8170  // and -c is passed, we still want to be able to generate a .ifs file while
8171  // we are also generating .o files. So we allow more than one output file in
8172  // this case as well.
8173  //
8174  // OffloadClass of type TY_Nothing: device-only output will place many outputs
8175  // into a single offloading action. We should count all inputs to the action
8176  // as outputs. Also ignore device-only outputs if we're compiling with
8177  // -fsyntax-only.
8178  if (FinalOutput) {
8179  unsigned NumOutputs = 0;
8180  unsigned NumIfsOutputs = 0;
8181  for (const Action *A : C.getActions()) {
8182  if (A->getType() != types::TY_Nothing &&
8183  A->getType() != types::TY_DX_CONTAINER &&
8184  !(A->getKind() == Action::IfsMergeJobClass ||
8185  (A->getType() == clang::driver::types::TY_IFS_CPP &&
8186  A->getKind() == clang::driver::Action::CompileJobClass &&
8187  0 == NumIfsOutputs++) ||
8188  (A->getKind() == Action::BindArchClass && A->getInputs().size() &&
8189  A->getInputs().front()->getKind() == Action::IfsMergeJobClass)))
8190  ++NumOutputs;
8191  else if (A->getKind() == Action::OffloadClass &&
8192  A->getType() == types::TY_Nothing &&
8193  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only))
8194  NumOutputs += A->size();
8195  }
8196 
8197  if (NumOutputs > 1) {
8198  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_output_argument_with_multiple_files);
8199  FinalOutput = nullptr;
8200  }
8201  }
8202 
8203  const llvm::Triple &RawTriple = C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple();
8204 
8205  // Collect the list of architectures.
8206  llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
8207  if (RawTriple.isOSBinFormatMachO())
8208  for (const Arg *A : C.getArgs())
8209  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch))
8210  ArchNames.insert(A->getValue());
8211 
8212  // Set of (Action, canonical ToolChain triple) pairs we've built jobs for.
8213  std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfoList> CachedResults;
8214  for (Action *A : C.getActions()) {
8215  // If we are linking an image for multiple archs then the linker wants
8216  // -arch_multiple and -final_output <final image name>. Unfortunately, this
8217  // doesn't fit in cleanly because we have to pass this information down.
8218  //
8219  // FIXME: This is a hack; find a cleaner way to integrate this into the
8220  // process.
8221  const char *LinkingOutput = nullptr;
8222  if (isa<LipoJobAction>(A)) {
8223  if (FinalOutput)
8224  LinkingOutput = FinalOutput->getValue();
8225  else
8226  LinkingOutput = getDefaultImageName();
8227  }
8228 
8229  BuildJobsForAction(C, A, &C.getDefaultToolChain(),
8230  /*BoundArch*/ StringRef(),
8231  /*AtTopLevel*/ true,
8232  /*MultipleArchs*/ ArchNames.size() > 1,
8233  /*LinkingOutput*/ LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8234  /*TargetDeviceOffloadKind*/ Action::OFK_None);
8235  }
8236 
8237  // If we have more than one job, then disable integrated-cc1 for now. Do this
8238  // also when we need to report process execution statistics.
8239  if (C.getJobs().size() > 1 || CCPrintProcessStats)
8240  for (auto &J : C.getJobs())
8241  J.InProcess = false;
8242 
8243  if (CCPrintProcessStats) {
8244  C.setPostCallback([=](const Command &Cmd, int Res) {
8245  std::optional<llvm::sys::ProcessStatistics> ProcStat =
8246  Cmd.getProcessStatistics();
8247  if (!ProcStat)
8248  return;
8249 
8250  const char *LinkingOutput = nullptr;
8251  if (FinalOutput)
8252  LinkingOutput = FinalOutput->getValue();
8253  else if (!Cmd.getOutputFilenames().empty())
8254  LinkingOutput = Cmd.getOutputFilenames().front().c_str();
8255  else
8256  LinkingOutput = getDefaultImageName();
8257 
8258  if (CCPrintStatReportFilename.empty()) {
8259  using namespace llvm;
8260  // Human readable output.
8261  outs() << sys::path::filename(Cmd.getExecutable()) << ": "
8262  << "output=" << LinkingOutput;
8263  outs() << ", total="
8264  << format("%.3f", ProcStat->TotalTime.count() / 1000.) << " ms"
8265  << ", user="
8266  << format("%.3f", ProcStat->UserTime.count() / 1000.) << " ms"
8267  << ", mem=" << ProcStat->PeakMemory << " Kb\n";
8268  } else {
8269  // CSV format.
8270  std::string Buffer;
8271  llvm::raw_string_ostream Out(Buffer);
8272  llvm::sys::printArg(Out, llvm::sys::path::filename(Cmd.getExecutable()),
8273  /*Quote*/ true);
8274  Out << ',';
8275  llvm::sys::printArg(Out, LinkingOutput, true);
8276  Out << ',' << ProcStat->TotalTime.count() << ','
8277  << ProcStat->UserTime.count() << ',' << ProcStat->PeakMemory
8278  << '\n';
8279  Out.flush();
8280  std::error_code EC;
8281  llvm::raw_fd_ostream OS(CCPrintStatReportFilename, EC,
8282  llvm::sys::fs::OF_Append |
8283  llvm::sys::fs::OF_Text);
8284  if (EC)
8285  return;
8286  auto L = OS.lock();
8287  if (!L) {
8288  llvm::errs() << "ERROR: Cannot lock file "
8289  << CCPrintStatReportFilename << ": "
8290  << toString(L.takeError()) << "\n";
8291  return;
8292  }
8293  OS << Buffer;
8294  OS.flush();
8295  }
8296  });
8297  }
8298 
8299  // If the user passed -Qunused-arguments or there were errors, don't warn
8300  // about any unused arguments.
8301  if (Diags.hasErrorOccurred() ||
8302  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_Qunused_arguments))
8303  return;
8304 
8305  // Claim -fdriver-only here.
8306  (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fdriver_only);
8307  // Claim -### here.
8308  (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH);
8309 
8310  // Claim --driver-mode, --rsp-quoting, it was handled earlier.
8311  (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_driver_mode);
8312  (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_rsp_quoting);
8313 
8314  bool HasAssembleJob = llvm::any_of(C.getJobs(), [](auto &J) {
8315  // Match ClangAs and other derived assemblers of Tool. ClangAs uses a
8316  // longer ShortName "clang integrated assembler" while other assemblers just
8317  // use "assembler".
8318  return strstr(J.getCreator().getShortName(), "assembler");
8319  });
8320  for (Arg *A : C.getArgs()) {
8321  // FIXME: It would be nice to be able to send the argument to the
8322  // DiagnosticsEngine, so that extra values, position, and so on could be
8323  // printed.
8324  if (!A->isClaimed()) {
8325  if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::NoArgumentUnused))
8326  continue;
8327 
8328  // Suppress the warning automatically if this is just a flag, and it is an
8329  // instance of an argument we already claimed.
8330  const Option &Opt = A->getOption();
8331  if (Opt.getKind() == Option::FlagClass) {
8332  bool DuplicateClaimed = false;
8333 
8334  for (const Arg *AA : C.getArgs().filtered(&Opt)) {
8335  if (AA->isClaimed()) {
8336  DuplicateClaimed = true;
8337  break;
8338  }
8339  }
8340 
8341  if (DuplicateClaimed)
8342  continue;
8343  }
8344 
8345  // In clang-cl, don't mention unknown arguments here since they have
8346  // already been warned about.
8347  if (!IsCLMode() || !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_UNKNOWN)) {
8348  if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::TargetSpecific) &&
8349  !A->isIgnoredTargetSpecific() && !HasAssembleJob &&
8350  // When for example -### or -v is used
8351  // without a file, target specific options are not
8352  // consumed/validated.
8353  // Instead emitting an error emit a warning instead.
8354  !C.getActions().empty()) {
8355  Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target)
8356  << A->getSpelling() << getTargetTriple();
8357  } else {
8358  Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_unused_argument)
8359  << A->getAsString(C.getArgs());
8360  }
8361  }
8362  }
8363  }
8364 }
8365 
8366 namespace {
8367 /// Utility class to control the collapse of dependent actions and select the
8368 /// tools accordingly.
8369 class ToolSelector final {
8370  /// The tool chain this selector refers to.
8371  const ToolChain &TC;
8372 
8373  /// The compilation this selector refers to.
8374  const Compilation &C;
8375 
8376  /// The base action this selector refers to.
8377  const JobAction *BaseAction;
8378 
8379  /// Set to true if the current toolchain refers to host actions.
8380  bool IsHostSelector;
8381 
8382  /// Set to true if save-temps and embed-bitcode functionalities are active.
8383  bool SaveTemps;
8384  bool EmbedBitcode;
8385 
8386  /// Get previous dependent action or null if that does not exist. If
8387  /// \a CanBeCollapsed is false, that action must be legal to collapse or
8388  /// null will be returned.
8389  const JobAction *getPrevDependentAction(const ActionList &Inputs,
8390  ActionList &SavedOffloadAction,
8391  bool CanBeCollapsed = true) {
8392  // An option can be collapsed only if it has a single input.
8393  if (Inputs.size() != 1)
8394  return nullptr;
8395 
8396  Action *CurAction = *Inputs.begin();
8397  if (CanBeCollapsed &&
8398  !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
8399  return nullptr;
8400 
8401  // If the input action is an offload action. Look through it and save any
8402  // offload action that can be dropped in the event of a collapse.
8403  if (auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(CurAction)) {
8404  // If the dependent action is a device action, we will attempt to collapse
8405  // only with other device actions. Otherwise, we would do the same but
8406  // with host actions only.
8407  if (!IsHostSelector) {
8408  if (OA->hasSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true)) {
8409  CurAction =
8410  OA->getSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true);
8411  if (CanBeCollapsed &&
8412  !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
8413  return nullptr;
8414  SavedOffloadAction.push_back(OA);
8415  return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
8416  }
8417  } else if (OA->hasHostDependence()) {
8418  CurAction = OA->getHostDependence();
8419  if (CanBeCollapsed &&
8420  !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
8421  return nullptr;
8422  SavedOffloadAction.push_back(OA);
8423  return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
8424  }
8425  return nullptr;
8426  }
8427 
8428  return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
8429  }
8430 
8431  /// Return true if an assemble action can be collapsed.
8432  bool canCollapseAssembleAction() const {
8433  return TC.useIntegratedAs() && !SaveTemps &&
8434  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_via_file_asm) &&
8435  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_FA) &&
8436  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa) &&
8437  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dxc_Fc);
8438  }
8439 
8440  /// Return true if a preprocessor action can be collapsed.
8441  bool canCollapsePreprocessorAction() const {
8442  return !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_no_integrated_cpp) &&
8443  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_traditional_cpp) && !SaveTemps &&
8444  !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc);
8445  }
8446 
8447  /// Struct that relates an action with the offload actions that would be
8448  /// collapsed with it.
8449  struct JobActionInfo final {
8450  /// The action this info refers to.
8451  const JobAction *JA = nullptr;
8452  /// The offload actions we need to take care off if this action is
8453  /// collapsed.
8454  ActionList SavedOffloadAction;
8455  };
8456 
8457  /// Append collapsed offload actions from the give nnumber of elements in the
8458  /// action info array.
8459  static void AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction,
8460  ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> &ActionInfo,
8461  unsigned ElementNum) {
8462  assert(ElementNum <= ActionInfo.size() && "Invalid number of elements.");
8463  for (unsigned I = 0; I < ElementNum; ++I)
8464  CollapsedOffloadAction.append(ActionInfo[I].SavedOffloadAction.begin(),
8465  ActionInfo[I].SavedOffloadAction.end());
8466  }
8467 
8468  /// Functions that attempt to perform the combining. They detect if that is
8469  /// legal, and if so they update the inputs \a Inputs and the offload action
8470  /// that were collapsed in \a CollapsedOffloadAction. A tool that deals with
8471  /// the combined action is returned. If the combining is not legal or if the
8472  /// tool does not exist, null is returned.
8473  /// Currently three kinds of collapsing are supported:
8474  /// - Assemble + Backend + Compile;
8475  /// - Assemble + Backend ;
8476  /// - Backend + Compile.
8477  const Tool *
8478  combineAssembleBackendCompile(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
8479  ActionList &Inputs,
8480  ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
8481  if (ActionInfo.size() < 3 || !canCollapseAssembleAction())
8482  return nullptr;
8483  auto *AJ = dyn_cast<AssembleJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
8484  auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
8485  auto *CJ = dyn_cast<CompileJobAction>(ActionInfo[2].JA);
8486  if (!AJ || !BJ || !CJ)
8487  return nullptr;
8488 
8489  // Get compiler tool.
8490  const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*CJ);
8491  if (!T)
8492  return nullptr;
8493 
8494  // Can't collapse if we don't have codegen support unless we are
8495  // emitting LLVM IR.
8496  bool OutputIsLLVM = types::isLLVMIR(ActionInfo[0].JA->getType());
8497  if (!T->hasIntegratedBackend() && !(OutputIsLLVM && T->canEmitIR()))
8498  return nullptr;
8499 
8500  // When using -fembed-bitcode, it is required to have the same tool (clang)
8501  // for both CompilerJA and BackendJA. Otherwise, combine two stages.
8502  if (EmbedBitcode) {
8503  const Tool *BT = TC.SelectTool(*BJ);
8504  if (BT == T)
8505  return nullptr;
8506  }
8507 
8508  if (!T->hasIntegratedAssembler())
8509  return nullptr;
8510 
8511  Inputs = CJ->getInputs();
8512  AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
8513  /*NumElements=*/3);
8514  return T;
8515  }
8516  const Tool *combineAssembleBackend(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
8517  ActionList &Inputs,
8518  ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
8519  if (ActionInfo.size() < 2 || !canCollapseAssembleAction())
8520  return nullptr;
8521  auto *AJ = dyn_cast<AssembleJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
8522  auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
8523  if (!AJ || !BJ)
8524  return nullptr;
8525 
8526  // Get backend tool.
8527  const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*BJ);
8528  if (!T)
8529  return nullptr;
8530 
8531  if (!T->hasIntegratedAssembler())
8532  return nullptr;
8533 
8534  Inputs = BJ->getInputs();
8535  AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
8536  /*NumElements=*/2);
8537  return T;
8538  }
8539  const Tool *combineBackendCompile(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
8540  ActionList &Inputs,
8541  ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
8542  if (ActionInfo.size() < 2)
8543  return nullptr;
8544  auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
8545  auto *CJ = dyn_cast<CompileJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
8546  if (!BJ || !CJ)
8547  return nullptr;
8548 
8549  // Check if the initial input (to the compile job or its predessor if one
8550  // exists) is LLVM bitcode. In that case, no preprocessor step is required
8551  // and we can still collapse the compile and backend jobs when we have
8552  // -save-temps. I.e. there is no need for a separate compile job just to
8553  // emit unoptimized bitcode.
8554  bool InputIsBitcode = true;
8555  for (size_t i = 1; i < ActionInfo.size(); i++)
8556  if (ActionInfo[i].JA->getType() != types::TY_LLVM_BC &&
8557  ActionInfo[i].JA->getType() != types::TY_LTO_BC) {
8558  InputIsBitcode = false;
8559  break;
8560  }
8561  if (!InputIsBitcode && !canCollapsePreprocessorAction())
8562  return nullptr;
8563 
8564  // Get compiler tool.
8565  const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*CJ);
8566  if (!T)
8567  return nullptr;
8568 
8569  // Can't collapse if we don't have codegen support unless we are
8570  // emitting LLVM IR.
8571  bool OutputIsLLVM = types::isLLVMIR(ActionInfo[0].JA->getType());
8572  if (!T->hasIntegratedBackend() && !(OutputIsLLVM && T->canEmitIR()))
8573  return nullptr;
8574 
8575  if (T->canEmitIR() && ((SaveTemps && !InputIsBitcode) || EmbedBitcode))
8576  return nullptr;
8577 
8578  Inputs = CJ->getInputs();
8579  AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
8580  /*NumElements=*/2);
8581  return T;
8582  }
8583 
8584  /// Updates the inputs if the obtained tool supports combining with
8585  /// preprocessor action, and the current input is indeed a preprocessor
8586  /// action. If combining results in the collapse of offloading actions, those
8587  /// are appended to \a CollapsedOffloadAction.
8588  void combineWithPreprocessor(const Tool *T, ActionList &Inputs,
8589  ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
8590  if (!T || !canCollapsePreprocessorAction() || !T->hasIntegratedCPP())
8591  return;
8592 
8593  // Attempt to get a preprocessor action dependence.
8594  ActionList PreprocessJobOffloadActions;
8595  ActionList NewInputs;
8596  for (Action *A : Inputs) {
8597  auto *PJ = getPrevDependentAction({A}, PreprocessJobOffloadActions);
8598  if (!PJ || !isa<PreprocessJobAction>(PJ)) {
8599  NewInputs.push_back(A);
8600  continue;
8601  }
8602 
8603  // This is legal to combine. Append any offload action we found and add the
8604  // current input to preprocessor inputs.
8605  CollapsedOffloadAction.append(PreprocessJobOffloadActions.begin(),
8606  PreprocessJobOffloadActions.end());
8607  NewInputs.append(PJ->input_begin(), PJ->input_end());
8608  }
8609  Inputs = NewInputs;
8610  }
8611 
8612 public:
8613  ToolSelector(const JobAction *BaseAction, const ToolChain &TC,
8614  const Compilation &C, bool SaveTemps, bool EmbedBitcode)
8615  : TC(TC), C(C), BaseAction(BaseAction), SaveTemps(SaveTemps),
8616  EmbedBitcode(EmbedBitcode) {
8617  assert(BaseAction && "Invalid base action.");
8618  IsHostSelector = BaseAction->getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_None;
8619  }
8620 
8621  /// Check if a chain of actions can be combined and return the tool that can
8622  /// handle the combination of actions. The pointer to the current inputs \a
8623  /// Inputs and the list of offload actions \a CollapsedOffloadActions
8624  /// connected to collapsed actions are updated accordingly. The latter enables
8625  /// the caller of the selector to process them afterwards instead of just
8626  /// dropping them. If no suitable tool is found, null will be returned.
8627  const Tool *getTool(ActionList &Inputs,
8628  ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
8629  //
8630  // Get the largest chain of actions that we could combine.
8631  //
8632 
8633  SmallVector<JobActionInfo, 5> ActionChain(1);
8634  ActionChain.back().JA = BaseAction;
8635  while (ActionChain.back().JA) {
8636  const Action *CurAction = ActionChain.back().JA;
8637 
8638  // Grow the chain by one element.
8639  ActionChain.resize(ActionChain.size() + 1);
8640  JobActionInfo &AI = ActionChain.back();
8641 
8642  // Attempt to fill it with the
8643  AI.JA =
8644  getPrevDependentAction(CurAction->getInputs(), AI.SavedOffloadAction);
8645  }
8646 
8647  // Pop the last action info as it could not be filled.
8648  ActionChain.pop_back();
8649 
8650  //
8651  // Attempt to combine actions. If all combining attempts failed, just return
8652  // the tool of the provided action. At the end we attempt to combine the
8653  // action with any preprocessor action it may depend on.
8654  //
8655 
8656  const Tool *T = combineAssembleBackendCompile(ActionChain, Inputs,
8657  CollapsedOffloadAction);
8658  if (!T)
8659  T = combineAssembleBackend(ActionChain, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
8660  if (!T)
8661  T = combineBackendCompile(ActionChain, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
8662  if (!T) {
8663  Inputs = BaseAction->getInputs();
8664  T = TC.SelectTool(*BaseAction);
8665  }
8666 
8667  combineWithPreprocessor(T, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
8668  return T;
8669  }
8670 };
8671 }
8672 
8673 /// Return a string that uniquely identifies the result of a job. The bound arch
8674 /// is not necessarily represented in the toolchain's triple -- for example,
8675 /// armv7 and armv7s both map to the same triple -- so we need both in our map.
8676 /// Also, we need to add the offloading device kind, as the same tool chain can
8677 /// be used for host and device for some programming models, e.g. OpenMP.
8678 static std::string GetTriplePlusArchString(const ToolChain *TC,
8679  StringRef BoundArch,
8680  Action::OffloadKind OffloadKind) {
8681  std::string TriplePlusArch = TC->getTriple().normalize();
8682  if (!BoundArch.empty()) {
8683  TriplePlusArch += "-";
8684  TriplePlusArch += BoundArch;
8685  }
8686  TriplePlusArch += "-";
8687  TriplePlusArch += Action::GetOffloadKindName(OffloadKind);
8688  return TriplePlusArch;
8689 }
8690 
8691 static void CollectForEachInputs(
8692  InputInfoList &InputInfos, const Action *SourceAction, const ToolChain *TC,
8693  StringRef BoundArch, Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind,
8694  const std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfoList>
8695  &CachedResults,
8696  const ForEachWrappingAction *FEA) {
8697  for (const Action *Input : SourceAction->getInputs()) {
8698  // Search for the Input, if not in the cache assume actions were collapsed
8699  // so recurse.
8700  auto Lookup = CachedResults.find(
8701  {Input,
8702  GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)});
8703  if (Lookup != CachedResults.end()) {
8704  if (!FEA->getSerialActions().count(Input)) {
8705  InputInfos.append(Lookup->second);
8706  }
8707  } else {
8708  CollectForEachInputs(InputInfos, Input, TC, BoundArch,
8709  TargetDeviceOffloadKind, CachedResults, FEA);
8710  }
8711  }
8712 }
8713 
8714 InputInfoList Driver::BuildJobsForAction(
8715  Compilation &C, const Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, StringRef BoundArch,
8716  bool AtTopLevel, bool MultipleArchs, const char *LinkingOutput,
8717  std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfoList>
8718  &CachedResults,
8719  Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
8720  std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
8721  A, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
8722  auto CachedResult = CachedResults.find(ActionTC);
8723  if (CachedResult != CachedResults.end()) {
8724  return CachedResult->second;
8725  }
8726  InputInfoList Result = BuildJobsForActionNoCache(
8727  C, A, TC, BoundArch, AtTopLevel, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput,
8728  CachedResults, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
8729  CachedResults[ActionTC] = Result;
8730  return Result;
8731 }
8732 
8733 static void handleTimeTrace(Compilation &C, const ArgList &Args,
8734  const JobAction *JA, const char *BaseInput,
8735  const InputInfo &Result) {
8736  Arg *A =
8737  Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ftime_trace, options::OPT_ftime_trace_EQ);
8738  if (!A)
8739  return;
8740  SmallString<128> Path;
8741  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_ftime_trace_EQ)) {
8742  Path = A->getValue();
8743  if (llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(Path)) {
8744  SmallString<128> Tmp(Result.getFilename());
8745  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Tmp, "json");
8746  llvm::sys::path::append(Path, llvm::sys::path::filename(Tmp));
8747  }
8748  } else {
8749  if (Arg *DumpDir = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT_dumpdir)) {
8750  // The trace file is ${dumpdir}${basename}.json. Note that dumpdir may not
8751  // end with a path separator.
8752  Path = DumpDir->getValue();
8753  Path += llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
8754  } else {
8755  Path = Result.getFilename();
8756  }
8757  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Path, "json");
8758  }
8759  const char *ResultFile = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Path);
8760  C.addTimeTraceFile(ResultFile, JA);
8761  C.addResultFile(ResultFile, JA);
8762 }
8763 
8764 InputInfoList Driver::BuildJobsForActionNoCache(
8765  Compilation &C, const Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, StringRef BoundArch,
8766  bool AtTopLevel, bool MultipleArchs, const char *LinkingOutput,
8767  std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfoList>
8768  &CachedResults,
8769  Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
8770  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation jobs");
8771 
8772  InputInfoList OffloadDependencesInputInfo;
8773  bool BuildingForOffloadDevice = TargetDeviceOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None;
8774  if (const OffloadAction *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(A)) {
8775  // The 'Darwin' toolchain is initialized only when its arguments are
8776  // computed. Get the default arguments for OFK_None to ensure that
8777  // initialization is performed before processing the offload action.
8778  // FIXME: Remove when darwin's toolchain is initialized during construction.
8779  C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, Action::OFK_None);
8780 
8781  // The offload action is expected to be used in four different situations.
8782  //
8783  // a) Set a toolchain/architecture/kind for a host action:
8784  // Host Action 1 -> OffloadAction -> Host Action 2
8785  //
8786  // b) Set a toolchain/architecture/kind for a device action;
8787  // Device Action 1 -> OffloadAction -> Device Action 2
8788  //
8789  // c) Specify a device dependence to a host action;
8790  // Device Action 1 _
8791  // \
8792  // Host Action 1 ---> OffloadAction -> Host Action 2
8793  //
8794  // d) Specify a host dependence to a device action.
8795  // Host Action 1 _
8796  // \
8797  // Device Action 1 ---> OffloadAction -> Device Action 2
8798  //
8799  // For a) and b), we just return the job generated for the dependences. For
8800  // c) and d) we override the current action with the host/device dependence
8801  // if the current toolchain is host/device and set the offload dependences
8802  // info with the jobs obtained from the device/host dependence(s).
8803 
8804  // If there is a single device option or has no host action, just generate
8805  // the job for it.
8806  if (OA->hasSingleDeviceDependence() || !OA->hasHostDependence()) {
8807  InputInfoList DevA;
8808  OA->doOnEachDeviceDependence([&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC,
8809  const char *DepBoundArch) {
8810  DevA.append(BuildJobsForAction(C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, AtTopLevel,
8811  /*MultipleArchs*/ !!DepBoundArch,
8812  LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8813  DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
8814  });
8815  return DevA;
8816  }
8817 
8818  // If 'Action 2' is host, we generate jobs for the device dependences and
8819  // override the current action with the host dependence. Otherwise, we
8820  // generate the host dependences and override the action with the device
8821  // dependence. The dependences can't therefore be a top-level action.
8822  OA->doOnEachDependence(
8823  /*IsHostDependence=*/BuildingForOffloadDevice,
8824  [&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC, const char *DepBoundArch) {
8825  OffloadDependencesInputInfo.append(BuildJobsForAction(
8826  C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, /*AtTopLevel=*/false,
8827  /*MultipleArchs*/ !!DepBoundArch, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8828  DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
8829  });
8830 
8831  A = BuildingForOffloadDevice
8832  ? OA->getSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true)
8833  : OA->getHostDependence();
8834 
8835  // We may have already built this action as a part of the offloading
8836  // toolchain, return the cached input if so.
8837  std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
8838  OA->getHostDependence(),
8839  GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
8840  if (CachedResults.find(ActionTC) != CachedResults.end()) {
8841  InputInfoList Inputs = CachedResults[ActionTC];
8842  Inputs.append(OffloadDependencesInputInfo);
8843  return Inputs;
8844  }
8845  }
8846 
8847  if (const InputAction *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(A)) {
8848  // FIXME: It would be nice to not claim this here; maybe the old scheme of
8849  // just using Args was better?
8850  const Arg &Input = IA->getInputArg();
8851  Input.claim();
8852  if (Input.getOption().matches(options::OPT_INPUT)) {
8853  const char *Name = Input.getValue();
8854  return {InputInfo(A, Name, /* _BaseInput = */ Name)};
8855  }
8856  return {InputInfo(A, &Input, /* _BaseInput = */ "")};
8857  }
8858  if (const BindArchAction *BAA = dyn_cast<BindArchAction>(A)) {
8859  const ToolChain *TC;
8860  StringRef ArchName = BAA->getArchName();
8861 
8862  if (!ArchName.empty())
8863  TC = &getToolChain(C.getArgs(),
8864  computeTargetTriple(*this, TargetTriple,
8865  C.getArgs(), ArchName));
8866  else
8867  TC = &C.getDefaultToolChain();
8868 
8869  return BuildJobsForAction(C, *BAA->input_begin(), TC, ArchName, AtTopLevel,
8870  MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8871  TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
8872  }
8873 
8874  if (const ForEachWrappingAction *FEA = dyn_cast<ForEachWrappingAction>(A)) {
8875  // Check that the main action wasn't already processed.
8876  auto MainActionOutput = CachedResults.find(
8877  {FEA->getJobAction(),
8878  GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)});
8879  if (MainActionOutput != CachedResults.end()) {
8880  // The input was processed on behalf of another foreach.
8881  // Add entry in cache and return.
8882  CachedResults[{FEA, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch,
8883  TargetDeviceOffloadKind)}] =
8884  MainActionOutput->second;
8885  return MainActionOutput->second;
8886  }
8887 
8888  // Build commands for the TFormInput then take any command added after as
8889  // needing a llvm-foreach wrapping.
8890  BuildJobsForAction(C, FEA->getTFormInput(), TC, BoundArch,
8891  /*AtTopLevel=*/false, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput,
8892  CachedResults, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
8893  unsigned OffsetIdx = C.getJobs().size();
8894  BuildJobsForAction(C, FEA->getJobAction(), TC, BoundArch,
8895  /*AtTopLevel=*/false, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput,
8896  CachedResults, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
8897 
8898  auto begin = C.getJobs().getJobsForOverride().begin() + OffsetIdx;
8899  auto end = C.getJobs().getJobsForOverride().end();
8900 
8901  // Steal the commands.
8902  llvm::SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<Command>, 4> JobsToWrap(
8903  std::make_move_iterator(begin), std::make_move_iterator(end));
8904  C.getJobs().getJobsForOverride().erase(begin, end);
8905 
8906  InputInfo ActionResult;
8907  for (std::unique_ptr<Command> Cmd :
8908  llvm::make_range(std::make_move_iterator(JobsToWrap.begin()),
8909  std::make_move_iterator(JobsToWrap.end()))) {
8910  const JobAction *SourceAction = cast<JobAction>(&Cmd->getSource());
8911  if (FEA->getSerialActions().count(SourceAction)) {
8912  C.addCommand(std::move(Cmd));
8913  continue;
8914  }
8915  ActionResult = CachedResults.at(
8916  {SourceAction,
8917  GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)}).front();
8918  InputInfoList InputInfos;
8919  CollectForEachInputs(InputInfos, SourceAction, TC, BoundArch,
8920  TargetDeviceOffloadKind, CachedResults, FEA);
8921  const Tool *Creator = &Cmd->getCreator();
8922  StringRef ParallelJobs;
8923  if (TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_SYCL)
8924  ParallelJobs = C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(
8925  options::OPT_fsycl_max_parallel_jobs_EQ);
8926 
8927  tools::SYCL::constructLLVMForeachCommand(
8928  C, *SourceAction, std::move(Cmd), InputInfos, ActionResult, Creator,
8929  "", types::getTypeTempSuffix(ActionResult.getType()), ParallelJobs);
8930  }
8931  return { ActionResult };
8932  }
8933 
8934  ActionList Inputs = A->getInputs();
8935 
8936  const JobAction *JA = cast<JobAction>(A);
8937  ActionList CollapsedOffloadActions;
8938 
8939  auto *DA = dyn_cast<OffloadDepsJobAction>(JA);
8940  const ToolChain *JATC = DA ? DA->getHostTC() : TC;
8941 
8942  ToolSelector TS(JA, *JATC, C, isSaveTempsEnabled(),
8943  embedBitcodeInObject() && !isUsingLTO());
8944  const Tool *T = TS.getTool(Inputs, CollapsedOffloadActions);
8945 
8946  if (!T)
8947  return {InputInfo()};
8948 
8949  // If we've collapsed action list that contained OffloadAction we
8950  // need to build jobs for host/device-side inputs it may have held.
8951  for (const auto *OA : CollapsedOffloadActions)
8952  cast<OffloadAction>(OA)->doOnEachDependence(
8953  /*IsHostDependence=*/BuildingForOffloadDevice,
8954  [&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC, const char *DepBoundArch) {
8955  OffloadDependencesInputInfo.append(BuildJobsForAction(
8956  C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, /* AtTopLevel */ false,
8957  /*MultipleArchs=*/!!DepBoundArch, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8958  DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
8959  });
8960 
8961  // Only use pipes when there is exactly one input.
8962  InputInfoList InputInfos;
8963  for (const Action *Input : Inputs) {
8964  // Treat dsymutil and verify sub-jobs as being at the top-level too, they
8965  // shouldn't get temporary output names.
8966  // FIXME: Clean this up.
8967  bool SubJobAtTopLevel =
8968  AtTopLevel && (isa<DsymutilJobAction>(A) || isa<VerifyJobAction>(A));
8969  InputInfos.append(BuildJobsForAction(
8970  C, Input, JATC, DA ? DA->getOffloadingArch() : BoundArch,
8971  SubJobAtTopLevel, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
8972  A->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
8973  }
8974 
8975  // Always use the first file input as the base input.
8976  const char *BaseInput = InputInfos[0].getBaseInput();
8977  for (auto &Info : InputInfos) {
8978  if (Info.isFilename()) {
8979  BaseInput = Info.getBaseInput();
8980  break;
8981  }
8982  }
8983 
8984  // ... except dsymutil actions, which use their actual input as the base
8985  // input.
8986  if (JA->getType() == types::TY_dSYM)
8987  BaseInput = InputInfos[0].getFilename();
8988 
8989  // Append outputs of offload device jobs to the input list
8990  if (!OffloadDependencesInputInfo.empty())
8991  InputInfos.append(OffloadDependencesInputInfo.begin(),
8992  OffloadDependencesInputInfo.end());
8993 
8994  // Set the effective triple of the toolchain for the duration of this job.
8995  llvm::Triple EffectiveTriple;
8996  const ToolChain &ToolTC = T->getToolChain();
8997  const ArgList &Args =
8998  C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, A->getOffloadingDeviceKind());
8999  if (InputInfos.size() != 1) {
9000  EffectiveTriple = llvm::Triple(ToolTC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(Args));
9001  } else {
9002  // Pass along the input type if it can be unambiguously determined.
9003  EffectiveTriple = llvm::Triple(
9004  ToolTC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(Args, InputInfos[0].getType()));
9005  }
9006  RegisterEffectiveTriple TripleRAII(ToolTC, EffectiveTriple);
9007 
9008  // Determine the place to write output to, if any.
9009  InputInfo Result;
9010  InputInfoList UnbundlingResults;
9011  if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(JA)) {
9012  // If we have an unbundling job, we need to create results for all the
9013  // outputs. We also update the results cache so that other actions using
9014  // this unbundling action can get the right results.
9015  for (auto &UI : UA->getDependentActionsInfo()) {
9016  assert(UI.DependentOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None &&
9017  "Unbundling with no offloading??");
9018 
9019  // Unbundling actions are never at the top level. When we generate the
9020  // offloading prefix, we also do that for the host file because the
9021  // unbundling action does not change the type of the output which can
9022  // cause a overwrite.
9023  InputInfo CurI;
9024  bool IsFPGAObjLink =
9025  (JA->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
9026  EffectiveTriple.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::SPIRSubArch_fpga &&
9027  C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ));
9028  if (C.getDriver().getOffloadStaticLibSeen() &&
9029  (JA->getType() == types::TY_Archive ||
9030  JA->getType() == types::TY_Tempfilelist)) {
9031  // Host part of the unbundled static archive is not used.
9032  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host)
9033  continue;
9034  // Host part of the unbundled object is not used when using the
9035  // FPGA target and -fsycl-link is enabled.
9036  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host && IsFPGAObjLink)
9037  continue;
9038  std::string TmpFileName = C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath(
9039  llvm::sys::path::stem(BaseInput),
9040  JA->getType() == types::TY_Archive ? "a" : "txt");
9041  const char *TmpFile = C.addTempFile(
9042  C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpFileName), JA->getType());
9043  CurI = InputInfo(JA->getType(), TmpFile, TmpFile);
9044  } else if (types::isFPGA(JA->getType())) {
9045  std::string Ext(types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA->getType()));
9046  types::ID TI = types::TY_Object;
9047  if (EffectiveTriple.isSPIROrSPIRV()) {
9048  if (!UI.DependentToolChain->getTriple().isSPIROrSPIRV())
9049  continue;
9050  // Output file from unbundle is FPGA device. Name the file
9051  // accordingly.
9052  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host) {
9053  // Do not add the current info for Host with FPGA device. The host
9054  // side isn't used
9055  continue;
9056  }
9057  if (JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCO) {
9058  TI = types::TY_TempAOCOfilelist;
9059  Ext = "txt";
9060  }
9061  if (JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR ||
9062  JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCX ||
9063  JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_AOCR_EMU) {
9064  if (IsFPGAObjLink)
9065  continue;
9066  // AOCR files are always unbundled into a list file.
9067  TI = types::TY_Tempfilelist;
9068  }
9069  } else {
9070  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_SYCL)
9071  // Do not add the current info for device with FPGA device. The
9072  // device side isn't used
9073  continue;
9074  TI = types::TY_Tempfilelist;
9075  Ext = "txt";
9076  }
9077  std::string TmpFileName = C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath(
9078  llvm::sys::path::stem(BaseInput), Ext);
9079  const char *TmpFile =
9080  C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpFileName), TI);
9081  CurI = InputInfo(TI, TmpFile, TmpFile);
9082  } else {
9083  // Host part of the unbundled object is not used when -fsycl-link is
9084  // enabled with FPGA target
9085  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host && IsFPGAObjLink)
9086  continue;
9087  std::string OffloadingPrefix = Action::GetOffloadingFileNamePrefix(
9088  UI.DependentOffloadKind,
9089  UI.DependentToolChain->getTriple().normalize(),
9090  /*CreatePrefixForHost=*/true);
9091  CurI = InputInfo(
9092  UA,
9093  GetNamedOutputPath(C, *UA, BaseInput, UI.DependentBoundArch,
9094  /*AtTopLevel=*/false,
9095  MultipleArchs ||
9096  UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP,
9097  OffloadingPrefix),
9098  BaseInput);
9099  }
9100  // Save the unbundling result.
9101  UnbundlingResults.push_back(CurI);
9102 
9103  // Get the unique string identifier for this dependence and cache the
9104  // result.
9105  StringRef Arch;
9106  if (TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP ||
9107  TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_SYCL) {
9108  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host)
9109  Arch = StringRef();
9110  else
9111  Arch = UI.DependentBoundArch;
9112  } else
9113  Arch = BoundArch;
9114  // When unbundling for SYCL and there is no Target offload, assume
9115  // Host as the dependent offload, as the host path has been stripped
9116  // in this instance
9117  Action::OffloadKind DependentOffloadKind;
9118  if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_SYCL &&
9119  TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_None &&
9120  !(isSYCLNativeCPU(Args) && isSYCLNativeCPU(C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple(), TC->getTriple())))
9121  DependentOffloadKind = Action::OFK_Host;
9122  else
9123  DependentOffloadKind = UI.DependentOffloadKind;
9124 
9125  CachedResults[{A, GetTriplePlusArchString(UI.DependentToolChain, Arch,
9126  DependentOffloadKind)}] = {
9127  CurI};
9128  }
9129  // Do a check for a dependency file unbundle for FPGA. This is out of line
9130  // from a regular unbundle, so just create and return the name of the
9131  // unbundled file.
9132  if (JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_Dependencies ||
9133  JA->getType() == types::TY_FPGA_Dependencies_List) {
9134  std::string Ext(types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA->getType()));
9135  std::string TmpFileName =
9136  C.getDriver().GetTemporaryPath(llvm::sys::path::stem(BaseInput), Ext);
9137  const char *TmpFile =
9138  C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpFileName), JA->getType());
9139  Result = InputInfo(JA->getType(), TmpFile, TmpFile);
9140  UnbundlingResults.push_back(Result);
9141  } else {
9142  // Now that we have all the results generated, select the one that should
9143  // be returned for the current depending action.
9144  std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
9145  A, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
9146  assert(CachedResults.find(ActionTC) != CachedResults.end() &&
9147  "Result does not exist??");
9148  Result = CachedResults[ActionTC].front();
9149  }
9150  } else if (auto *DA = dyn_cast<OffloadDepsJobAction>(JA)) {
9151  for (auto &DI : DA->getDependentActionsInfo()) {
9152  assert(DI.DependentOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None &&
9153  "Deps job with no offloading");
9154 
9155  std::string OffloadingPrefix = Action::GetOffloadingFileNamePrefix(
9156  DI.DependentOffloadKind,
9157  DI.DependentToolChain->getTriple().normalize(),
9158  /*CreatePrefixForHost=*/true);
9159  auto CurI = InputInfo(
9160  DA,
9161  GetNamedOutputPath(C, *DA, BaseInput, DI.DependentBoundArch,
9162  /*AtTopLevel=*/false,
9163  MultipleArchs ||
9164  DI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP,
9165  OffloadingPrefix),
9166  BaseInput);
9167  // Save the result.
9168  UnbundlingResults.push_back(CurI);
9169 
9170  // Get the unique string identifier for this dependence and cache the
9171  // result.
9172  StringRef Arch = TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP
9173  ? DI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host
9174  ? StringRef()
9175  : DI.DependentBoundArch
9176  : BoundArch;
9177 
9178  CachedResults[{A, GetTriplePlusArchString(DI.DependentToolChain, Arch,
9179  DI.DependentOffloadKind)}] = {
9180  CurI};
9181  }
9182 
9183  // Now that we have all the results generated, select the one that should be
9184  // returned for the current depending action.
9185  std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
9186  A, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
9187  auto It = CachedResults.find(ActionTC);
9188  assert(It != CachedResults.end() && "Result does not exist??");
9189  Result = It->second.front();
9190  } else if (JA->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
9191  Result = {InputInfo(A, BaseInput)};
9192  else {
9193  std::string OffloadingPrefix;
9194  // When generating binaries with -fsycl-link-target or -fsycl-link, the
9195  // output file prefix is the triple arch only. Do not add the arch when
9196  // compiling for host.
9197  if (!A->getOffloadingHostActiveKinds() &&
9198  (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_targets_EQ) ||
9199  Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_link_EQ))) {
9200  OffloadingPrefix = "-";
9201  OffloadingPrefix += TC->getTriple().getArchName();
9202  } else {
9203  // We only have to generate a prefix for the host if this is not a
9204  // top-level action.
9205  OffloadingPrefix = Action::GetOffloadingFileNamePrefix(
9206  A->getOffloadingDeviceKind(), TC->getTriple().normalize(),
9207  /*CreatePrefixForHost=*/isa<OffloadPackagerJobAction>(A) ||
9208  !(A->getOffloadingHostActiveKinds() == Action::OFK_None ||
9209  AtTopLevel));
9210  }
9211  if (isa<OffloadWrapperJobAction>(JA)) {
9212  if (Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o))
9213  BaseInput = FinalOutput->getValue();
9214  // Do not use the default image name when using -fno-sycl-rdc
9215  else if (!tools::SYCL::shouldDoPerObjectFileLinking(C))
9216  BaseInput = getDefaultImageName();
9217  BaseInput =
9218  C.getArgs().MakeArgString(std::string(BaseInput) + "-wrapper");
9219  }
9220  Result = InputInfo(A, GetNamedOutputPath(C, *JA, BaseInput, BoundArch,
9221  AtTopLevel, MultipleArchs,
9222  OffloadingPrefix),
9223  BaseInput);
9224  if (T->canEmitIR() && OffloadingPrefix.empty())
9225  handleTimeTrace(C, Args, JA, BaseInput, Result);
9226  }
9227 
9228  if (CCCPrintBindings && !CCGenDiagnostics) {
9229  llvm::errs() << "# \"" << T->getToolChain().getTripleString() << '"'
9230  << " - \"" << T->getName() << "\", inputs: [";
9231  for (unsigned i = 0, e = InputInfos.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9232  llvm::errs() << InputInfos[i].getAsString();
9233  if (i + 1 != e)
9234  llvm::errs() << ", ";
9235  }
9236  if (UnbundlingResults.empty())
9237  llvm::errs() << "], output: " << Result.getAsString() << "\n";
9238  else {
9239  llvm::errs() << "], outputs: [";
9240  for (unsigned i = 0, e = UnbundlingResults.size(); i != e; ++i) {
9241  llvm::errs() << UnbundlingResults[i].getAsString();
9242  if (i + 1 != e)
9243  llvm::errs() << ", ";
9244  }
9245  llvm::errs() << "] \n";
9246  }
9247  } else {
9248  if (UnbundlingResults.empty())
9249  T->ConstructJob(
9250  C, *JA, Result, InputInfos,
9251  C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, JA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()),
9252  LinkingOutput);
9253  else
9254  T->ConstructJobMultipleOutputs(
9255  C, *JA, UnbundlingResults, InputInfos,
9256  C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, JA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()),
9257  LinkingOutput);
9258  }
9259  return {Result};
9260 }
9261 
9262 const char *Driver::getDefaultImageName() const {
9263  llvm::Triple Target(llvm::Triple::normalize(TargetTriple));
9264  return Target.isOSWindows() ? "a.exe" : "a.out";
9265 }
9266 
9267 /// Create output filename based on ArgValue, which could either be a
9268 /// full filename, filename without extension, or a directory. If ArgValue
9269 /// does not provide a filename, then use BaseName, and use the extension
9270 /// suitable for FileType.
9271 static const char *MakeCLOutputFilename(const ArgList &Args, StringRef ArgValue,
9272  StringRef BaseName,
9273  types::ID FileType) {
9274  SmallString<128> Filename = ArgValue;
9275 
9276  if (ArgValue.empty()) {
9277  // If the argument is empty, output to BaseName in the current dir.
9278  Filename = BaseName;
9279  } else if (llvm::sys::path::is_separator(Filename.back())) {
9280  // If the argument is a directory, output to BaseName in that dir.
9281  llvm::sys::path::append(Filename, BaseName);
9282  }
9283 
9284  if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(ArgValue)) {
9285  // If the argument didn't provide an extension, then set it.
9286  const char *Extension = types::getTypeTempSuffix(FileType, true);
9287 
9288  if (FileType == types::TY_Image &&
9289  Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LD, options::OPT__SLASH_LDd)) {
9290  // The output file is a dll.
9291  Extension = "dll";
9292  }
9293 
9294  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Filename, Extension);
9295  }
9296 
9297  return Args.MakeArgString(Filename.c_str());
9298 }
9299 
9300 static bool HasPreprocessOutput(const Action &JA) {
9301  if (isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA))
9302  return true;
9303  if (isa<OffloadAction>(JA) && isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA.getInputs()[0]))
9304  return true;
9305  if (isa<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(JA) &&
9306  HasPreprocessOutput(*(JA.getInputs()[0])))
9307  return true;
9308  return false;
9309 }
9310 
9311 const char *Driver::CreateTempFile(Compilation &C, StringRef Prefix,
9312  StringRef Suffix, bool MultipleArchs,
9313  StringRef BoundArch,
9314  types::ID Type,
9315  bool NeedUniqueDirectory) const {
9316  SmallString<128> TmpName;
9317  Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fcrash_diagnostics_dir);
9318  std::optional<std::string> CrashDirectory =
9319  CCGenDiagnostics && A
9320  ? std::string(A->getValue())
9321  : llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("CLANG_CRASH_DIAGNOSTICS_DIR");
9322  if (CrashDirectory) {
9323  if (!getVFS().exists(*CrashDirectory))
9324  llvm::sys::fs::create_directories(*CrashDirectory);
9325  SmallString<128> Path(*CrashDirectory);
9326  llvm::sys::path::append(Path, Prefix);
9327  const char *Middle = !Suffix.empty() ? "-%%%%%%." : "-%%%%%%";
9328  if (std::error_code EC =
9329  llvm::sys::fs::createUniqueFile(Path + Middle + Suffix, TmpName)) {
9330  Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
9331  return "";
9332  }
9333  } else {
9334  if (MultipleArchs && !BoundArch.empty()) {
9335  if (NeedUniqueDirectory) {
9336  TmpName = GetTemporaryDirectory(Prefix);
9337  llvm::sys::path::append(TmpName,
9338  Twine(Prefix) + "-" + BoundArch + "." + Suffix);
9339  } else {
9340  TmpName =
9341  GetTemporaryPath((Twine(Prefix) + "-" + BoundArch).str(), Suffix);
9342  }
9343 
9344  } else {
9345  TmpName = GetTemporaryPath(Prefix, Suffix);
9346  }
9347  }
9348  return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName), Type);
9349 }
9350 
9351 // Calculate the output path of the module file when compiling a module unit
9352 // with the `-fmodule-output` option or `-fmodule-output=` option specified.
9353 // The behavior is:
9354 // - If `-fmodule-output=` is specfied, then the module file is
9355 // writing to the value.
9356 // - Otherwise if the output object file of the module unit is specified, the
9357 // output path
9358 // of the module file should be the same with the output object file except
9359 // the corresponding suffix. This requires both `-o` and `-c` are specified.
9360 // - Otherwise, the output path of the module file will be the same with the
9361 // input with the corresponding suffix.
9362 static const char *GetModuleOutputPath(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
9363  const char *BaseInput) {
9364  assert(isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA) && JA.getType() == types::TY_ModuleFile &&
9365  (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fmodule_output) ||
9366  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fmodule_output_EQ)));
9367 
9368  SmallString<256> OutputPath =
9369  tools::getCXX20NamedModuleOutputPath(C.getArgs(), BaseInput);
9370 
9371  return C.addResultFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(OutputPath.c_str()), &JA);
9372 }
9373 
9374 const char *Driver::GetNamedOutputPath(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
9375  const char *BaseInput,
9376  StringRef OrigBoundArch, bool AtTopLevel,
9377  bool MultipleArchs,
9378  StringRef OffloadingPrefix) const {
9379  std::string BoundArch = OrigBoundArch.str();
9380  if (is_style_windows(llvm::sys::path::Style::native)) {
9381  // BoundArch may contains ':', which is invalid in file names on Windows,
9382  // therefore replace it with '%'.
9383  std::replace(BoundArch.begin(), BoundArch.end(), ':', '@');
9384  }
9385 
9386  llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Computing output path");
9387  // Output to a user requested destination?
9388  if (AtTopLevel && !isa<DsymutilJobAction>(JA) && !isa<VerifyJobAction>(JA)) {
9389  if (Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o))
9390  return C.addResultFile(FinalOutput->getValue(), &JA);
9391  // Output to destination for -fsycl-device-only and Windows -o
9392  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fsycl_device_only))
9393  if (Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o))
9394  return C.addResultFile(FinalOutput->getValue(), &JA);
9395  }
9396 
9397  // For /P, preprocess to file named after BaseInput.
9398  if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_P) &&
9399  ((AtTopLevel && isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA)) ||
9400  isa<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(JA))) {
9401  StringRef BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
9402  StringRef NameArg;
9403  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fi))
9404  NameArg = A->getValue();
9405  return C.addResultFile(
9406  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), NameArg, BaseName, types::TY_PP_C),
9407  &JA);
9408  }
9409 
9410  // Redirect output for the generated source + integration footer.
9411  if (isa<AppendFooterJobAction>(JA)) {
9412  if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fsycl_footer_path_EQ)) {
9413  SmallString<128> OutName(A->getValue());
9414  StringRef BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
9415  if (isSaveTempsEnabled()) {
9416  // Retain the location specified by the user with -save-temps.
9417  const char *Suffix = types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType());
9418  std::string::size_type End = std::string::npos;
9419  if (!types::appendSuffixForType(JA.getType()))
9420  End = BaseName.rfind('.');
9421  SmallString<128> Suffixed(BaseName.substr(0, End));
9422  Suffixed += OffloadingPrefix;
9423  Suffixed += '.';
9424  Suffixed += Suffix;
9425  llvm::sys::path::append(OutName, Suffixed.c_str());
9426  } else {
9427  std::string TmpName =
9428  GetTemporaryPath(llvm::sys::path::stem(BaseName),
9429  types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType()));
9430  llvm::sys::path::append(OutName, llvm::sys::path::filename(TmpName));
9431  }
9432  return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(OutName));
9433  }
9434  }
9435 
9436  // Default to writing to stdout?
9437  if (AtTopLevel && !CCGenDiagnostics && HasPreprocessOutput(JA)) {
9438  return "-";
9439  }
9440 
9441  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_ModuleFile &&
9442  C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_module_file_info)) {
9443  return "-";
9444  }
9445 
9446  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm &&
9447  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dxc_Fc)) {
9448  StringRef FcValue = C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(options::OPT_dxc_Fc);
9449  // TODO: Should we use `MakeCLOutputFilename` here? If so, we can probably
9450  // handle this as part of the SLASH_Fa handling below.
9451  return C.addResultFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(FcValue.str()), &JA);
9452  }
9453 
9454  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Object &&
9455  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dxc_Fo)) {
9456  StringRef FoValue = C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(options::OPT_dxc_Fo);
9457  // TODO: Should we use `MakeCLOutputFilename` here? If so, we can probably
9458  // handle this as part of the SLASH_Fo handling below.
9459  return C.addResultFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(FoValue.str()), &JA);
9460  }
9461 
9462  // Is this the assembly listing for /FA?
9463  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm &&
9464  (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_FA) ||
9465  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa))) {
9466  // Use /Fa and the input filename to determine the asm file name.
9467  StringRef BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
9468  StringRef FaValue = C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa);
9469  return C.addResultFile(
9470  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), FaValue, BaseName, JA.getType()),
9471  &JA);
9472  }
9473 
9474  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_API_INFO &&
9475  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_emit_extension_symbol_graphs) &&
9476  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_o))
9477  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_unexpected_symbol_graph_output)
9478  << C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(options::OPT_o);
9479 
9480  // DXC defaults to standard out when generating assembly. We check this after
9481  // any DXC flags that might specify a file.
9482  if (AtTopLevel && JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm && IsDXCMode())
9483  return "-";
9484 
9485  bool SpecifiedModuleOutput =
9486  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fmodule_output) ||
9487  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fmodule_output_EQ);
9488  if (MultipleArchs && SpecifiedModuleOutput)
9489  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_module_output_with_multiple_arch);
9490 
9491  // If we're emitting a module output with the specified option
9492  // `-fmodule-output`.
9493  if (!AtTopLevel && isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA) &&
9494  JA.getType() == types::TY_ModuleFile && SpecifiedModuleOutput) {
9495  assert(!C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_modules_reduced_bmi));
9496  return GetModuleOutputPath(C, JA, BaseInput);
9497  }
9498 
9499  // Output to a temporary file?
9500  if ((!AtTopLevel && !isSaveTempsEnabled() &&
9501  (!C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo) ||
9502  // FIXME - The use of /Fo is limited when offloading is enabled. When
9503  // compiling to exe use of /Fo does not produce the named obj. We also
9504  // should not use the named output when performing unbundling.
9505  (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo) &&
9506  (!JA.isOffloading(Action::OFK_None) ||
9507  isa<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(JA) ||
9508  JA.getOffloadingHostActiveKinds() > Action::OFK_Host)))) ||
9509  CCGenDiagnostics) {
9510  StringRef Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
9511  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = Name.split('.');
9512  const char *Suffix =
9513  types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode() || IsDXCMode());
9514  // The non-offloading toolchain on Darwin requires deterministic input
9515  // file name for binaries to be deterministic, therefore it needs unique
9516  // directory.
9517  llvm::Triple Triple(C.getDriver().getTargetTriple());
9518  bool NeedUniqueDirectory =
9519  (JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_None ||
9520  JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_Host) &&
9521  Triple.isOSDarwin();
9522  return CreateTempFile(C, Split.first, Suffix, MultipleArchs, BoundArch,
9523  JA.getType(), NeedUniqueDirectory);
9524  }
9525 
9526  SmallString<128> BasePath(BaseInput);
9527  SmallString<128> ExternalPath("");
9528  StringRef BaseName;
9529 
9530  // Dsymutil actions should use the full path.
9531  if (isa<DsymutilJobAction>(JA) && C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dsym_dir)) {
9532  ExternalPath += C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_dsym_dir)->getValue();
9533  // We use posix style here because the tests (specifically
9534  // darwin-dsymutil.c) demonstrate that posix style paths are acceptable
9535  // even on Windows and if we don't then the similar test covering this
9536  // fails.
9537  llvm::sys::path::append(ExternalPath, llvm::sys::path::Style::posix,
9538  llvm::sys::path::filename(BasePath));
9539  BaseName = ExternalPath;
9540  } else if (isa<DsymutilJobAction>(JA) || isa<VerifyJobAction>(JA))
9541  BaseName = BasePath;
9542  else
9543  BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BasePath);
9544 
9545  // Determine what the derived output name should be.
9546  const char *NamedOutput;
9547 
9548  if ((JA.getType() == types::TY_Object || JA.getType() == types::TY_LTO_BC ||
9549  JA.getType() == types::TY_Archive) &&
9550  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo, options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
9551  // The /Fo or /o flag decides the object filename.
9552  StringRef Val =
9553  C.getArgs()
9554  .getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo, options::OPT__SLASH_o)
9555  ->getValue();
9556  NamedOutput =
9557  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), Val, BaseName, types::TY_Object);
9558  } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Image &&
9559  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fe,
9560  options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
9561  // The /Fe or /o flag names the linked file.
9562  StringRef Val =
9563  C.getArgs()
9564  .getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fe, options::OPT__SLASH_o)
9565  ->getValue();
9566  NamedOutput =
9567  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), Val, BaseName, types::TY_Image);
9568  } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Image) {
9569  if (IsCLMode()) {
9570  // clang-cl uses BaseName for the executable name.
9571  NamedOutput =
9572  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), "", BaseName, types::TY_Image);
9573  } else {
9574  SmallString<128> Output(getDefaultImageName());
9575  // HIP image for device compilation with -fno-gpu-rdc is per compilation
9576  // unit.
9577  bool IsHIPNoRDC = JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_HIP &&
9578  !C.getArgs().hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc,
9579  options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, false);
9580  bool UseOutExtension = IsHIPNoRDC || isa<OffloadPackagerJobAction>(JA);
9581  if (UseOutExtension) {
9582  Output = BaseName;
9583  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Output, "");
9584  }
9585  Output += OffloadingPrefix;
9586  if (MultipleArchs && !BoundArch.empty()) {
9587  Output += "-";
9588  Output.append(BoundArch);
9589  }
9590  if (UseOutExtension)
9591  Output += ".out";
9592  NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Output.c_str());
9593  }
9594  } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PCH && IsCLMode()) {
9595  NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(GetClPchPath(C, BaseName));
9596  } else if ((JA.getType() == types::TY_Plist || JA.getType() == types::TY_AST) &&
9597  C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
9598  StringRef Val =
9599  C.getArgs()
9600  .getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o)
9601  ->getValue();
9602  NamedOutput =
9603  MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), Val, BaseName, types::TY_Object);
9604  } else {
9605  const char *Suffix =
9606  types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode() || IsDXCMode());
9607  assert(Suffix && "All types used for output should have a suffix.");
9608 
9609  std::string::size_type End = std::string::npos;
9610  if (!types::appendSuffixForType(JA.getType()))
9611  End = BaseName.rfind('.');
9612  SmallString<128> Suffixed(BaseName.substr(0, End));
9613  Suffixed += OffloadingPrefix;
9614  if (MultipleArchs && !BoundArch.empty()) {
9615  Suffixed += "-";
9616  Suffixed.append(BoundArch);
9617  }
9618  // When using both -save-temps and -emit-llvm, use a ".tmp.bc" suffix for
9619  // the unoptimized bitcode so that it does not get overwritten by the ".bc"
9620  // optimized bitcode output.
9621  auto IsAMDRDCInCompilePhase = [](const JobAction &JA,
9622  const llvm::opt::DerivedArgList &Args) {
9623  // The relocatable compilation in HIP and OpenMP implies -emit-llvm.
9624  // Similarly, use a ".tmp.bc" suffix for the unoptimized bitcode
9625  // (generated in the compile phase.)
9626  const ToolChain *TC = JA.getOffloadingToolChain();
9627  return isa<CompileJobAction>(JA) &&
9628  ((JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_HIP &&
9629  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc,
9630  false)) ||
9631  (JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_OpenMP && TC &&
9632  TC->getTriple().isAMDGPU()));
9633  };
9634  if (!AtTopLevel && JA.getType() == types::TY_LLVM_BC &&
9635  (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm) ||
9636  IsAMDRDCInCompilePhase(JA, C.getArgs())))
9637  Suffixed += ".tmp";
9638  Suffixed += '.';
9639  Suffixed += Suffix;
9640  NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Suffixed.c_str());
9641  }
9642 
9643  // Prepend object file path if -save-temps=obj
9644  if (!AtTopLevel && isSaveTempsObj() && C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_o) &&
9645  JA.getType() != types::TY_PCH) {
9646  Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
9647  SmallString<128> TempPath(FinalOutput->getValue());
9648  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(TempPath);
9649  StringRef OutputFileName = llvm::sys::path::filename(NamedOutput);
9650  llvm::sys::path::append(TempPath, OutputFileName);
9651  NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TempPath.c_str());
9652  }
9653 
9654  if (isSaveTempsEnabled()) {
9655  // If we're saving temps and the temp file conflicts with any
9656  // input/resulting file, then avoid overwriting.
9657  if (!AtTopLevel && NamedOutput == BaseName) {
9658  bool SameFile = false;
9659  SmallString<256> Result;
9660  llvm::sys::fs::current_path(Result);
9661  llvm::sys::path::append(Result, BaseName);
9662  llvm::sys::fs::equivalent(BaseInput, Result.c_str(), SameFile);
9663  // Must share the same path to conflict.
9664  if (SameFile) {
9665  StringRef Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
9666  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = Name.split('.');
9667  std::string TmpName = GetTemporaryPath(
9668  Split.first,
9669  types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode() || IsDXCMode()));
9670  return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName));
9671  }
9672  }
9673 
9674  const auto &ResultFiles = C.getResultFiles();
9675  const auto CollidingFilenameIt =
9676  llvm::find_if(ResultFiles, [NamedOutput](const auto &It) {
9677  return StringRef(NamedOutput).equals(It.second);
9678  });
9679  if (CollidingFilenameIt != ResultFiles.end()) {
9680  // Upon any collision, a unique hash will be appended to the filename,
9681  // similar to what is done for temporary files in the regular flow.
9682  StringRef CollidingName(CollidingFilenameIt->second);
9683  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = CollidingName.split('.');
9684  std::string UniqueName = GetUniquePath(
9685  Split.first,
9686  types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode() || IsDXCMode()));
9687  return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(UniqueName));
9688  }
9689  }
9690 
9691  // Emit an error if PCH(Pre-Compiled Header) file generation is forced in
9692  // -fsycl mode.
9693  if (C.getArgs().hasFlag(options::OPT_fsycl, options::OPT_fno_sycl, false) &&
9694  JA.getType() == types::TY_PCH)
9695  Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_fsycl_with_pch);
9696  // As an annoying special case, PCH generation doesn't strip the pathname.
9697  if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PCH && !IsCLMode()) {
9698  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(BasePath);
9699  if (BasePath.empty())
9700  BasePath = NamedOutput;
9701  else
9702  llvm::sys::path::append(BasePath, NamedOutput);
9703  return C.addResultFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(BasePath.c_str()), &JA);
9704  }
9705 
9706  return C.addResultFile(NamedOutput, &JA);
9707 }
9708 
9709 std::string Driver::GetFilePath(StringRef Name, const ToolChain &TC) const {
9710  // Search for Name in a list of paths.
9711  auto SearchPaths = [&](const llvm::SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &P)
9712  -> std::optional<std::string> {
9713  // Respect a limited subset of the '-Bprefix' functionality in GCC by
9714  // attempting to use this prefix when looking for file paths.
9715  for (const auto &Dir : P) {
9716  if (Dir.empty())
9717  continue;
9718  SmallString<128> P(Dir[0] == '=' ? SysRoot + Dir.substr(1) : Dir);
9719  llvm::sys::path::append(P, Name);
9720  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(P)))
9721  return std::string(P);
9722  }
9723  return std::nullopt;
9724  };
9725 
9726  if (auto P = SearchPaths(PrefixDirs))
9727  return *P;
9728 
9729  SmallString<128> R(ResourceDir);
9730  llvm::sys::path::append(R, Name);
9731  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(R)))
9732  return std::string(R);
9733 
9734  SmallString<128> P(TC.getCompilerRTPath());
9735  llvm::sys::path::append(P, Name);
