9736  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(P)))
9737  return std::string(P);
9738 
9739  SmallString<128> D(Dir);
9740  llvm::sys::path::append(D, "..", Name);
9741  if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(D)))
9742  return std::string(D);
9743 
9744  if (auto P = SearchPaths(TC.getLibraryPaths()))
9745  return *P;
9746 
9747  if (auto P = SearchPaths(TC.getFilePaths()))
9748  return *P;
9749 
9750  return std::string(Name);
9751 }
9752 
9753 void Driver::generatePrefixedToolNames(
9754  StringRef Tool, const ToolChain &TC,
9755  SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Names) const {
9756  // FIXME: Needs a better variable than TargetTriple
9757  Names.emplace_back((TargetTriple + "-" + Tool).str());
9758  Names.emplace_back(Tool);
9759 }
9760 
9761 static bool ScanDirForExecutable(SmallString<128> &Dir, StringRef Name) {
9762  llvm::sys::path::append(Dir, Name);
9763  if (llvm::sys::fs::can_execute(Twine(Dir)))
9764  return true;
9765  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(Dir);
9766  return false;
9767 }
9768 
9769 std::string Driver::GetProgramPath(StringRef Name, const ToolChain &TC) const {
9770  SmallVector<std::string, 2> TargetSpecificExecutables;
9771  generatePrefixedToolNames(Name, TC, TargetSpecificExecutables);
9772 
9773  // Respect a limited subset of the '-Bprefix' functionality in GCC by
9774  // attempting to use this prefix when looking for program paths.
9775  for (const auto &PrefixDir : PrefixDirs) {
9776  if (llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(PrefixDir)) {
9777  SmallString<128> P(PrefixDir);
9778  if (ScanDirForExecutable(P, Name))
9779  return std::string(P);
9780  } else {
9781  SmallString<128> P((PrefixDir + Name).str());
9782  if (llvm::sys::fs::can_execute(Twine(P)))
9783  return std::string(P);
9784  }
9785  }
9786 
9787  const ToolChain::path_list &List = TC.getProgramPaths();
9788  for (const auto &TargetSpecificExecutable : TargetSpecificExecutables) {
9789  // For each possible name of the tool look for it in
9790  // program paths first, then the path.
9791  // Higher priority names will be first, meaning that
9792  // a higher priority name in the path will be found
9793  // instead of a lower priority name in the program path.
9794  // E.g. <triple>-gcc on the path will be found instead
9795  // of gcc in the program path
9796  for (const auto &Path : List) {
9797  SmallString<128> P(Path);
9798  if (ScanDirForExecutable(P, TargetSpecificExecutable))
9799  return std::string(P);
9800  }
9801 
9802  // Fall back to the path
9803  if (llvm::ErrorOr<std::string> P =
9804  llvm::sys::findProgramByName(TargetSpecificExecutable))
9805  return *P;
9806  }
9807 
9808  return std::string(Name);
9809 }
9810 
9811 std::string Driver::GetStdModuleManifestPath(const Compilation &C,
9812  const ToolChain &TC) const {
9813  std::string error = "<NOT PRESENT>";
9814 
9815  switch (TC.GetCXXStdlibType(C.getArgs())) {
9816  case ToolChain::CST_Libcxx: {
9817  auto evaluate = [&](const char *library) -> std::optional<std::string> {
9818  std::string lib = GetFilePath(library, TC);
9819 
9820  // Note when there are multiple flavours of libc++ the module json needs
9821  // to look at the command-line arguments for the proper json. These
9822  // flavours do not exist at the moment, but there are plans to provide a
9823  // variant that is built with sanitizer instrumentation enabled.
9824 
9825  // For example
9826  // StringRef modules = [&] {
9827  // const SanitizerArgs &Sanitize = TC.getSanitizerArgs(C.getArgs());
9828  // if (Sanitize.needsAsanRt())
9829  // return "libc++.modules-asan.json";
9830  // return "libc++.modules.json";
9831  // }();
9832 
9833  SmallString<128> path(lib.begin(), lib.end());
9834  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(path);
9835  llvm::sys::path::append(path, "libc++.modules.json");
9836  if (TC.getVFS().exists(path))
9837  return static_cast<std::string>(path);
9838 
9839  return {};
9840  };
9841 
9842  if (std::optional<std::string> result = evaluate("libc++.so"); result)
9843  return *result;
9844 
9845  return evaluate("libc++.a").value_or(error);
9846  }
9847 
9848  case ToolChain::CST_Libstdcxx:
9849  // libstdc++ does not provide Standard library modules yet.
9850  return error;
9851  }
9852 
9853  return error;
9854 }
9855 
9856 std::string Driver::GetTemporaryPath(StringRef Prefix, StringRef Suffix) const {
9857  SmallString<128> Path;
9858  std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::createTemporaryFile(Prefix, Suffix, Path);
9859  if (EC) {
9860  Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
9861  return "";
9862  }
9863 
9864  return std::string(Path);
9865 }
9866 
9867 std::string Driver::GetUniquePath(StringRef BaseName, StringRef Ext) const {
9868  SmallString<128> Path;
9869  std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::getPotentiallyUniqueFileName(
9870  Twine(BaseName) + Twine("-%%%%%%.") + Ext, Path);
9871  if (EC) {
9872  Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
9873  return "";
9874  }
9875 
9876  return std::string(Path.str());
9877 }
9878 
9879 std::string Driver::GetTemporaryDirectory(StringRef Prefix) const {

9881  std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::createUniqueDirectory(Prefix, Path);
9882  if (EC) {
9883  Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
9884  return "";
9885  }
9886 
9887  return std::string(Path);
9888 }

9890 std::string Driver::GetClPchPath(Compilation &C, StringRef BaseName) const {
9891  SmallString<128> Output;
9892  if (Arg *FpArg = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fp)) {
9893  // FIXME: If anybody needs it, implement this obscure rule:
9894  // "If you specify a directory without a file name, the default file name
9895  // is VCx0.pch., where x is the major version of Visual C++ in use."
9896  Output = FpArg->getValue();
9897 
9898  // "If you do not specify an extension as part of the path name, an
9899  // extension of .pch is assumed. "
9900  if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(Output))
9901  Output += ".pch";
9902  } else {
9903  if (Arg *YcArg = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc))
9904  Output = YcArg->getValue();
9905  if (Output.empty())
9906  Output = BaseName;
9907  llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Output, ".pch");
9908  }
9909  return std::string(Output);
9910 }
9911 
9912 const ToolChain &Driver::getToolChain(const ArgList &Args,
9913  const llvm::Triple &Target) const {
9914 
9915  auto &TC = ToolChains[Target.str()];
9916  if (!TC) {
9917  switch (Target.getOS()) {
9918  case llvm::Triple::AIX:
9919  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::AIX>(*this, Target, Args);
9920  break;
9921  case llvm::Triple::Haiku:
9922  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Haiku>(*this, Target, Args);
9923  break;
9924  case llvm::Triple::Darwin:
9925  case llvm::Triple::MacOSX:
9926  case llvm::Triple::IOS:
9927  case llvm::Triple::TvOS:
9928  case llvm::Triple::WatchOS:
9929  case llvm::Triple::XROS:
9930  case llvm::Triple::DriverKit:
9931  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::DarwinClang>(*this, Target, Args);
9932  break;
9933  case llvm::Triple::DragonFly:
9934  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::DragonFly>(*this, Target, Args);
9935  break;
9936  case llvm::Triple::OpenBSD:
9937  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::OpenBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
9938  break;
9939  case llvm::Triple::NetBSD:
9940  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::NetBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
9941  break;
9942  case llvm::Triple::FreeBSD:
9943  if (Target.isPPC())
9944  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::PPCFreeBSDToolChain>(*this, Target,
9945  Args);
9946  else
9947  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::FreeBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
9948  break;
9949  case llvm::Triple::Linux:
9950  case llvm::Triple::ELFIAMCU:
9951  if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::hexagon)
9952  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HexagonToolChain>(*this, Target,
9953  Args);
9954  else if ((Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::MipsTechnologies) &&
9955  !Target.hasEnvironment())
9956  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::MipsLLVMToolChain>(*this, Target,
9957  Args);
9958  else if (Target.isPPC())
9959  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::PPCLinuxToolChain>(*this, Target,
9960  Args);
9961  else if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::ve)
9962  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::VEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
9963  else if (Target.isOHOSFamily())
9964  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::OHOS>(*this, Target, Args);
9965  else
9966  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Linux>(*this, Target, Args);
9967  break;
9968  case llvm::Triple::NaCl:
9969  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::NaClToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
9970  break;
9971  case llvm::Triple::Fuchsia:
9972  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Fuchsia>(*this, Target, Args);
9973  break;
9974  case llvm::Triple::Solaris:
9975  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Solaris>(*this, Target, Args);
9976  break;
9977  case llvm::Triple::CUDA:
9978  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::NVPTXToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
9979  break;
9980  case llvm::Triple::AMDHSA:
9981  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::ROCMToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
9982  break;
9983  case llvm::Triple::AMDPAL:
9984  case llvm::Triple::Mesa3D:
9985  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::AMDGPUToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
9986  break;
9987  case llvm::Triple::Win32:
9988  switch (Target.getEnvironment()) {
9989  default:
9990  if (Target.isOSBinFormatELF())
9991  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_ELF>(*this, Target, Args);
9992  else if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO())
9993  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::MachO>(*this, Target, Args);
9994  else
9995  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_GCC>(*this, Target, Args);
9996  break;
9997  case llvm::Triple::GNU:
9998  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::MinGW>(*this, Target, Args);
9999  break;
10000  case llvm::Triple::Itanium:
10001  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CrossWindowsToolChain>(*this, Target,
10002  Args);
10003  break;
10004  case llvm::Triple::MSVC:
10005  case llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment:
10006  if (Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fuse_ld_EQ)
10007  .starts_with_insensitive("bfd"))
10008  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CrossWindowsToolChain>(
10009  *this, Target, Args);
10010  else
10011  TC =
10012  std::make_unique<toolchains::MSVCToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10013  break;
10014  }
10015  break;
10016  case llvm::Triple::PS4:
10017  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::PS4CPU>(*this, Target, Args);
10018  break;
10019  case llvm::Triple::PS5:
10020  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::PS5CPU>(*this, Target, Args);
10021  break;
10022  case llvm::Triple::Hurd:
10023  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Hurd>(*this, Target, Args);
10024  break;
10025  case llvm::Triple::LiteOS:
10026  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::OHOS>(*this, Target, Args);
10027  break;
10028  case llvm::Triple::ZOS:
10029  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::ZOS>(*this, Target, Args);
10030  break;
10031  case llvm::Triple::ShaderModel:
10032  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HLSLToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10033  break;
10034  default:
10035  // Of these targets, Hexagon is the only one that might have
10036  // an OS of Linux, in which case it got handled above already.
10037  switch (Target.getArch()) {
10038  case llvm::Triple::tce:
10039  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::TCEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10040  break;
10041  case llvm::Triple::tcele:
10042  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::TCELEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10043  break;
10044  case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
10045  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HexagonToolChain>(*this, Target,
10046  Args);
10047  break;
10048  case llvm::Triple::lanai:
10049  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::LanaiToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10050  break;
10051  case llvm::Triple::xcore:
10052  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::XCoreToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10053  break;
10054  case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
10055  case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
10056  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::WebAssembly>(*this, Target, Args);
10057  break;
10058  case llvm::Triple::avr:
10059  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::AVRToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10060  break;
10061  case llvm::Triple::msp430:
10062  TC =
10063  std::make_unique<toolchains::MSP430ToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10064  break;
10065  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
10066  case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
10067  if (toolchains::RISCVToolChain::hasGCCToolchain(*this, Args))
10068  TC =
10069  std::make_unique<toolchains::RISCVToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10070  else
10071  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::BareMetal>(*this, Target, Args);
10072  break;
10073  case llvm::Triple::ve:
10074  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::VEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10075  break;
10076  case llvm::Triple::spirv32:
10077  case llvm::Triple::spirv64:
10078  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::SPIRVToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10079  break;
10080  case llvm::Triple::csky:
10081  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CSKYToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
10082  break;
10083  default:
10084  if (toolchains::BareMetal::handlesTarget(Target))
10085  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::BareMetal>(*this, Target, Args);
10086  else if (Target.isOSBinFormatELF())
10087  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_ELF>(*this, Target, Args);
10088  else if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO())
10089  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::MachO>(*this, Target, Args);
10090  else
10091  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_GCC>(*this, Target, Args);
10092  }
10093  }
10094  }
10095 
10096  return *TC;
10097 }
10098 
10099 const ToolChain &Driver::getOffloadingDeviceToolChain(
10100  const ArgList &Args, const llvm::Triple &Target, const ToolChain &HostTC,
10101  const Action::OffloadKind &TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
10102  // Use device / host triples offload kind as the key into the ToolChains map
10103  // because the device ToolChain we create depends on both.
10104  auto &TC = ToolChains[Target.str() + "/" + HostTC.getTriple().str() +
10105  std::to_string(TargetDeviceOffloadKind)];
10106  if (!TC) {
10107  // Categorized by offload kind > arch rather than OS > arch like
10108  // the normal getToolChain call, as it seems a reasonable way to categorize
10109  // things.
10110  switch (TargetDeviceOffloadKind) {
10111  case Action::OFK_Cuda:
10112  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
10113  *this, Target, HostTC, Args, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
10114  break;
10115  case Action::OFK_HIP: {
10116  if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::amdgcn &&
10117  Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::AMD &&
10118  Target.getOS() == llvm::Triple::AMDHSA)
10119  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HIPAMDToolChain>(
10120  *this, Target, HostTC, Args, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
10121  else if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv64 &&
10122  Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor &&
10123  Target.getOS() == llvm::Triple::UnknownOS)
10124  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HIPSPVToolChain>(*this, Target,
10125  HostTC, Args);
10126  break;
10127  }
10128  case Action::OFK_OpenMP:
10129  // omp + nvptx
10130  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
10131  *this, Target, HostTC, Args, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
10132  break;
10133  case Action::OFK_SYCL:
10134  switch (Target.getArch()) {
10135  case llvm::Triple::spir:
10136  case llvm::Triple::spir64:
10137  case llvm::Triple::spirv32:
10138  case llvm::Triple::spirv64:
10139  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::SYCLToolChain>(*this, Target, HostTC,
10140  Args);
10141  break;
10142  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
10143  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
10144  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
10145  *this, Target, HostTC, Args, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
10146  break;
10147  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
10148  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::HIPAMDToolChain>(
10149  *this, Target, HostTC, Args, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
10150  break;
10151  default:
10152  if (isSYCLNativeCPU(Args)) {
10153  TC = std::make_unique<toolchains::SYCLToolChain>(*this, Target,
10154  HostTC, Args);
10155  }
10156  break;
10157  }
10158  break;
10159  default:
10160  break;
10161  }
10162  }
10163 
10164  return *TC;
10165 }
10166 
10167 bool Driver::ShouldUseClangCompiler(const JobAction &JA) const {
10168  // Say "no" if there is not exactly one input of a type clang understands.
10169  if (JA.size() != 1 ||
10170  !types::isAcceptedByClang((*JA.input_begin())->getType()))
10171  return false;
10172 
10173  // And say "no" if this is not a kind of action clang understands.
10174  if (!isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA) && !isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA) &&
10175  !isa<CompileJobAction>(JA) && !isa<BackendJobAction>(JA) &&
10176  !isa<ExtractAPIJobAction>(JA))
10177  return false;
10178 
10179  return true;
10180 }
10181 
10182 bool Driver::ShouldUseFlangCompiler(const JobAction &JA) const {
10183  // Say "no" if there is not exactly one input of a type flang understands.
10184  if (JA.size() != 1 ||
10185  !types::isAcceptedByFlang((*JA.input_begin())->getType()))
10186  return false;
10187 
10188  // And say "no" if this is not a kind of action flang understands.
10189  if (!isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA) && !isa<CompileJobAction>(JA) &&
10190  !isa<BackendJobAction>(JA))
10191  return false;
10192 
10193  return true;
10194 }

10196 bool Driver::ShouldEmitStaticLibrary(const ArgList &Args) const {
10197  // Only emit static library if the flag is set explicitly.
10198  if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_static_lib))
10199  return true;
10200  return false;
10201 }
10202 
10203 /// GetReleaseVersion - Parse (([0-9]+)(.([0-9]+)(.([0-9]+)?))?)? and return the
10204 /// grouped values as integers. Numbers which are not provided are set to 0.
10205 ///
10206 /// \return True if the entire string was parsed (9.2), or all groups were
10207 /// parsed (10.3.5extrastuff).
10208 bool Driver::GetReleaseVersion(StringRef Str, unsigned &Major, unsigned &Minor,
10209  unsigned &Micro, bool &HadExtra) {
10210  HadExtra = false;
10211 
10212  Major = Minor = Micro = 0;
10213  if (Str.empty())
10214  return false;
10215 
10216  if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Major))
10217  return false;
10218  if (Str.empty())
10219  return true;
10220  if (!Str.consume_front("."))
10221  return false;
10222 
10223  if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Minor))
10224  return false;
10225  if (Str.empty())
10226  return true;
10227  if (!Str.consume_front("."))
10228  return false;
10229 
10230  if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Micro))
10231  return false;
10232  if (!Str.empty())
10233  HadExtra = true;
10234  return true;
10235 }
10236 
10237 /// Parse digits from a string \p Str and fulfill \p Digits with
10238 /// the parsed numbers. This method assumes that the max number of
10239 /// digits to look for is equal to Digits.size().
10240 ///
10241 /// \return True if the entire string was parsed and there are
10242 /// no extra characters remaining at the end.
10243 bool Driver::GetReleaseVersion(StringRef Str,
10244  MutableArrayRef<unsigned> Digits) {
10245  if (Str.empty())
10246  return false;
10247 
10248  unsigned CurDigit = 0;
10249  while (CurDigit < Digits.size()) {
10250  unsigned Digit;
10251  if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Digit))
10252  return false;
10253  Digits[CurDigit] = Digit;
10254  if (Str.empty())
10255  return true;
10256  if (!Str.consume_front("."))
10257  return false;
10258  CurDigit++;
10259  }
10260 
10261  // More digits than requested, bail out...
10262  return false;
10263 }

10266 Driver::getOptionVisibilityMask(bool UseDriverMode) const {

10270  return llvm::opt::Visibility(options::CLOption);
10271  if (IsDXCMode())
10272  return llvm::opt::Visibility(options::DXCOption);
10273  if (IsFlangMode()) {
10274  return llvm::opt::Visibility(options::FlangOption);
10275  }
10276  return llvm::opt::Visibility(options::ClangOption);
10277 }

10302 bool clang::driver::isObjectFile(std::string FileName) {
10303  if (llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(FileName))
10304  return false;
10305  if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName))
10306  // Any file with no extension should be considered an Object. Take into
10307  // account -lsomelib library filenames.
10308  return FileName.rfind("-l", 0) != 0;
10309  std::string Ext(llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName).drop_front());
10310  // We cannot rely on lookupTypeForExtension solely as that has 'lib'
10311  // marked as an object.
10312  return (Ext != "lib" &&
10313  types::lookupTypeForExtension(Ext) == types::TY_Object);
10314 }
10315 
10316 bool clang::driver::isStaticArchiveFile(const StringRef &FileName) {
10317  if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName))
10318  // Any file with no extension should not be considered an Archive.
10319  return false;
10320  llvm::file_magic Magic;
10321  llvm::identify_magic(FileName, Magic);
10322  // Only .lib and archive files are to be considered.
10323  return (Magic == llvm::file_magic::archive);
10324 }

10326 bool clang::driver::willEmitRemarks(const ArgList &Args) {
10327  // -fsave-optimization-record enables it.

10329  options::OPT_fno_save_optimization_record, false))
10330  return true;
10331 
10332  // -fsave-optimization-record=<format> enables it as well.
10333  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsave_optimization_record_EQ,
10334  options::OPT_fno_save_optimization_record, false))
10335  return true;
10336 
10337  // -foptimization-record-file alone enables it too.
10338  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_foptimization_record_file_EQ,
10339  options::OPT_fno_save_optimization_record, false))
10340  return true;
10341 
10342  // -foptimization-record-passes alone enables it too.
10343  if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_foptimization_record_passes_EQ,
10344  options::OPT_fno_save_optimization_record, false))
10345  return true;
10346  return false;

10349 llvm::StringRef clang::driver::getDriverMode(StringRef ProgName,
10350  ArrayRef<const char *> Args) {
10351  static StringRef OptName =
10352  getDriverOptTable().getOption(options::OPT_driver_mode).getPrefixedName();
10353  llvm::StringRef Opt;
10354  for (StringRef Arg : Args) {
10355  if (!Arg.starts_with(OptName))
10356  continue;
10357  Opt = Arg;
10358  }
10359  if (Opt.empty())
10360  Opt = ToolChain::getTargetAndModeFromProgramName(ProgName).DriverMode;
10361  return Opt.consume_front(OptName) ? Opt : "";
10362 }

10365 
10366 llvm::Error driver::expandResponseFiles(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
10367  bool ClangCLMode,
10368  llvm::BumpPtrAllocator &Alloc,
10369  llvm::vfs::FileSystem *FS) {
10370  // Parse response files using the GNU syntax, unless we're in CL mode. There
10371  // are two ways to put clang in CL compatibility mode: ProgName is either
10372  // clang-cl or cl, or --driver-mode=cl is on the command line. The normal
10373  // command line parsing can't happen until after response file parsing, so we
10374  // have to manually search for a --driver-mode=cl argument the hard way.
10375  // Finally, our -cc1 tools don't care which tokenization mode we use because
10376  // response files written by clang will tokenize the same way in either mode.
10377  enum { Default, POSIX, Windows } RSPQuoting = Default;
10378  for (const char *F : Args) {
10379  if (strcmp(F, "--rsp-quoting=posix") == 0)
10380  RSPQuoting = POSIX;
10381  else if (strcmp(F, "--rsp-quoting=windows") == 0)
10382  RSPQuoting = Windows;
10383  }
10384 
10385  // Determines whether we want nullptr markers in Args to indicate response
10386  // files end-of-lines. We only use this for the /LINK driver argument with
10387  // clang-cl.exe on Windows.
10388  bool MarkEOLs = ClangCLMode;
10389 
10390  llvm::cl::TokenizerCallback Tokenizer;
10391  if (RSPQuoting == Windows || (RSPQuoting == Default && ClangCLMode))
10392  Tokenizer = &llvm::cl::TokenizeWindowsCommandLine;
10393  else
10394  Tokenizer = &llvm::cl::TokenizeGNUCommandLine;
10395 
10396  if (MarkEOLs && Args.size() > 1 && StringRef(Args[1]).starts_with("-cc1"))
10397  MarkEOLs = false;
10398 
10399  llvm::cl::ExpansionContext ECtx(Alloc, Tokenizer);
10400  ECtx.setMarkEOLs(MarkEOLs);
10401  if (FS)
10402  ECtx.setVFS(FS);
10403 
10404  if (llvm::Error Err = ECtx.expandResponseFiles(Args))
10405  return Err;
10406 
10407  // If -cc1 came from a response file, remove the EOL sentinels.
10408  auto FirstArg = llvm::find_if(llvm::drop_begin(Args),
10409  [](const char *A) { return A != nullptr; });
10410  if (FirstArg != Args.end() && StringRef(*FirstArg).starts_with("-cc1")) {
10411  // If -cc1 came from a response file, remove the EOL sentinels.
10412  if (MarkEOLs) {
10413  auto newEnd = std::remove(Args.begin(), Args.end(), nullptr);
10414  Args.resize(newEnd - Args.begin());
10415  }
10416  }
10417 
10418  return llvm::Error::success();
10419 }
10420 
10421 void Driver::populateSYCLDeviceTraitsMacrosArgs(
10422  const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args,
10423  const llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Triple, 4> &UniqueSYCLTriplesVec) {
10424  const auto &TargetTable = DeviceConfigFile::TargetTable;
10425  std::map<StringRef, unsigned int> AllDevicesHave;
10426  std::map<StringRef, bool> AnyDeviceHas;
10427  bool AnyDeviceHasAnyAspect = false;
10428  unsigned int ValidTargets = 0;
10429  for (const auto &TargetTriple : UniqueSYCLTriplesVec) {
10430  // Try and find the whole triple, if there's no match, remove parts of the
10431  // triple from the end to find partial matches.
10432  auto TargetTripleStr = TargetTriple.getTriple();
10433  bool Found = false;
10434  bool EmptyTriple = false;
10435  auto TripleIt = TargetTable.end();
10436  while (!Found && !EmptyTriple) {
10437  TripleIt = TargetTable.find(TargetTripleStr);
10438  Found = (TripleIt != TargetTable.end());
10439  if (!Found) {
10440  auto Pos = TargetTripleStr.find_last_of('-');
10441  EmptyTriple = (Pos == std::string::npos);
10442  TargetTripleStr =
10443  EmptyTriple ? TargetTripleStr : TargetTripleStr.substr(0, Pos);
10444  }
10445  }
10446  if (Found) {
10447  assert(TripleIt != TargetTable.end());
10448  const auto &TargetInfo = (*TripleIt).second;
10449  ++ValidTargets;
10450  const auto &AspectList = TargetInfo.aspects;
10451  const auto &MaySupportOtherAspects = TargetInfo.maySupportOtherAspects;
10452  if (!AnyDeviceHasAnyAspect)
10453  AnyDeviceHasAnyAspect = MaySupportOtherAspects;
10454  for (const auto &aspect : AspectList) {
10455  // If target has an entry in the config file, the set of aspects
10456  // supported by all devices supporting the target is 'AspectList'. If
10457  // there's no entry, such set is empty.
10458  const auto &AspectIt = AllDevicesHave.find(aspect);
10459  if (AspectIt != AllDevicesHave.end())
10460  ++AllDevicesHave[aspect];
10461  else
10462  AllDevicesHave[aspect] = 1;
10463  // If target has an entry in the config file AND
10464  // 'MaySupportOtherAspects' is false, the set of aspects supported by
10465  // any device supporting the target is 'AspectList'. If there's no
10466  // entry OR 'MaySupportOtherAspects' is true, such set contains all
10467  // the aspects.
10468  AnyDeviceHas[aspect] = true;
10469  }
10470  }
10471  }
10472 
10473  if (ValidTargets == 0) {
10474  // If there's no entry for the target in the device config file, the set
10475  // of aspects supported by any device supporting the target contains all
10476  // the aspects.
10477  AnyDeviceHasAnyAspect = true;
10478  }
10479 
10480  if (AnyDeviceHasAnyAspect) {
10481  // There exists some target that supports any given aspect.
10482  SmallString<64> MacroAnyDeviceAnyAspect(
10483  "-D__SYCL_ANY_DEVICE_HAS_ANY_ASPECT__=1");
10484  SYCLDeviceTraitsMacrosArgs.push_back(
10485  Args.MakeArgString(MacroAnyDeviceAnyAspect));
10486  } else {
10487  // Some of the aspects are not supported at all by any of the targets.
10488  // Thus, we need to define individual macros for each supported aspect.
10489  for (const auto &[TargetKey, SupportedTarget] : AnyDeviceHas) {
10490  assert(SupportedTarget);
10491  SmallString<64> MacroAnyDevice("-D__SYCL_ANY_DEVICE_HAS_");
10492  MacroAnyDevice += TargetKey;
10493  MacroAnyDevice += "__=1";
10494  SYCLDeviceTraitsMacrosArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(MacroAnyDevice));
10495  }
10496  }
10497  for (const auto &[TargetKey, SupportedTargets] : AllDevicesHave) {
10498  if (SupportedTargets != ValidTargets)
10499  continue;
10500  SmallString<64> MacroAllDevices("-D__SYCL_ALL_DEVICES_HAVE_");
10501  MacroAllDevices += TargetKey;
10502  MacroAllDevices += "__=1";
10503  SYCLDeviceTraitsMacrosArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(MacroAllDevices));
10504  }
10505 }

10507 static const char *GetStableCStr(llvm::StringSet<> &SavedStrings, StringRef S) {
10508  return SavedStrings.insert(S).first->getKeyData();
10509 }
10510 
10511 /// Apply a list of edits to the input argument lists.
10512 ///
10513 /// The input string is a space separated list of edits to perform,
10514 /// they are applied in order to the input argument lists. Edits
10515 /// should be one of the following forms:
10516 ///
10517 /// '#': Silence information about the changes to the command line arguments.
10518 ///
10519 /// '^': Add FOO as a new argument at the beginning of the command line.
10520 ///
10521 /// '+': Add FOO as a new argument at the end of the command line.
10522 ///
10523 /// 's/XXX/YYY/': Substitute the regular expression XXX with YYY in the command
10524 /// line.
10525 ///
10526 /// 'xOPTION': Removes all instances of the literal argument OPTION.
10527 ///
10528 /// 'XOPTION': Removes all instances of the literal argument OPTION,
10529 /// and the following argument.
10530 ///
10531 /// 'Ox': Removes all flags matching 'O' or 'O[sz0-9]' and adds 'Ox'
10532 /// at the end of the command line.
10533 ///
10534 /// \param OS - The stream to write edit information to.
10535 /// \param Args - The vector of command line arguments.
10536 /// \param Edit - The override command to perform.
10537 /// \param SavedStrings - Set to use for storing string representations.
10538 static void applyOneOverrideOption(raw_ostream &OS,
10539  SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
10540  StringRef Edit,
10541  llvm::StringSet<> &SavedStrings) {
10542  // This does not need to be efficient.
10543 
10544  if (Edit[0] == '^') {
10545  const char *Str = GetStableCStr(SavedStrings, Edit.substr(1));
10546  OS << "### Adding argument " << Str << " at beginning\n";
10547  Args.insert(Args.begin() + 1, Str);
10548  } else if (Edit[0] == '+') {
10549  const char *Str = GetStableCStr(SavedStrings, Edit.substr(1));
10550  OS << "### Adding argument " << Str << " at end\n";
10551  Args.push_back(Str);
10552  } else if (Edit[0] == 's' && Edit[1] == '/' && Edit.ends_with("/") &&
10553  Edit.slice(2, Edit.size() - 1).contains('/')) {
10554  StringRef MatchPattern = Edit.substr(2).split('/').first;
10555  StringRef ReplPattern = Edit.substr(2).split('/').second;
10556  ReplPattern = ReplPattern.slice(0, ReplPattern.size() - 1);
10557 
10558  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Args.size(); i != e; ++i) {
10559  // Ignore end-of-line response file markers
10560  if (Args[i] == nullptr)
10561  continue;
10562  std::string Repl = llvm::Regex(MatchPattern).sub(ReplPattern, Args[i]);
10563 
10564  if (Repl != Args[i]) {
10565  OS << "### Replacing '" << Args[i] << "' with '" << Repl << "'\n";
10566  Args[i] = GetStableCStr(SavedStrings, Repl);
10567  }
10568  }
10569  } else if (Edit[0] == 'x' || Edit[0] == 'X') {
10570  auto Option = Edit.substr(1);
10571  for (unsigned i = 1; i < Args.size();) {
10572  if (Option == Args[i]) {
10573  OS << "### Deleting argument " << Args[i] << '\n';
10574  Args.erase(Args.begin() + i);
10575  if (Edit[0] == 'X') {
10576  if (i < Args.size()) {
10577  OS << "### Deleting argument " << Args[i] << '\n';
10578  Args.erase(Args.begin() + i);
10579  } else
10580  OS << "### Invalid X edit, end of command line!\n";
10581  }
10582  } else
10583  ++i;
10584  }
10585  } else if (Edit[0] == 'O') {
10586  for (unsigned i = 1; i < Args.size();) {
10587  const char *A = Args[i];
10588  // Ignore end-of-line response file markers
10589  if (A == nullptr)
10590  continue;
10591  if (A[0] == '-' && A[1] == 'O' &&
10592  (A[2] == '\0' || (A[3] == '\0' && (A[2] == 's' || A[2] == 'z' ||
10593  ('0' <= A[2] && A[2] <= '9'))))) {
10594  OS << "### Deleting argument " << Args[i] << '\n';
10595  Args.erase(Args.begin() + i);
10596  } else
10597  ++i;
10598  }
10599  OS << "### Adding argument " << Edit << " at end\n";
10600  Args.push_back(GetStableCStr(SavedStrings, '-' + Edit.str()));
10601  } else {
10602  OS << "### Unrecognized edit: " << Edit << "\n";
10603  }
10604 }
10605 
10606 void driver::applyOverrideOptions(SmallVectorImpl<const char *> &Args,
10607  const char *OverrideStr,
10608  llvm::StringSet<> &SavedStrings,
10609  raw_ostream *OS) {
10610  if (!OS)
10611  OS = &llvm::nulls();
10612 
10613  if (OverrideStr[0] == '#') {
10614  ++OverrideStr;
10615  OS = &llvm::nulls();
10616  }
10617 
10618  *OS << "### CCC_OVERRIDE_OPTIONS: " << OverrideStr << "\n";
10619 
10620  // This does not need to be efficient.
10621 
10622  const char *S = OverrideStr;
10623  while (*S) {
10624  const char *End = ::strchr(S, ' ');
10625  if (!End)
10626  End = S + strlen(S);
10627  if (End != S)
10628  applyOneOverrideOption(*OS, Args, std::string(S, End), SavedStrings);
10629  S = End;
10630  if (*S != '\0')
10631  ++S;
10632  }
10633 }
